(497, 'è€é­ laowei', 'laowei', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/laowei.jpg', '<p>é­å¨å…ˆç”Ÿ:&nbsp;å½“ä»£ä¹¦ç”»å®¶,å¤ç‰©æ”¶è—å®¶.&nbsp;<br /><br />&rdquo; é­å¨å…ˆç”Ÿç‹¬åˆ°çš„æ°´å¢¨ç”»åˆ›ä½œï¼Œå»¶ç»­äº†æ—©å¹´æ¼«ç”»æ—¶ä»£çš„ä¸€äº›å½¢è±¡å’Œä¸»é¢˜ï¼Œä¹Ÿæ›´å¤šçš„åˆ›ä½œæ‹“å±•å‡ºä¸€ä¸ªç¥žä»™ä¸Žå¦–æ€ªå‡ºæ²¡çš„å±±æ°´å¼‚å¢ƒï¼Œå¸¸å‡ºçŽ°ä¼¼äººé—´ï¼Œåˆéžäººé—´ï¼Œå……ç›ˆæ´ªè’åŽŸåŠ›ï¼Œåˆæš—è—æœºæž¢çš„ç”»é¢ï¼Œä»¤äººå°è±¡æ·±åˆ»ã€‚&ldquo;<br /><br />&mdash;&mdash;èµ„æ·±è‰ºæœ¯å¸‚åœºåª’ä½“äººï¼Œä¸Šæµ·ç¬¬ä¸€è´¢ç»é¢‘é“è´¢ç»è¯„è®ºå‘˜ã€åˆ¶ç‰‡äººé¡¹ç«‹å¹³</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;çŠ¹æ¹¿åœ¨å¹›&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&mdash;&mdash;é»„çŽ„é¾™ï¼Œè‘—åæ”¶è—å®¶ï¼Œç¿¦æ·žé˜ä¸»äººã€‚</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;é­å¨é“å…„æœ‰ç«¥å¿ƒï¼Œæ‰€ç»˜æ±‚æ„å¢ƒï¼Œå½¢è€Œä¸Šï¼Œä¸Žäººå¼‚ã€‚æ‰€ç»˜ä»¥å±±æ°´ä¸ºæœ¬ï¼Œé••äººç‰©ã€åŠ¨ç‰©ã€èŠ±é¸Ÿç­‰äºŽä¸€ç‚‰ï¼Œé‡å¢¨è‰²ã€åˆ†é»‘ç™½ï¼Œç‚¹çº¿é¢åˆ«å‡ºæœºå·§ï¼Œè¯»å…¶ç”»å¦‚è¯»å®‹äººç¦…å®—æ•…äº‹ï¼Œå¾—ç”»å¤–å¢ƒç•Œã€‚&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&mdash;&mdash;è‘—åç¯†åˆ»å®¶ï¼Œä¹¦æ³•å®¶ï¼Œæ”¶è—å®¶ï¼Œä¹æ¾å›­ä¸é‚¹æ¶›</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;é«˜å¤å¥‡å´›ï¼Œæ—é€¸æ–œå‡ºï¼Œæ¸…æ–°éš½æ°¸ï¼Œæ—¢æœ‰å…«å¤§ä¹‹é—é£Žï¼Œåˆä¸å¤±å½“ä¸‹é”‹é”ã€‚å¬‰ç¬‘æ€’éª‚çš†æœ‰å¤„ï¼Œæš—é¦™æµ®åŠ¨éžé»„æ˜ã€‚&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&mdash;&mdash;ç½—å¥‡ï¼Œå¹¿å·žç¾Žæœ¯å­¦é™¢æ•™æŽˆ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/laowei31836757', 'https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/SJamtCLTAOO7qdbeVRZW4A', 'ruofuyun@163.com', '', '0', '1622675821', 'https://www.mintbase.io/zh/human/d0jwU6AaWkgUda9lcWiLvkexQUt1', ''),
(498, ' Tarwin Stroh-Spijer', 'tarwin-stroh-spijer', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/tarwin-stroh-spijer.png', '<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Long ago an artist. Inspired to create as the Internet feels like 2005 again.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/tarwin', 'https://tarwin.art/', '', '', '0', '1623716996', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/tarwin/'),
(499, 'Andy Wauman', 'andy-wauman', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/andy-wauman.jpeg', '<p>Andy Wauman\'s works speaks about the possibility of freedom. They are messages with a romantic sense for anarchy and love. In his statements, he oaymbols and gives them back their original romantic touch or even ideological meaning. The poetic quality is striking. Within an upcoming movement of new young artists using the language of the social context they grew up in, with the so-called popular culture and media as basic ingredients. Andy Wauman&rsquo;s feeling for materials and authentic meaning is a marker.</p>\r\n<p>Word by Dries Verstraete.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In a personal statement, Wauman comments on the nature of his artistic personality:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"Generally my work has it&rsquo;s origins in my conviction that a truly living culture can only arise from social structures and that the only theory a contemporary artist can feed on is necessarily a social one. I do not recycle existing forms, I try to make new ones based on my own background. Which is what distinguishes an artist from a marketeer. I try to inject the spontaneous energy from the street into my artistic practice, and I create my own contribution to the &lsquo;revolution of everyday life&rsquo; in the shape of texts and objects. Therefore, a recurrent element in my work is my protesting against cynicism and a preference for the sensuality and romantic value of the materials of the street, the ones the vagabond knows better than the bourgeois. But rather than a political activist, I like to call myself a poetical terrorist.\"</p>', 'https://twitter.com/copyplanetdotx1', 'https://andywauman.com/', 'frontsideinvert69@gmail.com', '', '0', '1624249620', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/copyplanetdotxyz/'),
(500, 'Pablo Salafurka', 'pablo-salafurka', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/pablo-salafurka.jpg', '<p>Born in a small town Dobrzany, but now living in the best place in Poland - Poznan.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Interested in interactive and real-time generative art.&nbsp;His passion is combining 2D and 3D graphics with experimental sounds and vice versa. When creating this form of expression&nbsp;he always try to add something new, something exploratory for him, so that each subsequent work is also a development - not just an answer to a given problem or topic.</p>\r\n<p>For Pablo, as an artist, the most important thing is to combine my two passions. Art and computer technology. He considers these two fields to be perfectly compatible with each other, following a common path since the beginning of the cyber world.</p>\r\n<p>That is why he creates interactive art. Objects, installations, films that need someone\'s gaze in order to live.</p>\r\n<p>As Pablo&nbsp;expands&nbsp;his exploration of the virtual world and the innovations associated with it,&nbsp;He expands&nbsp;his own barriers to creativity.&nbsp;He looks at the world, trying to make sense of what he sees, through the lens of what he can create.</p>', '', '', 'salafurka@gmail.com', '', '0', '1625532182', 'https://codame.threadless.com/collections/pablo-salafurka', 'https://www.instagram.com/m_plo_koon/'),
(511, 'Knits For Life', 'knits-for-life', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/knitsforlife.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Knits For Life are 1st Prize winners of the <a href=\"/events/rawthentic-art-tech-build-a-thon\">Rawthentic&nbsp;ART+TECH Build-A-Thon</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Jill and Lorna Watt, are sisters known as Knits For Life. Since 2011, we&rsquo;ve inspired audiences around the world with our unique and often guerrilla-style yarn bombs and fiber art installations. In 2013, Lorna was appointed Artist in Residence for the Downtown Business Association of San Mateo, California, where she produced public art for the Downtown Art Project. Most notably, with Jill, this time saw the birth of our world-renowned&nbsp;&ldquo;Squid Tree&rdquo; yarn bomb.</p>\r\n<p>In 2016 we won a prestigious&nbsp;Clio Award in Visual Marketing&nbsp;for&nbsp;yarn bombing an entire vintage Ford truck&nbsp;in Old Navy&rsquo;s Flagship San Francisco store. In 2017, SF Beautiful awarded us the&nbsp;Beautification Award in Placemaking.</p>\r\n<p>Today Knits For Life specializes in custom installations, including for&nbsp;SFMOMA,&nbsp;Twitter,&nbsp;Google,&nbsp;GitHub,&nbsp;Merck, and&nbsp;Meow Mix.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; caret-color: #000000;\">Our rotating public art installation that transformed trees into creatures, &ldquo;Knitting the Commons,&rdquo; was on view in Civic Center Plaza, San Francisco, for two years.</span></p>\r\n<p>We also spread our special brand of creativity through self-published DIY needle arts&nbsp;patterns for knitters and crocheters. Our patterns and work have appeared in numerous craft&nbsp;magazines and websites. We occasionally lead&nbsp;virtual knitting and crochet circles&nbsp;on how to yarn bomb. You can find us on Ravelry as&nbsp;Moipouf&nbsp;and&nbsp;Knitsforlife.</p>\r\n<p>Knits For Life currently operates out of a bright and upbeat space at&nbsp;Claremont Art Studios&nbsp;in San Mateo, halfway between San Francisco and the Silicon Valley. In our free time, Jill&nbsp;likes to research and make historic costumes and practice photography, while&nbsp;Lorna&nbsp;still likes to knit heirloom garments and gifts. When we&rsquo;re not lunching over comedies and talking about cats, we also&nbsp;make sock puppet movies, play room escape games, and&nbsp;make our own treasure hunts.</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vT5rFEIJCwW45Gs6DJMhUqrIlQ2Owxia_Bqlc5FUkDQ1_Nb4WjGvw6lhvgiQ7nwZqkeAZnoeHDSnY3r/embed?start=true&amp;loop=true&amp;delayms=3000\" width=\"960\" height=\"569\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>', 'https://twitter.com/KnitsforLife', 'https://knitsforlife.com/', '', '', '0', '1646280710', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/knitsforlife/'),
(501, 'Paula Levine', 'paula-levine', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/paula-levine.jpg', '<p><span data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\">Paula Levine is a Canadian-American artist working in media-based technologies. She been a resident at The Banff Centre for the Arts, the Experimental Television Center and received a ZERO1 Fellowship for a project entitled: \"On common ground//Empathy as a common good,\" researching the changing sense of &ldquo;local&rdquo; and it&rsquo;s potential to drive geopolitical intimacy through networked systems.<br /><br />An early proponent of, and experimenter with GPS, her series, \"Shadows from another place\" employed locative and mobile technologies to collapse the safety of geographical distance and map the impact of distant events, such as political trauma or upheaval, onto local ground.<br /><br /></span><span data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\">Her writings on locative media, new cartography and the expanding cartographic imagination have been presented at conferences at ISEA, ZERO1, MIT and the University of Wisconsin&rsquo;s Conney conference for Jewish Studies. Her work has shown at ISEA, Interactive Futures, in Vancouver, British Columbia where she was also a keynote speaker. Her writing on &ldquo;Art &amp; GPS&rdquo; was published in the Lea E-Journal in a special &ldquo;Locative Media Curriculum.&rdquo; Her writing, &ldquo;On Common Ground: Here as There,&rdquo; is a chapter in The Mobile Story: Narrative Practices with Locative Technologies edited by Jason Farman and published by Routledge.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\"><br /></span></p>', '', 'http://www.paulalevine.net', 'paula-levine@sbcglobal.net', '', '0', '1624249381', '', ''),
(502, 'Delta_Ark', 'delta-ark', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/delta-ark.jpeg', '<p>Delta_Ark is an experimental atelier concerned with media, computation and life science, broadly defined. The work from 2010-2020 portfolio was thematically focused on political issues of land-use, inequality and sustainability and their rendering into informative literary installations for architectural facades. e.g. &ldquo;The Beacon&rdquo; was an intervention for Occupy Wall St., where protesters&rsquo; testimonies were remixed into poetry and projected onto a tent wall at an encampment. The 2020-2030 pieces will primarily be focused on interactions between players and agents in VR, MR and cyber-physical systems (like drones). e.g., &ldquo;Gevurah,&rdquo; is a VR multiplayer human-swarm interaction simulator, meant to give indications about the promises and perils of artificial intelligence (and intelligence augmentation). The studio usually maintains several ongoing research threads, while also engaging in research-engineering fellowships at select companies. In the past, our work has been supported by Brown, RISD, Eyebeam, Buzzfeed and cypher/cyber/solar/eco punks the world over. (â—•â€¿â—•)â™¡</p>', 'https://twitter.com/delta_ark', 'http://delta.center/', '', '', '0', '1625533036', 'https://codame.threadless.com/collections/delta-ark', 'https://www.instagram.com/delta.ark/'),
(503, 'Anabela Costa', 'anabela-costa', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/anabela-costa.jpg', '<p dir=\"ltr\">1958 b. Lisbon, Portugal. Lives in Paris&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Visual Artist, studies Fine Arts at Lisbon Fine Arts University (1980)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Anabela Costa is a visual artist, her work was subject of several solo exhibitions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">From the eighties she becomes interested and moves progressively towards the digital image.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Since 2000 she is conducting research in the field of experimental film, based on two axes: the moving image -the aesthetics of representation of movement, and the formalization of thematic and scientific concepts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">She made&nbsp; a few experimental animation combining these two research areas: Web, TIME, LIQST_liquid state, and Landscape, In Motion, which were programmed and awarded in international festivals devoted to avant-garde cinema, animation, media arts and video-arts.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">She is also involved in international conferences where she presents these movies or articles about the image and its contemporary transformations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Living in Paris since 2010, she continued her artistic and technology research by working with experimental software in the generation of images -still images or moving image. Working with CUBE an Art and Creation Center&nbsp; and with the research team Aviz, that has as main research themes _perception,cognition,interaction and visualization at INRIA, Saclay, (which is the French National Institute for computer science and applied mathematics). This research team has made available to Anabela Costa an experimental software for generating stills and moving images. With this partnership her latest films were awarded with some prizes in animation, media arts in the United States, Australia and Europe,also selected for presentation in the Symposium of Electronic Arts ISEA, between other selections.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Her latest research widens with the design of films, moving image, media art in general for public spaces in led screens, performing arts and Virtual Reality projects.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'https://wwwanabelacostacom.blogspot.com/p/anabela-costabiovideography.html', 'anabelacosta@msn.com', '', '0', '1625531496', 'https://codame.threadless.com/collections/anabela-costa', ''),
(505, 'Anastazia Louise Aranaga', 'anastazia-louise-aranaga', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/anastazia-louise-aranaga.jpg', '<p>Anastazia Louise is a multi-media artist and the founder of Bad Unkl Sista performance ensemble.</p>\r\n<p>Anastazia is an artist, teacher, designer, and creativity consultant with over 25 years of professional experience spanning performance, costuming, and event production. She thrives on vibrant collaborations, inspiring authenticity, facilitating personal and interpersonal growth, and creating experiences for individuals and groups, performers and audiences.<br /><br />She is the founder and artistic director of Bad Unkl Sista, a performance art ensemble that combines choreography, original music, costuming, and physical theater elements to produce site-specific durational performances that provoke and inspire &ndash; changing how witnesses relate to the performers, to the world, and to themselves. This has also informed her approach to textile arts, and her performance costuming is designed to accommodate all body types, facilitate movement, enhance expression. and invoke a sense of awe in their power and complexity.<br /><br />Anastazia is also the founder of Stillness Studies Institute, a non-profit organization that offers programs to promote the use of stillness as a catalyst for creative, personal, and interpersonal development.</p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p>Photo by Marc Santos</p>', '', '', 'anastazia.louise@gmail.com', '', '0', '1632275697', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/anastazialouise'),
(504, 'Huili Chen', 'huili-chen', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/huili-chen.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; color: #ffffff;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Huili Chen is an antidisciplinary technologist/scientist/artist, currently pursuing a Ph.D at MIT Media Lab. She works at the intersection of social robotics, human-centered machine learning, and interactive storytelling. She conducts research that advances the state-of-the-art in socially intelligent robots that interact with humans, as well as research that investigates the social, cognitive and emotional impact of robots on humans in various contexts. She holds a M.S from MIT Media Lab, and a B.S. in Computer Science and a B.A. in Psychology from the University of Notre Dame. Huili&rsquo;s work has been published in top AI and HCI journals and conferences (e.g., ACM HRI, ACM ICMI), and won the Best Paper Nominee and Honorable Mention awards. Her artwork has been exhibited at different venues (e.g., the Museum of Wild and Newfangled Art). She is also the recipient of multiple competitions and awards such as MIT Graduate Women of Excellence, Media Lab Learning Fellow Award, and Forbes 30under30 China. Lastly, she has a real passion for social empowerment and advocacy, serving on the leadership team for China Education Symposium at Harvard and hosted Chinese LGBTQ visibility workshops in Boston. &quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:513,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;12&quot;:0}\">Huili Chen is an antidisciplinary technologist/scientist/artist, currently pursuing a Ph.D at MIT Media Lab. She works at the intersection of social robotics, human-centered machine learning, and interactive storytelling. She conducts research that advances the state-of-the-art in socially intelligent robots that interact with humans, as well as research that investigates the social, cognitive and emotional impact of robots on humans in various contexts. She holds a M.S from MIT Media Lab, and a B.S. in Computer Science and a B.A. in Psychology from the University of Notre Dame. Huili&rsquo;s work has been published in top AI and HCI journals and conferences (e.g., ACM HRI, ACM ICMI), and won the Best Paper Nominee and Honorable Mention awards. Her artwork has been exhibited at different venues (e.g., the Museum of Wild and Newfangled Art). She is also the recipient of multiple competitions and awards such as MIT Graduate Women of Excellence, Media Lab Learning Fellow Award, and Forbes 30under30 China. Lastly, she has a real passion for social empowerment and advocacy, serving on the leadership team for China Education Symposium at Harvard and hosted Chinese LGBTQ visibility workshops in Boston.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/huilichen_mlprg', 'https://huilichen25.github.io/', 'hchen25@mit.edu', '', '0', '1624113721', NULL, ''),
(508, 'Ezra Reaves', 'ezra-reaves', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/ezra-reaves.jpeg', '<p>Ezra Reaves (they/them) is a professional actor, comedian, experimental theater writer and performer, and ensemble member of the San Francisco Neo-Futurists. They\'ve toured nationally and internationally with The Neo-Futurists, performed over 150 shows as the lead character in the immersive show The Speakeasy and performed locally at SF Playhouse, Shotgun, ACT, NCTC, and Magic Theater. In NYC they have performed at LaMama Experimental Theater and PS122. As a comedian, Ezra has opened for Janeane Garofalo, Bob Odenkirk, John Hodgman, Paul F. Tompkins and even shared the stage with Michael Ian Black at SF Sketchfest. Their most recent project The Program sold out prior to opening and has extended due to popular demand!&nbsp;</p>', '', 'https://www.ezrareaves.com/', 'ezreaves@gmail.com', '', '0', '1643432207', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/ezrareaves/'),
(509, 'Amy Langer', 'amy-langer', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/amy-langer.jpeg', '<p>Amy Langer is a writer, performer, director, and performance artist living in the Bay Area. She is a founding member and co-artistic director of the San Francisco Neo-Futurists. She maintains the most casual video game blog at gentlegamers.com. You can hear her ever-changing, bite-sized audio pieces by calling 510-900-9831.</p>', '', 'https://www.amymlanger.com/', 'amy.m.langer@gmail.com', '', '0', '1643432851', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/sfneofuturists/'),
(510, 'Gervis Cash', 'gervis-cash', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/gervis-cash.png', '<p>Gervis is the Director of Ecosystem Evangelism at Twilio, previously head of Developer Relations at Snap, Product Designer at Apple, and Partnerships Manager at Evernote. During his time at Apple, he led creative workshops and helped guide design teams as part of the enterprise design lab. He has served as a board member of Leap, an organization that provides quality arts education programs that empower students to reach their fullest potential.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/gerrrrv', 'https://talentedgoods.com/', '', '', '0', '1643435917', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/gerrrrv/'),
(512, 'Lina Lopes', 'lina-lopes', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/lina-lopes.jpg', '<p>Lina Lopes is a consultant, entrepreneur and artist. She expresses in her trajectory the intersection between two worlds: art and technology. Graduated in Cinema by University of S&atilde;o Paulo and Master in Design by Anhembi-Morumbi College, she has an interdisciplinary background that also includes theater, engineering and computing.</p>\r\n<p>She has extensive experience in projects, working on the themes of parametric and generative design, video mapping, interactivity, Arduino programming, wearables, internet of things, biomaterials, among others. She is a speaker on innovation and mentor of bootcamps. Directs LILO.ZONE, space for creative use of technology and is at the forefront of the LILO.THINK initiative focused on immersive processes. She is enthusiastic of experimentation, collaboration and improvisation.</p>\r\n<p>In the wearables area, she has experience in research and prototyping projects with flexible conductive materials, pneumatic / soft robotics systems and biomaterials. In 2016, she realized the Touch Skin project, an artistic-scientific residence in the Media Lab of UFG to develop a temporary conductive tattoo, where she entered the universe of science and biological materials. In 2018 she founded BioLiLoLab, a biohacking laboratory within LILO.ZONE, where she is conducting research projects in biomaterials and bioart.</p>', '', 'https://www.linalopes.info', 'lina@lilo.zone', '', '0', '1645546754', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/lilo.think/'),
(513, 'Fereshteh Toosi', 'fereshteh-toosi', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/fereshteh-toosi.jpg', '<p>Fereshteh Toosi&nbsp;designs experiences that pose questions and foster animistic connections through encounter, exchange, and sensory inquiry. Their artwork often involves documentary processes, oral history, and archival research. These projects are augmented by audio, video, handmade electronics, and media transmissions. The live art events often take place outdoors in gardens, parks, and waterways. Immersive performances are produced in conjunction with small sculptures, short films, installations, scores, and poetry.</p>\r\n<p>In 2021, Fereshteh is participating in the Montr&eacute;al/Miami New Narratives Lab hosted by the National Film Board of Canada, O Cinema, MUTEK, and FilmGate Interactive. They also earned a Knight New Work 2020 award for their project&nbsp;Oil Ancestors, and a Miami Live Arts Lab Alliance residency to develop&nbsp;Metaphysical Hotline, a performance by telephone for an audience of one.&nbsp;Water Radio, a series of contemplative canoe and kayak outings, was supported by The Ellies Creator Award in 2018.</p>\r\n<p>Fereshteh lives and works in El Portal, Florida on stolen lands still stewarded by the Miccosukee and Seminole people, and previously by the Calusa and Tequesta tribal bands. They are&nbsp;an Assistant Professor in the Art and Art History Department of the College of Communication, Architecture, and the Arts at Florida International University.</p>', '', 'http://fereshteh.net/', 'ftoosi@gmail.com', '', '0', '1645410205', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/fereshtehtoosi'),
(514, 'Joshua Reeves', 'joshua-reeves', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/joshua-reeves.jpg', '<p>Joshua Reeves is a Web Developer who specializes in making things work together with other things. The aim is to make things, not just easier to use, but a delightful experience. He got serious about development in 2009 and has been finding ways to incorporate his creative side into the sometimes mundane world of programming.</p>\r\n<p>He finds his creative outlet in doodling and simple animation.</p>', '', 'https://albatrossd.com/', 'joshua@albatrossd.com', '', '0', '1645584850', '', ''),
(516, 'Moe Angelo', 'moe-angelo', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/moe-angelo.png', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Self-taught digital Artist skilled in many mediums, including projection mapping, FDA-varianced Laser Light, Neurofeedback and Biofeedback, 3D animation, and holographic content creation and displays.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/moestradamu5', 'https://linktr.ee/moestradamus', 'lightbrushprojections@gmail.com', '', '0', '1659587337', 'https://knownorigin.io/gallery/13913000-platonic-disco', 'https://instagram.com/moestradamus'),
(517, 'Serge Bulat', 'serge-bulat', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/serge-bulat.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Serge Bulat is a Moldovan-American multidisciplinary artist, composer and sound designer, who has been contributing to both European and American art scenes, exploring various mediums: from music and visuals to video games, radio and theater productions. Artist\'s most notable works are \"Queuelbum\" (the concept project that won an IMA award for Best Electronic Album Of The Year), the immersive video game \"Wurroom\" (created in collaboration with Michael Rfdshir), the audiovisual installations \"Third World Walker\" and \"INKBLOT\" (presented at festivals and conferences around the world including NYCEMF / USA, Convergence / UK, Technarte / Spain, New Music Gathering / USA, and Video Art Forum / Saudi Arabia. Bulat\'s artistic approach is often perceived as a meditation on arts, philosophy, science, and society; and deals with such diverse subjects as creativity, technology, reality, culture, and identity. Recent artistic activities include the release of the multi-format albums \"Wurmenai\", \"Similarities Between Fish And A Chair\" (a collaboration with artists from 10 countries), and the score for the experimental video game \"Isolomus\".</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/sergebulat', 'https://sergebulat.com/media', 'serge.bulat@yahoo.com', '', '0', '1647631754', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/sergebulat/'),
(518, 'arki', 'arki', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/arki.jpg', '<p>Bootz M. Plata is an architecture graduate 3d concept artist from the Philippines. He has been doing art ever since he can remember and has been heavily influenced by his father who is a painter and tattoo artist. Arki has been introduced to 3d in architecture school but what gave him the idea to make 3d art is beeple. When he first saw his work, he started learning blender and putting my imaginations into jpegs.</p>', 'https://twitter.com/arki_bootzz', '', 'bootzzplata@gmail.com', '', '0', '1652046387', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/bootzplata/'),
(524, 'Carlo Andrea Conte', 'carlo-andrea-conte', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/carlo-andrea-conte.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Synwrks (short for Synesthetic Works) is a project aimed at exploring the ways technology can resemble as closely as possible an individual\'s visual experience of music. The project involves researching and developing software prototypes to ease the intertwining of electronic music and 3D graphics. Works include multi-format music videos of original compositions (the most popular being the VR version of \"Synesthesia #2: A Blue Dwarf\'s Tale\", with 100k+ views in headsets), and more recently the weaving of original NFT 3D artworks with house and psytrance DJ sets.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/synwrks', 'https://www.synwrks.com', 'carloandreaconte@icloud.com', '', '0', '1653175743', NULL, 'https://instagram.com/synestheticworks'),
(525, 'Natural Warp', 'natural-warp', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/natural-warp.png', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Natural Warp is a project that\'s all about creating art and living a life inspired by the psychedelic experience. \"My visual creations translate these culture-bridging and world-unifying inner discoveries into recognizable and soul-touching experiences. Every piece is the result of such an attempt to express my constant awe for the unseen, the unknown, that of which we know is there but cannot touch, feel, hear or see. I noticed I feel a recurring need to narrate the unfathomable, to visualize those dimensions we are 100% intertwined with but which remain unrevealed for the worldly method of daily perception. This drives me to keep on creating and reinventing myself through the use of colors and geometry and let these speak about vibrations, perspectives and multi-dimensional event-horizons. This is the reason you will find Cosmic Freedom, Infinite Energy, Universal Geometry and Visionary Breakthrough often as re-occurring themes in my work.\" </span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/Natural_Warp', 'https://linktr.ee/Natural_Warp', 'art@naturalwarp.com', '', '0', '1659586782', 'https://makersplace.com/naturalwarp/center-of-non-existence-1-of-1-26732/', 'https://www.instagram.com/natural_warp_art/'),
(520, 'Camille Baker', 'camille-baker', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/camille-baker.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Camille Baker is an artist-performer/researcher/curator within various art forms: immersive experiences, participatory performance and interactive art, mobile media art, tech fashion/soft circuits/DIY electronics, responsive interfaces and environments, and emerging media curating. Maker of participatory performance and immersive artwork, Baker develops methods to explore expressive non-verbal modes of communication, extended embodiment and presence in real and mixed reality and interactive art contexts, using XR, haptics/ e-textiles, wearable devices and mobile media. She has an ongoing fascination with all things emotional, embodied, felt, sensed, the visceral, physical, and relational. Her 2018 book New Directions in Mobile Media and Performance showcases exciting approaches and artists in this space, as well as her own work. She has been running a regular meetup group with smart/e-textile artists and designers since 2014, called e-stitches, where participants share their practice and facilitate workshops of new techniques and innovations. Baker&nbsp; also has been Principal Investigator for UCA for the EU funded STARTS Ecosystem (starts.eu) Apr 2019-Nov 2021 and founder initiator for the EU WEAR Sustain project Jan 2017-April 2019 (wearsustain.eu).</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/swampgirl67', 'https://camillebaker.me', 'camille@camillebaker.me', '', '0', '1647633200', '', 'https://instagram.com/mythrakitty'),
(526, 'Omar Shehata', 'omar-shehata', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/omar-shehata.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Omar is a graphics programmer working on maps/geospatial tools currently based in Ithaca, NY. He grew up in Alexandria, Egypt and moved to the US for college. He loves creating interactive articles &amp; tutorials, or \"explorables\", that empower readers to learn about their world. Making flash games on Newgrounds was both his introduction to a software career and his creative outlet growing up.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/Omar4ur', 'https://omarshehata.me/projects', 'omar.sameh.shehata@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653176177', NULL, ''),
(527, 'winnie storey (skinniwini)', 'winnie-storey-skinniwini', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/winnie-storey-skinniwini.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Winnie Storey is a multimedia artist and visual designer based in the greater Houston area. Her design clients included Apple Inc, 3D systems, Amazon, Sunset Magazine, Kroger, and MTV. She holds a B.F.A of graphic design from California College of the Arts (C.C.A.) As a first generation immigrant to the US from Hong Kong, Winnie brings together the cultures of the East and the West showing the beauty that lies between them. \\n\\nExplore more of her art works at skinniwini.com and her design portfolio at winniestorey.com .Thanks!&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:897,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0}\">Winnie Storey is a multimedia artist and visual designer based in the greater Houston area. Her design clients included Apple Inc, 3D systems, Amazon, Sunset Magazine, Kroger, and MTV. She holds a B.F.A of graphic design from California College of the Arts (C.C.A.) As a first generation immigrant to the US from Hong Kong, Winnie brings together the cultures of the East and the West showing the beauty that lies between them.<br /><br />Explore more of her art works at skinniwini.com and her design portfolio at winniestorey.com .Thanks!</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/skinniwini', 'https://skinniwini.com', 'skinniwini@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653176290', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/skinniwini/'),
(528, 'Julia Shutkevych', 'julia-shutkevych', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/julia-shutkevych.png', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Julia Shu (Neometa) is a multimedia artist and new media creator from Ukraine, working in the field of generative graphics, animation, audiovisual media performances, AR &amp; VR as well as sculpture and collage. Julia has created an art movement called Neometa, or neometamodernism, which derives from the binary numeral system, the synergy of humaneness and technogenic. It&rsquo;s the way of working with reality divided between zero and one: harmony &amp; chaos, present &amp; future, digital &amp; analogue, man &amp; machine. Neometa uses transgressive art techniques to achieve the harmonious coexistence of these two categories. She also combines and reconciles all art practices to invite others to participate in discussion on our existence in a constantly changing entourage. In a world where awaiting for technological singularity became a new Doomsday Clock, Neometa invites us to look at machines as the cruel instrument to explore ourselves, or sometimes even as cocreators that became the part of our culture.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/neometa2', 'www.neometa.art', 'julia.shutkevych@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653700259', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/juliashu_gen/'),
(529, 'Melanie Clemmons', 'melanie-clemmons', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/melanie-clemmons.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\">Melanie Clemmons (she/they) is a new media artist interested in reimagining technology toward a more careful and sublime future. Her work has been exhibited in galleries and museums internationally, and consists of video, net art, installation, 3D printed sculpture and XR experiences. Clemmons toured with Pussy Riot performing visuals during their first North American tour, and has collaborated on several of their music videos. She has also collaborated with Zak Loyd since 2009, performing live visuals, and composing immersive video, laser, and XR installations. She is an assistant professor of digital/hybrid media at SMU in Dallas, TX.<br /><br />Zak Loyd (he/him) is a media artist and educator interested in mystical ramifications of video art histories, post-truth culture, and pop-gnosis. His intermodal work takes the form of installation, performance, and network-based compositions. He has shown at The Museum of Contemporary Art, Denver; Rhizome at The New Museum; and Casa Maauad, Mexico D.F. He is currently a Visual Art Technician and Adjunct Faculty in New Media Art at the University of North Texas.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/zakloyd', 'https://melanieclemmons.com/welcome/', 'melanieclemmons@gmail.com', '', '0', '1659586408', 'https://versum.xyz/token/versum/25674', 'https://www.instagram.com/auraquartz/'),
(530, 'Kaira Ray Villanueva', 'kaira-ray-villanueva', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/kaira-ray-villanueva.jpg', '<p>\"KYGOMEI (Kaira Villanueva) is a Filipino-American artist. Her artistic inspiration stems from transient states that often induce anxiety. Her art draws from gray areas. She loves exploring the boundaries of science-fiction and reality. Growing up, her faith, ethnicity, and physical environment often felt airy and ambiguous. KYGOMEI attempts to capture the misty amalgamation of uncertainties from her identity into a romanticized macabre, often buried in fantasy and science-fiction.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She studied at Columbia University and graduated with a degree in human rights specializing in technology design. She was listed as a Forbes 30 under 30 for game design and was invited to speak and give design workshops at places like NASA, The White House, New York City Comic Con, Indie Cade, and more. \"</p>', 'https://twitter.com/kygomei', 'www.kygomei.com', 'fzf.villanueva@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653700700', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/kygomei'),
(531, 'Lo Valdez', 'lo-valdez', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/lo-valdez.jpg', '<p>\"Lo Valdez is a digital designer based in the San Francisco Bay Area. She holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Graphic Design from San Jose State University. She has worked at startups as well as large companies like Fujitsu, Cisco, Intuitive Surgical, Apple and Facebook. Lo began learning Touchdesigner during the pandemic to help process the avalanche of grief she felt after her mom lost a long&nbsp; battle with cancer and to mitigate the loss of normalcy in her everyday life.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Her current art practice is focused on creating organic and abstract forms in Touchdesigner. Some include her original poetry that express common themes of love, loss and trauma. By being vulnerable, Lo feels she can have a deeper visual discourse with the viewer. As a society, we have all been through so much. She believes that by turning her pain into something beautiful she can help others to begin to heal as well. Transformation is possible through \"\"Digital Alchemy\"\".&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"</p>', '', 'https://lovaldez.com/', 'lorettaval@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653700923', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/l0valdez/'),
(532, 'Rui Zilhão', 'rui-zilh-o', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/rui-zilh-o.jpeg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\">Multidisciplinar artist. School of arts &ndash; Ceramics Technician, 2 years of Graphic Design, Fine Arts Master Degree - Painting (FBAUL 1997). Since 1997 doing different Art projects: 3 years collaboration in a project making human sculptures (from live molds) for museums, projects in the areas of Theatre, Design, Illustration, Music, live performance (portrait &amp; caricature). More recently, since 2010 creating also with the new medium, digital.</span></p>', '//twitter.com/ruizilhao', 'https://linktr.ee/rui_zilhao', 'rui.zilhao@gmail.com', '', '0', '1683699449', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/rui.zilhao'),
(553, 'Skip Rohde', 'skip-rohde', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/skip-rohde.jpg', '<p><br />I was an officer in the U.S. Navy for 22 years, but I have always been an artist.&nbsp;&nbsp;After I retired from the Navy, my wife and I came to the mountains near Asheville, North Carolina.&nbsp;&nbsp;I returned to school and earned a Bachelor of Fine Arts degree, with a concentration in painting, from the University of North Carolina at Asheville.&nbsp;&nbsp;Following graduation in 2003, I became a full-time artist with a studio in the River Arts District.&nbsp;&nbsp;My paintings have been exhibited in museums and galleries across the country\'s eastern half, and I\'ve had multiple solo exhibits in universities and art spaces in North Carolina and Tennessee.&nbsp;<br /><br />In 2008, I answered a call and went to Iraq for 18 months with the State Department to manage reconstruction programs around the country.&nbsp;&nbsp;That was followed by a year in Afghanistan, helping local officials, businessmen, and others better manage their government and economy.&nbsp;&nbsp;I returned home in 2012 and my wife won\'t let me go to war zones anymore.<br /><br />My studio is in a former textile mill next to the historic French Broad River just north of Asheville.&nbsp;&nbsp;I\'m always working on something new - currently a series of figures in charcoal and pastels, but also with new techniques in oils.&nbsp;&nbsp;My paintings have won recognition and awards in national and regional exhibitions.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Smithsonian Museum of American History has my \"Faces of Afghanistan\" drawings (over 80 drawings, mostly portraits of rural Afghans done from life) in their permanent collection.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to making my artwork, I teach workshops and mentor young students.&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/SkipRohde', 'http://www.skiprohde.com/', '', '', '0', '1683699280', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/skiprohde/'),
(533, 'Left', 'left', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/left.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">I major in visual art and I\'m a crypto artist who work with AI now. I attend both local and abroad art exhibitions more than 15 years, my art works have been collected by Shanghai Art Museum. I\'m the chief editor of &lt; 48 Artwork Codes &gt;.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/iloveleft', '', 'marcieno1@sina.com', '', '0', '1653701281', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/leftblack'),
(534, 'Hazel Griffiths', 'hazel-griffiths', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/hazel-griffiths.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\">I am an artist and visual storyteller creating work in a variety of media including oil, encaustic wax and watercolors and now, virtual and augmented reality. I have been creating for the last ten years and have been an active member of the South Florida art community, showing at art fairs, galleries and events from West Palm to Key West. I have a strong interest in nature and conservation and am currently working with Project Ark and the Ocean Rescue Alliance.<br /><br />My significant body of work is a series of imaginary landscapes informed by inner states of being - visionary places that reside within us. My work in virtual reality has become an immersive extension of these ideas, adding another dimension to my thought process.<br />These immersive worlds have been uploaded to Altspacevr for the first virtual burning man experience. More worlds will be created for this year&rsquo;s theme: Into the unknown. This piece is a foray into that concept, one that is continually expanding!<br />I have now minted two of the uploaded Altspace worlds as nfts, allowing the purchaser exclusive access to their own private world containing the virtual reality art pieces.<br /><br />My current body of work is mostly in digital media, specifically augmented and virtual reality in the form of virtual worlds and immersive digital experiences. these virtual pieces also become part of physical art pieces in the form of augmented reality, to create multiple viewing experiences and leave room for playing with multiple scales within the same piece. Most of my virtual work is fully immersive, narrative worlds or 3D light sculptures that can be translated into augmented reality pieces, that any person with a phone can experience, infusing an everyday scene with magical realism.<br />My augmented reality work is mostly in the form of these &lsquo;light sculptures&rsquo; or encapsulated worlds one can step into.<br /><br />My intent is to continue creating exhibition pieces that are a fusion of traditional techniques and new media to create unique viewing experiences, bringing the two worlds together to tell multi-dimensional stories.<br />Most of my virtual pieces are translated into augmented reality, as this medium is the most accessible and for me, is one of the most exciting spaces to be in.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/hazelgriffiths8', ' https://hazelgriffiths.com/', 'hazelispainting@gmail.com', '', '0', '1659574373', 'https://foundation.app/@HazelG/foundation/102659', 'https://www.instagram.com/hazelgriffithsart'),
(550, 'Lou Peralta', 'lou-peralta', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/lou-peralta.jpg', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As the fourth generation of a family of portrait photographers, I devote myself full time to the artistic exploration of portraiture.</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Description:</p>\r\n<p>After more than 30 years as a portrait photographer, photographing thousands of people, I ask myself: &ldquo;What is it I&rsquo;m really portraying?&rdquo;&nbsp; This series revealed new lines of research to me.&nbsp; Call it &ldquo;Ka,&rdquo; as in the Egyptian mythology, &ldquo;conscience,&rdquo; in the words of the psychologists, or &ldquo;soul,&rdquo; like some religions, I know now that what I was trying to portray was that living part, that vital energy that disappears when you die.&nbsp; In the search for that vital light, I try to make the &ldquo;soul&rdquo; visible.</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NFT link:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/matic/0x2953399124f0cbb46d2cbacd8a89cf0599974963/98456259310004152772380024615094159730586089372211649513628528023583760318465\">https://opensea.io/assets/matic/0x2953399124f0cbb46d2cbacd8a89cf0599974963/98456259310004152772380024615094159730586089372211649513628528023583760318465</a></p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ONLINE EXHIBITION ONLY</p>\r\n<p>MarsLandingGalleries.com</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>IG&nbsp;@lou_peralta_photo_based_artist</p>', 'https://twitter.com/LouPeraltaArt', 'https://www.louperalta.art/', '', '', '0', '1659584249', 'https://opensea.io/assets/matic/0x2953399124f0cbb46d2cbacd8a89cf0599974963/9845625931000415277238002', 'https://www.instagram.com/lou_peralta_photo_based_artist/'),
(551, 'Marcotic', 'marcotic', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/marcotic.jpg', '<p>Cyberhippie and cryptoartist.</p>\r\n<p>I mainly do 3D Animations, Trashart, 3DFractalpaintings, Glitchart, small animations and whatever I feel like doing.<br />My style is like me, in permanent change.<br />I like to describe myself as a puzzle that is put together every morning and sometimes some pieces don&rsquo;t fit well together ', 'https://twitter.com/marcotic12', 'https://marcotic.org/', '', '', '0', '1683698428', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/marcotic12/');
INSERT INTO `artists` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `pic`, `description`, `twitter`, `website`, `email`, `old_url`, `hidden`, `edited`, `shop_url`, `instagram`) VALUES
(535, 'Enki-Ea Isaac', 'enki-ea-isaac', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/enki-ea-isaac.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Visionary on the blockchain advocating for a sustainable future. \\n\\n17% of my sales goes towards organizations focused on:\\n\\n-the protection, conservation, preservation, and education of the Amazon Rainforest &amp; its Indigenous Peoples\\n\\n-combating human trafficking &amp; providing resources to its victims&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:897,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0}\">Visionary on the blockchain advocating for a sustainable future.<br /><br />17% of my sales goes towards organizations focused on:<br /><br />-the protection, conservation, preservation, and education of the Amazon Rainforest &amp; its Indigenous Peoples<br /><br />-combating human trafficking &amp; providing resources to its victims</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/Light_Ea_', 'www.light-ea.com', 'info@light-ea.com', '', '0', '1653701821', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/light.ea_'),
(562, 'Rob Jensen', 'rob-jensen', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/rob-jensen.jpg', '<p>Lead Artist Rob Jensen conceived the Sonic Runway while observing the effects of sound at Burning Man in 2002. As a visual artist, engineer, and musician, Rob has always been drawn to the intersection of science and art. Rob&rsquo;s day job also combines art and technology, where he alternates between animating and engineering at Pixar Animation Studios.</p>', '', '', '', '', '0', '1682367963', NULL, ''),
(563, 'Warren Trezevant', 'warren-trezevant', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/warren-trezevant.jpg', '<p>Warren enjoys creating experiences of wonder. From bringing characters to life on the movie screen, as a former animator at Pixar Animation Studios, to bringing them to life in the real world with the stroboscopic Toy Story Zoetrope, Peter Hudson&rsquo;s large-scale zoetropes Charon and Eternal Return, as well as the breathing for Marco Cochrane&rsquo;s R_Evolution.</p>', '', '', '', '', '0', '1682368951', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/warrentrezevant/'),
(537, 'Hakan Lidbo', 'hakan-lidbo', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/hakan-lidbo.png', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Following a career in electronic music with more than 350 records released, Hakan Lidbo explores new ideas within interactive art, music, robotics, games, urban planning, and design fiction. He is also the founder of Rumtiden Idea Lab in Stockholm Sweden</span></p>', '', 'http://rumtiden.com', 'hakan@hakanlidbo.com', '', '0', '1653702272', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/hakanlidbo'),
(538, 'Roly Skender', 'roly-skender', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/roly-skender.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;LightWaves is a dynamic audiovisual artwork which recreates a primal oceanic force in digital form. Giant, slow-motion waves build to a peak and crash in high-resolution, immersing audiences in projected light and atmospheric sound through a mesmerising cyclic spectacle.&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:897,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0}\">LightWaves is a dynamic audiovisual artwork which recreates a primal oceanic force in digital form. Giant, slow-motion waves build to a peak and crash in high-resolution, immersing audiences in projected light and atmospheric sound through a mesmerising cyclic spectacle.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/rolyskender', '', 'mail@frankensound.com.au', '', '0', '1653702391', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/frankensoundz'),
(539, 'ReVerse Butcher', 'reverse-butcher', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/reverse-butcher.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\">ReVerse Butcher is a multi-disciplinary artist with focuses in Virtual &amp; Augmented Reality art, unique artist&rsquo;s books, collages, visual art, film-making, writing &amp; performance. She will use any medium necessary to engage and subvert reality until it is less dull and oppressive. When she grows up, she wants to be a well-read recluse. She currently lives in Melbourne, Australia.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/x_rVb_x', 'www.reversebutcher.com ', 'reversebutcher@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653702512', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/reversebutcher'),
(540, 'Driven Arts Collective', 'driven-arts-collective', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/driven-arts-collective.jpeg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Driven Arts Collective is a Bay Area team of makers, dancers, visual artists, musicians, software engineers, and thinkers. We investigate planned and spontaneous ingenuity through technologically infused performance art, experimental modern contemporary dance, real-time generative music and video, custom programmed and designed wearable tech, film, video art, and whatever else we can get our hands on.&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:897,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;10&quot;:0,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0}\">Driven Arts Collective is a Bay Area team of makers, dancers, visual artists, musicians, software engineers, and thinkers. We investigate planned and spontaneous ingenuity through technologically infused performance art, experimental modern contemporary dance, real-time generative music and video, custom programmed and designed wearable tech, film, video art, and whatever else we can get our hands on.</span></p>', '', 'https://www.drivenartscollective.com/', 'driven.arts.collective@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653702722', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/driven.arts.collective/?hl=en'),
(541, 'Varsha Iyengar', 'varsha-iyengar', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/varsha-iyengar.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Varsha Iyengar is a dancer, engineer and creative technologist based in San Francisco, California. She is a a trained Indian classical dancer and danced part-time for Nritarutya, a leading dance company in India. She holds an MS in Arts, Media and Engineering. Her work largely involves creating multifaceted interactive environments by blending movement arts and technology. https://varshaiyengar.com/</span></p>', '', 'https://varshaiyengar.com/', 'varshaiyengar177@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653705109', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/framing.moves/?hl=en'),
(542, 'Michael Krzyzaniak', 'michael-krzyzaniak', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/michael-krzyzaniak.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Michael Krzyzaniak holds a Ph.D. in Media Arts + Sciences from Arizona State University. His background is in music composition. He studies human-machine interaction in creative contexts, and builds machines that play musical instruments. He develops techniques that allow the machines to learn how to play by listening to humans play. He also studies human movement and develops responsive audio environments for dance works. His most current work involves programming soccer balls to encourage practice and assist coaches. https://michaelkrzyzaniak.com/</span></p>', '', 'https://michaelkrzyzaniak.com/', 'michael.krzyzaniak@yahoo.com', '', '0', '1653705249', '', ''),
(545, 'Kasey Edgerton', 'kasey-edgerton', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/kasey-edgerton.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Kasey Edgerton is an artist and writer residing in New York, working primarily with experimental new media, and biological elements (bioart). She looks at the permeable boundaries between real and imagined, science and magic, objective and subjective. Kasey explores embodiment, co-collaboration with other species and AIs, and the nature of spirituality and human experience in our increasingly digitized and hyperconnected world. Through her work she hopes to reveal new ways for us to coexist with technology and the biological world.\\n\\n​Kasey holds an MFA in Visual Studies from Visual Studies Workshop, and is currently enrolled in the MA in Museum Studies graduate program at Harvard University. She is also currently studying Biodesign &amp; Regenerative and Ecological Design in the Diploma Programme with Ecodemia, based in London.\\n&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:513,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;12&quot;:0}\">Kasey Edgerton is an artist and writer residing in New York, working primarily with experimental new media, and biological elements (bioart). She looks at the permeable boundaries between real and imagined, science and magic, objective and subjective. Kasey explores embodiment, co-collaboration with other species and AIs, and the nature of spirituality and human experience in our increasingly digitized and hyperconnected world. Through her work she hopes to reveal new ways for us to coexist with technology and the biological world.<br /><br />​Kasey holds an MFA in Visual Studies from Visual Studies Workshop, and is currently enrolled in the MA in Museum Studies graduate program at Harvard University. She is also currently studying Biodesign &amp; Regenerative and Ecological Design in the Diploma Programme with Ecodemia, based in London.<br /></span></p>', '', 'https://www.kaseyedgerton.com/general-5', 'edgerton.kasey@gmail.com', '', '0', '1653762526', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/kasey.edgerton'),
(544, 'Lomakin', 'lomakin', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/lomakin.png', '', 'https://twitter.com/MrBrownNFT', 'https://mrbrownproject.com', 'brown@mrbrownproject.com', '', '0', '1653762250', '', ''),
(546, 'Fabio Cortés', 'fabio-cort-s', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/fabio-cort-s.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Creative developer from Bogot&aacute;, Colombia, and now based in Lausanne, Switzerland. Focused on immersive technologies, 3D development and generative art. Currently working as WebXR engineer at EPFL, creating AR/VR tools for research and education on chemistry and biology.</span></p>', 'https://twitter.com/fabiojcortes', 'https://www.fjcr.pro/', 'fabio@fjcr.pro', '', '0', '1683698527', ' https://objkt.com/asset/hicetnunc/709541', 'https://www.instagram.com/fabiojcortes/'),
(547, ' Daryl Slaton', 'daryl-slaton', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/daryl-slaton.jpg', '<p>My goal is to give the viewer a brief escape from our troubled times via fun art and AR animation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/DarylSlaton', '', '', '', '0', '1683700529', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/darylslaton/'),
(548, 'Edison Duran Lucena', 'edison-duran-lucena', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/edison-duran-lucena.jpeg', '<p>Edison is a Physicist, a member of the Venezuelan diaspora, currently living in Santiago, Chile. Over the years, he morphed into a social and tech entrepreneur, leading the creation of several NGOs in human and environmental rights and startups with social impact. He serves as co-founder and CEO of PleIQ, an ed-tech startup that uses XR technologies to improve early childhood education in LATAM.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In this creative project, he combines artificial intelligence and augmented reality to bring his poems beyond words. His artworks want to provide an immersive experience for the spectator, bringing him on a journey through the painting and its meaning. Concepts from topology, theoretical and quantum physics usually serve as metaphors to express their feelings and worldviews, looking for an interception between science and arts.</p>', 'https://twitter.com/edisondl', 'https://www.edisonduran.art/', '', '', '0', '1683700265', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/edison.ia.art/'),
(566, 'Carr Wilkerson', 'carr-wilkerson', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/carr-wilkerson.jpg', '<p>Carr Lane Wilkerson Jr. passed away on March 26, 2019, in Lafayette, LA. He was born in Pasay City, Philippines, on April 29, 1966. He grew up in Burlingame, California, attending Burlingame High School until age 16, when he and his family moved to Lafayette, LA. He was a graduate of Comeaux High School, Class of 1984. In 1986 he enlisted in the United States Navy Nuclear Propulsion Program. He was awarded an NROTC scholarship in 1988 and matriculated to Tulane University, earning a Bachelor of Science in Physics. After graduating, he reentered the Nuclear Propulsion Program as an Ensign. His first tour of duty was on a non-nuclear vessel, the USS McClusky (FFG-41), out of Yokosuka, Japan, as the Combat Information Center Officer. He made two tours of duty to the Persian Gulf in support of Operation Desert Watch. He then served on the nuclear-powered USS Arkansas (CGN-41) based in Bremerton, Washington, as M-Division Engineering Officer, earned his Nuclear Propulsion Engineering Qualification, and supported operations on the West Coast. His final tour was as the US Naval Liaison Officer to the French Naval Academy in Brest, France, for two years. He left the Navy in 2001 to enter the Master of Arts program at Stanford University\'s Center for Computer Research in Music and Acoustics (CCRMA). After graduating, he went back to Tulane University to complete a Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering. Interrupted by Hurricane Katrina, he left the program with a Master of Engineering, returning to Stanford\'s CCRMA program as a System Administrator and Instructor in Music Technology. After 10 years there, he moved back to Louisiana and, most recently, was Communications Director for the Council for the Development of French in Louisiana (CODOFIL) in Lafayette. His passions included all forms of music and music technology, as well as the French language and culture in Louisiana and North America.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'https://ccrma.stanford.edu/people/carr-wilkerson', '', '', '0', '1683747667', '', ''),
(549, 'ejthek', 'ejthek', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/ejthek.jpg', '<p>hey hey! I\'m a digital artist based in Canada and find myself driven to discover ways to express my thought journey in primarily abstract or surreal ways. I&rsquo;ve been minting&nbsp;NFT crypto art since 2020 and am grateful for the opportunity to participate as a longtime member of The Guild decentralized global artist consortium.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/ejthek_art', 'https://ejthek.myportfolio.com/', '', '', '0', '1683698932', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/ejthek_art/'),
(552, 'odbol', 'odbol', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/odbol.jpg', '<div class=\"figure\"><strong>odbol</strong>(aka Tyler Freeman) is an artist that specializes in designing interfaces that bring the body closer to the machine, thus enhancing the users ability to manipulate digital information efficiently and unobtrusively&nbsp; some people refer to these users as cyborgs, but the phenomenon is so rampant in todays world that the word cyborg really loses all meaning.</div>\r\n<div class=\"bio-container editable-group\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">odbol received his undergrad degree in Computer Science and his Masters in Digital Art and New Media at the University of California, Santa Cruz. He currently resides in San Francisco, CA. He is an active VJ who has played for numerous bands and acts throughout the United States and Europe, and has invented several performance interfaces such as&nbsp;DrumPants&nbsp;and&nbsp;WiiJ Video.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">Animated my wizard portrait that I commissioned from Pikio. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/motiondesign?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#motiondesign</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/illustration?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#illustration</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/magic?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#magic</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/z2oe6DIHVl\">pic.twitter.com/z2oe6DIHVl</a></p>\r\n&mdash; odbol (@odbol) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/odbol/status/1027731983030353921?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">August 10, 2018</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" async=\"\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/odbol', 'http://www.odbol.com/', '', '', '0', '1683701354', 'https://codame.threadless.com/collections/odbol', 'https://www.instagram.com/odbol/'),
(554, 'Sofía Maldonado', 'sof-a-maldonado', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/sof-a-maldonado.jpg', '<p>Puerto Rican artist of Cuban descent, from San Juan, Puerto Rico. She has spent most of her career in derelict spaces, constructing a poetic experience of colorful abstractions within uninhabited buildings. Maldonado\'s urban walkabouts inspired a desire to transform the environment with color by painting abandoned structures using a paint sprayer. Her career is focused on public art and color field painting. The artist also has a dynamic studio practice as a painter and digital illustrator. She develops a sense of community through workshops and versatile community engagement projects. Collaborations with musicians and underground subcultures are integral to her artistic practice and aesthetic.</p>\r\n<p>Maldonado\'s characteristic style is recognizable for its Caribbean palette and roots in muralismo. She deconstructs organic forms in order to explore color fields in her work. She represents feminine energy in her expressive outlines and sensually themed drawings. The artist&rsquo;s colorful landscapes extended in space indicate the passage of time and the ephemerality of architectural structures. Maldonado\'s highly saturated, almost fluorescent, tropical palette reflects her animated personality and creates optical vibrations due to her energetic marks and distinctive application of color.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Throughout her career, Maldonado&rsquo;s illustrations of femininity have been defiant and present the pleasure associated with the female experience in detail. Her architectural color interventions manifest a deep awareness of spatial deconstruction and what has been established.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As an artist, she reflects her colonial reality in site-specific projects such as Kala&ntilde;a, exhibited at the Whitney Museum Biennial, NY (2017). In this project, as in her massive abstract murals, she employs color as a signifier of abandonment rather than as a beautifying agent. Maldonado explores the spectrum of the feminine body by challenging cultural myths and social constructs from the outlooks of hip hop, trap music, and reggaeton.</p>\r\n<p>Maldonado has earned a BFA from the Escuela de Artes Pl&aacute;sticas de Puerto Rico and an MFA from Pratt Institute in Brooklyn, New York. She has participated in select exhibitions: PST:LA/LA at MOLAA, California (2017), La Bienal de Asunci&oacute;n, Paraguay (2014), CAAM, Canary Islands (2013), Museum of Art and Design, NY (2013), Museum of Contemporary Art of Puerto Rico (2012), Museo del Barrio Biennial, NY (2011) and the Havana Biennial, Cuba, and Real Arts Public, Real Art Ways, Hartford, CT (2008). She was awarded the Manhattan Community Arts Fund Grant, LMCC, (NY) in 2012.</p>', 'https://www.sofiamaldonado.com/gallery', 'https://www.sofiamaldonado.com/', '', '', '0', '1683700918', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/sofiamaldo/'),
(555, 'strayltd', 'strayltd', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/strayltd.jpg', '<p>Strayltd is an artist creating collages made from specially chosen sources to add context to the themes found within their art playfully.</p>\r\n<p>Using montage and collage processes, strayltd creates figurative art with contemporary cultural narratives. Work by strayltd appears on box sets and record covers for well-known bands and musicians, and features at small exhibitions in galleries around the world and in the metaverse.</p>\r\n<p>Also collected by respected artists and collectors in the form of cryptoart, strayltd&rsquo;s work has been minted to the etherium blockchain and exists as static, animated, programmable and generative nfts in single and multiple editions.</p>\r\n<p>When creating collage, the source of imagery for each artwork is specially chosen to playfully add context to the theme of each picture. Examples of this include the story of Adam and Eve made from i-D.vice.com, Illuminati inspired dreamscapes made from album covers of The Mars Volta, and portraits of the Queen made from 70s punk memorabilia.</p>\r\n<p>Working collaboratively, strayltd was one of 33 artists that made a portrait of cryptoartist Alotta Money for a cancer charity fundraiser. As a guest of the international artist collective The Guild, strayltd created The Dreamer for the sold-out, generative music nft, Dream Recorder. And in collaboration with musician plutonic mind, generative and animated audiovisual artworks have been minted by a number of well-known collectors.</p>\r\n<p>Regularly trending on cryptoart platforms, strayltd&rsquo;s work features among the Async Art top 30 blueprints and has also been minted on MakersPlace, Foundation, KnownOrigin and NiftyGateway. Portraits of The King and Queen have been on display in the PannVerse and at Kunsthalle Z&uuml;rich, and The Dreamer was exhibited for the first time at NFT.NYC 2023.</p>\r\n<p>Art direction of box sets and album covers by strayltd have also received accolades, with work for The Mars Volta and Omar Rodr&iacute;guez-L&oacute;pez having been entered for the Grammy Awards. And, most recently, a collection of album covers by strayltd featured in the In-Between exhibition at the Reeperbahn Festival in Germany.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>', 'https://twitter.com/strayltd', 'https://strayltd.com/art', '', '', '0', '1683699981', 'https://knownorigin.io/gallery/13347000-the-wheel-of-samsara-i', 'https://www.instagram.com/strayltd/'),
(567, 'Luke Dahl', 'luke-dahl', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/luke-dahl.jpg', '<p>Luke Dahl is an Assistant Professor of Composition and Computer Technologies in the Music Department at the University of Virginia. He teaches classes on music technology, audio signal processing, and music interaction design. His research is primarily situated in the interdisciplinary field of New Interfaces for Musical Expression (NIME), which investigates and explores the intersection of technology and musical practice through the activities of design, musical performance, and empirical research. He is especially interested in systems for digitally-mediated real-time music collaboration and the role of human gesture and movement in music.</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Dahl earned his Ph.D. in Computer-Based Music Theory and Acoustics from the Center for Computer Research in Music and Acoustics (CCRMA) at Stanford University and a bachelor&rsquo;s in Electrical Engineering at the University of Michigan. At CCRMA, he was a founding member of the Stanford Laptop Orchestra and the Stanford Mobile Phone Orchestra. His musical works include SoundBounce for mobile phone orchestra, which was performed at NIME in Sydney, and TweetDreams for audience interaction and live Twitter data, which was premiered at the MiTo Settembre Musica Festival in Milan and has been performed in Oslo, San Francisco, Stony Brook, and at TEDx Silicon Valley.</p>\r\n<p>Before returning to academia, Luke worked at the Joint E-mu/Creative Advanced Technology Center, where he developed reverb algorithms for the SoundBlasterLive sound card products and co-authored patents on audio signal processing, and at Apple, where he worked on audio for iPod and laptop products.</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Dahl has recently released alpha versions of two software libraries: Modosc is a Max library for processing motion-capture data in real-time to enable movement-based interactions, which was created in collaboration with Dr. Federico Visi. Bf-Pd is a library written in PureData that facilitates real-time data-sharing and collaboration between musicians in spontaneously formed ensembles. Bf-Pd was developed in collaboration with Dr. Florent Berthaut at Universit&eacute; de Lille.</p>', '', '', 'lsd5k@virginia.edu', '', '0', '1683748630', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/otto_telic'),
(557, 'synwrks', 'synwrks', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/synwrks.jpg', '<p>Collection of inner visions conjured by music and sound.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'https://www.synestheticworks.com/', '', '', '0', '1683697259', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/synwrks/'),
(556, 'plutonicmind', 'plutonicmind', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/plutonicmind.jpg', '<h2 data-kubio=\"kubio/heading\">&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-kubio=\"kubio/text\">\"AFTER PLAYING CHOPIN, I NEED TO PLAY BACH TO FEEL CLEAN AGAIN\"</p>\r\n<p data-kubio=\"kubio/text\">A classical pianist, composer and audiovisual artist using specialist recording techniques, plutonic mind creates contemporary classical and post minimalist music that is often combined with kaleidoscopic visuals.</p>\r\n<p data-kubio=\"kubio/text\">A member of the international artist-led collective,&nbsp;The Guild, and publishing her audio-visual artwork and music to the ethereum blockchain as NFTs, plutonic mind&rsquo;s work has been exhibited in real life and metaverse galleries.</p>', 'https://twitter.com/plutonicmind', 'http://plutonicmind.com/', '', '', '0', '1683697832', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/plutonicmind/'),
(558, 'Cassandra Mark', 'cassandra-mark', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/cassandra-mark.png', '<p>Title: G.A.I.A</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Artist: The Art Of Cassandra Mark</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Medium: Illustration + Animation</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Price: 1.27 ETH</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Edition: 1/1</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Bio: My creations are inspired by African Mythology, Anime and Star Wars.</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Description:</p>\r\n<p>Earth Mother, Queen of the BIo-sentinels, Guide us with your emerald tears. G.A.I.A is a sentient hive mind built in 2073 to reduce the rise of pollution and restore the ecosystem.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NFT link:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://rarible.com/token/0xc9154424b823b10579895ccbe442d41b9abd96ed:20158323215783746770496890217137548179788901066440645114110671836741879463937?tab=details\">https://rarible.com/token/0xc9154424b823b10579895ccbe442d41b9abd96ed:20158323215783746770496890217137548179788901066440645114110671836741879463937?tab=details</a></p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>IG @theart.of.wani</p>', 'https://twitter.com/casslives', 'https://theartofwani.my.canva.site/concept-art-portfolio-the-art-of-wani', '', '', '0', '1659662399', 'https://rarible.com/token/0xc9154424b823b10579895ccbe442d41b9abd96ed:2015832321578374677049689021713', 'https://www.instagram.com/theart.of.wani/'),
(560, 'Mario Klingemann', 'mario-klingemann', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/mario-klingemann.jpg', '<p>I&rsquo;m an artist and a skeptic with a curious mind. My preferred tools are neural networks, code and algorithms. My interests are manifold and in constant evolution, involving artificial intelligence, deep learning, generative and evolutionary art, glitch art, data classification and visualization or robotic installations. If there is one common denominator it&rsquo;s my desire to understand, question and subvert the inner workings of systems of any kind. I also have a deep interest in human perception and aesthetic theory.</p>\r\n<p>Since I taught myself programming in the early 1980s I have been trying to create algorithms that are able to surprise and to show almost autonomous creative behavior. The recent advancements in artificial intelligence, deep learning and data analysis make me confident that in the near future &ldquo;machine artists&rdquo; will be able to create more interesting work than humans.</p>', 'https://twitter.com/Quasimondo', 'https://underdestruction.com/', 'quasimodo@gmail.com', '', '0', '1679717780', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/quasimondo/'),
(561, 'Andre Roehrig', 'andre-roehrig', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/andr-r-hrig.jpg', '<p>Data Scientist. Experienced in deep learning and time-series modelling.</p>', '', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrerohrig/', '', '', '0', '1679718162', '', ''),
(569, 'Marco de Campos', 'marco-de-campos', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/marco-de-campos.jpg', '<p>Developer by experience, DevRel by vocation, and Geek at heart ❤️</p>', '', '', 'mdecampos@gmail.com', '', '0', '1684885260', '', ''),
(570, 'Maribel Mullins', 'maribel-mullins', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/maribel-mullins.jpg', '<p>Maribel Mullins is a Technology Partner Manager at Cloudinary, leading their Partner-built integrations program. She&rsquo;s been with Cloudinary for over 4 years. With her technical background, she has worked at various startup companies for the last 16 years in engineering, sales, and customer success. Her attention to detail and drive to continuously find new tools for her &ldquo;life&rsquo;s toolbox&rdquo; position her especially well to find solutions and manage resources.</p>', '', '', '', '', '0', '1684258090', NULL, ''),
(571, 'Ivan DelSol', 'ivan-delsol', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/ivan-delsol.jpeg', '<p><span style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\">Ivan DelSol is a west-coast based software developer, outlaw thespian, and social sculptor. He is part of the development team at Derivative, creators of the TouchDesigner visual development platform. His coding focuses are UI/UX and system design, including the TDAbleton interface between Ableton Live and TouchDesigner. He is also a co-founder of the Opal Center For Arts &amp; Education, a renegade community theater in rural Oregon, where he produces absurd pop-culture mashups, including Little Orphan Aliens, Xanadune, and Raising Oklahoma. Ivan&rsquo;s recent work includes digital experiments such as the Star Trek Machine and magical experiments such as the Ritual Tarot of The Boundless Heart. His other lives have included teaching, global adventuring, video game programming, VJing, freight train hopping, collectible card game design, and a hundred tiny revolutions.</span></p>', '', '', '', '', '0', '1686802287', NULL, ''),
(572, 'Vincent Naples', 'vincent-naples', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/vincent-naples.png', '<div style=\"caret-color: #000000; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 13.333333px;\">Vincent Naples is a multi-media artist and digital technologist working with time-based media, procedural design and generative AI processes. As a performer, tool builder and educator, his passion lies in creating novel interactive experiences, navigating the boundaries of emergent technology, and engaging environment as an instrument. Working with TouchDesigner, Ableton and various mapping and creative coding pipelines, his work aims to critically explore praxis as medium and subvert normative cultural understandings of technology as a tool for expression.</span></div>', '', 'https://drmbt.com/', 'Vincent@drmbt.com', '', '0', '1686802916', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/drmbt');
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(1, 'Adopt ART+TECH with Anouk & Reza', 'adopt-art-tech-with-anouk-reza', '2015-05-14', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/adopt-art-tech-with-anouk-reza.jpg', '<blockquote>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It might be surprising to note that a number of tech companies are investing increasingly in artist residency programs. In fact, two of the biggest tech companies in the regionâ€Š&mdash;â€ŠFacebook and Autodeskâ€Š&mdash;â€Šmaintain active residency programs. For companies without the infrastructure for such endeavors, local art and technology non-profit&nbsp;CODAME offers to pair tech companies with artists for individual projects through their &lsquo;Adopt An Artist&rsquo; program.&rdquo; &nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/up-in-the-air-how-will-tech-residencies-reshape-bay-area-art-eab5a7390e2f\" target=\"_blank\">Ceci Moss</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Join us for an evening to get inspired! Celebrate the&nbsp;<a href=\"/adopt/\">Adopt Program</a>&nbsp;with notable CODAME Featured Artists:&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/anouk-wipprecht/\">Anouk</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/reza/\">Reza</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Learn about their&nbsp;residency experiences, perspectives and projects. See for yourself how they embrace innovation through creativity, play, and collaboration between artists and technologists.</p>\r\n<p>Installation Premier: Interactive experience created&nbsp;by&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/donald-hanson/\">Donald Hanson</a>&nbsp;in collaboration with Anouk Wipprecht.</p>\r\n<p>Special thanks&nbsp;to the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/salesforceux\">Salesforce UX</a>&nbsp;team, our Host &amp; Sponsor for this event.</p>\r\n<p>Location: Salesforce Cafe&rsquo; Rincon Center, 101 Spear St., San Francisco, CA 94105</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/128102590\" width=\"738\" height=\"415\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>SCHEDULE</p>\r\n<p>6:00pm &ndash; Doors Open &ndash; Drinks and Snacks</p>\r\n<p>6:45pm &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/cvilly\" target=\"_blank\">Craig Villamor,</a>&nbsp;Chief Product Designer&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/SalesforceUX\" target=\"_blank\">@Salesforce</a>, on Art, Technology, and &ldquo;Adoptions&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>7:00pm &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/reza/\">Reza Ali</a>&nbsp;talk and Q&amp;A</p>\r\n<p>7:45pm &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/anouk-wipprecht/\">Anouk Wipprecht</a>&nbsp;talk and Q&amp;A</p>\r\n<p>8:30pm &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/donald-hanson/\">Donald Hanson</a>&nbsp;+ Anouk installation&nbsp;premiere</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/anouk.jpg\" alt=\"anouk\" width=\"743\" height=\"392\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/portfolio/anouk-wipprecht/\">Anouk Wipprecht</a>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;Dutch-based fashion-tech designer and innovator who&nbsp;works in the emerging field of electronic couture, a rare combination of fashion design combined with engineering, science and interaction/user experience design. &nbsp;Part futuristic, part anime-meets-high fashion, her designs move, breathe, and react to the environment around them &ndash;designs that bring together systems around the body that gravitate towards artificial intelligence.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Selfie_Black-small.jpg\" alt=\"Selfie_Black small\" width=\"737\" height=\"737\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/portfolio/reza/\">Reza Ali</a>&nbsp;is a computational designer and creative engineer who is interested in art, science, and entrepreneurship. He uses code to express himself visually, and creates tools and libraries to help others create by sharing his methodology.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>About CODAME ART+TECH Adopt Program</strong></p>\r\n<p>Based on a flexible model tailored to your unique organizational needs, the&nbsp;<a href=\"/adopt/\">Adopt Program</a>&nbsp;enables companies to collaborate with a diverse community of artists making and hacking in a range of media&mdash;from projection mapping, motion sensors and wearable technologies to robotics, data visualization and MIDI controllers. A few thought starters for the potential Adoptions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Interactive&nbsp;installations&nbsp;for conventions, trade shows or on your site.</li>\r\n<li>Artist In Residence&nbsp;create and collaborate for a week, month or quarter.</li>\r\n<li>Data visualizations&nbsp;to support marketing and branding efforts in a fun and creative way.</li>\r\n<li>Video&nbsp;installations&nbsp;to illuminate your vision and inspirit talent.</li>\r\n<li>Office space&nbsp;distinctive original artworks.</li>\r\n<li>Inspirational&nbsp;talks&nbsp;with artists working in the intersection of art and technology.</li>\r\n<li>Workshops&nbsp;with your teams of any discipline or size.</li>\r\n<li>Events&nbsp;private or public, always unique, educational, and community inspiring.</li>\r\n<li>Showcase&nbsp;capabilities of your products, while supporting the vital San Francisco creative culture.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/128102590\">Adopt ART+TECH with Anouk &amp; Reza</a> from <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/codame\">CODAME</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Adopt Program is Nonprofit:&nbsp;CODAME accepts tax deductible donations as members of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://theintersection.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Intersection for the Arts</a>,&nbsp;a 501(c)(3). We can tailor content to match any budget, with each project as unique as your organization.&nbsp;Let&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:adopt@codame.com\">begin the conversation</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Read&nbsp;about the Adopt Program and other artist residencies in the Bay Area:</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"Embedded story\" src=\"https://api.medium.com/embed?type=story&amp;path=%2Fcodame-art-tech%2Fup-in-the-air-how-will-tech-residencies-reshape-bay-area-art-eab5a7390e2f&amp;id=0&amp;collapsed=true\" width=\"307\" height=\"275\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>', 'anouk-wipprecht,reza-ali,donald-hanson', '', 'salesforce', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(54, 'ART+TECH Festival [2015]', 'art-tech-festival-2015', '2015-10-23', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/movement-art-tech-festival-2015.gif', '<p>Presenting our Annual CODAME ART+TECH Festival, a Two-day Event on October 23rd + 24th!</p>\r\n<p>Exploring the immersive landscape of MOVEMENT, CODAME&nbsp;will be showcasing new works that demonstrate the fusion of art and technology from new and exciting angles within our festival\'s theme including innovative dance compositions, mind-bending performances, immersive and interactive installations, generative art, new media, and concept pieces by local, national, and international artists.</p>\r\n<p>We bring together these independent artists, inviting all to join us in celebrating Art and Technology!</p>\r\n<p>Local and Collaborating Artists include:&nbsp;Kinetech Arts, Paul Ackerman, Saturn Rising, Marpi, Zoey Vero, Zen Cohen, Colton Long, Katherine Frazer and Xiaohan Zhang, Sustainable Magic, Idyll Collective, Rachel Rose Ulgado + Aaron Waterhouse, Christopher Shaw, Matthew Howell, Donald Hason, Raquel Boluda, Jeffrey Yip, Zach Vorhies,&nbsp;Jeffrey Bryant, Jasper Patterson, staRpauSe, Total Unicorn, Foxxy Newport, Anticlockwise Arts, and more!</p>\r\n<p>National Artists&nbsp;include: Kate Sicchio (NYC) and Leon Eckert (NYC)</p>\r\n<p>International Artists&nbsp;include: Natasha Singh (India), Alex Andre (Paris France), and Robert Allison (UK)</p>\r\n<p>Curator: Tiare Ribeaux</p>\r\n<p>Questions we asked the artists are: As technology is rapidly evolving around us, how does this affect our physical and emotional lives? How can we move with machines, and how do machines move with us? How can we continue to engage with each other and our environment actively in a digital world that seems to be making us increasingly more sedentary? How can we break out of our screens into multiple dimensions, using the new tools that technology can provide for us?</p>\r\n<p><strong>All proceeds from this event will be split with participating artists.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Date:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\">RSVP</a>&nbsp;for any of the two days,&nbsp;Friday&nbsp;23th or&nbsp;Saturday 24th October, 7pm &ndash; midnight</p>\r\n<p>Venue:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.monument.house/\">Monument</a>&nbsp;Located in the pulsing vein of San Francisco at 140 9th Street, Monument is a newly opened and renovated space.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dress code:&nbsp;It&rsquo;s close to Halloween! It\'s your&nbsp;opportunity to wear&nbsp;that art+tech outfit&nbsp;tonight! Costume or not, do come and enjoy!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Full Schedule:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Friday 10/23:&nbsp;Festival Launch: 7pm-12am&nbsp;Performance Lineup:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kinetech Arts</li>\r\n<li>Raquel Boluda</li>\r\n<li>Kate Sicchio</li>\r\n<li>Matthew Jones</li>\r\n<li>Zach Vorhies</li>\r\n<li>Christopher Shaw</li>\r\n<li>Paul Ackerman</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Saturday&nbsp;10/24</p>\r\n<p>Special Yoga Workshop with&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/showga\">Showga</a>: 6pm-7pm (prior doors open for the Festival)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>An opportunity to explore the healing dimensions of movement and music and how they interact.&nbsp;Participants will be guided through yoga postures and visualization exercises while live music is performed.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Night Festival: 7pm-12am Performance Lineup:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kate Sicchio</li>\r\n<li>Ian Heisters</li>\r\n<li>Micheal Garrigues</li>\r\n<li>Zoey Vero, Zen Cohen + Colton Long</li>\r\n<li>Saturn Rising w/Robert Allison</li>\r\n<li>Paul Ackerman</li>\r\n<li>Zach Vorhies</li>\r\n<li>Total Unicorn</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/207884332\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p>The motion graphic used in the flier is courtesy of <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/69948148\">JL Design &amp; KORB</a>.&nbsp;</p>', 'kinetech-arts,paul-ackerman,kate-sicchio,jeffrey-bryant,natasha-singh-timeblur,ian-heisters,marpi,zoey-vero,zen-cohen,leon-eckert,xiaohan-zhang,katherine-frazer,anticlockwise-arts,sustainable-magic,cruise,ooggee,capsvle,weidong-yang,jeffrey-yip,j-rmark,robert-allison,alex-andre,donald-hanson,foxxy-newport,total-unicorn,jordan-gray,tiare-ribeaux', 'bungsraum,transgress,metamorphosis,phenotyptych,gravity,ioio-plotter,nadi,windows,watercolor-walls', 'retronyms,design-system-team-salesforce-ux,organic', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(57, 'Github Universe After Party', 'github-universe-after-party', '2015-10-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/github-universe-after-party.jpg', '<p>We are very happy to announce Gitbub, another great organization, adopting&nbsp;ART+TECH.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME will featuring&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/outerbody\">Outerbody</a> and <a href=\"/projects/leapybird\">LeapyBird</a> for&nbsp;Github&nbsp;after party conference <a href=\"http://githubuniverse.com/\">Universe</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Find&nbsp;us Oct 1st at the official conference after party at the Village, music by <a href=\"http://www.mikerelm.com/\">Mike Relm</a> and surprise guests, brought to you by <a href=\"http://www.huawei.com\">Huawei</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/projects/leapybird\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leapybird2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"256\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/projects/outerbody\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/awesomeposter.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"761\" height=\"493\" /></a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'outerbody,leapybird', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(55, 'Call For Artists', 'call-for-artists', '2015-09-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/call-for-artists.gif', '<p>We are looking for performances that showcase the fusion of art and technology from new and exciting angles within our festival\'s theme \"Movement\". We seek dance compositions, immersive and interactive installations or performances, audio and visual collaborations, generative art, sculpture, fashion, new media, and concept pieces by local and national artists.</p>\r\n<p>Questions we are asking the artists are: As technology is rapidly evolving around us, how does this affect our physical and emotional lives? How can we move with machines, and how do machines move with us? How can we continue to engage with each other and our environment actively in a digital world that seems to be making us increasingly less sentient? How can we break out of our screens into multiple dimensions, using the new tools that technology can provide for us?</p>\r\n<p>Our goal is to engage and enrich the local Bay Area communities and create impactful experiences within art &amp; technology.</p>\r\n<p>All profits from the festival will be split with&nbsp;the artists.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2015\">More information about the 2015 ART+TECH Festival.</a></p>\r\n<p>Graphic courtesy of <a href=\"http://n-lite.tumblr.com/\">N-LITE</a>.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Call for Proposals Opens: July 15, 2015</strong><br /><strong>Call for Proposals Closes: September 1st, 2015</strong><br /><strong>Chosen Artists Contacted: September 15th, 2015</strong><br /><strong>Festival Dates: October 23rd + October 24th 2015</strong>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1DYg0LEDNgwN2to2ogxKDJhrb4IfFvEJEtTAGYNKV6dw/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"760\" height=\"2150\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loading...</iframe></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(2, 'Art by Code [2015]', 'art-by-code-2015', '2015-01-09', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-by-code-gallery-opening-.gif', '<p><strong>CODAME&nbsp;presents&nbsp;&ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo;&nbsp;in conjunction with&nbsp;Roll up Gallery.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo; is a triumph of human ingenuity and a tribute to artists who dare to imagine, invent, and test the limits creating art generated by code.</p>\r\n<p>All work will be on sale! Including the CODAME commissioned&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=6116\">NEON</a>&nbsp;is on Auction for&nbsp;a good cause!</p>\r\n<p>Put&nbsp;your bid amount and contact&nbsp;<a href=\"/bid/\">here</a>! Good luck and thanks for your support!</p>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_6176\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/10402636_654377321305266_2839915681685341657_n.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME NEON\" width=\"528\" height=\"528\" />\r\n<p>CODAME NEON on Auction at #ArtByCode</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Open Gallery:&nbsp;January 9th, 2015 with Music from&nbsp;DJ&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1159\">HARBOUR</a>,&nbsp;full body 3D scans&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=5139\">Modbod3D</a>, be&nbsp;captured by the&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1931\">IOIO&nbsp;plotter</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=5364\">PIXEL</a>&nbsp;ART&nbsp;LED Displays.</p>\r\n<p>Closing/Special&nbsp;Night:&nbsp;Soon to be officially announced&hellip;&nbsp;January 23rd, 2015. A special event with a special guest. Save the date!</p>\r\n<p>Open times:&nbsp;gallery is accessible as part of Public Works&nbsp;<a href=\"http://publicsf.com/listing\">events</a>, special&nbsp;arrangements could also be make by appointment,&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:curators@codame.com\">contact us</a></p>\r\n<p>Where:&nbsp;Roll up Gallery at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://publicsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">The Public Works SF</a>,&nbsp;161 Erie St, San Francisco, CA&nbsp;<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Public+Works,+Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;hl=en&amp;sll=37.768963,-122.419461&amp;sspn=0.010924,0.022724&amp;oq=public+wor161+Erie+St+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;t=h&amp;gl=us&amp;hq=Public+Works,&amp;hnear=Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+California+94103&amp;z=15&amp;iwloc=A\" target=\"_blank\">(map)</a></p>\r\n<p>Artists:&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=3853\">Reza Ali</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=6079\">Robert Allison</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1050\">Angat Gaata</a>, Tiare Ribeaux,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1096\">Donald Hanson</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/matthew-cella/\">Matthew Cella</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/brownshoesonly/\">Nick Ciontea</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/tim-cowley/\">Tim Cowley</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/joel-cretan/\">Joel Cretan</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=5474\">EMi</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1932\">Al Linke</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=2161\">DC Spensley</a>.</p>\r\n<p>RSVP:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://codame.eventbrite.com/</a></p>\r\n<p>Art curators:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/LoveModernArt\">Jaqueline Bacich</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/StarPause\">Jordan Gray</a>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/CODA_ME\">CODAME</a></p>\r\n<p>If interested showing your work in the future events with CODAME, get in touch with us&nbsp;by filling this&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=5517\">Call for Artists</a>&nbsp;form.</p>\r\n<div><hr />\r\n<p>&ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo; gives us an insight into a changing cyber universe populated by artists who brave new frontiers with their computational skills, and go beyond the limits of commercial software to create their unique codes that center on &lsquo;interactivity&rsquo; and &lsquo;user&rsquo; experiences.</p>\r\n<p>With &ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo; we aim to ignite the imagination of a new emerging generation and keep challenging the conventional ways of thinking about art and making art. The computer as the medium raises a host of intriguing questions and forces us to rethink what is art.</p>\r\n<p>The bay area artists have been generating increasingly complex visual forms with tools that rely on open-source. They use programs such as Java [processes], C++, [OpenFrameworks, Cinder], GLSL, JavaScript and AS3. These forms previously could not been imagined.</p>\r\n<p>The selection here represents a sampling of an explosive field and draws on the latest in computer technology from such fields like fractals, algorithmic processes, software art, generative art, data visualization, 3-D software, and much more.<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/7fbf0f1b108e7bbc440d0c96a44933253.jpg\" alt=\"Public Works San Francisco\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Gif Flier&nbsp;created with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.shadertoy.com/view/MdS3RG\">gtoledo3</a>&nbsp;code!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/art-by-code-shader-the-right-year.gif\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/art-by-code-shader-the-right-year.gif\" alt=\"art-by-code-shader-the-right-year\" width=\"773\" height=\"773\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>âŒ˜CâŒ˜V love!</p>', 'matthew-cella,joel-cretan,tim-cowley,donald-hanson,reza-ali,robert-allison,tiare-ribeaux,ytai-ben-tsvi,dc-spensley,emi,al-linke', 'ioio-plotter,codame-neon,modbod', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(3, 'LoveTech REACTIVATE', 'lovetech-reactivate', '2015-04-09', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/lovetech-reactivate.jpg', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">On Apr 9th,CODAME joins&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://lovetech.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">LoveTech</a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://feightsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">F8</a>&nbsp;as we REACTIVATE an innovative social music experience!</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">Spring into digital imagination space with hot new prototypes and get connected with emerging technologies that challenge what music and art creation can be when we do it together!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">+ We have a&nbsp;special&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://reactivate.lovetech.org/?discount=SyntheticDreams\"><span class=\"s2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">SyntheticDreams</span></span></a>&nbsp;code for 25% off for the Codame community. Grab it while you can!&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/lovetech-reactivate-tickets-16227773708?discount=SyntheticDreams\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP</a>&nbsp;now!</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"panel_section\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><center style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: solid none none; border-top-color: #dcdcdc; clear: both; color: #eeeeee; height: 1px; width: 676px; margin: 0px auto 2em; padding-top: 0px; background: none;\" />\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px;\">REACTIVATE with LoveTech for a creatively flourishing, ecstatically expanding evening!</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</center></div>\r\n<div class=\"panel_section\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"panel_section\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">Engage your entourage in energetic ensemble at the hands-on Digital Jam Lounge featuring&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://moldover.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Moldover</a>&lsquo;s melodically multiplayer&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://moldover.com/quicklinks/minimasher.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">MiniMasher</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/post/portfolio/al-linke/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Al Linke</a>&lsquo;s provocatively playful&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://ledpixelart.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">PIXEL</a>! Spark your synergic synapses in the Educational PlayShops! Vitalize your visual cortex with&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://vcovault.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">VCOVault</a>&lsquo;s riveting VJ action! Illuminate your intellect with&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://illuminationart.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Peter Tjeerdsma</a>&lsquo;s&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://youtu.be/vrOpSYVgSeo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Indra&rsquo;s Net</a>!\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: solid none none; border-top-color: #dcdcdc; clear: both; color: #eeeeee; height: 1px; width: 676px; margin: 0px auto 2em; padding-top: 0px; background: none;\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;REACTIVATING Musical Performances</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">REACTIVATE your inspiration with&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://controllerism.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Controllerism</a>&nbsp;founder&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://moldover.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">MOLDOVER</a>, bringing heartfelt music fresh from his forthcoming album,&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://alexkanemusic.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ALEX KANE</a>&nbsp;celebrating an energetic new EP,&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://zentope.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ZENOTOPE</a>&nbsp;rocking future bass with dancers in tow,&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://richddt.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">RICH DDT</a>commanding electrifying dance rhythms, and&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://eitch.bandcamp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">EITCH</a>&nbsp;swooning us with captivating vocal flow!</p>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://moldover.com/lovetech/bios/moldover_sm.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://moldover.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">MOLDOVER</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">The Godfather of Controllerism reaches deep into his soul to share an all new performance of heartsprung music from his forthcoming album, offering a timeless brilliance in its lyrical glow.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" align=\"right\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://moldover.com/lovetech/bios/alexkane_sm.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://alexkanemusic.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ALEX KANE</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">Passionately driven multi-instrumentalist and big beat electronic rocker harnessing sound &amp; video technology to break down the borders between the rock band and the DJ/Producer.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://moldover.com/lovetech/bios/ddt_sm.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://richddt.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">RICH DDT</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">Detonating Dance Tracks on his custom &ldquo;Controllitar&rdquo;, his contagiously funky glitch hop is live looped and electrifying, infused with exotic and nostalgic beats and bass blasted world flavors.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" align=\"right\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://moldover.com/lovetech/bios/zenotope_sm.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://zenotope.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ZENOTOPE</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">Enveloping the dancefloor with future bass waves that interweave downtempo glitch with surrealist and classical scifi, and featuring captivating dancers in synchronistic flow.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://moldover.com/lovetech/bios/eitch_sm.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://eitch.bandcamp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">EITCH</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">Fusing a blend of alternative, electronic &ldquo;Altronipop,&rdquo; her endless curiosity into cosmic reflections has crafted imaginative sonic structures of tantalizing lyricism and vocal radiance.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: solid none none; border-top-color: #dcdcdc; clear: both; color: #eeeeee; height: 1px; width: 676px; margin: 0px auto 2em; padding-top: 0px; background: none;\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\">Digital Jam Lounge!</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">Jam with your friends on&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://moldover.com/quicklinks/minimasher.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Moldover&rsquo;s MiniMasher</a>&nbsp;&mdash; an innovative 3-player visual and musical instrument of interactive delight!</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">Get your blinkies fix with PIXEL, the smartphone-enabled animated interactive LED panel by&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CODAME</a>&nbsp;featured artist Al Linke!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-weight: 100; line-height: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; word-wrap: break-word; font-size: 36px; text-align: center;\">Inspiring Educational Playshops!</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em;\">Come early and find yourself entangled in a tech mashup of musical mayhem and artistic awe as our talented instrumentalists lead you through their worlds of wonderous wizardry.</p>\r\n</div>', 'rich-ddt,moldover,vco-vault,dat-phan,jordan-gray', 'gifslap,modbod,receipt-bots', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(4, 'Celebrate and Play with CODAME @ 360|intersect', 'celebrate-and-play-with-codame-360-intersect', '2015-04-25', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/celebrate-and-play-with-codame-360-intersect.png', '<p><span style=\"color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">Join CODAME team members:&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\" href=\"/post/portfolio/starpause/\" target=\"_blank\">Jordan</a><span style=\"color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\" href=\"/post/portfolio/ani/\">Amy</a><span style=\"color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">&nbsp;@ 360|intersect,&nbsp;Children&rsquo;s Creativity Museum in San Francisco, April 25th, to celebrate ART+TECH, play and be inspired.</span></p>', 'jordan-gray,ani', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(5, 'Body Scan Asset Jam', 'body-scan-asset-jam', '2015-08-06', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/body-scan-asset-jam.jpg', '<ul>\r\n<li>On <a href=\"/events/codame-nightlife-live-2015\">August&nbsp;6th</a>, CODAME showcased at the <a href=\"/events/codame-nightlife-live-2015\">California Academy of Science</a>, the featuring submissions to the Body Scan Asset Jam.</li>\r\n<li>We now have over 800 models in our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/folders\">Sketchfab</a>&nbsp;collection.</li>\r\n<li>Let us know what you make with the models and tag us on social so we can share it too!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/sNJTSLmSJ9k\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>ORIGINAL CALL FOR&nbsp;ARTISTS / PLAYERS / MAKERS</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/portfolio/modbod3d/\">ModBod3D</a>&nbsp;has uploaded over 100 full body scans to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/folders\">Sketchfab</a>, all licensed under the Creative Commons for free remix, sharing and use.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To celebrate the asset dump, CODAME is holding a BODY SCAN ASSET JAM, starting now. All mediums are of interest: stylized renders, motion graphics, physical sculptures, traditional wall hanging pieces, VR/AR, music visualization/videos, etc!</p>\r\n<p>To be considered for the show,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1DYg0LEDNgwN2to2ogxKDJhrb4IfFvEJEtTAGYNKV6dw/viewform?edit_requested=true\" target=\"_blank\">Submit</a>&nbsp;your finished work or let us know about an idea you&rsquo;re excited about.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>PARTICIPATION INSTRUCTIONS</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/folders\">Grab</a>&nbsp;the assets (cleaned up stl meshes) for use in your creative and coding adventures.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/call-for-artists/\">Submit your work</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;consideration by August 1st Deadline.</li>\r\n<li>Join us August 6th at&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/codame-nightlife-live-2015\" target=\"_blank\">Cal Academy of Science NightLife</a>&nbsp;for the&nbsp;showcase!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>ADDITIONAL RESOURCES</strong></p>\r\n<p>Commercial:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://usa.autodesk.com/\" target=\"_blank\">3DS Max</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://autodesk.com/\" target=\"_blank\">AutoCAD</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://usa.autodesk.com/adsk/servlet/pc/index?id=13577897&amp;siteID=123112\" target=\"_blank\">Maya</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.materialise.com/Magics\" target=\"_blank\">Magics</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.rhino3d.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rhino3D</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.pixologic.com/home.php\" target=\"_blank\">ZBrush</a></p>\r\n<p>Free:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.glc-player.net/\" target=\"_blank\">GLC_Player</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://meshlab.sourceforge.net/\" target=\"_blank\">MeshLab</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.blender.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Blender</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/stlviewer/\" target=\"_blank\">STL-viewer</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://tinkercad.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Tinkercad</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.123dapp.com/\">Autodesk 123Apps</a></p>\r\n<p>ModBod3D STL ZIPS: <a href=\"http://starpause.com/stl/3d-k9d-normalized-for-body-scan-asset-jam.zip\" target=\"_blank\">compromised k9d</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s still time to be scanned and added to the collection as well, book&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/modbod3d/\">ModBod3D</a>&nbsp;scans for a private appointment or special event.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'ami-wang,jordan-gray,d0n-xyz', 'modbod', 'itseez3d', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(53, 'CODAME @ NightLife LIVE 2015', 'codame-nightlife-live-2015', '2015-10-15', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-nightlife-live-2015.png', '<p>CODAME as joined the California Academy of Sciences for&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.calacademy.org/nightlife/nightlife-live-june\" target=\"_blank\">NightLife LIVE</a>&nbsp;on a selected Thursday each month in 2015.</p>\r\n<p>Experience&nbsp;cutting-edge visual artists in an innovative intersection of science, music, and art.&nbsp;Witness special installations from a different featured artist at each event Art curated by CODAME and Betty Bigas.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"text-align: center;\">à¹›</span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>2015 Program</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>September 10</h3>\r\n<p>CODAME Featured Artist</p>\r\n<div><a href=\"/artists/anna-landa\">Anna Landa</a> is an artist based in New York City and San Francisco whose more recent work draws inspiration from the intersection of art and science. She creates two-dimensional works and installations reflecting her preoccupation with questions concerning the idea of self, time, and mortality.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>On display at the Academy of Science&rsquo;s NightLife event will be a new rendition of her sound installation &ldquo;The Fear&rdquo;. Inspired by research observing a fixed number of heartbeats in all mammals, the piece incorporates her own recorded heartbeat in an attempt to quantify human life&rsquo;s finite nature and bring the notion of mortality to the forefront of consciousness. The exhibit will utilize tactile transducers to convert the audio of the installation into a multi-sensory interactive experience for the viewer.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/130580627\" width=\"705\" height=\"396\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Live Music by</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://moonduo.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Moon Duo</a><br /><a href=\"http://peakinglights.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Peaking Lights Acid Test</a><br /><a href=\"http://folkyeah.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Britt Govea</a>&nbsp;(DJ set / Folkyeah)<br />Presented by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://folkyeah.com/\" target=\"_blank\">(((folkYEAH!)))</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://moonduo.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.calacademy.org/sites/default/files/styles/manual_crop_square_460px/public/assets/images/misc/1200x900_moonduo.png?itok=FHzvUgRv\" alt=\"MoonDuo\" width=\"597\" height=\"597\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><hr />\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">à¹›</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>August 6</h3>\r\n<p>CODAME is holding a&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/body-scan-asset-jam/\">BODY SCAN ASSET JAM</a>. Hosting a premier showcase featuring work created with&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/modbod3d/\">ModBod3D</a>&nbsp;assets.&nbsp;To be considered for the exhibition,<a href=\"/post/portfolio/call-for-artists/\">Submit</a>&nbsp;your work.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/portfolio/body-scan-asset-jam/\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/body-scan-asset-jam-final.jpg\" alt=\"body-scan-asset-jam-final\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Live Music by</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://alvvays.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Alvvays</a><br /><a href=\"http://grmlnband.tumblr.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GRMLN</a><br />Presented by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.sfoutsidelands.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Outside Lands</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img src=\"http://www.calacademy.org/sites/default/files/styles/manual_crop_square_460px/public/assets/images/misc/1200x900_alvvays.png?itok=Eu2u0qvv\" alt=\"Alvvays\" width=\"598\" height=\"598\" /></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">à¹›</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 11px;\">&nbsp;</span>July 9</h3>\r\n<p>CODAME is featuring artists from&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/magic-flowers/\">Sustainable Magic</a>. Using art and technology,&nbsp;Sustainable Magic&rsquo;s team&nbsp;creates engaging, interactive art with the aim to evoke&nbsp;surprise, wonder, delight, magic, and playfulness in their viewers, leading them to question their conception what what is possible.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Sustainable-Magic.jpg\" alt=\"Sustainable Magic\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></p>\r\n<p>Live Music by</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dodosmusic.net/\" target=\"_blank\">The Dodos</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.ilovedoeeye.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Doe Eye</a><br />DJ Omar<br />Aaron Axelson</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11px;\">Presented by&nbsp;</span><a style=\"font-size: 11px;\" href=\"http://www.popscene-sf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Popscene SF</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dodosmusic.net/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.calacademy.org/sites/default/files/styles/manual_crop_square_460px/public/assets/images/misc/1200x900_thedodos_photocreditchloeaftel.png?itok=2Zkv3ILs\" alt=\"The Dodos\" width=\"602\" height=\"602\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">à¹›</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3>June 11</h3>\r\n<p>CODAME is&nbsp;bringing our own style of ART+TECH including the interactive GIF visualizer known as&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/gifslap/\" target=\"_blank\">gifSlap</a>&nbsp;for hands-on play. You&rsquo;ll find our station on the patio outside of the Rainforest Dome next to the stage.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/gifslap-cover.jpg\" alt=\"gifslap-cover\" width=\"603\" height=\"457\" /></p>\r\n<p>Live Music by&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://hannielkhatib.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Hanni El Khatib</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.hotflashheatwave.bandcamp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Hot Flash Heat Wave</a><br /><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ProfessionalFans\" target=\"_blank\">Professional Fans DJs</a><br />Presented by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://noisepop.com/2015/\" target=\"_blank\">Noise Pop</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://hannielkhatib.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.calacademy.org/sites/default/files/styles/manual_crop_square_460px/public/assets/images/misc/1200x900_hannielkatib.png?itok=JYk7CmKO\" alt=\"Hanni El Katib\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">à¹›</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3>May 14</h3>\r\n<p>CODAME Featuring &ldquo;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/circuit-dancers/\">Circuit Dancers</a>&rdquo; by Victoria Mara Heilweil &amp; Phil Spitler,&nbsp;inspired by the dual cultures of dance and technology.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/portfolio/circuit-dancers/\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/MG_7515-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"_MG_7515\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Live Music by</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ninjatune.net/machinedrum/\" target=\"_blank\">Machinedrum Vapor City Live</a><br /><a href=\"http://bbravo.com/\" target=\"_blank\">B. Bravo</a><br /><a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/brogan-bentley\" target=\"_blank\">Brogan Bentley</a>&nbsp;(Piazza DJ)<br />Presented by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/djdials\" target=\"_blank\">DJ Dials</a></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.calacademy.org/sites/default/files/styles/manual_crop_square_460px/public/assets/images/misc/1200x900_machinedrum_photocredittonjethilesen.png?itok=b_wmyqtF\" alt=\"machinedrum\" width=\"602\" height=\"602\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>October 15</h3>\r\n<p>CODAME Featured Artist: <a href=\"/projects/leapybird\">#LeapyBird</a></p>\r\nYour bird wants to go on an adventure of epic proportions but needs you to make him fly! Place your hands over the sensor and flap your way through video game land, San Francisco, and CODAME memories on your way to the amazing end stage. 11 wholly frustrating and tiring scenes will have you dodge all manner of obstacles. Only the bravest and strongest can survive!\r\n<div id=\"fb-root\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #ffffff; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; background-color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\nLeapyBird art, game, and sound by&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7 !important;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ani/\">ANI</a>&nbsp;(Amy Lee).&nbsp;\r\n<p><a title=\"#LeapyBird\" href=\"/projects/leapybird\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leapybird1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"203\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Live Music by</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img src=\"http://www.calacademy.org/sites/default/files/styles/manual_crop_square_460px/public/assets/images/misc/1200x900_hundredwaters_photocreditj.verdugo.png?itok=v4J72OUa\" alt=\"Hundred Waters\" width=\"599\" height=\"599\" /></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">à¹›</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Science Side Shows</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Get hands-on with local science groups&nbsp;like Bay Area Science Festival, BioCurious, Counter Culture Labs and UC Santa Cruz&rsquo;s OpenLab.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>LIVE Happy Hour</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Head to the West Garden from&nbsp;6:00-7:45 pm and enjoy DJ sets, happy hour bites, cocktails, lawn games, and more! Plus, stop by the NightLife LIVE photobooth, provided by SnapYourself.</p>\r\n<p>Stage visuals provided by ALL OF IT NOW.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>Soundcloud Playlist</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Get a preview of who&rsquo;s&nbsp;hitting the LIVE stage this summer with the NightLife LIVE<a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/casnightlife/sets/nightlife-live-2015-playlist\" target=\"_blank\">Soundcloud playlist.&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'sustainable-magic,anna-landa,ani,jordan-gray,dat-phan,donald-hanson,phil-spitler,victoria-mara-heilweil', 'gifslap,circuit-dancers,leapybird,modbod', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(6, 'Art by Code (2014)', 'art-by-code-2014', '2015-01-30', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-by-code-final-reception-.gif', '<p>CODAME&nbsp;presents&nbsp;&ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo;&nbsp;in conjunction with&nbsp;Roll up Gallery.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo; is a triumph of human ingenuity and a tribute to artists who dare to imagine, invent, and test the limits creating art generated by code.</p>\r\n<p>Pricing list&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=6241\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Gallery Hours:&nbsp;January 30th, 6-9pm sharp.</p>\r\n<p>Where:&nbsp;Roll up Gallery at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://publicsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">The Public Works SF</a>, 161 Erie St, San Francisco, CA<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Public+Works,+Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;hl=en&amp;sll=37.768963,-122.419461&amp;sspn=0.010924,0.022724&amp;oq=public+wor161+Erie+St+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;t=h&amp;gl=us&amp;hq=Public+Works,&amp;hnear=Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+California+94103&amp;z=15&amp;iwloc=A\" target=\"_blank\">(map)</a></p>\r\n<p>Artists:&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=3853\">Reza Ali</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1050\">Angat Gaata</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=6260\">Tiare Ribeaux</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1096\">Donald Hanson</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=6079\">Robert Allison</a>,<a href=\"/post/portfolio/matthew-cella/\">Matthew Cella</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/brownshoesonly/\">Nick Ciontea</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/tim-cowley/\">Tim Cowley</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/joel-cretan/\">Joel Cretan</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=5474\">EMi</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1932\">Al Linke</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1197\">Josh Nimoy</a>and&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=2161\">DC Spensley</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Reception night:&nbsp;Enjoy music from&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/ideomux/\">IDMX</a>, play the&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/leapybird/\">LeapyBird</a>&nbsp;arcade game, go deep in the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://organic.com/\">Organic</a>&nbsp;VR Lounge, be captured by the&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=1931\">IOIO plotter</a>&nbsp;and customize<a href=\"/?p=5364\">PIXEL</a>&nbsp;ART LED Displays with your phone.</p>\r\n<p>RSVP (21+ only)&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://codame.eventbrite.com/</a></p>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"http://eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=15482255844&amp;ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></div>\r\n<p>Art curators:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/LoveModernArt\">Jaqueline Bacich</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/StarPause\">Jordan Gray</a>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/CODA_ME\">CODAME</a><br />If interested showing your work in the future events with CODAME, get in touch with us by filling this&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=5517\">Call for Artists</a>&nbsp;form.</p>\r\n<div><hr />\r\n<div id=\"attachment_6176\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/10402636_654377321305266_2839915681685341657_n.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME NEON\" width=\"528\" height=\"528\" />\r\n<p>CODAME NEON on Auction at #ArtByCode</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>All work will be on sale! Including the CODAME commissioned&nbsp;<a href=\"/?p=6116\">NEON</a>&nbsp;is on Auction for a good cause!</p>\r\n<p>Put your bid amount and contact&nbsp;<a href=\"/bid/\">here</a>! Good luck and thanks for your support!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo; gives us an insight into a changing cyber universe populated by artists who brave new frontiers with their computational skills, and go beyond the limits of commercial software to create their unique codes that center on &lsquo;interactivity&rsquo; and &lsquo;user&rsquo; experiences.</p>\r\n<p>With &ldquo;Art by Code&rdquo; we aim to ignite the imagination of a new emerging generation and keep challenging the conventional ways of thinking about art and making art. The computer as the medium raises a host of intriguing questions and forces us to rethink what is art.</p>\r\n<p>The bay area artists have been generating increasingly complex visual forms with tools that rely on open-source. They use programs such as Java [processes], C++, [OpenFrameworks, Cinder], GLSL, JavaScript and AS3. These forms previously could not been imagined.</p>\r\n<p>The selection here represents a sampling of an explosive field and draws on the latest in computer technology from such fields like fractals, algorithmic processes, software art, generative art, data visualization, 3-D software, and much more.<img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/7fbf0f1b108e7bbc440d0c96a44933253.jpg\" alt=\"Public Works San Francisco\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Gif Flier&nbsp;created with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4dsGzH\">bonniem</a>&nbsp;code!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/art-by-code-final-reception-half-resolution.gif\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/art-by-code-final-reception-half-resolution.gif\" alt=\"art-by-code-final-reception-half-resolution\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>âŒ˜CâŒ˜V love!</p>', 'reza-ali,joel-cretan,robert-allison,matthew-cella,donald-hanson,emi,tim-cowley,ytai-ben-tsvi,ideomux,dat-phan,jordan-gray', 'ioio-plotter,leapybird,modbod', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(7, 'CODAME @CODECONF in Nashville', 'codame-codeconf-in-nashville', '2015-06-25', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-codeconf-in-nashville.jpg', '<p><a href=\"http://github.com/\">Github</a>&nbsp;adopted&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/modbod3d/\">ModBod3D</a>&nbsp;for the after party at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codeconf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">CODECONF</a>&nbsp;in Nashville, TN, and it was a blast!</p>\r\n<p>Check out the scanned bodies on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codeconf.codame.com/\" target=\"_blank\">codeconf.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-4-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (4 of 44)\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-5-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (5 of 44)\" width=\"2448\" height=\"3264\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-8-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (8 of 44)\" width=\"1635\" height=\"2180\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-9-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (9 of 44)\" width=\"2448\" height=\"3264\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-13-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (13 of 44)\" width=\"2448\" height=\"3264\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-15-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (15 of 44)\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-22-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (22 of 44)\" width=\"2448\" height=\"3264\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-27-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (27 of 44)\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-28-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (28 of 44)\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-29-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (29 of 44)\" width=\"720\" height=\"1280\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-31-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (31 of 44)\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-32-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (32 of 44)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-33-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (33 of 44)\" width=\"774\" height=\"581\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-36-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (36 of 44)\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-39-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (39 of 44)\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-43-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (43 of 44)\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" /><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE-44-of-44.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME-CODECONF-GITHUB-NASHVILLE (44 of 44)\" width=\"3264\" height=\"2448\" /></p>', 'dat-phan,jordan-gray,donald-hanson,bruno-fonzi', 'modbod', 'github', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(52, 'CODAME ART+TECH Festival (2013)', 'codame-art-tech-festival-2013', '2013-11-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-art-tech-festival-2013.jpg', '<p>The CODAME 2013&nbsp;<strong>ART+TECH Festival</strong>&nbsp;was a curated experience into auditory, tactile, optical, taste and yes, olfactory installations called&nbsp;<strong>5ENSES</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>An&nbsp;exclusive,&nbsp;immersive&nbsp;&nbsp;guided&nbsp;journey&nbsp;that subverted your perception and re-awaken your senses&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/GeekdomSF\" target=\"_blank\">@GeekdomSF</a>&nbsp;startup co-working space from&nbsp;Rackspace San&nbsp;Francisco.</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"background-image: url(\'http://www.codame.com/new/admin/js/tinymce/skins/lightgray/img/object.gif\');\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/W0Xo1xVxpEQ?rel=0\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe><br />Thanks to&nbsp;<a href=\"http://845a.co/codamearttechfestivalinfo2013\" target=\"_blank\">845a.co</a>&nbsp;for the great video footage!</p>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME 2013 ART+TECH Festival&nbsp;5ENSES</strong></p>\r\n<p>Get ready for an&nbsp;exclusive,&nbsp;immersive&nbsp;guided&nbsp;journey&nbsp;that will subvert your perception and re-awaken your senses.</p>\r\n<p>A highly electrifying event to re-experience your five sense in a carefully curated immersive space. Your guides will lead you through each room where you will ignite each sense one by one, ultimately delivering you into the Gallery.</p>\r\n<p>The Gallery, the quintessential mashup of senses &mdash;art, music, tech, performances&mdash; that CODAME has come to be known for. Installations, dance, interactive art+tech will all await your freshly disrupted, re-experienced self.</p>\r\n<p>The ART+TECH Festival will also include:</p>\r\n<p><strong>#INDIE GAME Room&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Play a selection of&nbsp;CODAME&nbsp;GAMES&nbsp;and traditional arcade games, presented by&nbsp;<a title=\"Lanica Game Development Platform\" href=\"http://lanica.co/\" target=\"_blank\">Lanica</a>, the&nbsp;game developer experts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>#SIXTH SENSE Room</strong></p>\r\n<p>Join to find out more!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>#ART by CODE&nbsp;(Silent Auction)</strong></p>\r\nA silent auction for traditional wall hanging pieces by artists working with algorithms, logic and data! Work from&nbsp;Antonio Cortez,&nbsp;Kristin Henry,&nbsp;Josh Nimoy,&nbsp;Matthew Cella&nbsp;Curated by&nbsp;Hanna Regev</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>#DRINK Bar</strong></div>\r\n<p>Donation based drinks to deliver a fun and&nbsp;ultimate&nbsp;taste experience.</p>\r\n<p><strong>#HALLOWEEN</strong></p>\r\n<p>The CODAME Team will be hunting for the best ART+TECH dress for a special surprise!</p>\r\n<p><strong>#SUPPORT CODAME + ARTISTS</strong></p>\r\n<p>We are&nbsp;looking&nbsp;for&nbsp;sponsors,&nbsp;supporters,&nbsp;volunteers. if you can help, any pixel or bit counts! Join our&nbsp;Adopt an Artist&nbsp;initiative&nbsp;Contact us! Or just join us and donate by getting your&nbsp;ticket!</p>\r\n<p><strong>#PROGRAM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Curated by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.stefanocorazza.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Stefano Corazza</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://kirirong.tumblr.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Kiri Rong</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://starpause.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Jordan Gray</a>&nbsp;with the collaboration of some of the San Francisco Bay Area&rsquo;s top tech-artists:</p>\r\n<p>Bad Unkl Sista,&nbsp;Paolo Salvagione, Dolores Joya, Bryan and Vita Hewitt,&nbsp;Ken Murphy,&nbsp;Paul Clipson,&nbsp;Patrick Dintino,&nbsp;Jeff Cheung,&nbsp;Jonathan Wallraven,&nbsp;Leo Madrid, Bill Hsu,&nbsp;DC Spensley,&nbsp;Kinetech,&nbsp;Colin Roache,&nbsp;Carl Pisaturo,&nbsp;Issac Cohen, Kal Spelletich,&nbsp;Robert Edgar,&nbsp;Charlie Levin,&nbsp;Felipe Brahm, and&nbsp;more&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'jordan-gray,bruno-fonzi,stefano-corazza,bad-unkl-sista,jonathan-wallraven,eric-dyer,leo-madrid,kinetech-arts,14-bindlestick-frank,dolores-joya,jefferson-shulgin,colin-roache,alexandernaut,unicorn,patrick-dintino,jeff-cheung,carl-pisaturo,cabbibo,robert-edgar,charlie-levin,tim-thompson,al-linke,ytai-ben-tsvi,cory-barr,carson-day,moldover,rich-ddt,cdcm,enc,extent-of-the-jam,nonagon,dust-red-skies,sasha-leitman,fernando-lopez-lezcano,carr-wilkerson,bruno-ruviaro,luke-dahl,colin-sullivan,angat-gaada,nop-jiarathanakul,vco-vault,cstng-shdws,ken-murphy,timefly,david-o-reilly,andrew-benson,laturbo-avedon,cyriak,paul-clipson,beeple,renetta-sitoy,max-capacity,andrea-starr,ani,dc-spensley,gabriel-dunne,paolo-salvagione,bill-hsu,jordan-gray projects represented phracktography,gifslap,phracktography,gifslap sponsored by   partnered with   event date', 'phracktography,gifslap', 'rackspace', '', '', '', '1', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(9, 'ART+TECH VIRTUAL REALITY', 'art-tech-virtual-reality', '2014-11-21', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-virtual-reality-.gif', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Virtual Reality (VR) has finally arrived. What was science fiction is now fact. So whats the next step?</p>\r\n<p>Join hackers and artists at Mozilla San Francisco, as CODAME presents an evening of virtual reality experimentation and education. Be inspired, meet other VR pioneers and see how easy it is to start building your own VR worlds on the open web.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>PROGRAM</strong></p>\r\n<p>6:00 &ndash; INTRO</p>\r\n<p>7:00 &ndash; LIGHTNING&nbsp;TALKS</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Eddie Lee:&nbsp;A Psychedelic VR Trip Through the Large Hadron Collider</li>\r\n<li>Josh Carpenter:&nbsp;Virtual Reality &amp; The Future of the Web</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>8:00 &ndash; PLAY TIME!</p>\r\n<p>CODAME Featured&nbsp;Artists +&nbsp;Projects:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>DataGeyser, an immersive VR experience of data on Social Network, a collaboration&nbsp;by HackReactor students +&nbsp;Kinetech Art<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">s</a></li>\r\n<li>Psychedelic VR Trip Through the Large Hadron<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=5838\">&nbsp;</a>Collider, &nbsp;a collaboration effort with&nbsp;Eddie Lee&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://baiyon.com/english/\">Baiyon</a></li>\r\n<li>TIMEFLY, Gravity fashion brought to you by Kim Laughton and Kevin Heckart</li>\r\n<li>Metropulus::Drone,&nbsp;an interactive installation bringing the dystopian future right into your very hands</li>\r\n<li>ModBod3D,&nbsp;A&nbsp;whole body scanner out of a gaming computer, wheel bearing, plywood</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Mozilla VR&nbsp;Research Team Open Lab Experiments:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sechelt, a WebGL fly-through of coastal British Columbia built with Ricardo Cabello (aka&nbsp;Mr.doob) of Three.js</li>\r\n<li>The Polar Sea, a documentary by&nbsp;DEEP&nbsp;that takes users to the Arctic in 360&deg; VR video, powered by&nbsp;eleVR&rsquo;s WebGL&nbsp;VR video player.</li>\r\n<li>Information Diving, a visualization of data as art inspired by the work of artist&nbsp;<a href=\"http://complexitygraphics.com/\">Tatiana Plakhova</a>&nbsp;and built with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/auradeluxe\">Tony Parisi</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/ericrius1\">Eric Levin</a>&nbsp;using Tony&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/tparisi/vizi\">Vizi</a>&nbsp;framework</li>\r\n<li>Episode 4 of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://elevr.com/\">Talk Chat Show Thing</a>&mdash;the only talk show filmed in VR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>If&nbsp;interested showcasing an inspiring and playful art+tech demo,&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:events@codame.com\">contact us</a>.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div><hr />\r\n<p>&ldquo;The opportunity for VR on the Web is particularly exciting. The Web is a vibrant, connected universe where many different types of experiences can be created and shared. People can be productive, have fun and learn all from within their browser. &ldquo;&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://blog.bitops.com/\">Vladimir VukiÄ‡eviÄ‡</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://blog.bitops.com/\"><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/bringing-virtual-reality-to-the-web-vr-webgl-and-css-together-at-last-1-638.jpg\" alt=\"bringing-virtual-reality-to-the-web-vr-webgl-and-css-together-at-last-1-638\" width=\"638\" height=\"359\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Looking to experiment with VR on the Web?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Download those Firefox Nightly builds. Play, build and show your learnings, results at the CODAME ART+TECH event</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mac:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://vrhelloworld.com/builds/\">http://vrhelloworld.com/builds/osx</a></li>\r\n<li>PC:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://vrhelloworld.com/builds/win\">http://vrhelloworld.com/builds/win</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>More useful links from Mozilla:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Developer Browser Edition news:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://mzl.la/1tTRpgO\">http://mzl.la/1tTRpgO</a></li>\r\n<li>For developers:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/\">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US</a></li>\r\n<li>Newsletter:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/newsletter/\">https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/newsletter</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Use this promo code:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sv.gwcevents.com/en-us/Event/Login/10?code=GMICSVC100G\">GMICSVC100G</a>&nbsp;Valid only until Nov. 21.&nbsp;for a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sv.gwcevents.com/en-us/Event/Login/10?code=GMICSVC100G\">FREE&nbsp;</a><a href=\"http://sv.gwcevents.com/en-us/Event/Login/10?code=GMICSVC100G\">Gold Pass</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sv.gwcevents.com/en-us/Event/Login/10?code=GMICSVC100G\">GMIC</a>&nbsp;a 3 days largest mobile internet conference in Silicon Valley happening December 1 &ndash; 3 at Hilton Union Square.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Event Poster Graphic Credits:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://singularsociety.tumblr.com/post/98350544718\">#singularsociety</a></p>\r\n</div>', 'eddie-lee,josh-carpenter,kinetech-arts,dat-phan,jordan-gray,timefly,mr-doob', 'metropulus-drone,modbod,collider,datageyser,deep-dream-vision-quest', 'mozilla', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(185, 'Entwined Live Demonstration', 'entwined-live-demonstration', '2021-03-19', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/entwined-live-demonstration.jpg', '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Friday March 19&nbsp;</strong>from 7-8pm (PT)</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">Get excited for a live pattern show of the work you all created for <em>Entwined</em> at our workshop!&nbsp; We will be demonstrating what you created on Friday March 19th, including some awesome patterns from class alumnae Lindsay, Jason, Mattaniah, Sydney, and Quinn -- congrats!&nbsp; These new patterns have been quite a hit with the <em>Entwined</em> crew, so we\'re excited to show them off for the whole city to see!</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">Didn\'t get a chance to take the workshop or submit a pattern?&nbsp; This is still the perfect chance to drop by and enjoy the installation during its final month of exhibition!&nbsp; Come chat with like-minded tech artists and LED enthusiasts.&nbsp; We\'ll even have a controller so you can play around with the patterns live!<br /><br />Meet Colin and the CODAME Team&nbsp;at the&nbsp;San Francisco&nbsp;Golden&nbsp;Gate Park,&nbsp;Peacock Meadow, underneath the main tree. Dress warmly: The meadow can get surprisingly chilly at night!</div>', 'colin-hunt,charles-gadeken', 'entwined-meadow', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', 'create-led-patterns-for-entwined'),
(8, 'ART+TECH \'Virtual Reality\' @Mozilla', 'art-tech-virtual-reality-mozilla', '2014-11-21', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-virtual-reality-mozilla-video-streaming-.jpg', '<p>On Nov 21s 2014, CODAME brought ART+TECH and Mozilla brought Virtual Reality to the Web, making &nbsp;it a&nbsp;remarkable and inspiring experience.</p>\r\n<p>LIGHTNING&nbsp;TALKS</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=5815\">Eddie Lee</a>:&nbsp;A Psychedelic VR Trip Through the Large Hadron&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=5838\">Collider</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/josh-carpenter/\">Josh Carpenter</a>:&nbsp;Virtual Reality &amp; The Future of the Web</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://air.mozilla.org/event-codame-art-tech-virtual-reality/video/\" width=\"770\" height=\"426\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe><a href=\"/artists\">CODAME Featured</a>&nbsp;Artists +&nbsp;Projects:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=5547\">DataGeyser</a>, an immersive VR experience of data on Social Network, a collaboration&nbsp;by HackReactor students +&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech Arts</a></li>\r\n<li>Psychedelic VR Trip Through the Large Hadron<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=5838\">&nbsp;Collider</a>, &nbsp;a collaboration effort with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=5815\">Eddie Lee</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://baiyon.com/english/\">Baiyon</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/timefly-codame-featured-artist-s-gravity/\">TIMEFLY</a>, Gravity fashion brought to you by Kim Laughton and Kevin Heckart</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/metropulusdrone/\">Metropulus::Drone</a>,&nbsp;an interactive installation bringing the dystopian future right into your very hands</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/modbod/\">ModBod3D</a>,&nbsp;A&nbsp;whole body scanner out of a gaming computer, wheel bearing, plywood</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://mozvr.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Mozilla VR</a>&nbsp;Research Team Open Lab Experiments:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sechelt, a WebGL fly-through of coastal British Columbia built with Ricardo Cabello (aka&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/mrdoob\">Mr.doob</a>) of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://threejs.org/\">Three.js</a></li>\r\n<li>The Polar Sea, a documentary by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.deep-360.com/\">DEEP</a>&nbsp;that takes users to the Arctic in 360&deg; VR video, powered by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://elevr.com/\">eleVR</a>&rsquo;s WebGL&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/hawksley/eleVR-Web-Player\">VR video player</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Information Diving, a visualization of data as art inspired by the work of artist&nbsp;<a href=\"http://complexitygraphics.com/\">Tatiana Plakhova</a>&nbsp;and built with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/auradeluxe\">Tony Parisi</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/ericrius1\">Eric Levin</a>&nbsp;using Tony&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/tparisi/vizi\">Vizi</a>&nbsp;framework</li>\r\n<li>Episode 4 of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://elevr.com/\">Talk Chat Show Thing</a>&mdash;the only talk show filmed in VR</li>\r\n</ul>', 'josh-carpenter,timefly,kinetech-arts,dat-phan,jordan-gray,eddie-lee,mr-doob', 'collider,metropulus-drone,datageyser,modbod', '', '', '', '', '1', 'event', '', ''),
(10, 'ART+TECH FESTIVAL [2014]', 'art-tech-festival-2014', '2014-10-31', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/-in-secure-art-tech.gif', '<hr />\r\n<p>Join CODAME in hacking the world of security and privacy! Take a break from alarming reports of breaches and leaks for a night of playing with privacy, puzzles and cyberpunks at . All mediums are up for exploration including music, fashion, performance and interactive installations &amp; what better night to bring your avatar to life than Halloween!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Date and Location:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Friday October 31st, 7pm &ndash; midnight<br /> Geekdom &ndash; 620&nbsp;Folsom St., San Francisco</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>Dress code:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s Halloween night! Your opportunity to dress art+tech tonight! Costume or not, do come and enjoy!</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; text-align: left;\">\r\n<div style=\"position: relative; padding-bottom: 76%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;\"><iframe id=\"iframe\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0;\" src=\"http://flickrit.com/slideshowholder.php?height=75&amp;size=big&amp;setId=72157648808971676&amp;trans=1&amp;theme=1&amp;thumbnails=0&amp;transition=0&amp;layoutType=responsive&amp;sort=0\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></div>\r\n<p><strong>Artists</strong> (featured CODAME ART+TECH creators)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/al-linke/\">Al Linke</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/angat/\">Angat Gada</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/1071/\">Cory Barr</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/eder-cetina/\">Eder Cetina</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech</a></li>\r\n<li>Dat Phan</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-vco-vault-vco-vault-is-a/\">VCO Vault</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/vj-musashii/\">VJ Musashii</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Installations</strong> (Playful explorations of security and privacy)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/outerbody/\">Outerbody Labs</a> <em>See yourself seeing yourself</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/surveillance-phone/\">Surveillance Phone</a> <em>Cave Plexum is an &ldquo;alternate reality&rdquo; in which the object Surveillance Phone is the rabbit hole*.</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/datafountain/\">Datafountain</a> <em>An immersive 3D experience of data from your friends and your own on Facebook.</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/modbod/\">ModBod 3d Scans</a> <em>TSA meets Michelangelo to preserve your form forever</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/1071/\">Cyberattack</a> <em>Real attacks visualized in Real time.</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-from/\">ScreenVortex</a> <em>An infinite zoom through intimate screen captures.</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/visit-invisible/\">Visit Invisible</a> <em>Even the floor is listening to your steps, exploding into a fractal visuals.</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/faraday-cave/\">Faraday Cave</a> <em>kiss your connectedness goodbye in a tinfoil tent chill zone, big enough for you and a friend (or 3)</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/metropulusdrone/\">Metropulus::Drone</a> <em><em>Fly a spy drone through the streets of Metropulous, searching for core intel that may unlock the secret&hellip;</em></em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/portfolio/i-know-where-your-cat-lives/\">I Know Where Your Cat Lives</a>&nbsp;D<em>ata experiment that visualizes a sample of 1 million public pics of cats on a world map.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Music and performance</strong> (times are approximate &amp; may change)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>07pm doors + djay</li>\r\n<li>08pm <a href=\"/post/portfolio/visit-invisible/\">Visit Invisible</a> (dance)</li>\r\n<li>09pm <a title=\"Jefferson Shulgin\" href=\"/post/portfolio/jefferson-shulgin-codame-featured-musician/\">Jefferson Shulgin</a> (av set)</li>\r\n<li>10pm <a href=\"/post/portfolio/theuriah/\">TheUriah</a> (Angat Gada viz)</li>\r\n<li>11pm <a href=\"/post/portfolio/httpcodame-compost33148965267starpause-codame-featured-musician-bob-your/\">staRpauSe </a>(av set)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>While the evening is already stacked we are still accepting submissions and would love to hear about your project! Get on the <a href=\"/?p=5517\">Call for Artists</a> form.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Credits: GIF flier original by <a href=\"http://pretty-boy-luxx.tumblr.com/post/97736601980/tribal-gathering-numbers\">pretty-boy-luxx</a>, modified with permission</p>\r\n</div>', 'al-linke,angat-gaada,cory-barr,eder-cetina,kinetech-arts,dat-phan,vco-vault,vj-musashii,jefferson-shulgin,theuriah,jordan-gray', 'outerbody,surveillance-phone,datageyser,cyberattack,screenvortex,visit-invisible,faraday-cave,metropulus-drone,modbod,i-know-where-your-cat-lives', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(11, '8bit ROMANTIX', '8bit-romantix', '2011-04-21', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/8bit-romantix.png', '<div class=\"figure\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><a class=\"tumblr_blog\" href=\"http://gamesatcodame.tumblr.com/post/21511720221/the-nostalgic-journey-for-8-bit-videogames-art\" target=\"_blank\">gamesatcodame</a>:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div id=\"id_4f92fac7391f48a22988438\" class=\"text_exposed_root text_exposed\">The nostalgic journey for 8-bit videogames, art &amp; music.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Come join us as we celebrate retro-game culture with artworks inspired by the early days of video games.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME Team member: STARPAUSE&nbsp;<a href=\"http://starpause.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://starpause.com/</a>&nbsp;will be performing live and filling your ears with chiptune musical goodne<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ss. In addition to the art, we&rsquo;ll have a table-top game system loaded up with all the classics.</span></p>\r\n<p>If You&rsquo;ve never been to Sweet Breams before, be prepared to fall in love with their delicious Japanese Taiyaki cakes!<br /> <a href=\"http://sweetbreams.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://sweetbreams.com/</a></p>\r\n<p>Featuring art by:<br /> âœœ Alice Koswara<br /> âœœ Andy Helms<br /> âœœ Ben Seto<br /> âœœ Catmandru<br /> âœœ Elisa Sassi<br /> âœœ Eric Phoneticontrol Broers<br /> âœœ Jungshih Wang<br /> âœœ Mayo Tobita<br /> âœœ Omar Rodriguez<br /> âœœ Vicente Montelongo<br /> and other surprise guest artists!</p>\r\n<p>Curated by:<br /> Mike &ldquo;BAM&rdquo; Tyau &amp; Vicente Montelongo</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"text_exposed_root text_exposed\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>Click here to <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/305885922810309/\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>', 'mike-bam-tyau,elisa-sassi-perry-chan,jordan-gray', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(12, 'Adobe CS6 Launch Party!', 'adobe-cs6-launch-party-', '2012-05-29', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/adobe-cs6-launch-party-.jpg', '\r\n						<div class=\"figure\">\r\n</div>\r\n<p><a class=\"tumblr_blog\" href=\"http://gamesatcodame.tumblr.com/post/22372064089/adobe-creative-suite-6-launch-party-may-29\" target=\"_blank\">gamesatcodame</a>:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>May 29 – Adobe –  601 Townsend – </strong><strong>San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hosted by <a href=\"http://codame.com/\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME</a> and the Creative Suite San Francisco Group.</p>\r\n<p>There are a limited number of tickets available for this event. RSVP here  <a href=\"http://cs6.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://cs6.eventbrite.com</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Keynote Speaker(s)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mark Christiansen | Adobe After Effects Evangelist</li>\r\n<li>Scott Fegette | Adobe Dreamweaver & Web Product Manager</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>6:00 – 6:30 – Welcome & Keynote Presentation Introducing Adobe Creative Cloud</li>\r\n<li>6:30 – 7:30 – Town Hall | Mark Christiansen | After Effects CS6</li>\r\n<li>6:30 – 7:30 – Chaplin Room | David Hogue | Fireworks CS6</li>\r\n<li>7:40 – 8:30 – Town Hall | Kelly McCathran | InDesign CS6</li>\r\n<li>7:40 – 8:30 – Chaplin Room | Scott Fagette | Dreamweaver CS6</li>\r\n<li>8:30 – 8:45 – Break</li>\r\n<li>8:45 – 9:15- Town Hall | Kelly McCathran | Flash CS6</li>\r\n<li>8:45 – 9:15 – Chaplin Room | Sally Cox | Adobe Touch Apps</li>\r\n<li>9:20 – 9:40 – Town Hall | Kelly McCathran | Adobe Muse (HTML) & Adobe Edge (HTML5 & CSS3)</li>\r\n<li>9:45 – 10:00 – Wrap up & raffle prizes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Raffle Prizes</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Creative Cloud & CS6 Subscription</li>\r\n<li>Adobe Learn by Video(s) from <a href=\"http://www.video2brain.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\">video2brain.com</a></li>\r\n<li>1 Hour one-on-one eClass from <a href=\"http://onlineinstruct.com/\" target=\"_blank\">onlineinstruct.com</a></li>\r\n<li>2-Hour Open Enrollment eClass from <a href=\"http://onlineinstruct.com/\" target=\"_blank\">onlineinstruct.com</a></li>\r\n<li>Adobe Backpacks</li>\r\n<li>Adobe Branded Chachkis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n											', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/gamesatcodame-adobe-creative-suite-6-launch/', '', '1', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(13, 'CODAME Festival 2012 Artist Talks', 'codame-festival-2012-artist-talks', '2012-12-02', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-festival-2012-artist-talks.jpg', '<p><span class=\"userContent\"><strong>Did you miss the CODAME ART+TECH Festival this year?</strong> Were you in the waiting list and could not make it to the event? We have some good news for you!</span></p>\r\n<p>Join us to meet and learn about the CODAME Artists and Team presenting on stage their work and the CODAME 2012 Awards!</p>\r\n<p>Get your free ticket now! Do not miss out!<br /> <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://codame.eventbrite.com/</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>10 Artists 10 Minutes each!</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"vevent\"><span class=\"description\"><strong><a href=\"/post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Nimoy</a></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p>Josh is a prolific artist and composer that has created a great deal of work ranging from stunning computer generated art, to playful interactive pieces that allow the user to create fun visuals with a generated audio soundtrack. ï¿½His work contains a fusion of math and art ï¿½ which helped create the visual experience of the blockbuster film, Tron:Legacy as well as a number of gallery shows. ï¿½<a href=\"http://jtnimoy.net/?q=178\" target=\"_blank\">Read more</a>ï¿½about Nimoyï¿½s work on the film.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/post/33137081697/ani-codame-featured-musician-ani-is-a-monster\" target=\"_blank\">Amy Lee</a> (</strong><strong>aka ANI)</strong><strong><br /> </strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"single-photo\">\r\n<div class=\"icons\"><a href=\"/post/33137081697/ani-codame-featured-musician-ani-is-a-monster\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/cd4ba1ab733518fd720334a2197862604.jpg\" alt=\"ANI - CODAME Featured Musician ANI is a monster at improvisation, pumping out a constantly evolving progression of beats and melodies. ice on the cake, she does it all on an iPad running Nanostudio. Every performance is unique so be sure not to miss her set!Get name-your-price tickets now&amp; the SOMA, SF venue address will be reviled day-of via your registration =)\" /></a></div>\r\n<div class=\"icons\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"icons\">ANI is a monster at improvisation, pumping out a constantly evolving progression of beats and melodies. ice on the cake, she does it all on an iPad running Nanostudio. Every performance is unique so be sure not to miss her set!</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>Jason Wilson ï¿½ <a href=\"http://outerbody.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Outerbody</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://outerbody.org/huh/\" target=\"_blank\"><img id=\"picObj\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/1962bd194fc79148209af21cb7216dba4.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"600\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Outerbody use video goggles and cameras to move your sense of sight out of your body and into a third person point of view thatï¿½s looking back at yourself. This is an awe inspiring experiencewe had at CODAME ART+TECH Festival, join us to find out more.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/xavivives\" target=\"_blank\">Xavi Vives Riba</a></strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"single-photo\">\r\n<div class=\"photo\"><a href=\"/post/33367608081/xavi-vives-riba-codame-featured-artist-xavi-is-a\" target=\"_blank\"> <img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/c31573d6339762ab676942d78df110094.jpg\" alt=\"Xavi Vives Riba - CODAME Featured ArtistXavi is a developer with an artistic eye. An inventor at heart, Xavi turned to code to see his experiments through. Xavi is working on something very cool for CODAME, mixing animations and music.See Xavis work on Oct. 27 when CODAME takes over an entire venue in SOMA. Get your ticket today!\" /></a></div>\r\n<div class=\"photo\">Xavi is a developer with an artistic eye. An inventor at heart, Xavi turned to code to see his experiments through. He will present his CODAME project: <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ENLUeD4mK5c&amp;feature=colike\" target=\"_blank\">Ludovico</a> a music interactive projection based on GIF.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong><strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/VJKSKA\" target=\"_blank\">VJ KSKA</a></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/VJKSKA\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/78f8d70574d1ac5324ea30baa4e7a4f14.jpg\" alt=\"image\" /></a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Keisuke aka</strong><strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/VJKSKA\" target=\"_blank\"> VJ KSKA</a></strong><span class=\"fcg\">, Director of Software at <a href=\"http://www.miselu.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Miselu</a>, </span>visualizes the look and feel of what is happening on the dance floor in his abstract and stylish visuals. With his effective use of analogue controller and real time handling of motion graphics, VJ KSKA synchs the visuals with the dynamics of the music, building on the excitement generated by audiences.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/post/33372855985/wesley-grubbs-codame-featured-artist-codame-is\" target=\"_blank\">Wesley Grubbs</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/33372855985/wesley-grubbs-codame-featured-artist-codame-is\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/c8897da7f1858d79db5042868bab90104.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"580\" height=\"246\" /></strong></a></p>\r\n<div class=\"zoom\">\r\n<div class=\"photo\">Wesley takes overwhelming data sets and turns them into beautiful, easy to understand visuals. His work varies from designs, to user interfaces, to infographics, but thereï¿½s generally one common thread of political activism underlying it all. Knowing how well he can work with data, weï¿½re excited what Wesley decides to visualize for Codame.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><a href=\"/post/33237400933/jonathan-wallraven-codame-featured-artist-were\" target=\"_blank\">Jonathan Wallraven</a></strong><br /> <a href=\"/post/33237400933/jonathan-wallraven-codame-featured-artist-were\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/6dc9ee0dc7985f006dfab7b2407271a04.jpg\" alt=\"Jonathan Wallraven  CODAME Featured ArtistWere excited to announce another new CODAME artist, Jonathan Wallraven. Wallraven is a Bay Area artist who primarily works in black and white, blurring the lines between installation and comic book art. Wallravens work has a quality to it that both draws the eye in and overwhelms it at the same time. We cant wait to see his installation.The CODAME 2012 party goes down OCT27, grab a ticket to receive our SOMA venues exact address =)\" /></a>Jonathan Wallraven. Wallraven is a Bay Area artist who primarily works in black and white, blurring the lines between installation and comic book art. Wallravenï¿½s work has a quality to it that both draws the eye in and overwhelms it at the same time.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/post/33365285959/superdeux-codame-featured-artist-superdeux-is\" target=\"_blank\">Superdeux</a> &amp; <a href=\"http://www.deux.me/\" target=\"_blank\">Ray McClure</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/f51ff4a2893753e16ca0308d2dbf71734.gif\" alt=\"image\" /></p>\r\n<p>Sebastian Deux (aka <a href=\"http://www.deux.me/about/\" target=\"_blank\">Superdeux</a>) is a Frenchmen living in SF. Superdeux has become known for his cute and playful character art, many characters having a French flair to them. Superdeux art is known to take many forms, from plastic figurines to animated shorts and everything between. In collaboration with Ray McClure from <a href=\"https://secretfeature.com\" target=\"_blank\">Secrete Feature</a>ï¿½ built a interactive tec+art using xbox Kinect named <a href=\"http://blog.secretfeature.com/?p=9\" target=\"_blank\">I wish I could talk</a>. Join CODAME to learn more!</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/post/49786209834/reza\" target=\"_blank\">Reza Ali </a></strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/49786209834/reza\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/f1d66eaa4023bdd45aad650443d97c874.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"600\" height=\"1200\" /></a>Reza wil present his latest project shown at CODAME titled: Undefined Behavior, a Real-time Interactive C++ audio-reactive visual exploration of glitchy generative art. It show cases a beautiful error which typically occurs when a computer program accessing an array beyond its bounds.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><a href=\"/post/33383194086/ryan-alexander-codame-featured-artist-ryan\" target=\"_blank\">Ryan Alexander</a></strong><br /> <img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/bb0a102909ae6ec776104a521ee348f85.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1442\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Ryan is one of those artists who really enjoys programming. Through a mix of data visualization and programs like processing, Ryan finds beauty hidden inside of code. Heï¿½s created Chrome Experiments and given us a different perspective on the world.</p>', 'josh-nimoy,ani,xavi-vives-riba,superdeux,reza-ali,ryan-alexander', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(14, 'CODAME: The Future Imagined', 'codame-the-future-imagined', '2013-01-10', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-the-future-imagined.png', '<p>Fundraising Event</p>\r\n<p>PERFORMANCE ART INSTITUTE, Thursday, Jan. 10 at 7:00&nbsp;pm, 75 Boardman Place,&nbsp;San Francisco, CA</p>\r\n<p>RSVP at <a title=\"RSVP\" href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">codame.eventbite.com</a></p>\r\n<p>Hosted by <strong>CODAME</strong> Team:<strong> Olia Pospelova </strong>aka<strong> Strela, </strong>Music with <strong>Jordan Gray</strong>&nbsp;(<a href=\"/artists/starpause\" target=\"_blank\">Starpause</a>)</p>\r\n<p>The Performance Art Institute (PAI)&nbsp; &amp; CODAME cordially invites you&nbsp;to <strong>&ldquo;The Body as the Design&rdquo;</strong>, a talk by &nbsp;<a title=\"Scott Summit\" href=\"/artists/scott-summit\" target=\"_blank\">Scott Summit </a><strong title=\"Michal Gavish\">&nbsp;</strong>inventor, designer and participating artist&nbsp;of &ldquo;The Future Imagined: What&rsquo;s next? The talk will be followed by&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;The Future is Design&rdquo;</strong> a short presentation by&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/tim-mcneil\" target=\"_blank\">Tim McNeil</a>, professor of design and director of the Design Museum at the University of California, Davis, and a moderated discussion led by <a title=\"Jonathon Keats\" href=\"/artists/jonathon-keats\" target=\"_blank\">Jonathon Keats</a><strong>,&nbsp;</strong>experimental philosopher, journalist, art critic, and artist.</p>\r\n<p>When we think of a prosthetic limb, the image that typically comes to mind involves titanium pipes, bolts, mechanical flanges, and a rubber, lifelike foot. The product, though a vital and intimate part of the wearer&rsquo;s life, appears mechanical and utilitarian, devoid of individuality or personality. The forms appear disjointed and brutal in the context of the fluid forms of the human body. Why do we assume that this must be the definition for something intended to return normalcy to an individual&rsquo;s life?</p>\r\n<p>This project set out to explore how design, technology, and a fundamentally new outlook may rethink the prosthetic limb. A combination of 3D scanning, parametric computer modeling, and 3D printing allows design and individuality to be infused into the product on a per-person basis. It invites design and style into an area previously defined only by mechanical necessity. It invites attention and engagement, attempting to celebrate the human it complements.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About the Panel:</strong></p>\r\n<p>This panel discussion event is part of a series <a href=\"http://www.zero1.org/\" target=\"_blank\">2012 ZERO1 Biennial</a> and &ldquo;The Future Imagined&rdquo; series of conversations that delve into an in-depth discussion about the intersection of art and technology, and the future of design.</p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"yui_3_7_2_17_1352104388588_519\"><a class=\"hoverZoomLink\" href=\"http://thefutureimagined.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/summit.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"float: left;\" title=\"summit\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/5551d77093594a6a01363132c79eb7b31.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a></strong><a title=\"Scott Summit\" href=\"/artists/scott-summit\" target=\"_blank\">Scott Summit</a><strong title=\"Michal Gavish\"><a title=\"Scott Summit\" href=\"/artists/scott-summit\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;</a></strong>&nbsp;is an industrial designer who focuses on the intersection of human needs, new technology, and design.&nbsp; He founded Bespoke Innovations to explore how this combination may address challenging and nuanced needs, and how it may scale to help people throughout the world. Summit is the director of Technology, Bespoke Products at 3D Systems Corporation</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"hoverZoomLink\" href=\"http://thefutureimagined.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Pic_TMcNeil.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"float: left;\" title=\"Pic_TMcNeil\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/33b5833963c368e3a08e2a9c8914ece61.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a><a href=\"/artists/tim-mcneil\" target=\"_blank\">Tim McNeil</a> is so up on museums&nbsp;and design it isn&rsquo;t funny.&nbsp;Never without a vision, he is also a professor of design and director of the Design Museum at the University of California, Davis.&nbsp;An authority on environmentally sustainable design&nbsp;solutions for exhibition environments,&nbsp;he chairs the California Association of Museums&nbsp;Green Museum Initiative, founded&nbsp;the Green Museums Accord, and in 2008&nbsp;was inducted into the National Environmental Hall of Fame for his work on the NRDC&rsquo;s Environmental Action Center.&nbsp;His award winning design research has been featured in multiple publications and he a frequent speaker at museum and design conferences.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><a class=\"hoverZoomLink\" href=\"http://thefutureimagined.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Keats.dessinger.med_.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"float: left;\" title=\"Keats.dessinger.med\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/86c35b8baadb83a889e22d2c6460360d1.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a></strong></strong></strong><a title=\"Jonathon Keats\" href=\"/artists/jonathon-keats\" target=\"_blank\">Jonathon Keats</a>&nbsp;is an experimental philosopher, artist and writer. Exhibited at venues including the Berkeley Art Museum and the Wellcome Collection, his art projects have been documented by PBS, NPR, and the BBC World Service and covered in periodicals ranging from the New Yorker to the Economist to Nature. He is also the art critic for San Francisco Magazine, a visual arts columnist for Forbes.com, and most recently the author of &ldquo;Forged: Why Fakes Are the Great Art of Our Age&rdquo;, published this year by Oxford University Press. He is represented by Modernism Gallery in San Francisco.</p>', 'jordan-gray,scott-summit,tim-mcneil,jonathon-keats', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(15, 'Exploring the dimensions of 3D Printing', 'exploring-the-dimensions-of-3d-printing', '2013-05-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/exploring-the-dimensions-of-3d-printing.jpg', '<p><strong>CODAME exploring the dimensions of 3D Printing -</strong>&nbsp;Fundraising Event</p>\r\n<p>What used to be exclusive to sophisticated research labs is now accessible to everyone. Get inspired by artists and 3D prototyping enthusiasts sharing their vision and experience. See creative energy in action, fueling good design and rapid prototyping techniques.</p>\r\n<p>Start by gaining insight into current state and future potential of the 3D printing Industry. Find out how complex human needs can be connected with design and technology. Continue by exploring delicate results of cooperation between science, artistic practice, and 3D printing virtuosity. &nbsp;Explore how 3D printing cloud engine services allow anyone to benefit from available technologies. Learn about clever software that enables more than one person to be a part of the product creation process, and how product plans are being shared safely and freely across the web. Investigate the concept of 4D rapid prototyping and how it can change the world we live in.</p>\r\n<p>Get creative, and bring your own work to the event! See a 3D printer in action and get your questions about how it works and how to build your own answered. Interested to get involved or have a cool project to share? <a href=\"mailto:us@codame.com\" target=\"_blank\">Contact us</a>.</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/X5AZzOw7FwA?wmode=transparent&amp;autohide=1&amp;egm=0&amp;hd=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;showsearch=0\" width=\"891\" height=\"501\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Featured Speakers &amp; Artists</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>The art and business in 3D printing</em></strong><br /> <a href=\"/post/48598679416/scott-summit-codame-featured-design-industry\" target=\"_blank\">Scott Summit</a>, Director of Technology, Bespoke Products at 3D Systems Corporation.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Art, Biology and 3D printing</em></strong><br /> <a href=\"/post/48598675079/natacha-merrit-codame-featured-artist-an\" target=\"_blank\">Natacha Merrit</a>, Photographer, artist and biologist.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>3D Printing is the Future of Manufacturing</em></strong><br /> <strong>Marine Cor Baillais</strong>, Sculpteo CMO, Industry Insider.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Social 3D Printing in Minecraft</strong></em><br /> <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/michael-amundsen-codame-featured-artist/\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Amundsen</a>, Graduating BFA student.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Art and 3D Printing</strong></em><br /> <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kristen-turner-codame-featured-speaker-kristen/\" target=\"_blank\">Kristen Turner</a>, Ponoko CMO, Industry Insider</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>4D printing</em></strong><br /> <a href=\"/post/48598643358/stefano-corazza-codame-featured-artist-stefano\" target=\"_blank\">Stefano Corazza</a>, Mixamo CEO &amp; Co-founder and CODAME team member.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Live DJ Set</strong> <a href=\"/artists/starpause\">staRpauSe</a></p>\r\n<p>RSVP on&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://codame.eventbrite.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>More information about 3D printing:</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Achieved using an <em>additive process</em>, where successive layers of material are laid down in different shapes.3D printing is considered distinct from traditional machining techniques, which mostly rely on the removal of material by methods such as cutting or drilling (<em>subtractive </em>processes).</p>\r\n<p>A materials printer usually performs 3D printing processes using digital technology. Since the start of the twenty-first century there has been a large growth in the sales of these machines, and their price has dropped substantially.</p>\r\n<p>The technology is used in jewelry, footwear, industrial design, architecture, engineering and construction (AEC), automotive, aerospace, dental and medical industries, education, geographic information systems, civil engineering, and many other fields.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Interested in 3D Printing?</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Make sure to check out this event from our Swissnex friends:</strong></p>\r\n<p>T<a href=\"http://swissnexsanfrancisco.org/Ourwork/events/ethics3dprinting\" target=\"_blank\">he Ethics and Sustainability of 3D Printing</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://swissnexsanfrancisco.org/Ourwork/events/ethics3dprinting\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/61cbbbfe3f5514f50aee013102240f141.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', 'natacha-merrit,michael-amundsen,kristen-turner,stefano-corazza,jordan-gray', 'music-performance', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(16, 'CODAME PLAY @ SubZERO', 'codame-play-subzero', '2013-06-07', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-play-subzero.jpg', '<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/3b1b43223ff6e1bcff977cd65841bcb71.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/6a1a0c9ced749119f4708a780fca0ea91.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/6f337b4b783fa4f9ff1296397ff4d0cb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/1e1c5c760fcb0df414cfaf2ef7f1760d1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>CODAME <strong>PLAY</strong> @ SubZERO ï¿½ Fundraising Event</p>\r\n<p>Friday, June 7, 2013 from 6:00 PM to 11:59 PM (PDT) ï¿½ CA <span class=\"pipe\">|</span> SoFA district in Downtown San Jose <a id=\"page_url\" href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://codame.eventbrite.com</a></p>\r\n<p>A <strong>playfull</strong> event with a lot of toys for some ART+TECH FUN!</p>\r\n<p><strong>#SUPPORTERS</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>We are accepting new <a title=\"Sponsorships\" href=\"/sponsors\" target=\"_blank\">sponsors</a> supporting the CODAME ART+TECH community, <a title=\"Sponsorship\" href=\"mailto:sponsor@codame.com\" target=\"_blank\">contact us</a>. Any pixel or bit counts!</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>#ARTISTS</strong></p>\r\n<p>More details soon to be announced. Stay tuned!ï¿½<strong>Be ready to PLAY!</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Josh Nimoy</strong></a>: multiple touchscreens with OSC signals with musical heartbeats.</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/33367608081/xavi-vives-riba-codame-featured-artist-xavi-is-a\" target=\"_blank\">Xavi Vives Riba</a></strong>: Play with <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ENLUeD4mK5c&amp;feature=colike\" target=\"_blank\">Ludovico</a> a music interactive projection based on GIFs.</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/49787645371/jamesmorgan\" target=\"_blank\">James Morgan</a>:</strong> video arcade.</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/33365285959/superdeux-codame-featured-artist-superdeux-is\" target=\"_blank\">Superdeux</a></strong>: Project (TBA)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/49788901258/vinit\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Vinit Patil</strong></a>: appology, more information coming up. stay tuned!</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/33375814182/proteus-codame-featured-game-proteus-is-what\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Ed Key</strong> + <strong>David Kanaga</strong></a>, Proteus pushing the boundaries of games.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/33148965267/starpause-codame-featured-musician-bob-your\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>StarPause</strong></a> + <a href=\"http://camaltamura.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Cam Altamura</strong></a> #naughtBothered generative art featuring gifs submitted by realtime viewers</li>\r\n<li><strong>Dan Lynch, Lucas Calderin &amp; Spencer Poff</strong>ï¿½: Laser Harp, YES!ï¿½ Freakinï¿½ laser beams!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>#OUTERBODY</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>We are happy to offer you a chance to test your sensory adaptation skills in the OuterBody Grand Prix at SubZero 2013.<br /> This is no ordinary race. You will steer yourself around a racetrack track while only seeing through a camera suspended high up in the air. Will you be able to stay in bounds? Will you be able to avoid the other racers? Will you even be able to distinguish yourself from them? Can you get your name on the leader board? Maybe youï¿½ll be the champion of the festival!<br /> For examples of previous OuterBody installations, and to get a sense of what youï¿½re in for, visit <a href=\"http://outerbody.org/events\" target=\"_blank\">outerbody.org/events</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong><a title=\"CODAME PLAY @ SubZERO\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482672822%20\" target=\"_blank\">Buy your tickets</a> in advance for guaranteed entry and priority race times. Limited tickets available.</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>About SubZERO Festival</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Focused on emerging and present subcultures thriving in our region, SubZERO is a diy, artistically bent, hi/lo-techno mashup where street meets geek. Come downtown on June 7th to San Joseï¿½s SoFA District from 6pm ï¿½til midnight for an inspired evening of arts &amp; culture. In addition to the South FIRST FRIDAYS monthly art walk youï¿½ll find outdoor stages of entertainment plus artists, performers &amp; musicians celebrating the indie creative spirit!<strong><strong><strong><em><br /> </em></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><em>The mosaic above includes photos from:<br /> <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/villagesavant/sets/72157619363651296/\" target=\"_blank\">Brian Eder</a>, <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/fenchurch/tags/subzero/\" target=\"_blank\">Fenchurch</a>, <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/cherrilakey/sets/72157619381314871/\" target=\"_blank\">Cherri Lakey</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/happyfunpaul/sets/72157620198918185/\" target=\"_blank\">Paul Robinson</a></em><em>.</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'josh-nimoy,xavi-vives-riba,james-morgan,superdeux,jordan-gray,cam-altamura', 'proteus,naughtbothered', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(17, 'Art by Code [2013]', 'art-by-code-2013', '2013-06-26', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-art-by-code-roll-up-gallery.png', '<div class=\"figure\">Roll up Gallery and CODAME ART+TECH will present 11 artists in conjunction with CODAME</div>\r\n<p><strong><em>Art by Code</em> is a triumph of human ingenuity and a tribute to artists who dare to imagine, invent, and test the limits.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>From: </strong>June 26 to July 14 open from 6:00 to 9:00 PM</p>\r\n<p><strong>Where: </strong><a href=\"http://publicsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">The Public Works SF</a> 161 Erie St, San Francisco, CA&nbsp;<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Public+Works,+Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;hl=en&amp;sll=37.768963,-122.419461&amp;sspn=0.010924,0.022724&amp;oq=public+wor161+Erie+St+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;t=h&amp;gl=us&amp;hq=Public+Works,&amp;hnear=Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+California+94103&amp;z=15&amp;iwloc=A\" target=\"_blank\">(map)</a></p>\r\n<div><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/7fbf0f1b108e7bbc440d0c96a44933253.jpg\" alt=\"Public Works San Francisco\" /></div>\r\n<div><strong>RSPV:</strong> <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://codame.eventbrite.com/</a>\r\n<p><em><strong>Art by Code</strong></em>&nbsp;is about computer code, art &amp; language, digital art, and conceptual art and artists who are pioneering powerful ways in bridging art and technology.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Artists use code as their primary artistic tool. Their creations represent dynamic systems incorporating algorithmic rules, simulation of physical properties, and complex systems theory that are generated by a variety of unique and complex written codes.</p>\r\n<p>We are proud to announce the following artist lineup:<br /> <a href=\"/post/49786209834/reza%60\" target=\"_blank\">Reza Ali</a>,<a href=\"http://www.iquilezles.org/blog/%20\" target=\"_blank\">Inigo Quilez</a>, <a href=\"/post/53171832401/matthew-cella-codame-featured-artist-matt\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew Cella</a>, <a href=\"/post/33383194086/ryan-alexander-codame-featured-artist-ryan\" target=\"_blank\">Ryan Alexander</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/53173010263/jon-kuzmich-codame-featured-artist-as-an\" target=\"_blank\">Jon Kuzmich</a>, <a href=\"/post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Nimoy</a>, <a href=\"/post/53163702656/antonio-cortez-codame-featured-artist-antonio\" target=\"_blank\">Antonio Cortez</a>, <a href=\"/post/51663304990/tiffany-trenda-codame-featured-artist-the\" target=\"_blank\">Tiffany Trenda</a>, <a href=\"/post/33372855985/wesley-grubbs-codame-featured-artist-codame-is\" target=\"_blank\">Wes Grubbs</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/krees\" target=\"_blank\">Kim Rees</a>, <a href=\"/post/53259772717/nolan-love-codame-featured-artist-nolan-love-is\" target=\"_blank\">Nolan Love</a>, <a href=\"/post/53175634592/kristin-henry-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Kristin Henry</span></span></a></p>\r\n<p>The exhibition curated by:<strong>Hanna Regev</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Bruno Fonzi&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>Betty Bigas.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>About CODAME ART+TECH</strong><br /> Non-profit events bringing together artists, coders, game developers, creators, performers and musicians to experience the intersection of Art and Technology.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Curatorial Statement</strong> by Hanna Regev</p>\r\n<p><em>\"Art by Code\"</em> gives us an insight into a changing cyber universe populated by artists who brave new frontiers with their computational skills, and go beyond the limits of commercial software to create their unique codes that center on interactivity and user experiences.</p>\r\n<p>With <em>\"Art by Code\"</em> we aim to ignite the imagination of a new emerging generation and keep challenging the conventional ways of thinking about art and making art. The computer as the medium raises a host of intriguing questions and forces us to rethink what is art.</p>\r\n<p>The bay area artists have been generating increasingly complex visual forms with tools that rely on open-source. They use programs such as Java [processes], C++, [OpenFrameworks, Cinder], GLSL, JavaScript and AS3. These forms previously could not been imagined.</p>\r\n<p>The selection here represents a sampling of an explosive field and draws on the latest in computer technology from such fields like fractals, algorithmic processes, software art, generative art, data visualization, 3-D software, and much more.</p>\r\n<p><em>\"Art by Code\"</em> is a triumph of human ingenuity and a tribute to artists who dare to imagine, invent, and test the limits.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'reza-ali,inigo-quilez,matthew-cella,ryan-alexander,jon-kuzmich,josh-nimoy,antonio-cortez,tiffany-trenda,wes-grubbs,kim-rees,nolan-love,kristin-henry', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(18, 'CODAME FASHION+TECH', 'codame-fashion-tech', '2013-05-25', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-fashion-tech.jpg', '<div class=\"figure\"><strong>When: </strong>Wednesday, June 26, 2013 from 7:00 PM to 2:00 AM (Next Day)</div>\r\n<p><strong>Where: </strong><a href=\"http://publicsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">The Public Works SF</a> 161 Erie St, San Francisco, CA&nbsp;<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Public+Works,+Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;hl=en&amp;sll=37.768963,-122.419461&amp;sspn=0.010924,0.022724&amp;oq=public+wor161+Erie+St+San+Francisco,+CA+94103&amp;t=h&amp;gl=us&amp;hq=Public+Works,&amp;hnear=Erie+St,+San+Francisco,+California+94103&amp;z=15&amp;iwloc=A\" target=\"_blank\">(map)</a></p>\r\n<div><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/cff83e9fb5669f9cd38ec11ab83380221.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"216\" /><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/03adf5bbb0bd103b9b7fd9c1a33dfcc71.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /><img class=\"\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/7fbf0f1b108e7bbc440d0c96a44933252.jpg\" alt=\"Public Works San Francisco\" width=\"803\" height=\"176\" /></div>\r\n<p><em><strong>RSVP</strong>: on <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Eventbrite</a></em><br /> Wearable technology is thought to be the next big revolution in tech. Many expect this new wave of wearable devices and apparel to reshape not only the consumer electronics industry, but also fashion and manufacturing. CODAME has created a platform to showcase how the tech and fashion industries are collaborating to innovate within this arena.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>CODAME FASHION+TECH&nbsp;</strong>presents a night where fashion tech designers, entrepreneurial fashionistas, musicians, and visual artists come together in one space. Together, they will explore the future of tech-inspired appare where form and function meet visionary genius. These pioneers in the fashion technology space will provide insights into their creative design processes, cover challenges on prototyping and manufacturing, and conduct live demonstrations of their groundbreaking pieces of technology enabled apparel. Infusions of music and visual artistry will complement this interactive environment of dialogue and presentations.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>#SCHEDULE</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cozy talks from artists and industry insiders to share their knowledge and inspire us.</li>\r\n<li>Live Performances</li>\r\n<li>Music/Visual Showcase</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Full Program Coming soon. Stay tuned!</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>#ARTISTS</strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Speakers</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/50382930978/linda-franco\" target=\"_blank\">Linda Franco</a>, Co-Founder &amp; CMO @ MACHINA Wearable Technology, sharing her current project <a href=\"http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/machina/midi-controller-jacket-v01\" target=\"_blank\">Midi Controller Jacket v1.0</a>.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/anouk-wipprecht/\" target=\"_blank\">Anouk Wipprecht</a>,Interactive Fashiontech Designer &amp; Innovator, unveiling prototype of her new fashiontech design.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/tiffany-trenda/\" target=\"_blank\">Tiffany Trenda</a>, American digital performance artist, will submerge you into the world of creative expression with her new piece Proximity Cinema.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/51663707460/anders-nelson-codame-featured-fashiontech\" target=\"_blank\">Anders Nelson</a>, Becca McCharen &amp; Dustin Maberry will take us into the world of wearable LED display development premiere shown at CODAME.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Special Installations<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/53167942222/yumika-tanaka-codame-featured-artist-yumika\" target=\"_blank\">Yumika Tanaka</a>, <em>We are What we Wear.</em></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/53163702656/antonio-cortez-codame-featured-artist-antonio\" target=\"_blank\">Antonio Cortez</a>, Objects of Desire Made Still.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Music &amp; Visuals<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/36970171828/keisuke\" target=\"_blank\">Keisuke Shingu</a> aka VJ KSKA</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/52025428748/cstng-shdws-codame-featured-video-artists\" target=\"_blank\">CSTNG-SHDWS</a> #videoart #gaffta #idn #createdigitalmotion #motionserved #motionographer</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/33148965267/starpause-codame-featured-musician-bob-your\" target=\"_blank\">STARPAUSE</a> #8bitpeoples #hexawe #naughtBothered #mp3death #creativecommons #8bitsf</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/51904006509/sebastien-deux-codame-featured-dj-lady-hear\" target=\"_blank\">Sebastian Deux</a> #cdj #secretfeature #superduex #partyanimal</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/51908585817/the-spectrum-electric-codame-featured\" target=\"_blank\">The Spectrum Electric</a> #audiovisual #javascript #netaudio #creativecommons #gridwalklabs</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/post/52684134478/humanimal-codame-featured-musician-a-favorite\" target=\"_blank\">HUMA&Omega;IMâˆ†L</a> pre- post-apocalyptic maximalist tech-step</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Fashion Models (from </strong><strong><strong><a href=\"http://raeagency.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rae Agency</a>) </strong></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Candace, Syrene, Stephanie Cardoza, Julie Bedecarre</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Dancers (DTX</strong><strong><strong>)</strong></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Maria Perez, Jayde Ci, Darian Johnson, Jennifer Perez, Ijay Espinoza, Alyssa Hutzly, Kelsi Shae</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Make Up + Hair </strong>provided by:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://teresa-reynolds.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Theresa Reynolds</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Art by Code&nbsp; Gallery Opening<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>6-9pm</strong></strong> at the Roll up Gallery (as part of Public Works)</p>\r\n<p>With an Amazing Artist lineup: <a href=\"/post/53163702656/antonio-cortez-codame-featured-artist-antonio\" target=\"_blank\">Antonio Cortez</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.iquilezles.org/blog/%20\" target=\"_blank\">Inigo Quilez</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/53175634592/kristin-henry-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Kristin Henry</span></span></a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/53173010263/jon-kuzmich-codame-featured-artist-as-an\" target=\"_blank\">Jon Kuzmich</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Nimoy</a>,<a href=\"/post/53171832401/matthew-cella-codame-featured-artist-matt\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew Cella</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/53259772717/nolan-love-codame-featured-artist-nolan-love-is\" target=\"_blank\">Nolan Love</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/49786209834/reza%60\" target=\"_blank\">Reza Ali</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/33383194086/ryan-alexander-codame-featured-artist-ryan\" target=\"_blank\">Ryan Alexander</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/51663304990/tiffany-trenda-codame-featured-artist-the\" target=\"_blank\">Tiffany Trenda</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/33372855985/wesley-grubbs-codame-featured-artist-codame-is\" target=\"_blank\">Wes Grubbs</a>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/krees\" target=\"_blank\">Kim Rees</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/post/52877021929/roll-up-gallery-and-codame-art-tech-will-present\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><img class=\"\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/d6e25eb7a72912813aa5688a8fd749962.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"807\" height=\"435\" /></strong></a></p>\r\n<p>A triumph of human ingenuity and a tribute to artists who dare to imagine, invent, and test the limits.<strong><br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p>Art by Code is about computer code, art &amp; language, digital art, and conceptual art and artists who are pioneering powerful ways in bridging art and technology.</p>\r\n<p>Artists use code as their primary artistic tool. Their creations represent dynamic systems incorporating algorithmic rules, simulation of physical properties, and complex systems theory that are generated by a variety of unique and complex written codes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>#MASTERCLASS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/post/51080448192/anouk\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"photo\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/df6bbf5060a22e1f0924dfc373fbc2581.jpg\" alt=\"2-hour Masterclass with Fashiontech Specialist Anouk Wipprecht [NL]  This is a fundraising masterclass. Any profit will go towards not-for-profit CODAME ART+TECH initiative.  When: June 29th, 2013 from 11am to 2pmWhere: TBD (SoMa, San Francisco)  Only 50 spots. Tickets.  Anouk will take you into the world of wearable tech and some of the amazing projects she has worked on with colleagues and celebrities. Through slides and show &amp; tell, giving an inside look in how to combine fashion and technology; the complications that hit her road, and showing you her tricks and tweaks regarding to the systems she applies, to make her designs behave and twirl around the body.  MASTERCLASS TOPICS: FASHIONTECH DESIGN &amp; WEARABLE ELECTRONICS | INTERACTION DESIGN | USER EXPERIENCE DESIGN | MICROCONTROLLERS + BASIC ENGINEERING | SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT | ROBOTICS &amp; MECHANICS | SENSORS and SENSORY SYSTEMS  About Anouk Wipprecht:    What does fashion lack? &ldquo;Microcontrollers&rdquo; according to Dutch based fashiontech designer and innovator Anouk Wipprecht. As she is working in the emerging field of fashionable technology; a rare combination of fashion design combined with engineering, science and interaction/user experience design, she created an impressive body of tech-enhanced designs bringing together fashion and technology in an unusual way. She creates technological couture; with systems around the body that tend towards artificial intelligence; projected as &lsquo;host&rsquo; systems on the human body, her designs move, breath, and react to the environment around them.  Top photo courtesy of Robert Lunak.ï¿½Smoke Dress - A collaboration between fashiontech designer Anouk Wipprecht [NL] and technologist Aduen Darriba [NL].      You can also meet Anouk at ourï¿½CODAME FASHION+MUSIC Eventï¿½onï¿½June 26th, 2013 from 7pm-2am at Public Works, San Francisco.  ï¿½\" width=\"798\" height=\"570\" /></a></strong></p>\r\n<p>You can also learn more about wearable technology with our Fundraising <a href=\"/post/51080448192/anouk\" target=\"_blank\">FASHIONTECH Masterclass with Anouk Wipprecht</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;We have a limit for 50 people max. <strong>Not to be missed!</strong> Get your ticket on <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/6803801353\" target=\"_blank\">Eventbrite</a>!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Time &amp; Date:</strong> 11am-2pm, Saturday, June 29th, 2013<strong> Venue</strong>: (Chartio) in San Francisco, CA. Drinks/Food included!</p>\r\n<p>More information <a href=\"/post/51080448192/anouk\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>#SUPPORTERS</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://generalassemb.ly/?utm_source=Codame&amp;utm_medium=Website&amp;utm_term=2013+Q2+San+Francisco+Summer+Partnerships&amp;utm_content=Fashion+Music+Event+Page&amp;utm_campaign=Codame+Art+Tech\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/bb7529c062411de9bcd87df8ba2539123.png\" alt=\"\" /></strong></a></p>\r\n<p>Interested to sponsor, volunteer, participate or have a cool project to show?&nbsp;<a title=\"Support us\" href=\"/support\" target=\"_blank\">Contact us</a>. You can also support&nbsp;<strong>CODAME&nbsp;</strong>by making a donation with your&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482462192\" target=\"_blank\">ticke</a>&nbsp;purchase.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignleft\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/b809278aab65976e106791474d0be2dd1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"333\" height=\"857\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'linda-franco,anouk-wipprecht,tiffany-trenda,anders-nelson,yumi-tanaka,antonio-cortez,keisuke-shingu-aka-vj-kska,cstng-shdws,sebastien-deux,spectrum-electric,humanimal,jordan-gray', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(19, '24hrs of CODAME âœ˜ DEF CON', '24hrs-of-codame-def-con', '2013-08-03', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/24hrs-of-codame-10008-def-con.gif', '<p>We are super hyped &amp; excited to join DEF CON this year! CODAME is hosting an interactive lounge,&nbsp;open&nbsp;all night and day,&nbsp;for you to art/hack/play/enjoy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We have a&nbsp;special&nbsp;offer for you!&nbsp;Join us for&nbsp;24hrs, the ticket&nbsp;includes:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.defcon.org/html/defcon-21/dc-21-index.html\" target=\"_blank\">DEF CON</a> conference for 24hrs, starting&nbsp;at 6pm Saturday (Aug 3) to Sunday (Aug 4)</li>\r\n<li><strong>CODAME</strong> ART+TECH Party Celebration</li>\r\n<li>Spiffy DEF CON badge.&nbsp;The badges alone are worth the price! Check last year badges featured on <a href=\"http://www.wired.com/threatlevel/2012/07/defcon20-badge/\" target=\"_blank\">Wired Magazine</a>!</li>\r\n<li>And much more! Check full DEF CON&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.defcon.org/html/defcon-21/dc-21-schedule.html\" target=\"_blank\">schedule</a>&nbsp;or <a href=\"https://www.defcon.org/html/defcon-21/dc-21-entertainment.html\" target=\"_blank\">party events</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Badges can be collected at the CODAME lounge (Located at the Miranda conference room starting at 6pm, Aug 3rd)</p>\r\n<h1><iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/142946769?title=0&amp;byline=0\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"></iframe></h1>\r\n<h1>CODAME</h1>\r\n<p><a target=\"_blank\">CODAME</a> is bringing ART+TECH to the DEF CON 24/7 chillout lounge at the Rio Hotel in Las Vegas (August 1st &ndash; 4th). If that wasn&rsquo;t enough, on Saturday, August 3rd we&rsquo;ll borrow the SomaFM&rsquo;s soundsystem for a celebration featuring the following performances!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Installations in Miranda/chillout, visible 24/7:</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56068681722/cory-barr-codame-featured-artist-anticlockwise\" target=\"_blank\">Anticlockwise</a> </strong><em>Realtime data visualisation of cyber attacks.</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56159936601/naughtbothered-is-a-generative-new-media-piece\" target=\"_blank\">Cam Altamura &amp; Jordan Gray</a> </strong> <em>C4D renders semi-randomly combined with analog video captures &amp; user generated content tagged #naughtBothered on twitter.</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56069858161/dan-moore-codame-featured-artist-dan-writes\" target=\"_blank\">Dan Moore</a>&nbsp;</strong><em>Slitscan photobooth will capture your twisted existance for internet and offline consumption.</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/codame-featured-artist-laturbo-avedon-laturbo/\" target=\"_blank\">LaTurbo Avedon</a> </strong><em>3d Idol exploring The Artist Is Not Present</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56072636434/codame-featured-artist-from\" target=\"_blank\">&Eacute;&plusmn;&Eacute;&uml;&AElig;&trade;&Eacute;&acirc;&dagger;&raquo;&Egrave;&iquest;&acirc;&dagger;&ordm;&AElig;&yen;&Eacute;&sect;&AElig;&laquo; &aring;&hellip;Ž</a> </strong><em>Screen Vortex xetorV neercS</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56263343870/outerbody-labs-codame-featured-artist-outerbody\" target=\"_blank\">Outerbody Labs</a> </strong><em>Physical games for disembodied eyesight. See yourself seeing yourself. Operating at 8pm every day!</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56127513027/timefly-codame-featured-artist-s-gravity\" target=\"_blank\">TIMEFLY</a> </strong><em>Digitally printed garments featuring images from renowned net artists.</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56128285255/tyler-freeman-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\">Tyler Freeman</a> </strong><em>Hosting an audio-reactive, interactive video space.</em></li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56129773987/zebbler-studios-codame-featured\" target=\"_blank\">Zebbler Studios</a> </strong><em>Large scale. Video mapped. Suspended structures.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>August 3rd Celebration AV Lineup</strong> (<a href=\"http://8tracks.com/starpause/codame-def-con-21/\" target=\"_blank\">listen to the teaser</a>):</p>\r\n<p>8pm kickoff, done by 2am, in order of appearance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56266414488/jefferson-shulgin-codame-featured-musician\" target=\"_blank\">Jefferson Shulgin</a></strong> presenting <strong>Wiretap</strong> AV set</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56265724078/albert-elmore-codame-featured-musician-a-butt\" target=\"_blank\">Albert Elmore</a></strong> w/ [45isdistance] projecting</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56279683643/timeheater-codame-featured-musician-if-you\" target=\"_blank\">TIMEHEATER</a></strong> w/ <a href=\"/post/56281719387/starpause-codame-featured-musician-co-founder\" target=\"_blank\">starPause</a> projecting</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56280842456/zen-albatross-codame-featured-musician-since\" target=\"_blank\">Zen Albatross</a></strong> w/ <a href=\"/post/56128285255/tyler-freeman-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\">TIMEFLY</a> projecting</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56278740531/rhinostrich-codame-featured-musician-shits\" target=\"_blank\">rhinostrich</a></strong> w/ <a href=\"/post/56128285255/tyler-freeman-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\">odbol</a> projecting</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/33310952896/benito-codame-featured-musician-you-may\" target=\"_blank\">Benito</a></strong> w/ <a href=\"/post/56669089324/jumeiravisualsolutions-com-angat-is-an-artist\" target=\"_blank\">angat</a> projecting</li>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/56281719387/starpause-codame-featured-musician-pedal-bike\" target=\"_blank\">starPause</a></strong> w/ <a href=\"/post/56128285255/tyler-freeman-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\">TIMEFLY</a> projecting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Art by Code Gallery:</strong>&nbsp;A silent auction with works by:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"/post/53163702656/antonio-cortez-codame-featured-artist-antonio\" target=\"_blank\">Antonio Cortez</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/53175634592/kristin-henry-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Kristin Henry</span></span></a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Nimoy</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/53171832401/matthew-cella-codame-featured-artist-matt\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew Cella</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>TICKETS</h1>\r\n<p><a href=\"/support\" target=\"_blank\">Support</a> CODAME at DEFCON by getting a ticket, or having your company <a href=\"/sponsors\" target=\"_blank\">sponsor us</a>!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/56234900?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/56234900\" target=\"_blank\">The DEFCON Documentary Preview Reel</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/user411865\" target=\"_blank\">Jason Scott</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>Made possible with support from:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://organic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Organic, Inc</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://futurelighting.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Future Lighting</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.crypton.co.jp/miku_eng\" target=\"_blank\">Crypton Future</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>', 'anticlockwise-arts,jordan-gray,jefferson-shulgin,laturbo-avedon,timefly,odbol,vicente-montelongo,zebbler-studios,amy-warehouse,timeheater,zen-albatross,benito,dan-moore,angat-gaada,rhinostrich', 'naughtbothered,outerbody,watercolor-walls,phracktography', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(20, 'Masterclass with Fashiontech Specialist Anouk Wipprecht', 'masterclass-with-fashiontech-specialist-anouk-wipprecht', '2013-06-29', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/masterclass-with-fashiontech-specialist-anouk-wipprecht.jpg', '<hr />\r\n<p>This is a fundraising masterclass. Any profit will go towards not-for-profit CODAME ART+TECH initiative.</p>\r\n<p>Only 50 spots. <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/6803801353\" target=\"_blank\">Tickets</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>When</strong>: June 29th, 2013 from 11am to 2pm<br /> <strong>Where</strong>: Chartio, 445 Bryant St.&nbsp;<span class=\"adr\"><span class=\"locality\">San Francisco</span>, <span class=\"region\">CA</span> 94107</span></p>\r\n<p>Anouk will take you into the world of wearable tech and some of the amazing projects she has worked on with colleagues and celebrities. Through slides and show &amp; tell, giving an inside look in how to combine fashion and technology; the complications that hit her road, and showing you her tricks and tweaks regarding to the systems she applies, to make her designs behave and twirl around the body.</p>\r\n<p>MASTERCLASS TOPICS: FASHIONTECH DESIGN &amp; WEARABLE ELECTRONICS | INTERACTION DESIGN | USER EXPERIENCE DESIGN | MICROCONTROLLERS + BASIC ENGINEERING | SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT | ROBOTICS &amp; MECHANICS | SENSORS and SENSORY SYSTEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>About <a href=\"/post/50323275480/anouk-wipprecht-codame-featured-artist-what\" target=\"_blank\">Anouk Wipprecht</a>:</strong></p>\r\n<div><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/2e69d01dab96fa52e8d3a010c9a74cd11.png\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What does fashion lack? Microcontrollers, according to Dutch based fashiontech designer and innovator Anouk Wipprecht. As she is working in the emerging field of fashionable technology; a rare combination of fashion design combined with engineering, science and interaction/user experience design, she created an impressive body of tech-enhanced designs bringing together fashion and technology in an unusual way. She creates technological couture; with systems around the body that tend towards artificial intelligence; projected as host systems on the human body, her designs move, breath, and react to the environment around them.</p>\r\n<p>Top photo courtesy of Robert Lunak.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G-0lTP90hVc\" target=\"_blank\">Smoke Dress</a>&nbsp; A collaboration between fashiontech designer Anouk Wipprecht [NL] and technologist Aduen Darriba [NL].</p>\r\n<p>You can also meet Anouk at our&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/47176875119/fashion\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME FASHION+MUSIC Event</a>&nbsp;on June 26th, 2013 from 7pm-2am at Public Works, San Francisco.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/G-0lTP90hVc\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong>/// SUPPORTERS</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/81c8ce768aac53fde1fb5d14681fa8131.png\" alt=\"\" /><strong>Special kudos to our supporter <a href=\"http://chartio.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Chartio</a> providing an awesome friendly space, snack food and drinks!</strong></p>\r\n<p>Interested to sponsor, volunteer, participate or have a cool project to show?&nbsp;<a href=\"/support\" target=\"_blank\">Contact us</a>. You can also support&nbsp;<strong>CODAME&nbsp;</strong>by making a donation with your&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482462192\" target=\"_blank\">ticket</a>&nbsp;purchase.</p>\r\n</div>', 'anouk-wipprecht', '', 'chartio', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(21, 'Art by Code Reception 2013', 'art-by-code-reception-2013', '2013-06-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-by-code-reception-2013.jpg', '<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Join&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">CODAME ART+TECH</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">&nbsp;in honoring the&nbsp;</span><a style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"http://artbycode.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">Art by Code&nbsp;</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">artists in the groundbreaking exhibition that celebrates the spirit of creativity, innovation, and human ingenuity in the best tradition of the Silicon Valley.</span></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The mostly bay area computer artists have been busily generating increasingly complex visual forms with tools that rely on open-source and use programs such as Java [processes], C++, [OpenFrameworks, Cinder], GLSL, JavaScript and AS3. These forms previously could not been imagined. The selection here represents a very small sampling of an explosive field and draws on the latest in computer technology from such fields like fractals, algorithmic processes, software art, digital illustration, 3-D software, and much more.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We hope to see many of you come in support of <strong>CODAME</strong> and the artists they promote so we can continue on this evolutionary path. <a href=\"http://artbycode.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">Art by Code</a> is here to stay!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Artists: <a href=\"/post/53163702656/antonio-cortez-codame-featured-artist-antonio\" target=\"_blank\">Antonio Cortez</a>, <a href=\"http://www.iquilezles.org/blog/%20\" target=\"_blank\">Inigo Quilez</a>, <a href=\"/post/53175634592/kristin-henry-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Kristin Henry</span></span></a>, <a href=\"/post/53173010263/jon-kuzmich-codame-featured-artist-as-an\" target=\"_blank\">Jon Kuzmich</a>, <a href=\"/post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Nimoy</a>, <a href=\"/post/53171832401/matthew-cella-codame-featured-artist-matt\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew Cella</a>, <a href=\"/post/53259772717/nolan-love-codame-featured-artist-nolan-love-is\" target=\"_blank\">Nolan Love</a>, <a href=\"/post/49786209834/reza%60\" target=\"_blank\">Reza Ali</a>, <a href=\"/post/33383194086/ryan-alexander-codame-featured-artist-ryan\" target=\"_blank\">Ryan Alexander</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/51663304990/tiffany-trenda-codame-featured-artist-the\" target=\"_blank\">Tiffany Trenda</a>, <a href=\"/post/33372855985/wesley-grubbs-codame-featured-artist-codame-is\" target=\"_blank\">Wes Grubbs</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/krees\" target=\"_blank\">Kim Rees</a>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Reception in the Gallery followed by short presentations by artists who reveal secrets behind their creations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Sunday July 14, 1 to 3pm at The Roll Up Gallery at Public Works, 162 Erie Street, San Francisco</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\">RSVP on <a href=\"http://artbycode.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">artbycode.eventbrite.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://artbycode.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/c24f9751a4176d808502077022407571.png\" alt=\"Roll up Gallery and CODAME ART+TECH will present 11 artists in conjunction with our FASHION+MUSIC - Fundraising Event  Art by Code is a triumph of human ingenuity and a tribute to artists who dare to imagine, invent, and test the limits.&nbsp;  When: Wednesday, June 26, 2013 from 6:00 to 9:00 PM  Where: The Public Works SF 161 Erie St, San Francisco, CA&nbsp; (map)    RSPV: http://codame.eventbrite.com/  Art by Code is about computer code, art &amp; language, digital art, and conceptual art and artists who are pioneering powerful ways in bridging art and technology.  Artists use code as their primary artistic tool. Their creations represent dynamic systems incorporating algorithmic rules, simulation of physical properties, and complex systems theory that are generated by a variety of unique and complex written codes.  We are proud to announce the following artist lineup:Reza Ali,Inigo Quilez, Matthew Cella, Ryan Alexander,&nbsp; Jon Kuzmich, Josh Nimoy, Antonio Cortez, Tiffany Trenda, Wes Grubbs, Kim Rees, Nolan Love, Kristin Henry  The exhibition curated by:  Hanna Regev (http://thefutureimagined.com/) Bruno Fonzi, CODAME ART+TECH (http://codame.com/) Betty Bigas, Roll Up Gallery (http://publicsf.com/gallery)About CODAME ART+TECH Non-profit events bringing together artists, coders, game developers, creators, performers and musicians to experience the intersection of Art and Technology.Curatorial Statement by Hanna Regev  Art by Code gives us an insight into a changing cyber universe populated by artists who brave new frontiers with their computational skills, and go beyond the limits of commercial software to create their unique codes that center on interactivity and user experiences.  With Art by Code we aim to ignite the imagination of a new emerging generation and keep challenging the conventional ways of thinking about art and making art. The computer as the medium raises a host of intriguing questions and forces us to rethink what is art.  The bay area artists have been generating increasingly complex visual forms with tools that rely on open-source. They use programs such as Java [processes], C++, [OpenFrameworks, Cinder], GLSL, JavaScript and AS3. These forms previously could not been imagined.  The selection here represents a sampling of an explosive field and draws on the latest in computer technology from such fields like fractals, algorithmic processes, software art, generative art, data visualization, 3-D software, and much more.  Art by Code is a triumph of human ingenuity and a tribute to artists who dare to imagine, invent, and test the limits.\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'antonio-cortez,inigo-quilez,kristin-henry,jon-kuzmich,josh-nimoy,matthew-cella,nolan-love,reza-ali,ryan-alexander,tiffany-trenda,wes-grubbs,kim-rees', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(22, 'CODAME on The Playa!', 'codame-on-the-playa', '2013-07-29', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-on-the-playa.gif', '<p><a href=\"http://burningman.com\" target=\"_blank\">Burning Man</a> is an experience of self expression featuring projects and workshops of all kinds and combining the old, the new and the never seen before in one place for one week. It attracts a crowd of creators and inventors that gather in the desert to celebrate without the boundaries of civilized space and society. CODAME wants to jump into this melting pot to spread the spark of passion for technology further and gather like-minded people for a celebration of ART+TECH.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clusterf*ck (plural clusterf*cks)</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>(slang, chiefly military)</em> A confusing or chaotic situation or event, often caused by a failure of communication, an excessive number of people attempting to accomplish a given task.</p>\r\n<p>United <em>(adjective)</em></p>\r\n<p>Involving the joint activity of multiple agents.</p>\r\n<p>A camp without any specific goal other than of encouraging 100% participation, self-expression, creativity, and community from EVERY member.</p>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME on the PLAYA</strong> is a celebration of Art+Tech with drinks, music, prototypes, inventions, games and more and will happen on <strong>Thursday, August 29th at dusk</strong> at 4:30 art plaza at 8:30 up to 9:00, along G.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/e3f22f789625b1e4e26a3c85452e9e56.png\" alt=\"image\" /></p>\r\n<p>Our mission is to bring together artists, technologists, and designers that push the boundaries of hardware, software, and physical/digital mediums for one evening to play and share.</p>\r\n<p>Emerging talents that will show their projects are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/33367608081/xavi\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Xavi Vives Riba</strong></a>, with his award winning project Ludovico. Licensed under Creative Commons, Ludovico is an interactive visual piece of software that works with GIFs.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pablo Alvarez Yanez</strong>, with an Arduino powered sound reactive installation: Dust, intricate messy wires, LEDs and paper lanterns will transport you into the underworld of a cyberpunk far East metropolis where electronic beats and light spheres take over the night of Black Rock City</li>\r\n<li><strong>You!</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If interested to put up your piece at Clusterf*ck United please <a href=\"mailto:team@codame.com\" target=\"_blank\">email us </a>to inquire about tech specs and space for art.</p>\r\n<p>We can provide transportation of your piece to the playa and a camping space at Clusterf*ck United.</p>\r\n<p>Please be aware that Black Rock City is a place of extreme weather conditions, all installations need to be secured for wind and dust and lightened at night.</p>', 'xavi-vives-riba', 'ludovico', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(137, 'Make Beats (Music Fundamentals)', 'make-beats-music-fundamentals', '2020-11-28', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/make-ringtone-loops-beats-for-beginners.gif', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">#CodeArtTogether<br />with Abhinay Khoparzi</p>\r\n<h3>Have you day dreamed of making your own music but don\'t know where to start? Time to pick up the fundamentals of rhythm and melodic music theory! Use a point and click, browser based piano roll to make your own loops. Export your creation to use as a ringtone or bring it to <a href=\"http://codame.com/events/visualize-music-using-hydra-blocks\">Samarth\'s music visualizer workshop</a>. Skills from this workshop will transfer to Digital Audio Workstations and Livecoding environments.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this in to your website where you want the widget to appear. Do no change the code or the widget may not work properly. -->\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/450377/chk/8a5e/ref/website_widget\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/450377/chk/8a5e/ref/website_widget\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- End of Ticket Tailor Widget -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Time Schedule</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sat Nov 28, 2020</li>\r\n<li>11am - 1pm PT (2 hours)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://time.is/1100AM_17_October_2020_in_San_Francisco/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\">Time.is Localizer</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Skill Level</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all levels.</li>\r\n<li>No specific background required for this workshop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Workshop Outline</strong></h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li>Basics of making beats</li>\r\n<li>Time/Rhythm/Percussion</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to explore &amp; sharing discoveries</em></li>\r\n<li>Pitch/Key/Melody</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to explore &amp; sharing discoveries</em></li>\r\n<li>Noob Notes, DMP, other sources of inspiration</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to explore &amp; sharing discoveries</em></li>\r\n<li>Next steps:&nbsp;Livecoding, Music Visualization&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>What to Bring</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger.</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: 2nd monitor or screen so you can see the Zoom while working.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>We Will Provide</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CODAME Slides</li>\r\n<li>Instructor Slides</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Buy tickets for Make Ringtone Loops (Beats For Beginners)\" href=\"https://buytickets.at/codame/435545/r/codame-dot-com\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://app.tickettailor.com/images/btns/bt_pu.gif\" alt=\"Buy tickets for Make Ringtone Loops (Beats For Beginners)\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /> Get tickets now to reserve your spot for <br />an extraordinary learning experience. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">This workshop is part of<br />#CodeArtTogether</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ§ âœ¨</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸŽ¨ðŸš§ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create</span><br /></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ¤©ðŸ’¬ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Celebrate</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The pillars of #CodeArtTogether workshops by CODAME:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Connect</strong> with peers and new neurons in your brain.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Create</strong> art work and generate innovative ideas.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Celebrate</strong> by showing and selling what you build.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We also offer private team building events, <a href=\"http://codame.com/pages/support-art-tech\">contact us to learn more and support ART+TECH</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Buy tickets for Make Ringtone Loops (Beats For Beginners)\" href=\"https://buytickets.at/codame/435545/r/codame-dot-com\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://app.tickettailor.com/images/btns/bt_pu.gif\" alt=\"Buy tickets for Make Ringtone Loops (Beats For Beginners)\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Join us</h2>\r\n<center>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/join-us\">Join us</a>. Sponsor, Volunteer or lead a workshop.&nbsp;<br />What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;<br />Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>.</p>\r\n<p>All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.&nbsp;<br /><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n</center><center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'abhinay-khoparzi', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://buytickets.at/codame/435545/r/codame-dot-com', NULL),
(23, 'CODAME GAMES', 'codame-games', '2013-08-21', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-games.png', '\r\n						<p>On <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st CODAME</a> will be running an event dedicated to Gaming, join us to be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite <span class=\"vevent\"><span class=\"description\">Indie Game.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>#SPEAKERS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>“Some Observations on Video Game Evolution: A look at 3 video game series over 30 years.”</em> – Eric Wing, Software Engineer at <a href=\"http://Lanica.co\" target=\"_blank\">Lanica.co</a> – <strong>UPDATE</strong><span>: Presentation recording </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/59424278755/video-game-evolution-observations-over-30\" target=\"_blank\">here</a><span>!</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span><em>“Bringing emotions into games: the power of character animation.”</em> – </span><span> Stefano Corrazza, CEO at </span><a href=\"http://mixamo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Mixamo</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span><strong>#ART by CODE</strong> (Silent Auction)</span></p>\r\n<p>Gallery work created by: <a href=\"http://codame.com/post/53163702656/antonio-cortez-codame-featured-artist-antonio\" target=\"_blank\">Antonio Cortez</a><span>, </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/53175634592/kristin-henry-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Kristin Henry</span></span></a><span>, </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Nimoy</a><span>, </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/53171832401/matthew-cella-codame-featured-artist-matt\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew Cella</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>#INDIE GAMES developers showcase</strong></p>\r\n<p><span>A great opportunity to showcase your work and get feedback from your peers and others in the game industry, as well be eligible to be chosen for an award and the opportunity to attend </span><a title=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2013\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a><span><br>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Presenting Games: </strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58535721163/codame-featured-game-lost-toys-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">Lost Toys</a> by <a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58535721163/codame-featured-game-lost-toys-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">Barking Mouse Studio</a></li>\r\n<li><span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58429222086/codame-featured-game-full-bore-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">Full Bore</a> by </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58429222086/codame-featured-game-full-bore-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">Casey Carlin</a></li>\r\n<li><span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58383733111/codame-featured-game-enhanced-wars-with\" target=\"_blank\">Enhanced Wars</a> by </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58383733111/codame-featured-game-enhanced-wars-with\" target=\"_blank\">Ethan Levy</a></li>\r\n<li><span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58260241928/codame-featured-game-retrobooster-with\" target=\"_blank\">Retrobooster</a> by </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58260241928/codame-featured-game-retrobooster-with\" target=\"_blank\">Terry Welsh</a></li>\r\n<li><span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58096951752/codame-featured-game-eugene-houdin-with-the\" target=\"_blank\">Eugene Houdin</a> by </span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58096951752/codame-featured-game-eugene-houdin-with-the\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Nick Smith</span></a></li>\r\n<li><span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58761033031/codame-featured-game-super-marshmallow-ninja\" target=\"_blank\">Super Marshmallow Ninja</a> by </span><span><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58761033031/codame-featured-game-super-marshmallow-ninja\" target=\"_blank\">ArdentKid</a></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58897602879/codame-featured-game-undead-overlord-by-jumpcore\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"s2\">Undead Overlord</span></a></span> by <a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58897602879/codame-featured-game-undead-overlord-by-jumpcore\" target=\"_blank\">JumpCore Productions</a></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://turtle-sandbox.com/website/index_stage.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"s2\">Canon Brawl</span></a></span><span> by Turtle Sandbox</span></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58897149424/codame-featured-game-byterider-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">byteRider</a> by <a class=\"account-group js-account-group js-action-profile js-user-profile-link js-nav\" href=\"http://codame.com/post/58897149424/codame-featured-game-byterider-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">Alec McEachran</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Judges Panel: </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://twitter.com/carlosicaza\" target=\"_blank\">Carlos Icaza</a><span>, Lanica CEO</span></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://twitter.com/ivanski\" target=\"_blank\">Ivan Cavero Belaude</a><span>, </span><span>Chief Architect, Imaging at Nokia</span></li>\r\n<li><span><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=301973\" target=\"_blank\">James Hsu</a>, SVP at </span><span>Tilting Point</span></li>\r\n<li><span><a href=\"http://twitter.com/jamesyoung\" target=\"_blank\">James Young</a>, </span><span>Co-founder at Playviews.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>#VOTE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give your love to your favorite indie game on <a href=\"http://codame.com/vote\" target=\"_blank\">codame.com/vote</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>#GAME ARCADE</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"image\" src=\"\"></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The Digital Game Museum is a Silicon Valley based videogame museum will be exhibiting three games that feature non-traditional game play plus the original art from an indie game that went viral and was a category finalist at Indiecade 2011.  All games will be playable!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><span>The Digital Game Museum preserves, presents, and studies the history and evolution of digital games and explores the impact of games on individuals, communities, and society.  The museum has an emphasis on conservation, research and community engagement.  Visit the website at </span><a href=\"http://digitalgamemuseum.org\" target=\"_blank\">http://digitalgamemuseum.org</a><span> for more information.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><strong>#SOCIALIZE</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">DJ <a href=\"http://twitter.com/STARPAUSE\" target=\"_blank\">STARPAUSE</a> will be keeping the vibes alive. Catch up with old friends or make new ones!</p>\r\n<p><em>Supported by our friends at</em></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://mixamo.com\" target=\"_blank\"><em><img alt=\"image\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/a59eb8d6351231b457498499c5271bd8.png\"></em></a></p>\r\n<p><em><a title=\"GamesBeat\" href=\"http://gamesbeat.com/?ref=CODAME.COM\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"image\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/f906bfca0ecef47c92af565d13c1474c.jpg\"></a></em></p>\r\n											', '', 'lost-toys,full-bore,enhanced-wars,retrobooster,eugene-houdin,super-marshmallow-ninja,undead-overlord,canon-brawl,byterider', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-games/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(24, 'DATAVIZ @ Geekdom SF with Chartio', 'dataviz-geekdom-sf-with-chartio', '2013-10-03', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/dataviz-geekdom-sf-with-chartio.jpg', '<div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Celebrateï¿½<strong>DATA VISUALIZATION</strong>ï¿½ART+TECH with CODAME</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>WHERE+WHENï¿½</strong> Thursday, Oct 3, 2013 from 6:30 to 10:30pmï¿½San Francisco, CA at Geekdom ï¿½ 620 Folsom St. <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP</a> <strong>CONFIRMED VISUAL</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"../post/61572435443/cabbibo-com-is-a-triptastic-experimental\" target=\"_blank\">Cabbibo</a> interactive leap installation</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://deeje.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Deeje</a>ï¿½multi-touchscreen visuals generated from your dancing finger data points</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../post/61740832709/codame-featured-artist-kinetech-is-an-art-dance\" target=\"_blank\">Kinetech</a>ï¿½Time Bubble, where a wave of hands brings you back the past.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>CONFIRMED AUDIO</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"../post/61652425032/tr-cer-is-the-alias-of-chris-osborn-an\" target=\"_blank\">TR&Lambda;CER</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20130429/greenpoint/data-driven-band-csv-soundsystem-makes-music-from-spreadsheets\" target=\"_blank\">CSV Soundsystem</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../post/33373653824/exit-only-codame-featured-musician-exit-only\" target=\"_blank\">EXIT ONLY</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>BYOB OFFICIAL</strong> In addition to the confirmed artists we are hosting <a href=\"http://www.byobworldwide.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">Bring Your Own Beamer</a> space! If you plan on bringing a projector with your work please <a href=\"mailto:dataviz@codame.com\" target=\"_blank\">contact us</a>ï¿½ahead of time for planning, and we will add your name/link here if desired. <strong>ART by CODE</strong> A silent auction for traditional wall hanging pieces by artists working with algorithms, logic and data!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"../post/53163702656/antonio-cortez-codame-featured-artist-antonio\" target=\"_blank\">Antonio Cortez</a>,ï¿½<a href=\"../post/53175634592/kristin-henry-codame-featured-artist\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Kristin Henry</span></span></a>,ï¿½<a href=\"../post/31799851067/codame-featured-artist-josh-nimoy\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Nimoy</a>,ï¿½<a href=\"../post/53171832401/matthew-cella-codame-featured-artist-matt\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew Cella</a>ï¿½ï¿½</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>CELEBRATE + DONATE</strong> Drink to support CODAME!ï¿½Drinks made only for this event, available for yourï¿½enjoymentï¿½and consumption. Thanks toï¿½<a href=\"http://Chartio.com\" target=\"_blank\">Chartio</a> and <a href=\"http://Rackspace.com\" target=\"_blank\">Rackspace</a>ï¿½sï¿½love for ART+TECH! <strong>CALL FOR ARTISTS</strong> If you want your fingers off homerow and into the pi, <a href=\"mailto:dataviz@codame.com\" target=\"_blank\">contact us</a>! Always keen to integrate fresh work exploring the intersection of ART+TECH, and especially #dataviz for this event. <strong>SPONSORS</strong> CODAME is possible with allies like youï¿½ <a href=\"mailto:dataviz@codame.com\" target=\"_blank\">contact us</a> to contribute. Every bit and byte helps!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Supported by</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://chartio.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2013/10/tumblr_msn2a2zUtp1qixx7ho4_r1_400.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Hosted by</div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://geekdom.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://31.media.tumblr.com/60317e7989be1e5b23bf2ba16a0daf8d/tumblr_msn2a2zUtp1qixx7ho2_r1_1280.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n<div>Food and Drinks Served by</div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://pomdoro.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://25.media.tumblr.com/85782dabbccc606c5674ee1287c46225/tumblr_msn2a2zUtp1qixx7ho2_r2_1280.gif\" alt=\"Pomdoro\" /></a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>As part of</div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://dataweek.co/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://25.media.tumblr.com/81ed89dcd005f228485c0df9487bbbf8/tumblr_msn2a2zUtp1qixx7ho3_r1_1280.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', 'cabbibo,csv-soundsystem,exit-only,eric-fickes,tracer,deeje,kinetech-arts', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', NULL),
(25, 'CODAME GAMES @ Geekdom SF', 'codame-games-geekdom-sf', '2013-11-02', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-games-geekdom-sf.png', '\r\n						<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img alt=\"\" src=\"\"></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/11f8991e1d58833075fd6074107b2812.png\"></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/f302ba6b898714fae406005a5a8672e8.png\"></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/e8a0951e1c88fa3e6ab1eebc81c9090b.jpg\"></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/89c519f6fc9d08b9866d23775c37bf1b.jpg\"></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Our <strong><a href=\"http://codame.com/games\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a></strong> showdown earlier this month was a total blast! Amid all the excellent submissions, our judges had the next-to-impossible task of picking only a handful of winners.</p>\r\n<p>In the second round our <a href=\"http://codame.com/sponsors\" target=\"_blank\">sponsors</a> will select the CODAME 2013 ART+TECH GAME of the year at our <a href=\"http://codame.com/festival\" target=\"_blank\">festival</a> taking place November 1-2.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Top Honors:</strong>  <a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58096951752/codame-featured-game-eugene-houdin-with-the\" target=\"_blank\">Eugene Houdin</a>, by McNeil Media<br>\r\nA stick-figure fighting game that’s insanely fun to play and ingeniously designed.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Most Fun:  </strong><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58260241928/codame-featured-game-retrobooster-with\" target=\"_blank\">Retrobooster</a>, by Terry Welsh<br>\r\nA gorgeous space shooter with superb controls and updated <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_Lander_(arcade_game)\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Lunar Lander</em></a> style graphics.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Most Original:  </strong><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58429222086/codame-featured-game-full-bore-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">Full Bore</a>, by Whole Hog Games<br>\r\nA retro-tinged arcade digger with very elaborate level design and a fun pork-themed motif.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Most Epic:  </strong><a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58897937775/codame-featured-game-canon-brawl-by-turtle\" target=\"_blank\">Canon Brawl</a>, by Turtle Sandbox<br>\r\nAn artillery/Warcraft style 2D head-to-header with explosions and destructible terrain. Scorch the Earth to your heart’s content, and emerge victorious!</li>\r\n<li><strong>Most Artistic:</strong>  <a href=\"http://codame.com/post/58535721163/codame-featured-game-lost-toys-with-the-codame\" target=\"_blank\">Lost Toys</a>, by Barking Mouse<br>\r\nA beautiful Myst<em>–</em>style attic exploration game. You can certainly tell that they put a lot of time into the visuals and overall atmosphere of this game.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you missed them the first time around, be sure to come out and check out these games in-person. They truly are extraordinary, and perfectly embody the “art vs. tech” theme of <a href=\"http://codame.com/festival\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Big thanks to our <a href=\"http://codame.com/sponsors\" target=\"_blank\">Sponsors</a> and judges: <a href=\"http://twitter.com/carlosicaza\" target=\"_blank\">Carlos Icaza</a>, <a href=\"http://twitter.com/ewingfighter\" target=\"_blank\">Eric Wing</a>, <a href=\"http://twitter.com/ivanski\" target=\"_blank\">Ivan Cavero Belaude</a>, <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=301973\" target=\"_blank\">James Hsu</a>, <a href=\"http://twitter.com/jamesyoung\" target=\"_blank\">James Young</a> and all the fans who voted for their favorite game on the CODAME <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.511840552225611.1073741847.121190041290666\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook page</a>!</p>\r\n<p><strong>See you <a href=\"http://codame.com/festival\" target=\"_blank\">Nov 1-2 at Geekdom SF</a> for the second and final round</strong><strong>!</strong></p>\r\n											', '', 'eugene-houdin,retrobooster,full-bore,canon-brawl,lost-toys', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/finals/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(26, 'ART+TECH FESTIVAL [2013]', 'art-tech-festival-2013', '2013-11-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-2013-art-tech-festival.gif', '<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/W0Xo1xVxpEQ\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME 2013 ART+TECH Festival</strong></p>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s art+tech festival is a curated experience that delves into all the senses with auditory, tactile, optical, taste and yes, olfactory installations. We&rsquo;ll even explore the 6th sense with some experimental arts and performances.</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s so much to see, we&rsquo;re running the festival for two days, so join us to RE-EXPERIENCE THE 5ENSES with CODAME at GeekdomSF.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Get ready for an&nbsp;<strong>exclusive</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>immersive</strong>&nbsp;guided&nbsp;<strong>journey</strong>&nbsp;that will subvert your perception and re-awaken your senses.</p>\r\n<p>On November 1st and 2nd, 2013 CODAME will be opening the doors to&nbsp;<strong>5ENSES</strong>.&nbsp;<strong>@GeekdomSF</strong>, 620 Folsom St., San Francisco, CA from 7pm to 1am</p>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s CODAME Festival includes:</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// IMMERSIVE 5ENSES SPACE</strong></p>\r\n<p>A highly electrifying event to re-experience your five sense in a carefully curated immersive space. Your guides will lead you through each room where you will ignite each sense one by one, ultimately delivering you into the Gallery.</p>\r\n<p><em>Stefano Corazza,&nbsp;Dolores Joya,&nbsp;Bad Unkl Sista,&nbsp;Paolo Salvagione,&nbsp;Carr,&nbsp;Bruno,&nbsp;Colin,&nbsp;Gabriel Dunne,&nbsp;Sasha, Kevin Koechley</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>/// HAPPENINGS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bad Unkl Sista&nbsp;performing in the gallery at midnight</li>\r\n<li>SIXTH SENSE room&nbsp;Jonathan Wallraven&nbsp;(with&nbsp;E Dyer) and&nbsp;Leo Madrid</li>\r\n<li>Brand new IRL game&nbsp;flattery&nbsp;by&nbsp;DC Spensley</li>\r\n<li>Interactive performance by&nbsp;Kinetech</li>\r\n<li>Tribute to Lou Reed by&nbsp;14 Bindlestick Frank</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>/// AUDIO VISUAL SETS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Jefferson Shulgin,&nbsp;Leftbody,&nbsp;Alexandernaut</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// GALLERY INSTALLATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unicorn</li>\r\n<li>Phracktography Gifalizer Booth</li>\r\n<li>Patrick Dintino</li>\r\n<li>Jeff Cheung</li>\r\n<li>Carl Pisaturo</li>\r\n<li>Issac Cohen</li>\r\n<li>Robert Edgar</li>\r\n<li>Charlie Levin</li>\r\n<li>Tim Thompson</li>\r\n<li>Al linke</li>\r\n<li>Ytai Ben-Tsvi</li>\r\n<li>Cory Barr</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>/// SOUND SYSTEM</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Carson Day</li>\r\n<li>Moldover (DJ Set)</li>\r\n<li>Rich DDT</li>\r\n<li>CDCM</li>\r\n<li>Bill Hsu/ Ollie Bown/ raven</li>\r\n<li>ENC</li>\r\n<li>Extent of the Jam</li>\r\n<li>Nonagon</li>\r\n<li>STARPAUSE</li>\r\n<li>Dust Red Skies</li>\r\n<li>Sasha Leitman</li>\r\n<li>Fernando Lopez-Lezcano</li>\r\n<li>Carr Wilkerson</li>\r\n<li>Bruno Ruviaro</li>\r\n<li>Luke Dahl</li>\r\n<li>Colin Sullivan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>/// AUDIO REACTIVE STAGE PROJECTIONS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Angat Gaada,&nbsp;Nop Jiarathanakul,&nbsp;VCOVAULT,&nbsp;CSTNG-SHDWS</p>\r\n<p><strong>///&nbsp;VIDEO LOOPS&nbsp;Station</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Ken Murphy,&nbsp;TIMEFLY,&nbsp;&nbsp;David O&rsquo;reilly,&nbsp;Andrew Benson,&nbsp;Laturbo Avedon,&nbsp;&nbsp;Ben Mikrosopht,&nbsp;&nbsp;Cyriak,&nbsp;&nbsp;Paul Clipson,&nbsp;Beeple,&nbsp;Renetta Sitoy,&nbsp;Max Capacity,&nbsp;Andrea Starr</em>&nbsp;Curated by&nbsp;Amy Lee.</p>\r\n<p><strong>///&nbsp;INDIE GAME&nbsp;Room</strong></p>\r\n<p>Play a selection of&nbsp;CODAME&nbsp;GAMES&nbsp;and traditional arcade games, presented by&nbsp;Lanica, the&nbsp;game developer experts.</p>\r\n<p><strong>///&nbsp;ART by CODE&nbsp;(Silent Auction)</strong></p>\r\n<p>A silent auction for traditional wall hanging pieces by artists working with algorithms, logic and data! Work from&nbsp;<em>Antonio Cortez,&nbsp;Kristin Henry,&nbsp;Josh Nimoy,&nbsp;Matthew Cella</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>/// HALLOWEEN</strong></p>\r\n<p>There will be both tricks and treats.&nbsp;The CODAME Team will be hunting for the best ART+TECH dress!</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// DRINK Bar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Donation based drinks to deliver a fun and&nbsp;ultimate&nbsp;taste experience.</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// KIDS &amp; FAMILY TIME</strong></p>\r\n<p>Swing through early (6pm) on Saturday with your kids and family. Stay as late as you like!</p>\r\n<p><strong>///&nbsp;SUPPORT&nbsp;CODAME + ARTISTS</strong></p>\r\n<p>We are&nbsp;looking&nbsp;for&nbsp;sponsors,&nbsp;supporters,&nbsp;volunteers. if you can help, any pixel or bit counts! Join our&nbsp;Adopt an Artist&nbsp;initiative&nbsp;Contact us! Or just join us and donate by getting your&nbsp;ticket!</p>\r\n<p><strong>///&nbsp;</strong><strong>CURATED</strong>&nbsp;by&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>Stefano Corazza,&nbsp;&nbsp;Kiri Rong,&nbsp;Hanna Regev&nbsp;and&nbsp;&nbsp;Jordan Gray&nbsp; with the collaboration of some of the San Francisco Bay Area&rsquo;s top tech-artists!</p>', 'bad-unkl-sista,jonathan-wallraven,anastazia-louise-aranaga,e-dyer,leo-madrid,kinetech-arts,14-bindlestick-frank,dolores-joya,jefferson-shulgin,colin-roache,alexandernaut,unicorn,patrick-dintino,jeff-cheung,carl-pisaturo,cabbibo,robert-edgar,charlie-levin,tim-thompson,al-linke,ytai-ben-tsvi,cory-barr,carson-day,moldover,rich-ddt,cdcm,enc,extent-of-the-jam,nonagon,dust-red-skies,sasha-leitman,fernando-lopez-lezcano,carr-wilkerson,bruno-ruviaro,luke-dahl,colin-sullivan,angat-gaada,nop-jiarathanakul,vco-vault,cstng-shdws,ken-murphy,timefly,david-o-reilly,andrew-benson,laturbo-avedon,cyriak,paul-clipson,beeple,renetta-sitoy,max-capacity,andrea-starr,ani,dc-spensley,gabriel-dunne,paolo-salvagione,bill-hsu,jordan-gray', 'phracktography,gifslap', 'rackspace', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(205, 'Meet the Artists at Sonic Runway', 'meet-the-artists-at-sonic-runway', '2023-04-24', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/meet-the-artists-at-sonic-runway.png', '<div><strong>Sonic Runway</strong> is a light-art installation that visualizes the speed of sound created by a team of artists, including lead artist Rob Jensen, co-lead Warren Trezevant, and design by Stockhausen.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Sonic Runway was installed at City Hall from November 2017 to March 2018 as part of the Playa to Paseo partnership between the City of San Jos&eacute; Office of Cultural Affairs and the Burning Man Project. Due to popular demand, this new version of Sonic Runway is a multi-year installation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>This will be a great opportunity to meet Rob Jensen and Warren Trezevant, who will walk you through the conceptual and technical. The small gathering of performers and artists is an opportunity to think about how you can create and imagine this incredible platform.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>You will be able to ask the artists some technical questions and explore the platform\'s abilities. It can be a curricular container for new media art, experimental music, performance, games, etc. Or it can be used as a performance platform for sound, dance, and experimental media. The platform allows audio input on each end and responds in color to the input sound.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>When</strong></div>\r\n<div>Monday April, 24th, 2023 from 7 - 9 pm</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Where</strong></div>\r\n<div>Sonic Runway at 200 E. Santa Clara Street, San Jose.<br /><br />Organized by&nbsp;<strong>San Jose Cultural Affairs</strong></div>\r\n<div>San Jos&eacute;\'s lead agency for supporting the development of a rich arts and cultural environment for this diverse city.</div>', 'rob-jensen,warren-trezevant', 'sonic-runway', '', 'san-jose-cultural-affairs', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(206, 'Together', 'together', '2023-05-13', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/together.gif', '<p dir=\"ltr\">San Francisco ART+TECH enthusiasts, CODAME is back and ready to bring us together for an intimate and inclusive gathering. As a local organization deeply rooted in the art and tech community, we invite you to join us!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Whether you\'re a seasoned CODAME artist, volunteer, supporter, or a curious newcomer, this is the perfect opportunity to share your work, learn from others, and be part of something inspiring and uniquely San Franciscan.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Join us in person at the Gray Area Grand Theater, located in the heart of the city\'s vibrant Mission District, to reconnect, discuss, and explore potential new projects and collaborations. Together, we\'ll delve into the intersection of art and technology and work towards shaping the future of this thriving community.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Save the date on your calendar for Saturday, May 13th, 2023, from 3 to 5 pm, and <a href=\"https://app.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/2375770/chk/80a2/?modal_widget=true&amp;widget=true\">RSVP</a> now to secure your spot. This is an incredible chance to connect, learn, and create alongside a supportive and passionate community of San Franciscan ART+TECH enthusiasts.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We can\'t wait to see you there and to celebrate the unique creativity and innovation that San Francisco is known for!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Looking forward to connecting with you,</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Bruno Fonzi and Jordan Gray</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">CODAME\'s co-founders</p>\r\n<!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this into your website where you want the widget to appear. Do not change the code or the widget may not work properly. -->\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/2375770/chk/80a2/\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg_89052\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/2375770/chk/80a2/\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\" data-inline-inherit-ref-from-url-param=\"\" data-inline-ref=\"\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- End of Ticket Tailor Widget -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>///</p>\r\n<p>CODAME is a member of Gray Area, a nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization. All proceeds will be split with the participating artists. Thank you for the support for ART+TECH !!! <a href=\"http://codame.com/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct for all attendees</a>.</p>', 'bruno-fonzi,jordan-gray', '', '', 'gray-area', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://app.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/2375770/chk/80a2/?modal_widget=true&widget=true', ''),
(207, 'Stories On The Road - San Francisco', 'stories-on-the-road---san-francisco', '2023-05-22', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/stories-on-the-road---san-francisco.png', '<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Where</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Homebrew, 1481 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103 (<a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/1481+Folsom+St,+San+Francisco\">map</a>)</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>When</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Monday, 22nd May 2023, from 5pm to 9pm</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Get your <a href=\"https://ti.to/beyondtellerrand/stories-on-the-road/with/yi6anjit-24\">free ticket</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p>Stories on the Road&nbsp;is a traveling show that will tour selected cities in different countries to bring the community together at free events, share valuable insight, and have a great time together!</p>\r\n<p>CODAME is&nbsp;partnering with&nbsp;Storyblok and beyond tellerrand&nbsp;bringing&nbsp;Stories onto the Road to San Francisco on May 22nd for an evening full of exciting talks and conversations&nbsp;with&nbsp;Vitaly Friedman,&nbsp;Cindy Clark,&nbsp;Maribel Mullins, and&nbsp;Marco de Campos.</p>\r\n<p>Connect with peers from&nbsp;San Francisco, take home an amazing and exclusive show bag, and, to close your night, enjoy some nice snacks and drinks with a bunch of incredible people.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Talks</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Vitaly Friedman</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Boosting Web Performance in 2023</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Even heavy, framework-driven, legacy-haunted apps can get into the green Core Web Vitals and great Lighthouse scores. With partial hydration, critical rendering, clean CSS architecture, Qwik, AVIF, service workers, web workers, predictive prefetching, and a dash of client hints, resource hints, and early hints, we must apply the right performance strategy to get there. So how do we do that? Let&rsquo;s figure out some of the most critical optimization strategies to get your website blazingly fast &mdash; in 60 mins or less!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cindy Clark</strong>&nbsp;- Cultivating Creativity</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">My&nbsp;Journey of Leveraging Technology for Exploration and Discovery with CODAME</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-32c17ddb-7fff-6961-3a0c-b76e0f7d9ce2\">Cindy is a Product Designer with a background in fine jewelry. She introduced CAD tech to the American Jewelry industry and introduced AR virtual try-on for a jewelry company. A versatile problem solver, she creates impactful solutions for intuitive user experiences. Cindy is also a longstanding member of CODAME, a renowned non-profit organization in San Francisco that celebrates creativity through inspiring experiences that leverage technology for exploration and discovery.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Maribel Mullins</strong>&nbsp;- Talk: TBA</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Maribel Mullins is a Technology Partner Manager at Cloudinary, leading their Partner-built integrations program. She&rsquo;s been with Cloudinary for over 4 years. With her technical background, she has worked at various startup companies for the last 16 years in engineering, sales, and customer success. Her attention to detail and drive to continuously find new tools for her &ldquo;life&rsquo;s toolbox&rdquo; position her especially well to find solutions and manage resources.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Marco de Campos</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Breaking the Monolith</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">The headless revolution. Back to de basics to understand the headless architecture</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Marco de Campos is a Developer Relations Engineer at Storyblok. From Medell&iacute;n, Colombia, he has more than 20 years of experience in software development as a Full Stack Developer.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">~~~</h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Space is limited to ~50 people.</h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Get your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ti.to/beyondtellerrand/stories-on-the-road/with/yi6anjit-24\">Free ticket</a>&nbsp;now before it is too late.</strong></h3>\r\n<p>///</p>\r\n<p>CODAME is a member of Gray Area, a nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization. All proceeds will be split with the participating artists. Thank you for the support for ART+TECH !!!&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.com/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct for all attendees</a>.&nbsp;</p>', 'vitaly-friedmann,marco-de-campos,cindy-clark,maribel-mullins', '', '', 'storyblok,beyond-tellerrand', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://ti.to/beyondtellerrand/stories-on-the-road/with/yi6anjit-24', ''),
(27, 'Grand Opening Night at Rackspace Geekdom', 'grand-opening-night-at-rackspace-geekdom', '2013-11-05', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/grand-opening-night-at-rackspace-geekdom.jpg', '<p>CODAME brought our flavor of ART+TECH to Geekdom San Fracisco\'s grand opening party.</p>\r\n<p class=\"js-clip_title\">Amidst the great drinks/food/dancing/games going on, we had our CODAME GIF BOOTH (aka <a href=\"http://tmblr.co/ZYZPfxzjZIdK\" target=\"_blank\">Phracktography</a> 3.0) video loops, based on the Gifalizer software, and CODAME artists on hand!</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/78994787\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong>Credits:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Video: Amy Lee</p>\r\n<p>Audio: <a href=\"/admin/starpause.com\" target=\"_blank\">STARPAUSE</a></p>\r\n<p>Lower 3rd Graphics: <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/69080509\" target=\"_blank\">Beeple</a></p>\r\n<p>CODAME Logo Motion Design: <a href=\"http://camaltamura.com\" target=\"_blank\">Cam Altamura</a></p>', 'ani,jordan-gray,beeple,cam-altamura', 'phracktography', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(28, 'ArtsTech Meetup: CODAME Debrief', 'artstech-meetup-codame-debrief', '2013-11-19', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/artstech-meetup-codame-debrief.jpg', '<p><img alt=\"\" /><br /> Theï¿½<a href=\"/\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME</a>ï¿½Team has been invited byï¿½<a href=\"http://bayarea.impacthub.net/event/artstech-meetup\" target=\"_blank\">Impact Hub</a>ï¿½for anï¿½<a href=\"http://bayarea.impacthub.net/event/artstech-meetup\" target=\"_blank\">ArtsTech</a>meetup to chat and learn more about ourï¿½<a href=\"/5enses\" target=\"_blank\">5ENSES 2013 ART+TECH Festival</a>. We willï¿½explore the ways in which social media and technology can help bring arts and culture to the masses.</p>\r\n<p>ï¿½Democratizingï¿½ the arts has been a long-standing goal in the art world, and no medium makes it more feasible than the web.ï¿½Join us to share ideas, strategies, successes, challenges and network.</p>\r\n<p>Light refreshments and snacks will be served.ï¿½<strong>Pleaseï¿½<a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/artstech-meetup-codame-debrief-tickets-8912777357\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP</a>ï¿½hereï¿½</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://bayarea.impacthub.net/event/artstech-meetup\" target=\"_blank\">http://bayarea.impacthub.net/event/artstech-meetup</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Featured speakers:</strong></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/6ec22a77c08f391cef2d65f9729aad01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"115\" height=\"115\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/post/33237400933/jonathan-wallraven-codame-featured-artist-were\" target=\"_blank\">Jonathan Wallraven</a><strong>,ï¿½</strong></strong>San Francisco-based artist Jonathanï¿½s work simultaneously draws in and overwhelms the eye. His primary body of work isï¿½<em>The Spiral</em>, a series of site-specific black and white wall drawings that blur the lines between installation and comic book art. Since becoming involved with CODAME, his practice has grown to encompass collaboration and interactivity. For the ART+TECH Festival, Wallraven premieredï¿½<em>Techn-O-Ccultic Conjurations</em>, an interactive multimedia performance-installation.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">ï¿½</span></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/4ad5b1a58f7701cfcff8520176f0b4f0.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"115\" height=\"115\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Bruno Fonzi</strong></a>,ï¿½Co-Founder at CODAME ART+TECH and Lanica, Inc.ï¿½Commodore at CODAME, running not-for-profit ART+TECH events bringing together artists, coders, game developers, creators, performers and musicians to create and experience the intersection of Art and Technology. Bruno is also a startup advisor and co-founder atï¿½<a href=\"http://lanica.co\" target=\"_blank\">Lanica</a>ï¿½building a state-of-art mobile development platform. In his previous years, he worked at Adobe where he led a worldwide team of engineers, responsible for product development of the creative suite of applications and services to support mobile devices.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/f0ffc173891e886c59568023d49625c2.jpg\" alt=\"Jordan Gray\" width=\"115\" height=\"115\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://twitter.com/Starpause\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Jordan Gray</strong></a>ï¿½(aka starPause the k9d) is Manager of Creative Labs @<a href=\"http://Organic.com\" target=\"_blank\">OrganicInc</a>ï¿½and co-founder of CODAME, a SF based event celebrating the intersection of ART+TECH. He loves modular analog video synthesis, bicycles, photography, electronic music, dayan qigong &amp; haiku.</p>\r\n<p>ï¿½</p>', 'jonathan-wallraven,bruno-fonzi,jordan-gray', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(29, 'Dissident Futures Art and Ideas Festival', 'dissident-futures-art-and-ideas-festival', '2013-10-18', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-at-the-ybca-dissident-futures-art-and-ideas-festival.jpg', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>YBCA and CODAME invites you to participate in a one-day interactive festival in conjunction with the Dissident Futures visual arts exhibit in our Downstairs Gallery. The festival will bring our communities together to explore and investigate possible futures envisioned by artists, urban planners, environmentalists, scientists, robotic experts, designers, programmers, and food activists through dynamic workshops, lectures, performances, interactive media, music, and more.</p>\r\n<p>The worldwide effort to consider and shape the future is being conducted by a diverse number of artists, scientists, teachers, and activists. In the Bay Area, there are a wealth of future-facing projects, many involving practical innovations in technology and science. Some of these creative and pragmatic endeavors are informed by utopian dreams and fueled by a local culture that looks to the future with hope and optimism for what may come. The breadth of ideas and emergent forms ranges vastly, and given the rising pace of these activities and aspirations for the future, it is an exciting time for us to look critically at the participants in this conversation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">We want to bring people together in dialogue with members of our Bay Area community who have the tools to envision a future that expands beyond the best of our aspirations and builds on our technological advances, while also keeping in check negative realities such as climate change, rising income inequalities, and gaps in power distribution and influence. We seek to look at the entire ecology and foster discussions that move us toward a world we can help to create.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Join</span><span class=\"s2\"> <a href=\"/\"><span class=\"s3\">CODAME</span></a> </span><span class=\"s1\">to</span> <span class=\"s1\">Play, Celebrate and Inspire the intersection between Art and Technology</span> <span class=\"s1\">at the</span><span class=\"s2\"> <a href=\"http://dissidentfestival.tumblr.com/\"><span class=\"s3\">Dissident Futures Art and Ideas Festival</span></a> </span><span class=\"s1\">with a presentation in this order starting at 2:30.</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul1\">\r\n<li class=\"li2\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Commodore</strong></span> <span class=\"s1\">(in-Chief): Bruno Fonzi @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\"><span class=\"s4\">BrunoFonzi</span></a></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"li2\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Atari</strong></span> <span class=\"s1\">(Artist Canvas): Vicente Montelongo @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/mexist\"><span class=\"s4\">Mexist</span></a></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"li2\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Amiga</strong></span> <span class=\"s1\">(Guru Meditation Handler): Jordan Gray @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/Starpause\"><span class=\"s4\">Starpause</span></a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s5\">and a short selection of</span><span class=\"s6\"> <a href=\"/artists\"><span class=\"s3\">CODAME Featured Artists</span></a> </span><span class=\"s5\">Weidong Yang (from</span><span class=\"s6\"> <span class=\"s3\">Kinetech</span></span><span class=\"s5\">),</span><span class=\"s6\"> <span class=\"s3\">Al linke</span></span><span class=\"s5\">,</span><span class=\"s6\"> <span class=\"s3\">Renetta Sitoy</span></span><span class=\"s5\">,</span><span class=\"s6\"> <span class=\"s3\">Jonathan Wallraven</span></span><span class=\"s5\">,</span><span class=\"s6\"> <span class=\"s3\">Robert Edgar</span></span><span class=\"s5\">,</span><span class=\"s6\"> <span class=\"s3\">LaTurbo Avedon</span> </span><span class=\"s5\">and</span><span class=\"s6\"> <span class=\"s3\">DC Spensley</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">You will find us at the</span> <span class=\"s1\">YAAW Lounge</span><span class=\"s2\"> &nbsp;</span><span class=\"s1\"> 1st floor </span><span class=\"s2\">&nbsp; </span><span class=\"s1\">between 2:30 and 4:00</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"s5\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; -webkit-text-stroke-width: initial;\">FREE w/ RSVP</span><span class=\"s6\" style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width: initial;\"> <a href=\"http://ybca.org/art-and-ideas\"><span class=\"s3\">http://ybca.org/art-and-ideas</span></a>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"s5\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; -webkit-text-stroke-width: initial;\"> more info at</span><span class=\"s6\" style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width: initial;\"> <span class=\"s3\"><a href=\"http://dissidentfestival.tumblr.com\">http://dissidentfestival.tumblr.com</a></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-2166\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/ybca-logo.jpg\" alt=\"ybca-logo\" width=\"644\" height=\"382\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'al-linke,renetta-sitoy,jonathan-wallraven,robert-edgar,laturbo-avedon,dc-spensley,kinetech-arts,bruno-fonzi,jordan-gray', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(30, 'CODAME Artists at LeBook Connections', 'codame-artists-at-lebook-connections', '2014-02-27', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-artists-at-lebook-connections.jpg', '\r\n						<p>We are thrilled to present our <a href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\">Adopt Art+Tech</a> program at LeBook Connections, an opportunity for your organization to support, collaborate with CODAME and our ART+TECH artists at <strong>Le Book <a href=\"http://connexsf.splashthat.com/\">CONNECTIONS</a></strong> in San Francisco. Find our booth at CONNECTIONS an annual meeting for the creative community and we invite you to be a part of it. Registration is by invitation only, attendance is complimentary.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-3200 aligncenter\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/LeBook_CatalogBanner_01.jpg\" alt=\"LeBook_CatalogBanner_01\" width=\"920\" height=\"92\"> CODAME at lebook CONNECTIONS –<em> THE NWBLK, 1999 Bryant St, San Francisco, CA, 94110 – on – Thursday, February 27, 11:30 AM – 8:00 PM</em></p>\r\n<p>Designers like Jonathan Ive at Apple, Joe Gebbia at Airbnb, and the rockstar design team at Dropbox (just to name a few) are changing the digital world today – not entirely because they have better tech, but because they make their products more usable & more desirable. The space is more competitive than ever before and the winning ingredients are compelling content and engaging user experiences. CONNECTIONS is an opportunity to discover some of the best international content creators. Over the course of a day in San Francisco, you will meet, connect, and exchange ideas with 30 of the best creative partners & services who will be on hand to present their work.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">PRINT, DIGITAL, EXPERIENCE, FILM, SOCIAL. <strong>CONNECTIONS</strong> IS WHERE IT’S AT.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding: 10px;\"><a href=\"http://connexsf.splashthat.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Register Now</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>SCHEDULE</strong></p>\r\n<div><strong>11:30 AM </strong> PANEL DISCUSSION | <strong>THE IMPACT OF TECHNOLOGY on BRANDING</strong> Bridget Dolan, VP, Interactive Media & Content |<strong> SEPHORA</strong> Jessica L’Esperance, VP, User Experience | <strong>HUGE</strong> Jesse McMillin, Executive Creative Director | <strong>VIRGIN AMERICA</strong> Evie Nagy, Writer | <strong>FAST COMPANY</strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>12:30 PM </strong> <strong>Portfolio & Reel</strong> viewing begins with <a href=\"http://connectionsbylebook.com/sf2014/exhibitors\">THE EXHIBITORS</a></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>3:00 PM</strong>  PANEL DISCUSSION | <strong>DESIGN: CREATING WHAT’S NEXT</strong> Len Peltier, VP, Global Creative Director | <strong>LEVI’S</strong> Billy Sorrentino, Creative Director | <strong>WIRED</strong> Roberto Tagliabue, Founder & Creative Director |<strong> AWAKE</strong> Simon Waterfall, VP, Creative Director | <strong>INTEL Media</strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>6:00 PM</strong> Open wine tasting & mingling</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>7:00 PM </strong>LE BOOK + <a href=\"http://www.noisepop.com/2014/\">NOISEPOP</a> + <a href=\"http://www.7x7.com/\">7×7  </a>invite you to <strong>RE-CONNECT</strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"> * As space is limited, please be sure to</span><b style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"> <a href=\"http://connexsf.splashthat.com/\">RSVP</a></b><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"> to all events you wish to attend</span></p>\r\n											', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/lebook-connections/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(31, 'CELEBRATE DEMOSCENE ART+TECH with CODAME', 'celebrate-demoscene-art-tech-with-codame', '2014-03-28', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/celebrate-demoscene-art-tech-with-codame.gif', '\r\n						<p>Friday March 28th <a href=\"http://twitter.com/GeekdomSF\" target=\"_blank\">@GeekdomSF</a> – 620 Folsom St. 6PM – 11PM, Eventbrite <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/demoscene-arttech-tickets-10888087563\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP</a> for entry</p>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demoscene\" target=\"_blank\">demoscene</a> is a electronic art subculture that specializes in producing demos, which are audio-visual presentations that run in real-time on a computer. The main purpose of a demo is to show off the combined effort of programming, graphical artistic and musical skills.</p>\r\n<p>We will be screening the <a href=\"http://nv.scene.org/2014/\" target=\"_blank\">NVScene 2014</a> Results in CODAME Style!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/demoscene-arttech-tickets-10888087563\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3318\" alt=\"NVSceneFlyer_01\" src=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\"></a></p>\r\n<p>The demoscene first appeared during the 8-bit era on computers such as the Commodore64, ZX Spectrum, Atari 800 and Amstrad CPC, and came to prominence during the rise of the 16/32-bit home computers (mainly the Amiga and Atari ST). We are really excited to host our first DEMOSCENE ART+TECH at CODAME in San Francisco!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/PidTKpKLYZM\" height=\"315\" width=\"560\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Check out <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PidTKpKLYZM\">the NVScene 2008 reel</a> for examples of demos and demoscene art!</p>\r\n<p>To learn more about the history of DEMOSCENE check out<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demoscene\" target=\"_blank\"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demoscene</a></p>\r\n<p>Supported by: <a href=\"http://codame.com/\">CODAME</a> + <a href=\"http://scene.org/\">Scene.org</a> + <a href=\"http://geekdom.com/san-francisco\">GeekdomSF</a></p>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; text-align: left;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=10888087563&ref=etckt\" height=\"293\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe><p></p>\r\n<div style=\"font-family: Helvetica, Arial; font-size: 10px; padding: 5px 0 5px; margin: 2px; width: 100%; text-align: left;\"><a style=\"color: #ddd; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/r/etckt\" target=\"_blank\">Sell Tickets</a> <span style=\"color: #ddd;\">through</span> <a style=\"color: #ddd; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com?ref=etckt\" target=\"_blank\">Eventbrite</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n											', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/celebrate-demoscene-arttech-with-codame/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(32, 'ADOPT an ARTIST Showcase', 'adopt-an-artist-showcase', '2014-04-16', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/adopt-an-artist-showcase.jpg', '<p>Join CODAME ART+TECH for an exclusive evening with the CODAME Featured Artists part of our&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists\">ADOPT AN ARTIST</a>&nbsp;program.&nbsp;Immersive storytelling through new technology&nbsp;is at the roots of the CODAME Adopt an Artist program for one night only at the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://autodesk.com/Gallery\" target=\"_blank\">Autodesk Gallery</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The following artists will be showcasing their work:<br /><a href=\"/post/anouk-wipprecht/\">Anouk Wipprecht</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/carl-pisaturo/\">Carl Pisaturo</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/dr-woohoo/\">Dr. Woohoo!</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/jonathan/\">Jonathan Wallraven</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/laturbo/\">Laturbo Avedon</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/matthew-cella/\">Matthew Cella</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/micah/\">Micah Elizabeth Scott</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/outerbody/\">Outerbody</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/paolo-salvagione/\">Paolo Salvagione</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/reza/\">Reza Ali</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/scott-kildall/\">Scott Kildall</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Our featured artists will showcase original work and engage the audience through live&nbsp;presentations and direct engagement. The 5-minute presentations will highlight the process and complexities of their art. Each testimonial will make a case for establishing artists in&nbsp;residencies programs and point to the value found in collaborations with host companies.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These collaborations act as catalysts for new unexpected creative endeavors that lead to new frontiers. Adopt an Artist is a chance to engage with the artist of your choice. Some of the Artist work is available for commission through CODAME.</p>\r\n<p>The event will start with a showcase of the artists work, followed by a discussion with&nbsp;renowned speakers from organizations such as&nbsp;<a href=\"http://autodesk.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Autodesk</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rackspace.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rackspace</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"https://salesforce.com\">Salesforce</a>,&nbsp;ending with a Q&amp;A session with the audience&nbsp;Q&amp;A session &nbsp;moderated by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\">Bruno Fonzi</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/HRegev\">Hanna Regev</a></p>\r\n<div><a href=\"/artists\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/LeBook_CatalogBanner_01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"60\" /></a></div>\r\n<p>You can find the CODAME Featured Artists on our site&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists\">codame.com/artists</a></p>\r\n<div><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Support-ART+TECH.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"131\" /></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>Big kudos to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.salesforce.com/design\" target=\"_blank\">Salesforce Design</a>&nbsp;team for supporting ART+TECH in providing Drinks and Appetizers at this event.</div>\r\n<p>Join CODAME\'s &ldquo;<a href=\"/artists\">Adopt an Artist</a>&rdquo; program, a pioneering initiative,&nbsp;that seeks to embrace and support the creators, producers, enablers, and collectors of media art and technology. Support and engage with a CODAME Artist of your choice.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/AdoptAnArtist_Showcase_Autodesk_codame_Schedule-1120x724.png\" alt=\"Adopt An Artist Showcase Schedule\" width=\"1120\" height=\"724\" /></p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'reza-ali,carl-pisaturo,paolo-salvagione,micah-scott,anouk-wipprecht,jonathan-wallraven,antonio-cortez,scott-kildall,matthew-cella,al-linke,dr-woohoo', '', 'salesforce,autodesk,rackspace', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(33, 'Featured Artist: Reza Ali @ Organic', 'featured-artist-reza-ali-organic', '2014-05-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/featured-artist-reza-ali-organic.jpg', '<p><a href=\"http://organic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Organic</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/\">CODAME</a>&nbsp;have come together to bring you code-generated art by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/reza/\">REZA</a>. The&nbsp;<a href=\"/adopt\">Adopt-an-Artist</a>&nbsp;program is an experiment that invites you to learn and play. Artists are currently struggling to maintain their practice in San Francisco. This collaboration marks Organic&rsquo;s efforts to sustain the arts in this city. We are excited to showcase Reza Ali&rsquo;s work at Organic.</p>\r\n<p>WHEN: Thursday, May 1, 2014 from 4:00 PM to 8:00 PM (PDT)<br />WHERE: Organic, 555 Market St., San Francisco, CA<br />WHO: You!&nbsp;<a href=\"http://adoptanartist.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Donate to RSVP</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/reza/\"><img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/eventlogos/1877435/rezaflyer01b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"727\" height=\"1078\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s going to be a casual gathering, join is anytime between 4-8pm</p>\r\n<p>04:00 PM&nbsp;~ Organic + CODAME Introductions</p>\r\n<p>04:10 PM&nbsp;~ Reza Introduction</p>\r\n<p>04:20 PM&nbsp;~ DJ IDEOMUX</p>\r\n<p>06:00 PM&nbsp;~ Organic + CODAME Introductions (for late arrivals)</p>\r\n<p>06:10 PM&nbsp;~ Reza Introduction (for late arrivals)</p>\r\n<p>06:20 PM&nbsp;~ C-REX live electronic music</p>\r\n<p>About Organic</p>\r\n<p>Organic is a leading marketing agency grounded in digital that successfully blends creativity with unmatched predictive intelligence. By creating and continuously testing and optimizing marketing systems, Organic helps global brands accurately predict outcomes, spot trends, identify behaviors, and create a much deeper connection with consumers. Founded in 1993, Organic has offices in New York, San Francisco, Los Angeles, Detroit and London and is part of Omnicom Group Inc.</p>\r\n<p>About Reza</p>\r\n<p>Reza is a new media artist and researcher. His work and research is centered around computational design, user interfaces, software studios, and wearables (hardware + software + form). As an artist, he uses technology (code, form and electronics) to express himself. His works manifest themselves as either visual art, spatial sculptures, and interactive installations. Reza is interested in the ideas and implications of his works, tools, and way of working. As a researcher, Reza is passionate about solving complex problems by creating new technologies and open sourcing them to allows others to build on his work and build the future. As an artist and researcher he is deeply interested in the feedback cycle that occurs when customs tools are written to accomplish an artwork, and how those tools can enable artworks to go beyond what the artist had originally envisioned. He hopes to change the world by making a difference in how people use technology, design products and experience new media art and entertainment.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/eventlogos/1877435/1047204817418711a8da2o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"755\" height=\"755\" /></p>\r\n<p>About the Series:</p>\r\n<p>Title: FluidScapes Prints</p>\r\n<p>Medium:&nbsp;Gloss Finished&nbsp;Aluminum Metal Prints Coated with Polyester</p>\r\n<p>About: FluidScapes are about making the invisible visible and the interplay of two generative systems. These images are snapshots in time of a&nbsp;simulated fluid field affecting the height of a generative terrain made from particles and springs. Custom software was used to simulate and visualize the generative systems interplay with each other in real-time. In this exhibition the FluidScapes have been rendered as prints, but they exist as digital files which can be 3D printed or CNC machined into FluidScape Sculptures.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/reza/\"><img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/eventlogos/1877435/codameadoptanartist0009reza02.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"190\" height=\"190\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/reza/\"><img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/eventlogos/1877435/codameadoptanartist0009reza03.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"191\" height=\"191\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/reza/\"><img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/eventlogos/1877435/codameadoptanartist0009reza04.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"191\" height=\"191\" /></a></p>', 'reza-ali,ideomux,c-rex', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-reza-ali-at-organic/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(35, 'Programmable LEDs by ANI (Amy Lee)', 'programmable-leds-by-ani-amy-lee', '2014-05-12', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/programmable-leds-by-ani-amy-lee.gif', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">Artist in Residence&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-musician-ani-amy-lee-aka-ani/\">ANI</a>&nbsp;presented a tech talk to the Rackspace team in the<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.geekdom.com/san-francisco\">Geekdom SF</a>&nbsp;offices about programmable LEDs, specifically the WS2812b LEDs that&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.adafruit.com/category/168\">come in fun shapes</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://rgb-123.com/shop/\">large matrices</a>. The hard stuff is taken care of by the Fadecandy&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Fadecandy hardware\" href=\"http://www.adafruit.com/products/1689\">hardware</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Fadecandy software\" href=\"https://github.com/scanlime/fadecandy\">software</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px; text-align: center;\"><iframe style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc; border-width: 1px 1px 0px; margin-bottom: 5px;\" src=\"http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/34643343\" width=\"427\" height=\"356\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px; margin-bottom: 5px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"LEDs Are Awesome - Amy Lee / ANI - CODAME\" href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/amster1/leds-are-awesome-amy-lee-ani-codame\" target=\"_blank\">LEDs Are Awesome &ndash; Amy Lee / ANI &ndash; CODAME</a>&nbsp;</span>from&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/amster1\" target=\"_blank\">ANI Lee</a></span></div>', 'ani', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/programmable-leds-fadecandy-presentation-by-ani-amy-lee/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(34, 'ART+TECH Rendezvous #1', 'art-tech-rendezvous-1', '2014-05-22', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-rendezvous-1.gif', '            \r\n						<p>We are happy to announce a new CODAME initiative, a regular monthly, playful, fun and inspiring event: <strong>ART+TECH Rendezvous <a title=\"@GeekdomSF\" href=\"http://twitter.com/GeekdomSF\">@GeekdomSF</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>WHEN</strong>: Thursday, May 22nd, 2014 from 6:00 PM to 10:00 PM (PDT)<br>\r\n<strong>WHERE</strong>: Geekdom, 620 Folsom St. #100, San Francisco, CA<br>\r\n<strong>WHO</strong>: Art + Tech lovers!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Guarantee your ticket, before it’s sold out, by making a donation on <a href=\"https://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com/\">https://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>Our first Rendezvous will be May 22nd, an evening starts with a GIF HAPPY HOUR together with artist <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-mike-hales/\">Mike Hales</a>‘s unique comic book style GIF animations, while grooving to the improvisational sounds of <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-thisissami/\">THISISSAMI</a>, a Vancouver based Ableton Live Looper/multimedia artist. It will follow up with an Ableton Live workshop  with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/lenny-kiser/\">Lenny Kiser</a>. We will close the evening with some more music and opportunity to play with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/gifslap-vj-software-for-people-who-love-gifs/\">gifSlap</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule for May 22, 2014</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote><p>06:00 – 07:00 pm: <b>GIF HAPPY HOUR</b>, Interactive gif art feat. the work of SF artist <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-mike-hales/\">Mike Hales</a> // electronic performance by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-thisissami/\">THISISSAMI</a> (Vancouver)</p>\r\n<p>07:00 – 09:00 pm: <strong>Workshop</strong> with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/lenny-kiser/\">Lenny Kiser</a> – Making Beats and Basslines with Ableton Live</p>\r\n<p>09:00 – 10:00 pm: <b>More</b> music //  social happy hour //  play time with the <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/gifslap-vj-software-for-people-who-love-gifs/\">gifSlap</a> VJ program.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>RSVP on <a href=\"https://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com/\">https://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com</a></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p><strong>Workshop with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/lenny-kiser/\">LENNY KISER </a>(San Francisco, CA)</strong><br>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-171\" title=\"Ableton_CT_logo_screen\" src=\"http://www.lennykiser.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/ableton_certified_trainer_logo_white_bg.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"53\"></p>\r\n<p>An introductory course to learn how to make original beats and music in Ableton Live.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Length: 2 Hours<br>\r\n<strong>Recommended Materials:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li>Laptop Computer</li>\r\n<li>Headphones</li>\r\n<li>Ableton Live 9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Free 30 Day trial version of Ableton Live 9 (<a title=\"Free 30 Day trial version of Ableton Live 9\" href=\"https://www.ableton.com/en/trial/\" target=\"_blank\">download</a>)<br>\r\n<b>Part 1: Creating Beats</b> (30 Mins)<br>\r\n<b>Activity</b>: Create your first beat with the 808 drum machine (10 Mins)</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li>Drum Programming and Drum Racks</li>\r\n<li>Learn the Interface and Navigation Tour</li>\r\n<li>What are Clips and Scenes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Part 2: Using Loops, Instruments and Effects</b> (30 Mins)<br>\r\n<b>Activity</b>: Write your first bass line, work with loops and get creative with audioeffects (10 Mins)</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li>Working with Loops</li>\r\n<li>Audio Effects</li>\r\n<li>Use Lives Instruments to write music</li>\r\n<li>Start putting the pieces together to make a song</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Activity</b>: Perform your song into the arrangement (10 Mins)<br>\r\n<b>Q&A and Review</b></p>\r\n<p>Reserve your ticket by making a donation on <a href=\"https://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com/\">https://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com</a></p>\r\n											          ', 'mike-hales,thisissami,lenny-kiser,spectrum-electric', 'gifslap', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/arttech-rendezvous-geekdomsf-may-22/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(36, 'DANCE+HACK @ CODAME', 'dance-hack-codame', '2014-05-31', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/dance-hack-codame.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">On Saturday, May 31st, 2014 As a featured part of <a title=\"CODAME ART+TECH Playground\" href=\"https://codame.com/events/art-tech-playground\">CODAME ART+TECH Playground</a>&nbsp;join us for DANCE+HACK with Kinetech Arts, Bay Area Tech-artists and dancers. With a fantastic evening performance series emceed by New Eccentrics, this hack day will explore the future of art/tech interaction by expanding the tools available to artists to capture and transform movement. Come see the artist-of-tomorrow redefine what art and performance can be in a new virtual world!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>SCHEDULE</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br /> 10:00 AM&nbsp;-&nbsp;Registration/Mixer<br /> 10:30 AM&nbsp;- Welcome/Introductions<br /> 11:00 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;- Hack start<br /> 01:00 PM&nbsp;- Isadora and interactive media dance workshop with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ian-winters/\">Ian Winters</a><br /> 02:00 PM - Openframeworks in dance workshop with Weidong Yang from <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech Arts</a><br /> 03:00 PM&nbsp;- GLSL WebGL and livecoding workshop with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/florian-hoenig\">Florian Hoenig</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"k:%20http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/chris-birke\" target=\"_blank\">Chris Birke</a><a href=\"k:%20http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/chris-birke\" target=\"_blank\"><br /> </a>07:00 PM&nbsp;- Open Bar<br /> 08:00 PM&nbsp;- Demos<br /> <a title=\"ART+TECH Playground\" href=\"https://codame.com/events/art-tech-playground\">ART+TECH Playground</a> continues</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>CONFIRMED ARTISTS</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"/admin/www.calidance.info/\" target=\"_blank\">Christine Cali</a><br /><a href=\"/admin/daiane-sf.tumblr.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Daiane Lopes da Silva</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/david-glowacki/\">David Glowacki</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ian-winters/\" target=\"_blank\">Ian Winters</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech Arts</a><br /><a href=\"http://nosuch.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Tim Thompson</a><br /><a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/nicolezvarik/\" target=\"_blank\">Nicole Zvarik</a><br /><a href=\"http://welcomemattsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Matt Langlois</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In Parnership with&nbsp;<br /><a href=\"http://www.hackreactor.com/\">Hack Reactor</a><br /><a href=\"https://tessel.io/\">Tessel.io</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>WORKSHOPS / TECHNOLOGY</strong></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<div>01:00 AM&nbsp;- Workshop w/ Isadora and interactive media dance with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ian-winters/\">Ian Winters<br /> </a>02:30 PM&nbsp;- Workshop w/ Weidong Yang on Openframeworks<br /> 03:00 PM&nbsp;- Workshop w/&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/florian-hoenig\">Florian Hoenig </a>and <a href=\"k:%20http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/chris-birke\" target=\"_blank\">Chris Birke </a>on GLSL WebGL and livecoding</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><br /> <strong>LOCATION</strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>80 Turk St.,<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=+&amp;q=80+turk+st+sf&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=80+Turk+St,+San+Francisco,+California+94109&amp;t=m&amp;z=16&amp;vpsrc=0\" target=\"_blank\">San Francisco, CA 94109</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br /><img src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/api/staticmap?size=300x300&amp;maptype=roadmap&amp;sensor=false&amp;markers=color:red%7C37.783361,-122.410403&amp;client=google-maps-sharing&amp;signature=X3MdpZXt6eln_Wsn63B9oD4asmE=\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>FAQ</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Who should attend?</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>Dancers<br /> This is an great opportunity to explore how movement interact with technology to expand performance possibilities. Hack n Dance!</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>Coders<br /> Tech ninjas, game programmers, and hackers. Come to hack sensors, algorithms and interactivity with a moving body.</div>\r\n<div><br /> Artists<br /> People making things look beautiful, sound amazing. Shall we say visual and audio hacking?</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Enthusiasts</div>\r\n<div>Love ART+TECH?&nbsp; Curious about all the hype? Come check out what all the fuss is about!</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">What should I bring?</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>This is a very hands-on and grassroots event. Bring your dance shoes, laptops, mobile phones, Kinects, Oculus Rifts, Leap Motions, wearable computing devices, to whatever inspires you but above all, your energy and your brain! Don\'t worry if you forget something, there will be tons of stuff to do.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">What\'s the goal of the day?</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>We want to create an environment that embraces new ideas and technology solutions for the intersection of dance and technology.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">How do I form or join a team and why?</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>The goal is more along discovering the connection between technology and dancer rather than creating new technology. In this hack day we encourage teams to use pre-build technologies. We do encourage participants to start forming teams before the event.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">Would you or your organization like to support ?</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>CODAME events are made possible thanks to&nbsp;<a href=\"/contribute\">volunteers</a>, event <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\">donation </a>tickets and <a href=\"/sponsors\">sponsors</a>.We welcome the opportunity for you to join us in a collaborative relationship with support, either financial or in-kind, to continue raising the bar of what\'s possible at the nexus of ART+TECH. Any bits or pixel counts!</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<p>Can I make a nonprofit&nbsp; Tax Deductible Donation?</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Yes! We are members of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://theintersection.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Intersection for the Arts</a>, a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, which allows us to offer you tax deductions for your contributions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://donatenow.networkforgood.org/1442843\">Donate Now!</a>&nbsp;Make sure to select CODAME ART+TECH as the designated donation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</blockquote>', 'kinetech-arts,christine-cali,daiane-lopes-da-silva,david-glowacki,ian-winters,tim-thompson,nicole-zvarik,matt-langlois,florian-hoenig', '', '', 'counterpulse', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(96, 'Augmented Reality Art', 'workshop-augmented-reality-art', '2019-10-26', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/workshop-augmented-reality-art.gif', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Artivive with Angeli Clarisse Lata</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2019-space\" target=\"_blank\">October 26th</a>&nbsp;@&nbsp;GitHub San Francisco</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://codame.eventbrite.com?aff=dotcom#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"Eventbrite - ART+TECH Festival [2018]\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Bring your artwork to life with a smartphone! Join <span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; caret-color: #000000;\">Angeli Clarisse Lata</span>&nbsp;for this hands-on&nbsp;Augmented Reality Workshop. Discover the ARTIVIVE platform and create your own interactive AR experiences.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">ARTIVIVE works with 7 international museums including 150 exhibitions, 9.000 artworks and 2 million views worldwide. The platform has become as fundamental to artists in the 21st century (both professional and casual) as the canvas and the brush.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Workshops focus on &ldquo;constructive or destructive&rdquo; strategies and visual narratives allowing artists to quickly iterate AR concepts then generate high-resolution results rendered in the cloud. Attendees will engage in a process of iterative image generation and capture. They will apply 2D or 3D AR to original content using built-in network effects from the large install base. Each participant will receive an ARTIVIVE account with 15 free projects ($250 value).</p>\r\n<p>After 5 pm the images will be printed and augmented reality art showcased &ndash; transforming the training room into an interactive experience. Saturday Night at CODAME&nbsp;<strong style=\"text-align: center;\">ART+TECH Festival 2019&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2019-space\">ã€Ž&nbsp;SPACE&nbsp;ã€</a>&nbsp;</strong>visitors will be invited to download the ARTIVIVE application on their smartphones to interact with the AR developed in the workshop.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>SKILL LEVEL</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">No technical experience required. You will be guided every step of the way.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>WHAT TO BRING</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Laptop running MacOS or Windows</li>\r\n<li>Mobile device (works on both Android and Apple iOS platforms)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>SOFTWARE TO BE INSTALLED</strong></p>\r\n<p>ARTIVIVE app (<a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/artivive/id1188737494\" target=\"_blank\">iOS App Store</a>, <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.artivive&amp;hl=en_US\" target=\"_blank\">Android Google Play</a>)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Get your tickets while still available for an extraordinary learning experience.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://codame.eventbrite.com?aff=dotcom#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"Eventbrite - ART+TECH Festival [2018]\" /></a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>This workshop is part of&nbsp;CODAME&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong><a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2019-space\">ART+TECH Festival 2019 ã€Ž&nbsp;SPACE&nbsp;ã€</a>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Space_9.3_banner_S_.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'angeli-clarisse-lata', 'art-tech-festival-2019-space', '', 'artivive', '', '', '0', 'workshop', NULL, NULL),
(37, 'Bring Your Own Beamer', 'bring-your-own-beamer', '2014-05-31', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/bring-your-own-beamer.gif', '\r\n						<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em style=\"color: #505050;\">Lights off for <a href=\"http://www.byobworldwide.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Bring Your Own Beamer</a></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em style=\"color: #505050;\">May 31 2014  </em><em style=\"color: #505050;\">as part of the </em><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" title=\"CODAME ART+TECH Playground\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/playground/\">CODAME Playground</a><span style=\"color: #505050;\"> @ the Doll House, 80 Turk, SF.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong> WHAT IS BYOB?</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #111111;\">BYOB (Bring Your Own Beamer) is a series of one-night-exhibitions hosting artists and their projectors. BYOB is a series of one-night-exhibitions curated by different people around the world. The idea is simple: Find a place, invite many artists, ask them to bring their projectors.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #111111;\">BYOB is a way of making a huge show with zero budget. It is also an exploration of the medium of projection.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #111111;\"><img src=\"http://katjanovi.net/byob/byoblogo_black.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"413\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #111111;\"><strong>Who created BYOB?</strong><br>\r\nBYOB is an idea by <a style=\"color: #111111;\" href=\"http://www.byobworldwide.com/\">Rafaël Rozendaal</a>. The first edition of BYOB was initiated by <a style=\"color: #111111;\" href=\"http://www.annedevries.info/\">Anne de Vries</a> & Rafael Rozendaal in Berlin.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #111111;\"><strong>What does BYOB mean?</strong><br>\r\nBYOB is an acronym for “Bring Your Own Beamer”. In Europe projectors are often referred to as “beamers”.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How many artists should I invite to my BYOB?</strong><br>\r\nThe more the better.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Can anyone with a projector just walk in and join the exhibition?</strong><br>\r\nRSVP on <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com\">codame.eventbrite.com</a></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=10560014287&ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"630\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong>Why BYOB?</strong><br>\r\nBYOB is a celebration of the new world we live in and a glimpse of what computing could look like in the future. Today the internet is confined to screens. Tomorrow information will surround us, composing our surfaces, defining our spaces, enmeshing itself with the ether. A moving image is never an object, and when it is coupled with the increased flexibility of portable projection, the realm of experience quickly expands.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Is BYOB only for internet artists?</strong><br>\r\nNo! BYOB is for anyone who is interested in moving light, sound and performance. Projection can mean many things. Projections are very flexible and create a freedom to react to each others works, move things around, and create a dynamic collaborative experience. Hopefully there will be many different kinds of BYOB’s.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Are there any rules?</strong><br>\r\nBYOB should be easy, fun & no stress.</p>\r\n<p>Rafaël Rozendaal, 2010 – 2012</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #111111;\">More information on <a href=\"http://www.byobworldwide.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.byobworldwide.com</a></p>\r\n											', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/bring-your-own-beamer/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(38, 'SHADOWTRAVEL US Tour 2014 (SF)', 'shadowtravel-us-tour-2014-sf', '2014-05-31', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/shadowtravel-us-tour-2014-sf.gif', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is hosting the <a href=\"http://www.shadowtravel.radiograffiti.org/\" target=\"_blank\">SHADOWTRAVEL</a> US Tour 2014 ï¿½in San Francisco</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em style=\"color: #505050;\">May 31 2014 ï¿½</em><em style=\"color: #505050;\">as part of theï¿½</em><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" title=\"CODAME ART+TECH Playground\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/playground/\">CODAME Playground</a><span style=\"color: #505050;\">ï¿½@ the Doll House, 80 Turk, SF.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #141823;\">Nullsleep, Starpause, and Stagediver will be conducting a nationwide tour from May 31 ï¿½ June 7 to coincide with their recent 7&Prime; releases on Radiograffiti. A week long series of sonic strikes across the United States, hitting key targets in San Francisco, Los Angeles, Milwauke</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"color: #141823;\">e, Chicago, New York, and Philadelphia. Supplemental release parties bookend the tour in Austin and Minneapolis.</span></p>\r\n<p>Copies of the Nullsleep / Starpause split 7&Prime; Shadowtravel and Stagediverï¿½s III will be available on all dates. Limited to 500 copies Shadowtravel features art by Videogrammo in a custom tri-fold hand-assembled package designed by Mikrosopht and Minusbaby.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"color: #141823;\"><em>#SHADOWTRAVEL<br /> </em><br /> </span></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=10560014287&amp;ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"640\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></p>', 'nullsleep,jordan-gray,stagediver', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(39, 'ART+TECH Playground', 'art-tech-playground', '2014-05-31', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-playground-may-31-2014.gif', '<header>\r\n<div>CODAME in transforming the Doll House, future home of CounterPULSE in the Tenderloin, into a vibrant playground for ART + TECH enthusiasts and practitioners. Join us, anytime during the day, for a playful day full of ART+TECH activities, live performances, workshops, electronic music, and interactive projections. Come play with CODAME while supporting artists and the community!</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<article id=\"post-3080\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>On Saturday, May 31st, 2014 join&nbsp;<a href=\"/\">CODAME</a>&nbsp;in transforming the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://counterpulse.org/new-home/\" target=\"_blank\">Doll House</a>, future home of&nbsp;CounterPULSE&nbsp;in the Tenderloin, into a vibrant playground for ART + TECH enthusiasts and practitioners. Join us, anytime during the day, for a&nbsp;playful day full of ART+TECH activities, live performances, workshops, electronic music, and interactive projections. Come play with CODAME while supporting artists and the community!</p>\r\n<p>10:00 AM&nbsp;&ndash; Open Doors<br />10:30 AM&nbsp;&ndash; Start to&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/dance-hack-codame\" target=\"_blank\">DANCE+HACK</a><br />01:00 PM&nbsp;&ndash; Isadora and interactive media dance workshop with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ian-winters/\">Ian Winters</a><br />02:00 PM&nbsp;&ndash; Openframeworks in dance workshop with Weidong Yang from&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech Arts</a><br />03:00 PM&nbsp;&ndash; GLSL WebGL and livecoding workshop with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/florian-hoenig\">Florian Hoenig</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/chris-birke\" target=\"_blank\">Chris Birke</a><br />07:00 PM&nbsp;&ndash; Open Bar<br />08:00 PM&nbsp;&ndash; Demos of&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/dance-hack-codame\" target=\"_blank\">DANCE+HACK</a>&nbsp;projects<br />08:45&nbsp;PM&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/led-ecstatic-ephiphany-innaguration/\">Ecstatic Epiphany</a>&nbsp;interactive LED installation&nbsp;opening ceremony<br />09:00 PM&nbsp;&ndash; Lights off for&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/bring-your-own-beamer/\">Bring Your Own Beamer</a>&nbsp;(BYOB)<br />09:00 PM&nbsp;&ndash; Live electronic music by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/datatwins\" target=\"_blank\">Datatwins</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/starpause\" target=\"_blank\">staRpauSe</a>,<a href=\"https://twitter.com/nullsleep\" target=\"_blank\">Nullsleep</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/__TSC_\" target=\"_blank\">Stagediver</a>&nbsp;as part of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/shadowtravel-us-tour-2014-sf/\">SHADOWTRAVEL</a>&nbsp;US tour 2014&nbsp;(SF)</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Nullpause-First-Look-Crop.jpg\" alt=\"7inch release goodies\" /></p>\r\n<p>Splurge and reserve a limited (50 copies) Glow In The Dark screen printed version of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/shadowtravel-us-tour-2014-sf/\">SHADOWTRAVEL 7&Prime; record</a>&nbsp;by getting an&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">eventbrite ticket</a>.</p>\r\n<p>FREE FOR ALL TO ENJOY: We will be also unveiling the &ldquo;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ecstatic-ephiphany/\">Ecstatic Epiphany</a>&rdquo; LED Interactive&nbsp;installation at 8:45PM from CODAME Featured Artist&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/qa-with-codame-featured-artist-micah-elizabeth-scott/\">Micah Elizabeth Scott</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ecstatic-ephiphany/\"><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ei-frame-1.png\" alt=\"ei-frame-1\" width=\"1500\" height=\"844\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>This ticket will also include the opportunity to&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codedancehack-at-the-codame-playground/\">code, dance and hack</a>&nbsp;with Kinetech Arts, other Bay Area Tech-artists for a day of&nbsp;playful exploratory environment.This is non-profit event of artists and technologists in the bay&nbsp;shaping the future of what online interaction could be.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codedancehack-at-the-codame-playground/\"><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Vigil_white-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"Ian winters\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Have questions about CODAME ART+TECH PLAYGROUND?&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/codame-arttech-playground-tickets-10560014287\">Contact CODAME ART+TECH</a></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Facade_01.jpg\" alt=\"Facade_01\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" /></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://counterpulse.org/new-home/\" target=\"_blank\">Doll House</a>, future home of&nbsp;CounterPULSE&nbsp;in the Tenderloin.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><img src=\"https://evbdn.eventbrite.com/s3-s3/eventlogos/1877435/80turk600x372.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"834\" height=\"517\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</article>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'ian-winters,kinetech-arts,florian-hoenig,chris-birke,datawins,nullsleep,stagediver,micah-scott,jordan-gray', 'ecstatic-epiphany', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(106, 'Recoding CripTech', 'recoding-criptech', '2020-01-23', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/recoding-criptech.png', '<div data-id=\"6b13cf97\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"><center><strong>Recoding CripTech</strong><br />Opening reception, Thursday, January 23, 2020, 6&ndash;9pm<br />Exhibition run, Friday January 24&ndash;Tuesday, February 25, 2020<br />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Curated by Vanessa Chang and Lindsey D. Felt,&nbsp;Recoding CripTech&nbsp;reimagines enshrined notions of what a body can be or do through creative technologies, and how it can move, look, or communicate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Working with a broad understanding of technology, from prosthetic tools to the built environment, this multidisciplinary community art exhibition explores how disability&mdash;and artists who identify as such&mdash;can redefine design, aesthetics, and the relationship between user and interface. Exhibiting artists engage with technology in manifold ways from conception to production and beyond. As the term &ldquo;crip&rdquo; reclaims the word for disability culture and recognizes disability as a cultural and political identity, so too do artists hack technologies to make them more accessible and inclusive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&ldquo;In academic circles and in the disability community, there is a recognition that people with disabilities have profoundly contributed to technological advancement, but we would like to nurture these conversations in public discourse and spaces,&rdquo; say Chang and Felt. &ldquo;Rather, technology is often held up as something of a cure for disability, instead of an ongoing dialogue between diverse bodies, abilities, and communities. While we&rsquo;ve seen art and technology shows, and disability shows, we haven&rsquo;t seen an exhibition that embodies the living interaction of these communities in the Bay Area.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">By cripping the camera&rsquo;s gaze,&nbsp;Todd Herman&nbsp;asks us to reevaluate how we look at others. Spanning organic and virtual prostheses,&nbsp;M Eifler,&nbsp;Chun-shan&nbsp;(Sandie Yi), and&nbsp;Jillian Crochet&nbsp;make visible the private, and intimate lives of disability that intertwine care and memory.&nbsp;Jennifer Justice&nbsp;reveals built space as a technological incarnation of access and privilege, inviting us to reorient our relationship to these spaces.&nbsp;Sara Hendren, Alice Sheppard,&nbsp;and&nbsp;TEMPT ONE&nbsp;recreate urban spaces and movement through unexpected mediums.&nbsp;Darrin Martin&nbsp;and&nbsp;Allison Leigh Holt&nbsp;formulate a crip eco-consciousness that situates prosthetic technologies in natural environments and landscapes, and&nbsp;Sonia Soberats&nbsp;and&nbsp;Pete Eckert&nbsp;redefine the relationship of sight, touch, perception and the image.<br /><br />Together, these artists inscribe new movements and navigations through private, public, virtual, and natural spaces and places.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&ldquo;We&rsquo;d like our audiences to reflect on and question for whom technologies and spaces are built, and to whom they deny access. By engaging a variety of senses in their interactions with museum spaces and artworks, we hope for them to understand how certain bodies have been privileged over others,&rdquo; shares Chang and Felt.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Opening with a free, all ages reception on&nbsp;Thursday, January 23, 6&ndash;9pm, the evening program features an artist panel discussion and Q&amp;A, led by disability scholar and UC Berkeley professor&nbsp;Karen Nakamura&nbsp;featuring&nbsp;disability activist and&nbsp;Disability Visibility&nbsp;host,&nbsp;Alice Wong.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Berkeley professor of English and disability studies scholar&nbsp;Georgina Kleege&nbsp;will guide participants throughout the exhibition with tactile and sensory aesthetic experiences with&nbsp;Tactile Explorations&nbsp;on&nbsp;Thursday, February 6, 6&ndash;9pm.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Recoding CripTech&nbsp;closes with&nbsp;Neurodivergent Media Workshop&nbsp;Thursday, February 20, 6&ndash;9pm&nbsp;facilitated by exhibiting artist and educator&nbsp;&nbsp;Allison Leigh Holt. Together, participants will develop scripts, learn storyboarding techniques, and stage scenes.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">RECODING CRIPTECH</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Exhibiting Artists</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Jillian Crochet</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Pete Eckert&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">M Eifler aka BlinkPopShift &amp; Steve Sedlmayr</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Sara Hendren</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Todd Herman</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Allison Leigh Holt</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Jennifer Justice</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Darrin Martin</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">TEMPT ONE</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Sonia Soberats&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Chun-shan (Sandie) Yi&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Alice Sheppard, in collaboration with Katherine Helen Fisher, Shimmy Boyle, Laurel Lawson, Lisa Niedermeyer, and Missy Mazzoli</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Yevgeniya Zastavker, and Katie Butler, Daniel Daugherty, Duncan Hall, Andrew Holmes, Erica Lee, Scott Mackinlay, Apurva Raman, March Saper, Alexander Scott, Kimberly Winter, Rachel Yang, Jingyi Xu, with support from Olin College.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Opening Reception Artist Panel &amp; Discussion</strong><br />Thursday, January 23, 6&ndash;9pm<br />Artist panel discussion and Q&amp;A, led by disability scholar and UC Berkeley professor Karen Nakamura and featuring disability activist and&nbsp;Disability Visibility&nbsp;host, Alice Wong, performer and producer Claudia Alick, and exhibiting artists Darrin Martin and M Eifler aka BlinkPopShift. The panel will be recorded and uploaded to Wong&rsquo;s podcast.&nbsp; To learn more visit&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.somarts.org/events/recodingcriptechopening\">somarts.org/events/recodingcriptechopening</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 600; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">Tactile Explorations</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Thursday, February 6, 6&ndash;9pm</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Led by disability studies scholar Georgina Kleege, participants will explore the exhibition through tactile and sensory aesthetic experiences. This program is limited to 12 participants, Eventbrite link and wait list to follow. To learn more visit&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background: 0px 0px transparent; color: #d04349; text-decoration-line: none; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; box-shadow: none;\" href=\"https://www.somarts.org/events/tactileexplorations\">somarts.org/events/tactileexplorations</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Neurodivergent Media Workshop</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Thursday, February 20, 6&ndash;9pm</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Participants join exhibiting artist and educator Allison Leigh Holt to develop develop scripts, learn storyboarding techniques, and stage scenes. This workshop is limited to 10 participants, Eventbrite link to follow. To learn more visit&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background: 0px 0px transparent; color: #d04349; text-decoration-line: none; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; box-shadow: none;\" href=\"https://www.somarts.org/events/neurodivergent\">somarts.org/events/neurodivergent</a></p>\r\n</center></div>', 'blinkpopshift,vanessa-chang', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(40, 'ART+TECH Rendezvous #2', 'art-tech-rendezvous-2', '2014-06-26', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-rendezvous-2.jpg', '                        \r\n						<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>WHEN</strong>: Thursday, June 26th, 2014 from 6:00 PM to 10:00 PM (PDT)<br>\r\n<strong>WHERE</strong>: <a href=\"http://twitter.com/GeekdomSF\" target=\"_blank\">@GeekdomSF</a>, 620 Folsom St. #100, San Francisco, CA<br>\r\n<strong>WHO</strong>: Art + Tech lovers!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">RSVP on <a href=\"https://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com/\">artrendezvous.eventbrite.com</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>SCHEDULE</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>6-7:00: </b>GIF Happy Hour</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">We’ll kick off the evening featuring GIF art by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/jonathan\">Jonathan Wallraven</a> and the Electronic performance by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ideomux/\">idmx</a>, and an opportunity to play with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/gifslap-vj-software-for-people-who-love-gifs/\">gifSlap</a>!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>7-8:30: </b>Art+Tech enlightening talks from <a href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\">CODAME Adopted Artists</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Learn and meet the team behind three exceptional projects adopted by organizations <a href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\">supporting Art+Tech</a></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li>“<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ecstatic-ephiphany/\">Ecstatic Epiphany</a>” w/ <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/micah/\">Micah Elizabeth Scott</a> (adopted by <a href=\"http://CounterPULSE.org\" target=\"_blank\">CounterPULSE</a>)</li>\r\n<li>“GIF Video Booth” w/ <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/jonathan\">Jonathan Wallraven</a> (adopted by <a href=\"http://Rackspace.com\" target=\"_blank\">Rackspace</a>)</li>\r\n<li>“<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ardent-mobile-cloud-platform/\">Ardent Mobile Cloud Platform</a>”  w/ Ian Baker (adopted by <a href=\"http://www.calacademy.org/\" target=\"_blank\">California Academy of Science</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>8:30+: </b>Networking / Social / Music and more play time w/ <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/the-spectrum-electric-codame-featured/\">Spectrum Electric</a> DJ set</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Limited quantity available, so reserve yours before they’re gone!</p>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; text-align: left;\"><iframe src=\"//eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=11536587243&ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"370\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></div>\r\n											                    ', 'jonathan-wallraven,ideomux,micah-scott,spectrum-electric,ian-baker', 'gifslap,ecstatic-epiphany,ardent-mobile-cloud-platform', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/arttech-rendezvous-geekdomsf-june-26th/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(41, 'THE OTHER SIGHT: AN EXPLORATION ON SURVEILLANCE', 'the-other-sight-an-exploration-on-surveillance', '2014-07-19', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/the-other-sight-an-exploration-on-surveillance.jpg', '\r\n						<p>CODAME Featured Artist: <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech Arts</a> presents the premiere of  THE OTHER SIGHT: AN EXPLORATION ON SURVEILLANCE</p>\r\n<p><em>“Best Genre Defying Sci-Artistic Collaborative in San Francisco.”</em> -SF Weekly</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Tickets\" href=\"https://app.arts-people.com/index.php?actions=22&p=2\">BUY TICKETS</a></p>\r\n<p>Choreography by Daiane Lopes da Silva in collaboration with Becky Robinson-Leviton, Colin Epstein, Katherine Disenhof, Irene Hsiao, Qinmin Liu, and Priscilla Park</p>\r\n<p>Technology by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/weidong-yang/\">Weidong Yang</a></p>\r\n<p>Visual Art by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-charlie-levin-charlie-is/\">Charlie Levin</a> and Raymond Larrett</p>\r\n<p>Original music by Robert Edgar, Robin Edgar and Jean Tarantino</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n											', 'kinetech-arts,weidong-yang,charlie-levin,raymond-larrett,robert-edgar,robin-edgar', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/the-other-sight-an-exploration-on-surveillance/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(42, 'LED Pixel Art Workshop with Al Linke', 'led-pixel-art-workshop-with-al-linke', '2014-06-18', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/led-pixel-art-workshop-with-al-linke.gif', '\r\n						<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">This workshop is part of our <span style=\"color: #000000;\">Monthly <a title=\"CODAME ART+TECH Rendezvous\" href=\"http://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">ART+TECH Rendezvous</a> curated by CODAME staff, happening <a href=\"http://twitter.com/GeekdomSF\" target=\"_blank\">@GeekdomSF</a>. The series focuses on contemporary art and tech artists, electro-music and performance, mixing and networking, electronic improvisation, artistic inspiration, and play time.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4835\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/RendezvousBanner1.png\" alt=\"Art Rendezvous\" width=\"841\" height=\"208\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/al-linke/\">Al Linke</a> is the creator of an LED display for art and advertising called <a href=\"http://ledpixelart.com/\"><span class=\"s1\">PIXEL</span></a>, a successfully crowd funded project. With it’s ultra-bright LEDs, the effect is quite unique. And unlike other LED displays, PIXEL can be programmed from the ease of an Android phone.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">During the workshop, Al will give a brief talk on how PIXEL came to be including an overview of what pixel art is and how he collaborated with 12 pixel artists to create the content for PIXEL. Al will unveil a new piece called “<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BV2cUweLCio\"><span class=\"s1\">Signs of Temptation</span></a>” during the talk. After the talk, you are welcome to stick around and create your own pixel art using your Android phone and display it on PIXEL. There will be a few extra Android devices available for those without an Android. Feel free to download the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ledpixelart.pixelesque\"><span class=\"s1\">pixel art editor Android app</span></a> now and start creating as well as the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ledpixelart.piledriver\"><span class=\"s1\">app for PIXEL’s built in content</span></a> and then send to PIXEL during the workshop.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Limited quantity available, so <a href=\"http://artrendezvous.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\">reserve</a> yours before they’re gone.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">PIXEL comes in two sizes:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li>PIXEL: 1,024 multi-color LEDs / 32×32 resolution, dimensions 7.5” x 7.5” x 1.5”</li>\r\n<li>SUPER PIXEL: 4,096 multi-color LEDs / 64×64 resolution, dimensions 16.5” x 16.5” x .1.5”</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">More info about PIXEL on <span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://ledpixelart.com/\">ledpixelart.com</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Cidc6k3EwKM?rel=0\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>PIXEL LED Art | Carl Douglas | Argyle | USA</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/BV2cUweLCio?rel=0\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>Signs of Temptation” by Jacob Giordano (King*Kaiju) at the Kaleid Art Gallery in San Jose, CA</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong style=\"color: #000000;\">/// SATISFACTION GUARANTEE</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We organize this group to promote art and the intersection of technology. If you purchase a ticket and aren’t happy with the experience, can’t make it, or decide that you don’t want to support the CODAME for any reason, We are happy to refund your money. Please note that if you do need to cancel your reservation, we request that you do so at least 24 hours before the event so that the tickets can be shared with others who may be waiting.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Us</a></p>\r\n											', 'al-linke', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/led-pixel-art-workshop/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(43, 'ART+TECH Rendezvous #3', 'art-tech-rendezvous-3', '2014-07-18', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-rendezvous-3.gif', '\r\n						<p>Monthly series curated by CODAME staff, happening @GeekdomSF. The series focuses on contemporary art and tech artists, electro-music and performance, mixing and networking, electronic improvisation, artistic inspiration, and play time.</p><p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>/// SCHEDULE</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>6-7:00: GIF Happy Hour</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">We’ll kick off the evening with an electronic music set by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/william-s-braintree-codame-featured-musician/\">William S. Braintree</a> and an opportunity to play with <a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/gifslap-vj-software-for-people-who-love-gifs/\">gifSlap</a>! Our featured Gif Artist for the month is <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/doctor-popular/\">Doctor Popular</a>, with his <a href=\"http://www.missionmission.org/author/doctor-popular/\"><em>3D City</em></a> series of gifs.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>7-8:30: Art+Tech enlightening talks or play time</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">LED Pixel Art Workshop with <a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/led-pixel-art-workshop/\">Al Linke</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">8<strong>:30+: Networking / Social / Music</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">More play time w/ <a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/the-spectrum-electric-codame-featured/\">Spectrum Electric</a> DJ set</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>/// CONNECT</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://instagram.com/codame\">#CODAME</a> • <a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\">CODAME ART+TECH Facebook</a> • <a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://twitter.com/CODA_ME\">@CODA_ME</a></p>\r\n<p>Limited quantity available, so reserve yours before they’re gone!</p>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; text-align: left;\"><iframe src=\"//eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=12112160799&ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></div>\r\n<p><strong style=\"color: #000000;\">/// SATISFACTION GUARANTEE</strong> We organize this group to promote art and the intersection of technology. If you purchase a ticket and aren’t happy with the experience, can’t make it, or decide that you don’t want to support the CODAME for any reason, We are happy to refund your money. Please note that if you do need to cancel your reservation, we request that you do so at least 24 hours before the event so that the tickets can be shared with others who may be waiting. <a style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2em; text-decoration: none; color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Us</a></p>\r\n											', 'doctor-popular,william-s-braintree,al-linke,spectrum-electric', 'gifslap', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/rendezvous-july-18th/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(44, '@ Rackspace::Solve After-Party', 'rackspace-solve-after-party', '2014-07-28', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/rackspace-solve-after-party.png', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our ART+TECH friends Rackspace is hosting a party!</strong><br /> Not in the clouds! Not Virtual! At Geekdom San Francisco in 620 Folsom.<a href=\"/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3200\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/LeBook_CatalogBanner_01.jpg\" alt=\"LeBook_CatalogBanner_01\" width=\"920\" height=\"92\" /></a>Look out for the following Artists and their projects up for <a href=\"/adopt\">Adoption</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Join CODAMEï¿½for the Rackspace::Solve after-party.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/rackspacesolve-after-party-tickets-12270277731\">RSVP for Entrance</a>&nbsp;(FREE)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Monday, July 28, at 6:30 to 9:30</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">at 620 Folsom (btw 2nd &amp; 3rd st)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">a short walk from the St. Regis Hotel where the <a href=\"http://RackspaceSolve.com\">Rackspace::Solve</a> summit is being held.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Mix and mingle with our friends, partners and speakers from Solve, including CoreOS, Docker, New Relic, Wepay and many more. Also on site are the Rackspace leadership team and engineers behind great projects like: OnMetal, Mailgun, Airbrake, and ObjectRocket.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Dinner will be served along with delicious cocktails. Explore interactive art, challenge a peer to poker, meet special guests and listen to local CODAME DJs as we celebrate the best of our industry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is also an opportunity to meet the companies &amp; members part of <a href=\"http://geekdomsf.com\">Geekdom</a>, an active startup community located in the Rackspace office in San Francisco.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-4803\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/gif_pixel.gif\" alt=\"led pixel art\" width=\"919\" height=\"919\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>', 'kinetech-arts,ani,angat-gaada,donald-hanson,al-linke,jonathan-wallraven,jordan-gray', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(45, 'CODAME @ NightLife LIVE Illuminate', 'codame-nightlife-live-illuminate', '2014-08-07', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-ardent-at-the-california-academy-of-sciences.jpg', '<p>Join the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://amcp.ardentheavyindustries.com/\">Ardent</a>&nbsp;Mobile Cloud Platform at the California&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.calacademy.org/events/nightlife/\">Academy of Sciences</a>&nbsp;Nightlife Illuminate&nbsp;event presented by&nbsp;<a href=\"/\">CODAME</a>&nbsp;ART+TECH in support of&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href=\"/adopt\">Adopt an Artist</a>&nbsp;program.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12920212525_96630bd49d_o.jpg\" alt=\"Burning Man 2013\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1001\" /></p>\r\n<p>Featuring musicians from Outside Lands and light art including an inflatable glowing forest and the&nbsp;Ardent&nbsp;Mobile Cloud.</p>\r\n<p>Play conductor as you take control of the Cloud&rsquo;s cutting-edge LED and sound effects, creating an orchestra of sunsets, lightning storms, and thunder with the touch of a button.</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;re excited to announce that aerialist Lyra Levin will give an exciting aerial performance suspended from the Cloud. Along with her aerial artistry, Lyra was one of the main engineers of the Cloud itself.</p>\r\n<p>To RSVP, visit the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.calacademy.org/events/nightlife/\">Cal Academy&rsquo;s event page</a></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/photo4.jpg\" alt=\"photo4\" width=\"605\" height=\"325\" /> <img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/photo8.jpg\" alt=\"photo8\" width=\"605\" height=\"325\" /></p>', 'ian-baker', 'ardent-mobile-cloud-platform', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/join-codame-ardent-at-the-california-academy-of-sciences/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(46, 'ART+TECH Rendezvous #4', 'art-tech-rendezvous-4', '2014-08-15', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-rendezvous-4.gif', '<p><strong>/// SCHEDULE</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>6-7:00: GIF Happy Hour</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ll kick off the evening with an electronic music set by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/tracer-aka-chris-osborn\" rel=\"nofollow\">TR/\\CER</a>, and GIFs by our featured artist <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/joel-cretan/\">Joel Cretan</a>, running in the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/gifslap-vj-software-for-people-who-love-gifs/\" rel=\"nofollow\">gifSlap</a>&nbsp;interactive installation.</p>\r\n<p>7-8:30: Art+Tech enlightening talks or play time</p>\r\n<p>Playtime with projects open for <a href=\"/adopt\">adoption</a>:</p>\r\n<p>Live 3D scanning and Interactive GIF Booth &ldquo;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/technopticon/\">TechnOpticon</a>&ldquo;</p>\r\n<p>8:30+: Networking / Social / Music and</p>\r\n<p>More play time w/&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/the-spectrum-electric-codame-featured/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Spectrum Electric</a>&nbsp;DJ set</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>/// CONNECT</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://instagram.com/codame\">#CODAME</a>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\">CODAME ART+TECH Facebook</a>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/CODA_ME\">@CODA_ME</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>/// ART+TECH SATISFACTION GUARANTEE</strong></p>\r\n<p>We organize this group to promote art and the intersection of technology. If you purchase a ticket and aren&rsquo;t happy with the experience, can&rsquo;t make it, or decide that you don&rsquo;t want to support the CODAME for any reason, We are happy to refund your money. Please note that if you do need to cancel your reservation, we request that you do so at least 24 hours before the event so that the tickets can be shared with others who may be waiting.Thank you for the&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0083b9;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support</a>.</p>', 'tr-923-cer,joel-cretan,spectrum-electric', 'techn-o-pticon,gifslap,modbod', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(47, 'FIRE.ME at ProtoHack', 'fire-me-at-protohack', '2014-08-23', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/fire-me-at-protohack.jpg', '\r\n						<p class=\"p1\">Build your prototype and play with CODAME’s <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/fire-me/\">FIRE.ME</a> at <a href=\"http://protohack.org/\" target=\"_blank\">ProtoHack</a>, a code-free hackathon for designers and business people.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5123\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/jpeg1.jpg\" alt=\"jpeg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"359\">No coding is required. Instead you will leverage prototyping tools, drag and drop editors, mockups, wireframes and anything else you can think of to VISUALLY demo your idea on stage. (We’ve put together the best tools for non-coders, so don’t fret if you’ve never prototyped.)</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">At the end, you or your team will present on stage to a panel of judges consisting of developers and investors to get feedback on the technical challenges of building your idea and to see if its fundable.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><object width=\"802\" height=\"451\" classid=\"clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" data=\"https://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf\"><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"intl_lang=en-US&photo_secret=02f7174cf0&photo_id=10716513783&hd_default=false\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"https://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#000000\"><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"><embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" src=\"https://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf\" bgcolor=\"#000000\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" flashvars=\"intl_lang=en-US&photo_secret=02f7174cf0&photo_id=10716513783&hd_default=false\" width=\"802\" height=\"451\"></object></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\">Adopt this project for your events too!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>When: </b>Saturday, August 23 from 9:30AM to 10PM</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Where: </b>Galvanize, 543 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94105</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Their <a href=\"http://protohack.org/may-2014-san-francisco/\"><span class=\"s2\">last event</span></a> sold out in 3 weeks, so get your ticket soon!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://protohack.org/san-francisco-august-23-2014\">REGISTER NOW</a> </span>Code: <b>meetup20 </b>will get you 20% off tickets</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5118\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Speakeasy_4.jpg\" alt=\"Speakeasy_4\" width=\"1024\" height=\"677\"> <img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5120\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/gSF-Roof-Deck.jpg\" alt=\"gSF Roof Deck\" width=\"1000\" height=\"662\"> <img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5119\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Speakeasy_1.jpg\" alt=\"Speakeasy_1\" width=\"1024\" height=\"677\"></b></p>\r\n											', 'kinetech-arts', 'fire-me', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/fire-me-at-protohack/', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(48, 'Geekdom Demo Day + Happy Hour', 'geekdom-demo-day-happy-hour', '2014-08-28', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/geekdom-demo-day-happy-hour.jpg', '<p><strong>CODAME, on August 28, will showcase some of the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects\">projects</a>&nbsp;we have created&nbsp;as&nbsp;Artists in Residence at <a href=\"http://www.geekdomsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Geekdom San Francisco</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>We are thrilled to be part of one of the most dynamic community of developers, creatives, and entrepreneurs at Geekdom coworking space.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME and each Geekdom company will have ~5 minutes to pitch their product, with a few minutes for Q &amp; A.</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy some beers while meeting our community.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Open to the public! <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/RackHackSF/events/202416162/\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP here.</a></strong></p>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_5213\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 1368px;\">\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Adopt ART+TECH for your events!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>About Geekdom SF</strong></p>\r\n<p>Geekdom is a community designed for developers and startups. Our coworking provides easy access to industry partners, mentors, and events. Come work next to startups and entrepreneurs from Y-Combinator, TechStars, StartX.&nbsp;For upcoming events follow&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #c95b59;\" href=\"https://twitter.com/geekdomsf\">@GeekdomSF</a></p>\r\n<p>Check out&nbsp;Geekdom SF&rsquo;s&nbsp;current <a href=\"http://geekdomsf.com/san-francisco/members.html\" target=\"_blank\">list of members</a>&nbsp;and our list of <a href=\"/projects\">projects</a>.</p>\r\n<article id=\"events\" class=\"content container\" style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>About Rackspace</strong></article>\r\n<article class=\"content container\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></article>\r\n<article class=\"content container\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Rackspace is dedicated to open source and open community. We want to empower and support developers to rapidly innovate, build applications on OpenStack clouds and to make a difference in the community. We offer developers a $300 Rackspace Cloud credit for free, your guests can signup here:&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #c95b59;\" href=\"http://developers.rackspace.com/\">http://developers.rackspace.com/</a></article>\r\n<footer style=\"color: #717171;\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</footer>', '', 'art-tech-mascot,fluidscapes,ardent-mobile-cloud-platform,leapybird,fire-me,techn-o-pticon,codame-vj-cart,ecstatic-epiphany,gifslap,modbod', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(49, 'ART+TECH Rendezvous #5', 'art-tech-rendezvous-5', '2014-09-19', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-rendezvous-5.gif', '<header>\r\n<div>ART+TECH Rendezvous is CODAME&rsquo;s monthly series curated by CODAME staff, happening @GeekdomSF. The series focuses on contemporary art and tech artists, electro-music and performance, mixing and networking, electronic improvisation, artistic inspiration, and play time.</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<article id=\"post-5314\">\r\n<p>/// SCHEDULE</p>\r\n<p>6pm: GIF Happy Hour feat. Art by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/naughtbothered-is-a-generative-new-media-piece/\">Cam Altamura</a>&nbsp;co-creator of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/naughtbothered-is-a-generative-new-media-piece/\">#naughtbothered</a></p>\r\n<p>7pm:&nbsp;Art+Tech enlightening talks with:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jamie Kosoy&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/receipt-bot/\">Receipt bot</a>&nbsp;new project from NYC&nbsp;to&nbsp;SF, now&nbsp;as part of the CODAME<a href=\"/projects\">&nbsp;Adopt a Project</a>&nbsp;program</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/vinit/\">Vinit Patil</a>: Creative introduction to the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-at-boxworks/\">Collab Zone project</a>&nbsp;adopted by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://box.com/\">Box Inc.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>8pm: Play time with&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects\">CODAME Projects</a>&nbsp;open for&nbsp;Adoption:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/modbod/\">MobBod 3D Scan</a>:&nbsp;Full body scans for stylized identities</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/t-shirt-screen-printing/\">T-Shirt Screen Printing</a>:&nbsp;Personalized. Unique. Live Printing with your favorite codame art</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/technopticon/\">TechNopTICon</a>: Camera booth&nbsp;generating&nbsp;special effect animated GIF images</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/gifslap/\">GifSlap</a>: Browser-based VJ program controlled by MIDI</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>9pm: DJ Set by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/jpeg-artifacts-vapor-babes/\">.Jpeg Artifacts</a>&nbsp;+ Networking / Social / Music</p>\r\n<p>/// CONNECT</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://instagram.com/codame\">#CODAME</a>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\">CODAME ART+TECH Facebook</a>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/CODA_ME\">@CODA_ME</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Limited quantity available, so reserve yours before they&rsquo;re gone!</p>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"http://eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=12112160799&amp;ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>If you like what you see,&nbsp;<a href=\"/adopt\">Adopt</a>&nbsp;a Project for&nbsp;your events!&nbsp;Create&nbsp;unique, educational, and inspirational community outreach&nbsp;events.&nbsp;Display&nbsp;original installation works on site.Choose your favorite&nbsp;project at this event or on our site and&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:adopt@codame.com\">contact us</a>!</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"/adopt\"><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<p>Any bit or pix counts!</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</article>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'jpeg-artifacts,cam-altamura,spectrum-electric,jamie-kosoy,vinit-patil,dat-phan,jordan-gray', 'gifslap,receipt-bots,collab-zone,techn-o-pticon,modbod', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(50, 'Designers of Things 2014 Conference', 'designers-of-things-2014-conference', '2014-09-24', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/designers-of-things-2014-conference.png', '<p class=\"p1\"><a href=\"http://www.designersofthings.com\" target=\"_blank\">Designers of Things</a> 2014 kicks off this week to cover the very best in Wearable Tech, 3D Printing, and the Internet of Things.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">CODAME will be there!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Join us September 23-24 at the Mission Bay Conference Center in San Francisco to take in educational sessions, inspirational talks, and the exciting Demo Hall featuring exhibits, demos, and networking events.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"s2\">We have some <strong>c</strong></span><strong>omplimentary Demo Passes</strong> for the ART+TECH Community,&nbsp;</span>Use code&nbsp;<span class=\"s3\">DEMOMEETUP20&Prime;,&nbsp;</span>this offer is limited in quantity! &nbsp;<a href=\"https://designersofthings.tech.ubm.com/2014/\">RSVP</a>&nbsp;now!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For a&nbsp;<strong>15% off VIP &amp; Tech Passes</strong>: use code &nbsp;<span class=\"s3\">DOTMEETUP20&Prime; when you&nbsp;<a href=\"https://designersofthings.tech.ubm.com/2014/\">RSVP</a>!</span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Designers of Things is a two-day conference and demo hall dedicated to the explosive and exciting potential of Wearable Tech, 3D Printing, and the Internet of Things, giving the growing design and development community around these three innovative technologies a meeting place to discuss and share insights about the road ahead, and view a large-scale showcase of the newest technologies and products.</p>\r\n<p>Through educational sessions, inspirational talks, a huge demo hall featuring exhibits and demos of the latest future tech and exciting networking events, you will:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"indent\">\r\n<li>Meet like-minded designers, developers and innovators</li>\r\n<li>See and touch the latest 3D printers &amp; their creations</li>\r\n<li>Test the newest wearable technology products on the market</li>\r\n<li>Hear from the top innovators and the stories behind product evolution from idea to customer</li>\r\n<li>Meet with VCs and project funders to understand the nuts &amp; bolts of how to get funding</li>\r\n<li>Discover what enterprise companies are working on</li>\r\n<li>Learn about the state of industry today and future areas of opportunity</li>\r\n<li>Gain an understanding on how the Internet of Things will connect it all and more!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Learn more at<a href=\"http://www.designersofthings.com\" target=\"_blank\"> <span class=\"s1\">www.designersofthings.com</span></a></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'event', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(51, 'Ephemeral Vessels', 'ephemeral-vessels', '2014-09-27', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/ephemeral-vessels.gif', '<p><iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/110418837?title=0&amp;byline=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>CODAME is teaming up withï¿½<a href=\"http://www.b4bel4b.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">B4BEL4B</a>, an experimental art gallery and interactive modular community and event space based out of Oakland, California. ï¿½Saturday, September 27th to present a multimedia group art show + tech mixer where both levels of B4BEL4B Gallery will be covered with live visual projections, interactive art + interfaces, light sculptures, video art, holograms, live 3D scanning, live music performance + more for a one night only fully immersive sensory experience!</p>\r\n<p>Featuring 14 different local Bay Area artists from both Oakland + San Francisco, this event will brings together the best of both sides of the bridge and will be a night to remember!</p>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; text-align: left;\">\r\n<p><strong>// DATE + LOCATION </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Saturday, <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/ephemeral-vessels-tickets-13112422609\" target=\"_blank\">September 27th 7pm ï¿½ 3am</a></li>\r\n<li>B4BEL4B Gallery,ï¿½<a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/184+10th+St,+Oakland,+CA+94607\">184 10th St. Oakland, CA</a>, Okland, CA</li>\r\n<li>2 blocks away from Lake Merritt Bart Station, and begins earlier in the night for SF attendees!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>// SCHEDULE</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Gallery doors open at 7pm</li>\r\n<li>Upstairs Gallery:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>9:00-9:30pmï¿½<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/elia-vargas/\"><span class=\"s1\">Elia Vargas</span></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Downstairs Stage:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>9:30-10:30pm ï¿½ï¿½<span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/ani/\">ANI</a></span></li>\r\n<li>10:30pm ï¿½ 11:00pmï¿½<span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/the-spectrum-electric-codame-featured/\">Spectrum Electric</a></span></li>\r\n<li>11:00pm ï¿½ 11:20pm Shalo P + his new feature film!</li>\r\n<li>11:20pm ï¿½ 12:00am JaMile Jackson w/ dance performance by Black Magic Adventure</li>\r\n<li>12:00am ï¿½ 1:00amï¿½<span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/teeps/\">TEEPS</a></span></li>\r\n<li>1:00am ï¿½ 2:30amishï¿½<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/starpause/\"><span class=\"s1\">staRpauSe</span></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>// ART INSTALLATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p5\"><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/emi/\">EMi</a></span>,ï¿½<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-artist-vco-vault-vco-vault-is-a/\"><span class=\"s1\">VCO Vault</span></a>,ï¿½Dat Phan,ï¿½,ï¿½<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/laturbo/\"><span class=\"s1\">LaTurbo Avedon</span></a>, Luke Judd, Gary Roberts, Jamie Kosoy</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>// TICKETS</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Gets your <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/ephemeral-vessels-tickets-13112422609\" target=\"_blank\">ticket now</a>, support ART+TECH, CODAME and theï¿½Artists</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/ephemeral-vessels-tickets-13112422609\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5442\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/10574307_10204723876917231_8441181516083105375_n.jpg\" alt=\"10574307_10204723876917231_8441181516083105375_n\" width=\"750\" height=\"500\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>ï¿½</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>', 'spectrum-electric,ani,jordan-gray,teeps,emi,elia-vargas,vco-vault,dat-phan,laturbo-avedon,jamie-kosoy', 'receipt-bots,gifslap', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(56, 'UNCUBED SF', 'uncubed-sf', '2015-09-24', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/uncubed-sf.jpg', '<p>Join <a href=\"http://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\">@BrunoFonzi</a>&nbsp;+ <a href=\"http://twitter.com/StarPause\">@StarPause</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: #f64c3f;\" href=\"http://sf.uncubed.com/codame\" target=\"_blank\">sf.uncubed.com/codame</a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a class=\"tumblelog\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: #f64c3f;\" href=\"http://www.somarts.org\" target=\"_blank\">SOMArts</a>, Sept. 24th 2015 for an art+tech talk!</p>\r\n<p><strong>&ldquo;How the Collision of Art and Tech can Optimize your Creativity in the Workplace&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discounted CODAME passes available at this link:&nbsp;<a style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; text-decoration: none; color: #f64c3f;\" href=\"http://sf.uncubed.com/codame\" target=\"_blank\">sf.uncubed.com/codame</a></p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p>25 Hiring Startups // Live Art // Tech Talks on 9/24</p>\r\n<p>On&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Thursday (9/24)</span>&nbsp;we&rsquo;re partnering with our friends over at Uncubed for their next event.&nbsp;<a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: #f64c3f;\" href=\"http://sf.uncubed.com/codame\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SF Uncubed</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">&nbsp;</span>is a creative full-day gathering of hiring startups and SF&rsquo;s top designers, programmers, engineers, &amp; senior biz talent. Think startup showcase meets tech conference meets circus.</p>\r\n<p>Join the teams behind SF companies like&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">GitHub, Evernote, FutureAdvisor, Credit Karma + more&nbsp;</span>for a full-day of startup discovery &amp; career-advancing classes taught by Founders, Engineers, Lead Designers &amp; PMs pioneering the technology. Plus open bar, a live art showcase, music &amp; more surprises throughout the day.</p>\r\n<p>Speakers include, CODAME co-founders Jordan Gray &amp; Bruno Fonzi (co-leading a class: &ldquo;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How the Collision of Art and Tech can Optimize Your Creativity in the Workplace</span>&rdquo;), Founder/CEO of PredictSpring, CTO &amp; SVP of Product at Recurly, VP of Science &amp; Tech at PlaceIQ, &amp; many more.</p>', 'jordan-gray', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(83, 'Kids & Art Foundation - Happy Hour & Friendraising! ', 'kids-art-foundation---happy-hour-friendraising', '2017-11-28', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/kids-art-foundation---happy-hour-friendraising.png', '<p>Cancer Sucks. Art Heals.&nbsp;<br />Attend the event, share it with like minded folks. Help heal pediatric cancer through art!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/happy-hour-friendraising-registration-38504449846\">Join us</a> on GivingTuesday for a 21+ night of looking good while giving back. Rock your style at Cambria Gallery, a natural stone showroom in SOMA and raise funds for Kids &amp; Art Foundation. Drink wine and strike a pose in front of quartz backdrops, while photographers and sketch artists capture your best angles. GivingTuesday is a global day of giving, and all proceeds from this event fund healing art programs for children with cancer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CODAME in support for the&nbsp;Kids &amp; Art Foundation, is&nbsp;bringing&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/modbod\">Modbod</a>&nbsp;3D scanning&nbsp;booth to create gifs&nbsp;that print into awesome figurines--of you to at this \"<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/happy-hour-friendraising-registration-38504449846\">Happy Hour &amp; Friendraising</a>\" event.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/attached-to-base-test.gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/projects/modbod\">Modbod</a></p>\r\n<p>Venue Sponsor:&nbsp;Cambria Gallery</p>\r\n<p>Event Sponsors:&nbsp;Sheri Sobrato Brisson,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.sheppardmullin.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Sheppard Mulin</a>,<a href=\"http://www.whamix.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Whamix</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.breallaw.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Breall &amp; Breall LLP</a>, and&nbsp;Ludell&nbsp;Deutscher.<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vRADg6N0sfS6nx9wJwDgIya40eoHUmaoyope9AziNN-CyqtxMItPUx147brSOud8EBk0abZEmgVCsGs/pub?start=false&amp;loop=false&amp;delayms=3000\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\"><br /></a></p>\r\n<p>In-Kind sponsors:&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/modbod\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Codame</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.newdelhirestaurant.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">New Delhi Restaurant, SF</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nothingbundtcakes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Nothing Bund Cake</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://powisvr.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Powis VR</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wholefoodsmarket.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Whole Foods</a>, Fete Fraiche</p>\r\n<p>Raffle Prizes:&nbsp;Wearable wireless Helix Cuff from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ashleychloe.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Ashley Chloe</a>,<a href=\"https://www.annaborgia.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Annaborgia</a>, ethical luxury for conscious fashionistas;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.bluxomewinery.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Bluxome Street Winery</a>&nbsp;tasting for four,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fiorella-sf.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Fiorella</a>, San Francisco\'s neighborhood Italian,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.kanjanadesigns.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Kanjana</a>, luxury fashion, signed&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nomnompaleo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Nom Nom Paleo</a>&nbsp;Ready or Not Cookbook;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://powisvr.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Powis VR</a>&nbsp;headsets, Signed poster and books from Oscar nominated artist&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.gheehappy.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Sanjay Patel</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.winery-sf.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">The Winery, SF</a>&nbsp;Wine tasting and special barrel sampling for 10,</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/SpiderDress.gif\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">#celebrateyou #celebratelife #givingmakesyoulookgood&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you cannot attend but you would like to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.kidsandart.org/givingtuesday\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">donate</a>, please click here&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.kidsandart.org/givingtuesday\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">https://www.kidsandart.org/givingtuesday</a></p>', 'jordan-gray,bruno-fonzi', 'modbod', 'kids-art-foundation', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(62, '500 VR', '500-vr', '2016-05-17', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/500-vr.jpg', '<p>Google is reportedly planning to reveal a new Android VR headset at its I/O developer&rsquo;s conference next week. The headset is expected to be a low-cost alternative to rivals such as Oculus Rift, but pricier than Google&rsquo;s current bare-bones offering, Cardboard. The anticipated launch follows an active period for virtual reality startup investment, with Google-backed VR software developer Magic Leap raising close to $800 million in a February round led by Alibaba. Other VR startups that have raised capital in recent months include Envelop VR and Avegant.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME has been exploring the VR space since Oculus Rift Kickstarter in 2012, in 2014 we had an unforgettable&nbsp;ART+TECH event dedidcated&nbsp;to VR at <a href=\"/events/art-tech-virtual-reality\">Mozilla</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On May 17th, on the eve of Google I/O, we\'re pleased to showcase&nbsp;with our friends at 500 Mobile Collective and&nbsp;SFNT&nbsp;together with some of&nbsp;the best and most innovative minds in VR to show you their latest and greatest!</p>\r\n<p>Connect with the best VR experts in the field, play with latest VR content &amp; devices and learn the latest and greatest trends for VR at this very special event.</p>\r\n<p>Use \"codame20\" for a 20% discount.&nbsp;Get you ticket <a href=\"https://sfnewtech.com/event/051716/#register\">here</a>.</p>', 'cabbibo,jordan-gray', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(59, '3D Web Fest [2016]', '3d-web-fest-2016', '2016-06-15', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/3d-web-fest.gif', '<div id=\"g-861285\">\r\n<div id=\"element-custom-block-131984273\">\r\n<div id=\"sfid-131984273\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Shift Is On.</strong></p>\r\n<p>3D Web Fest kicks off on June 15th, and you\'re invited to take part in the festivities. The Festival Pavilion at Fort Mason Center for Arts &amp; Culture is our meeting spot for a night of fun and excitement.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com\">RSVP</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Location</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Fort Mason - Festival Hall&nbsp;<br />2 Marina Blvd&nbsp;<br />San Francisco, CA 94123</p>\r\n<p><strong>Program</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"dtstart\">Wednesday, June 15, 2016</span></p>\r\n<p>4:00 Early access to exhibit hall at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://forge.autodesk.com/conference/\">Autodesk Forge DevCon</a>.</p>\r\n<p>6:00&nbsp;Welcome Reception&nbsp;Drinks &amp;&nbsp;Snacks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>6:30&nbsp;Theater Opens</p>\r\n<p>7:00&nbsp;Show Starts -&nbsp;Lasts 2 hours&nbsp;with&nbsp;15-minute intermission&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>9:00&nbsp;Post-Show Reception -&nbsp;Drinks &amp; Networking</p>\r\n<p>Following the program attendees are invited to participate in a short panel session with the performers on the future of the 3D Web including audience Q&amp;A. &nbsp;You are then invited to mix and mingle with other industry leaders and influencers at the after show party. Stay tuned for more announcements <a href=\"https://twitter.com/codame\">@CODAME</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>About The 3D Web Fest</strong></p>\r\n<div id=\"g-513126\">\r\n<div id=\"element-custom-block-131984271\">\r\n<div id=\"sfid-131984271\">\r\n<p>Experience the most innovative commercial, non-commercial, experimental or game-based projects by&nbsp;top thought leaders, influencers and creators in 3D Web.&nbsp;The festival showcases websites that are the best mixture of music, art and technology, and exhibit what is possible with the advent of 3D Web. Come one, come all, bring a guest, and hang loose. You can find out more on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.3dwebfest.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3dwebfest.com</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Special Guest</strong></p>\r\n<p>DrinkBot will make a presence. The Dress allows its wearer to decide who to serve a shot to (and who to leave dry). We invite everyone to give it a shot! A project by CODAME labs director&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/anouk-wipprecht\">Anouk Wipprecht</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/drinkbot5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"748\" height=\"498\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Sponsors</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Special thanks to the 3D Web Fest Team and&nbsp;Autodesk. All attendee ticket fee&rsquo;s go direct to CODAME in support for our ART+TECH program.</p>\r\n<p>To become a sponsor <a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">contact us</a>.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/3dwebfest-poster.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"745\" height=\"1118\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME Project</strong></p>\r\n<p>We brought ModBod3D to scan you!</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://sketchfab.com/playlists/embed?collection=dda59e836fa947119323a24196659359\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal; margin: 5px; color: #4a4a4a;\"><a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/collections/3d-web-fest-2016?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">3D Web Fest 2016</a> by <a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH</a> on <a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">Sketchfab</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Artists</strong></p>\r\n<p>Marpi,&nbsp;Isaac Cohen,&nbsp;Travis Bennett, Michael Chang, Jason Marsh,&nbsp;Jaume Sanchez,&nbsp;Edan Kwan, Felix Woitzel,&nbsp;David Paul Rosser,&nbsp;Arash Akbari,&nbsp;Xiaohan Zhang,&nbsp;Josh Staples,&nbsp;Tarek Sherif,&nbsp;Augusto Goncalve,&nbsp;Andrew Ray and&nbsp;Brendon Smith.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/RIe2doFTctU\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>', 'marpi,cabbibo,anouk-wipprecht,yagiz-mungan', 'illy,modbod,mass-migrations', 'autodesk', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(60, 'stARTup artfair sf', 'startup-artfair-sf', '2016-05-01', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/startup-artfair-sf.jpg', '<p>Join CODAME co-founders,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\" target=\"_blank\" data-preserve-html-node=\"true\">Bruno Fonzi</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Starpause\" target=\"_blank\" data-preserve-html-node=\"true\">Jordan Gray</a>, for an art conversation at the&nbsp;stARTup artfair San Francisco</p>\r\n<p>When: Sunday, May 1 at&nbsp;2:30 pm&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Where: Room 225&nbsp;|&nbsp;Hotel Del Sol | 3100 Webster St.&nbsp;|&nbsp;San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://sf.startupartfair.com/events/#FindingTheMatch\">Finding the Match: Tech Partnerships in the Creative Sector</a></p>\r\n<p>With the growth of the technology sector in San Francisco, there are huge opportunities for artists, creatives and technologists to partner. In this conversation, we will explore how can artists creatives find the best partner, what makes a good partner match, what to look out for, and some best practices and challenges. Join moderator&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/beatrizdominguez\" target=\"_blank\" data-preserve-html-node=\"true\">Bea Dominguez</a>&nbsp;(Senior Community &amp; Events Manager at PicsArt),&nbsp;<a href=\"http://centerfornewmusic.com/staff/\" target=\"_blank\" data-preserve-html-node=\"true\">Adam Fong</a>&nbsp;(Founder and Executive Director of the Center for New Music),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\" target=\"_blank\" data-preserve-html-node=\"true\">Bruno Fonzi</a>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Starpause\" target=\"_blank\" data-preserve-html-node=\"true\">Jordan Gray</a>&nbsp;(Founders of CODAME), and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://heistersgenerative.com/about.html\" target=\"_blank\" data-preserve-html-node=\"true\">Ian Heisters</a>&nbsp;(Founder, Heisters Generative) as they explore some reasons why partnering with the tech sector could be the right fit&nbsp;for you and your next project.</p>\r\n<p>For more inforamtion about the overall event, check out&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sf.startupartfair.com\">sf.startupartfair.com</a></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Screen_Shot_2016-04-28_at_9.48_.45_PM_.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>', 'jordan-gray,bruno-fonzi', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(64, 'ART+TECH FESTIVAL [2016] #ARTEX', 'art-tech-festival-2016-artex', '2016-11-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/artificial-experiences.jpg', '<h1 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">#ARTEX</h1>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-0f6a5025-81bd-9e06-5482-e06eef32048b\">@ Hotel Zetta</span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">November 11, 2016</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Join CODAME and explore Artificial Experiences with some of the most artistic, inspiring and visionary designers, engineers, architects, makers, hackers and technologists.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Artificial Experiences</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As technology seeps into every second of our waking lives, what experiences from the digital realm are real and worthy of engagement? What moments spent in flesh are glossed over and abstracted, losing their authenticity? How do we assign value to experiences, inside and outside of our screens? How is that value reflected in the ways we work and play in San Francisco and other urban environments?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Where</strong>:&nbsp;Hotel Zetta, 55 5th Street in San Francisco, California</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>When</strong>:&nbsp;11/11, 2016 from 6pm to 11:11:11</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Tickets</strong>:&nbsp;Event profits support participating artists, in line with the CODAME mission of sustaining the arts.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Drinks</strong>:&nbsp;Cash bar.&nbsp;Ask for a&nbsp; special CODAME discount at the S&amp;R Lounge.</p>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; text-align: left;\"><iframe src=\"//eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=28324833339&amp;ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"325\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></div>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>What</strong>: Music, art installations and performances. Meet the&nbsp;artists&nbsp;and learn about their&nbsp;work:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ModBod by CODAME Labs</li>\r\n<li>Illy by Yagiz Mungan</li>\r\n<li>Mass Migrations by Marpi</li>\r\n<li>DeepDreamVisionQuest by Gary Boodhoo</li>\r\n<li>A Flourish of Tiny Regrets by Bill Hsu</li>\r\n<li>Psychometric Cinema by Ultrabianka</li>\r\n<li>Cleverbot IRL by Wave Chair Ghost</li>\r\n<li>Refraction Spheres by Yanling He</li>\r\n<li>Internet of Consciousness by Elaine Cheung</li>\r\n<li>Recurrent by Joey Verbeke and Yagmur Uyanik</li>\r\n<li>Soft Landscapes by v21</li>\r\n<li>Motion Graphics by Erica Anderson et al.</li>\r\n<li>Inverse Dollhouse</li>\r\n<li>Permutation by Ahree Lee</li>\r\n<li>Around the Body by Philippe Jestin</li>\r\n<li>Holoshatter by Yosun and staRpauSe</li>\r\n<li>Music Performance by Real DJ Heroes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>At 7:30pm there will be brief&nbsp;artist talks.</p>\r\n<p>This is event is possible&nbsp;thanks to your donations, volunteers and our supporters:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Hotel Zetta</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">CODAME thanks Hotel Zetta for hosting this event. We appreciate their partnership and admire their desire to support local artists.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Located at the iconic convergence of San Francisco&rsquo;s Union Square, SoMa and Financial Districts, Hotel Zetta is perfectly situated to experience the best of San Francisco&rsquo;s fashion, arts, technology and music scene. Originally built in 1913 and re-opened on its 100th anniversary, this 116-room property effortlessly combines state-of-the-art amenities with intuitive service. With 2,760 square feet of meeting and event space, and the ultimate Playroom. Hotel Zetta will be the go-to hotspot for San Francisco&rsquo;s leading-edge cultural and business communities. Hotel Zetta is located at 55 5th Street in San Francisco, California. For reservations, please call 415-543-8555 or visit the hotel&rsquo;s web site at <a href=\"http://www.hotelzetta.com/\">www.hotelzetta.com</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/HotelZetta-logotype_horizontal_Black_white.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Capital One</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">CODAME gives a big thanks to Capital One, a great partner supporting our mission, embracing&nbsp;innovation through creativity, play, and collaboration&nbsp;between artists and technologists.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">At the event, meet with the top creative minds and makers in the&nbsp;industry:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/apuzinio\">Apurva Shah</a>&nbsp;- Head of Creative Technology&nbsp;and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/jasondeperro\">Jason DePerro</a>&nbsp;- Experience lead of Creative Technology from <a href=\"https://www.capitalone.com/\">Capital One</a>&nbsp;Creative Technology Group (CTG)</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">CTG&rsquo;s mission is to experiment on the bleeding-edge of emerging technologies, but stay anchored in human centered design. Their team&rsquo;s aim is not to foreshadow products with these experiments, but to discover solutions to the unmet problems real people face with their finances.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"s1\">Apurva, Jason and the entire CTG team are very excited to be a part of the creative art and tech community.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/CTG-logo.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'ultrabianka,wave-chair-ghost,myles-thompson,gary-boodhoo,raktor,jasper-patterson,yagiz-mungan,marpi,real-dj-heroes,jordan-gray,joey-verbeke,yagmur-uyanik,erica-anderson,dustin-freeman,bill-hsu,yosun,v21,ahree-lee,elaine-cheung,yanling-he,mike-bam-tyau,philippe-jestin', 'mass-migrations,illy,holoshatter,refraction-spheres,psychometric-cinema,a-flourish-of-tiny-regrets,recurrent,deep-dream-vision-quest,motion-graphics,inverse-dollhouse,modbod,music-performance,soft-landscapes,permutation,internet-of-consciousness,cleverbot-irl,artformar', 'capital-one,hotel-zetta,organic', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(67, 'ART+TECH FESTIVAL [2012]', 'art-tech-festival-2012', '2012-10-27', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-festival-2012.jpg', '<p>Experience the convergence of Art and Technology.<br /><br />- 5 Floors of Art, Tech and Music<br />- 15+ Artists<br />- 17 Musicians<br /><br />Our 3rd year strong, CODAME brings together independent artists, creators, performers and musicians for one night to find where Art and Technology meet. Join us as we explore this year&rsquo;s theme, DIMENSIONS.<br /><br />We are inviting artists to submit works to exhibit at the festival.<br /><br />Special prizes for&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Live Drawing Art&nbsp;Contest</li>\r\n<li>Indie Game Arcade&nbsp;Awards</li>\r\n<li>Best&nbsp;Halloween&nbsp;costume</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This is a non-profit event. Tickets are limited! Grab yours now! Doors open on Saturday, Oct. 27th, 2012 at 8PM with no hard stop.</p>', 'cyriak,ani,wes-grubbs,josh-nimoy,reza-ali,ryan-alexander,alexandernaut,xavi-vives-riba,superdeux,keisuke-shingu-aka-vj-kska,elisa-sassi,jonathan-wallraven,chris-ritson,bad-unkl-sista,david-oreilly,anastazia-louise-aranaga', 'outerbody', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(68, 'ART+TECH FESTIVAL [2011]', 'art-tech-festival-2011', '2011-05-12', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-festival-2011---video.png', '<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/23732051\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/23732051\">CODAME 2011</a> from <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/rikirocket\">Riki-Rocket</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br />The CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2011 is a&nbsp;unique experience that features the convergence of art, tech and filmmaking with engagement of the audience documenting the moment. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Join other creative minds, cool speakers, independent short films and enjoy local artist\'s work &nbsp;- Music &amp; Drinks included!<br /><br />Meet with a wide variety of new media &amp; video 2.0 producers, creators, writers, bloggers, journalists, technologists, developers, managers, executive, investors, advertisers, small and large businesses, fans and more.&nbsp;<br /><br />Give away prize:</p>\r\n<p>Be spontaneous, don\'t need to be a pro, grab your camera and start shooting! Win Adobe CS5.5 Production Premium for the most voted video</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 400; font-size: 30px; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 10px 0px; margin: 0px; color: #dfdfdf; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">CODAME 2011 IMPRESSIONS</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 400; font-size: 30px; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 10px 0px; margin: 0px; color: #dfdfdf; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7 !important; font-size: medium;\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/codame/albums/72157633919457078\">PHOTOS</a><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;TAKEN BY&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7 !important; font-size: medium;\" href=\"http://twitter.com/photonburst\">@PHOTONBURST</a><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;</span></h2>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/9ad7a7d59d9079e5dbd1997a7f4c24e53.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/e73879ddd8d919a46a60ba59ac47b26e3.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/da89c55ca76e2a0e6fda438748dd851e3.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/43f6d79000e02a74159faa0b76fa15726.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/10ec9abf678b00c9d9e89b8566b406943.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/ecdcdbe58e267e1747a51028dd886d9a3.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/673b7c5a53c0374fee559673fbe929913.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/9de87cf1c2639d880be933a6632c4bc83.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/cbecf68868cc6cbb7a95f3695094209b3.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/43f6d79000e02a74159faa0b76fa15727.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/S8Ok-kMLrkQ\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>', 'jordan-gray,harbour,bruno-fonzi', '', 'adobe', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(69, 'ART+TECH FESTIVAL [2010]', 'art-tech-festival-2010', '2010-08-10', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-festival-2010.gif', '<p><a title=\"Buy tickets for CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020ã€Ž JOYNT ã€\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486854/chk/ccda/?modal_widget=true&amp;widget=true\"><img src=\"https://app.tickettailor.com/images/btns/bt_bl.gif\" alt=\"Buy tickets for CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020ã€Ž JOYNT ã€\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>After years of waiting an inspiring and great Flash event returns to San Francisco and we want to celebrate and share the excitement with you around&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fitc.ca/events/about/?event=110\">FITC</a>&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a href=\"/\">CODAME</a></p>\r\n<p>If you are a geek, designer or developer join&nbsp;<a href=\"/\">CODAME</a>,&nbsp;a&nbsp;San Francisco&nbsp;party for the tech industries greatest creative minds, packed together on a roof deck with the brightest Bay Area Art Geek regulars.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/\">CODAME</a>&nbsp;is an invitation only exclusive gathering, space is limited.<br />Monday, 16th of August, 2010 (day before FITC starts) at 8pm til midnight.</p>\r\n<p>Final confirmation and exact location will be sent some days before the event, only to registered people.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://twitter.com/Starpause\">@Starpause</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/keisukes\">@keisukes</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/andremichelle\">@andremichelle</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://beta.lostscience.org/front/albums#23\">TrustFundKilla</a>&nbsp;(LostScience) will be playing some tunes on the roof-top.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/radley\">@radley</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/calebhaye\">@calebhaye</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/jamiew\">@jamiew</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/EvanMorris\">@EvanMorris</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://transmote.com/\">transmote.com</a>&nbsp;by Eric Socolofsky&nbsp;art tech artist projects will be on display.</p>\r\n<p>Plus, amazing location- private roof-top downtown San Francisco &ndash; with superb view included. This event will be simply a blast !</p>\r\n<p>We have some amazing local volunteers helping. If you want to help too, show your work under the stars or have a cool idea for the event.&nbsp;Contact <a href=\"http://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\">@BrunoFonzi</a></p>\r\n<p>Powerflasher&nbsp;is one of the main sponsors for this event&nbsp;celebrating&nbsp;one year anniversary in USA&nbsp;as a Digital Interactive Development&nbsp;company.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you so far for the following supporters:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://gaiaonline.com/\">Gaia Online</a>&nbsp;Founded in 2003, Gaia Online is the leading online hangout for teens and young adults. More than eight million visitors come to Gaia Online every month to make friends, play games, and participate in the world&rsquo;s most active online community. Gaia Online provides a fun, social environment that inspires individuality and creativity. With everything from art contests to discussion forums on poetry, politics, celebrities and more, to fully customizable profiles, digital characters and cars, Gaia Online is a place where teens can create their own space and express their individual style. They are hiring, so&nbsp;<a href=\"http://gcorp.gaiaonline.com/careers\">look out</a>&nbsp;!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://organic.com/\">Organic</a>&nbsp;is a leading digital communications agency that uses a&nbsp;consumer-empathy-based approach, combined with a holistic view of the&nbsp;digital landscape, to design and build exceptional interactive&nbsp;experiences that effectively engage and persuade customers. &nbsp;Founded&nbsp;in 1993, Organic has offices in New York, San Francisco, Los Angeles,&nbsp;Detroit, London and Toronto. &nbsp;Adweek ranked Organic as the number one&nbsp;interactive agency in their 2007 interactive agency report card.&nbsp;Organic is a part of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://omnigroup.com/\">Omnicom Group Inc.</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://mypressi.com/\">Mypressi</a>&nbsp;has become the rockstar of the espresso world with the first handheld device that can make a perfect shot of espresso with water or, more relevantly, any other liquid. They will be pulling amazing shots at the CoDaMe Party. Stop by for some super smooth &lsquo;spro-based cocktails. And remember, always code responsibly.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://influxis.com/\">Influxis</a>&nbsp;powers interactive Flash applications and the best parties for the community ðŸ˜‰ The team will have its own bar and serving very hot cool cocktails during CODAME, I hope you can handle it!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://fitc.ca/sf\">FITC</a>&nbsp;knows how to build amazing flash events! FITC has been generous to support CODAME by offering&nbsp;major discounts&nbsp;if you decide to support CODAME too, we need more more drinks and food for hungry flash developers &amp; designers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"bar-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #dfdfdf; float: left; width: 650px; background: #1d1a1c; border-width: 1px 0px; border-image: initial; padding-left: 10px; margin: 20px 0px; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: medium; border-color: #333333 initial #333333 initial; border-style: solid initial solid initial;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 400; font-size: 30px; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 10px 0px; margin: 0px;\">CODAME 2010 IMPRESSIONS</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 400; font-size: 30px; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 10px 0px; margin: 0px;\"><a style=\"font-size: medium;\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/smoc/galleries/72157624768535298\">Photos</a><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;taken by&nbsp;</span><a style=\"font-size: medium;\" href=\"http://twitter.com/photonburst\">@photonburst</a><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><a style=\"font-size: medium;\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/smoc/4925313999/\">video</a><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;taken by&nbsp;</span><a style=\"font-size: medium;\" href=\"http://twitter.com/keisukes\">@keisukes</a></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"text-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 15px; padding: 20px 0px; color: #ffffff; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; background-color: #000000;\">\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/codame-2010-impressions-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"725\" height=\"543\" /><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/02a10e12ca32b6533a16434bc304c1022.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/ab25b4eca3ea0570aa45d829585409562.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/e54462bc42b47b86fea2713254518ad12.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/0b0c9b1e0585fd2af30c2bf23e379d9a2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/207d3a0f112243f56fa024be3a9dcd032.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/f46c57fe8da56823fe25ce7c658219682.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/73ac30185b5f69637e4628aabfd05d002.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img class=\" alignnone\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/79b35fcd7d69997736b3c934a32742172.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><img class=\" alignnone\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/d6e0d7a44965c3c56a52c797b5fc6ac92.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n</div>', 'jordan-gray,keisuke-shingu-aka-vj-kska', '', 'organic', 'the-grid', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://shop.codame.com/', 'e-lit-games-playing-with-words, shaders, live-streaming-performances, github-universe-after-party, codame-codeconf-in-nashville, adopt-art-tech-with-anouk-reza, art-by-code-2014'),
(111, 'MUTEK NEXUS Experience', 'mutek-nexus-experience', '2020-05-23', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/mutek-nexus-experience.jpg', '<p>Leaders of ART+TECH in San Francisco are joining forces for an incredible two day online festival!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>WORKSHOPS</strong></p>\r\n<p>SAT MAY 23 - 4PM PT - Char Stiles - Shader Workshop</p>\r\n<p>SUN MAY 24 - 6PM PT - Jordan Gray -&nbsp;Dayan Qigong Workshop</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>DIGITAL GALLERY</strong></p>\r\n<p>With CODAME featured&nbsp;artists Kenny Myers, d0n.xyz &amp; Cabbibo</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>SCREENINGS</strong></p>\r\n<p>With CODAME featured&nbsp;artists Tiare&nbsp;Ribeaux,&nbsp;Norma Jeane and Jody Stillwaters</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>TICKETS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Donate for perks and 100% of the funds will be split beteween the artists!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://nexus.mutek.us/\">Free with RSVP</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Nexus_CharWorkshop_Partner_Tile(s).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Nexus_jordangray_Partner_Tile(s).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"/uploaded_images/donxyz-_SMTile_(s).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/KennyMyers_-_SMTile_(s).jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>', 'char-stiles,d0nxyz,cabbibo,jordan-gray,tiare-ribeaux,norma-jeane,jody-stillwater,kenny-myers', 'shybot,cyanovisions,heliophagis,darkness-light-soul,frequency-piece,desert-monolith,wild-goose-moving-meditation', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(70, 'Disruption: Innovation vs. Incumbents', 'disruption-innovation-vs-incumbents', '2017-01-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/disruption-innovation-vs-incumbents.jpg', '<p>CODAME has been invited to bring ART+TECH to the <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/disruption-innovation-vs-incumbents-tickets-30929203079?aff=CODAME\">Young Leaders Circle</a>&nbsp;event, from&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.pacificresearch.org\">Pacific Research Institute</a>&nbsp;for a conversation&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/katiebiber\" data-hovercard=\"/ajax/hovercard/user.php?id=577366545&amp;extragetparams=%7B%22directed_target_id%22%3A1217698904980222%7D\" data-hovercard-prefer-more-content-show=\"1\">Katie Biber</a>.</p>\r\n<p><em>The \"sharing economy\" used to be a buzzword only Silicon Valley insiders spoke -- but these days, it crosses the lips of every politician trying to be cool. Join us for a conversation on breaking rules, following rules, and everything in between.</em></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>WHEN:&nbsp;Wed, January 11, 2017, 5:30 PM &ndash; 8:30 PM PST</p>\r\n<p>WHERE: Maritime Wine Tasting Studio, 222 Columbus Avenue, San Francisco, CA 94133</p>\r\n<p>RSVP on <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/disruption-innovation-vs-incumbents-tickets-30929203079?aff=CODAME\">Eventbrite</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://cdn.evbuc.com/eventlogos/154936427/katie.biber.headshot.jpg\" alt=\"Katie.Biber\" width=\"291\" height=\"332\" /><img src=\"/uploaded_images/csm_YLC_logo_color_393aeedd3f.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"330\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/katiebiber\" data-hovercard=\"/ajax/hovercard/user.php?id=577366545&amp;extragetparams=%7B%22directed_target_id%22%3A1217698904980222%7D\" data-hovercard-prefer-more-content-show=\"1\">Katie</a>&nbsp;currently serves as general counsel at Thumbtack. Previously, she was senior counsel at Airbnb and before that she served as general counsel to the Romney for President Campaign. Katie is a frequent speaker on topics such as politics, tech, and the overlap between the two, as well as strategies to increase the presence of women in both industries.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/donald-hanson1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"615\" height=\"412\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/artists/donald-hanson\">Donald Hanson</a> will present his <a href=\"/projects/gifslap\">GifSlap</a> project by creating strange and colorful patterns that loop and shimmer with the playback of GIFs. This was designed as a live visual to enhance electronic music shows, but it can also be used to create compelling compositions and net art. So come and experience the age of disruption for yourself!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/gifslap1.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"638\" height=\"329\" /></p>', 'donald-hanson', 'gifslap', 'pacific-research-institute', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(71, 'Paseo Public Protoytping Challenge', 'paseo-public-protoytping-challenge', '2017-04-07', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/paseo-public-protoytping-challenge-and-festival.jpg', '<div title=\"Page 1\">\r\n<p>San JoseÌ. The Paseo Public Prototyping Festival will celebrate the culminating prototypes during an all-day indoor/ outdoor public arts, culture and technology festival held on the Paseo de San Antonio Plaza at the newly opened SJSU/ Hammer Theatre Center in downtown San JoseÌ, April 7th&nbsp;and 8th, 2017.</p>\r\n<p>The Paseo Public Prototyping Challenge invites multidisciplinary student teams at San JoseÌ State University to envision and build innovative prototypes using art, design, engineering, science and technology to address social and environmental problems facing the City of San Jose, CA. More information on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.lastfestival.org\">paseoprototyping.org</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>L.A.S.T. CALL FOR PROPOSALS</strong></p>\r\n<p>The 4th L.A.S.T. (Life Art Science Technology) festival, is being organized by San JoseÌ State University in partnership with the Paseo Public Prototyping Challenge and Festival taking place April 7th and 8th. L.A.S.T. is seeking technology based artworks for exhibition that advantage human-machine interaction to address new forms of engagement, participation and immersive experience. We are particularly interested in works addressing the intersection of art and science that explore futures for civic engagement, creative placemaking, urban life, the human condition and social innovation</p>\r\n<p>The L.A.S.T. festival will take place at the SJSU Hammer Theatre Center in San JoseÌ. CA. The exhibition will take place in the &lsquo;black box&rsquo; theater with additional outdoor and performative works staged on the 4th floor terrace overlooking the City of San JoseÌ.</p>\r\n<p>Artists and creators working in all formats and disciplines (visual, installation, sound, and performance art as well as engineering and science) are welcome to submit proposals. An honoraria up to $300 will be provided based on project acceptance. When applying, please include:</p>\r\n<p>An artist&rsquo;s bio<br /> A description of the artwork<br /> URL of the artist&rsquo;s website<br /> State of the project<br /> Images or videos or other documentation of the project Materials required<br /> Floor space required<br /> and any other relevant information</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div title=\"Page 2\">\r\n<p>The deadline for submissions is February 20, 2017. Early submissions are encouraged &ndash; a final selection will be announced March 1st. Artists based outside the Bay Area are welcome to submit projects, but we are unable to provide support for travel or shipping. Submissions should be directed to <a href=\"mailto:submit@lastfestival.com\">submit@lastfestival.com</a> with &ldquo;LAST Submission 2017&rdquo; in the subject line.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About LAST</strong></p>\r\n<p>The L.A.S.T. (Life Art Science Technology) festival, founded in 2014, promotes interdisciplinary forms of technology-intensive art-making that expand the potential for audience engagement. The first L.A.S.T. festival was held in San Jose at the ZERO1 Garage on June 6-7, 2014. The second L.A.S.T. festival was held at San Francisco&rsquo;s legendary The Lab on October 23-25, 2014. The third LAST festival took place October 15-18, 2015, at Stanford University.</p>\r\n<p>Festivals are structured around four program strands:<br /> Interactive art installations<br /> Inspirational talks by luminaries on cutting-edge technology and science Live performances<br /> Interactive workshops and/or talks by artists</p>\r\n<p>Previous speakers and artists can be seen at the LAST website:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.lastfestival.org\">www.lastfestival.org</a></p>\r\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'event', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(72, 'Desert X', 'desert-x', '2017-02-25', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/desert-x.png', '<p>CODAME will be releasing&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/shybot\">ShyBot</a>&nbsp;for the inaugural exhibition of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.desertx.org/\">Desert X</a>&nbsp;biennial of art, in&nbsp;Coachella Valley Feb.25th, 2017.</p>\r\n<p>ShyBot is an art project from <a href=\"/artists/norma-jeane\">Norma Jeane</a>, an autonomous, self-driving, human-avoiding rover, solar powered, computer vision enabled and GPS tracked. Join us a try to catch the ShyBot (if you can)</p>\r\n<p><strong>About Desert X</strong></p>\r\n<p>Desert X is a site-specific show that will take place in the spring of 2017. Artists from different parts of the world will be invited to make work that responds to the unique conditions of Palm Springs and the surrounding Coachella Valley.</p>\r\n<p>The desert of Desert X is the blank canvas upon which contemporary artists - like the writers, architects,&nbsp;musicians and other before them &ndash;&nbsp;will be invited to project their vision and to create of the extraordinary natural and social history around them objects and experiences that reflect upon the matchless spectacle of the geologic epic, the radical abstraction of the surroundings and the singular incursions of man into the seemingly barren landscape.&nbsp;Unique in that it takes the landscape itself as its exhibition space, Desert X will offer the opportunity to explore both the familiar and the unknown through the eyes of others.</p>\r\n<p>If the desert is indeed God without man, then Desert X is art without constraint.&nbsp;</p>', 'norma-jeane,ben-lerchin,bruno-fonzi,jordan-gray,donald-hanson,eric-hanson', 'shybot', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(74, 'ShyBot Panel and Exhibition', 'shybot-panel-and-exhibition', '2017-03-04', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/shybot-panel-and-exhibition.jpg', '<div id=\"block-a5b95223e6cb7f6ce4a4\" data-block-type=\"2\">\r\n<div id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1487282628924_325\">\r\n<p>Italian&nbsp;artist&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/norma-jeane\">Norma Jeane</a>&nbsp;worked with CODAME&nbsp;to design a robot that they subsequently liberated in Palm Desert for the&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/desert-x\">Desert X</a>&nbsp;Art Biennale<br /><br />ShyBot has no function in the traditional sense. It does not serve us; it probably will not enslave us (perhaps only our imagination). Instead, this robot is programmed to&nbsp;run. To run immediately, with nervous electric heartbeat, in the opposite direction as soon as it senses the presence of a human being.</p>\r\n<h3>Imagine a shy robot</h3>\r\n<p>Shyness is considered a trait unique to the human condition &mdash; no animals, let alone machines, can be ever be shy. The story goes that shyness is a reflection of our self-consciousness, of our uncertainty about who we are in relationship to a world made up of other uncertain beings. As humans we arecondemned&nbsp;to be free: there are no moral supports, no justifications, and no algorithms on which we can base our decisions. We must make and remake our significance within that world, constantly and from moment to moment.</p>\r\n<p>The ShyBot, equipped with a camera, transmits to The Lab a live stream of its point-of-view &ndash; a view based on an algorithm designed precisely to evade the human perspective. This is Norma Jeane&rsquo;s fantasy of the desert sublime: the machine is let loose in the landscape, free of the human determinism that thus far framed its existence, and we, in turn, are free to imagine a world liberated from the indeterminacy of&nbsp;us.</p>\r\n<p>Follow the shybot on:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://shybot.codame.com\">shybot.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<h3>Panel Discussion</h3>\r\n<p>A discussion on the relationship between human and artificial intelligence, with an anthropologist, a designer, and a physicist.</p>\r\n<p>WHEN: Saturday, March 4, 7:30-8:30pm</p>\r\n<p>WHERE: The Lab,&nbsp;2948 16th St, San Francisco</p>\r\n<p>WITH:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/artists/norma-jeane\">Norma Jeane</a>, artist<br />David Moretti, creative director<br /><a href=\"/artists/eric-hanson\">Eric Hanson</a>, designer of the SHYBOT<br />Tobias Rees, anthropologist<br /><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federico_Faggin\">Federico Faggin</a>, physicis,&nbsp;inventor and entrepreneur, widely known for designing the first commercial&nbsp;microprocessor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A powerful question that emanates from the Shybot concerns similarity and difference between &lsquo;the&rsquo; human and &lsquo;the&rsquo; machine. Can one draw clear boundaries between humans and machines? It is common wisdom that humans think (and are shy) &ndash;&ndash; and that machines neither think nor are shy. Machines are mute, cold, endowed with neither reason nor emotion.</p>\r\n<p>But what if &hellip; ?</p>\r\n<p>What would it mean to discover a shared ground between humans and machines? What would it mean to think about both humans and machines from the perspective of this commonality? What new, what unexpected understanding of the human &ndash;&ndash; or of machines &ndash;&ndash; would emerge? Or is this all futile nonsense, because humans are humans and machines machines?</p>\r\n<h3>The Exhibition</h3>\r\n<p>Norma Jeane stages&nbsp;Scene with ShyBot&nbsp;as liberation at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.thelab.org/projects/2017/2/27/norma-jeane-scene-with-shybot\">The Labs</a>, San Francisco, Monday, February 27 &mdash; Saturday, March 4,&nbsp;5:30-7:30pm&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Curated by Dena Beard and Marina Pugliese and is a collaboration between&nbsp;The Lab and the IIC&nbsp;(Italian Cultural Institute - San Francisco)&nbsp;with support of Desert X and CODAME ART+TECH.</p>\r\n<p><br />Norma Jeane: Scene with ShyBot is part of the <a href=\"http://mappingthecity.org\">Mapping the City</a>&nbsp;project.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/itt.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Shybot-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'norma-jeane,jordan-gray,donald-hanson,eric-hanson,ben-lerchin,bruno-fonzi', 'shybot', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(75, 'Maker Faire', 'maker-faire', '2017-05-19', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/maker-faire.png', '<p>CODAME will be showing off its bots at the @<a href=\"http://makerfaire.com/\">MakerFaire</a>&nbsp;on May 19-21, 2017.</p>\r\n<p>Looking for <a href=\"/pages/join-us\">volunteers, artists and new projects</a> to bring with us!</p>\r\n<p>Stay tuned for more news and make sure to come see us&nbsp;there!&nbsp;</p>', 'yagiz-mungan,jamie-kosoy,jordan-gray,bruno-fonzi', 'shybot,illy,receipt-bots', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(76, '3D Web Fest [2017]', '3d-web-fest-2017', '2017-06-30', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/3d-web-fest-2017.png', '<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Experience the most innovative ART+TECH projects, pushing the boundaries of technology&nbsp;in today\'s web browsers in</span><span class=\"s2\">&nbsp;a&nbsp;film festival style showcase. Stunning audio-visual performances created with WebGL, CSS, Javascript will be&nbsp;presented live by&nbsp;</span>top 3D web developers, artists, and creators. Several of the selected works are open source, inviting you to dig into the nuts and bolts after your curiosity and inspiration have been tickled on the big screen!</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>CONNECTION</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The theme for the 3rd annual 3D Web Fest is CONNECTION. Connections have a subtle but powerful presence, weaving through the micro and macro of our lives. Opposites connect to define each other and synapses connect to create a self. Individuals connect into communities and governments connect locales. Join us June 30th, 2017 to turn the online world inside out at the 3D Web Fest.</span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/tumblr_onrddbgr551qixx7ho1_1280.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"s1\">Hosted&nbsp;at&nbsp;</span><span class=\"s1\">the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://palaceoffinearts.org/\"><span class=\"s2\">Palace of Fine Arts Theat</span></a></span><span class=\"s2\"><a href=\"https://palaceoffinearts.org/\">re</a>&nbsp;in San Francisco on June 30th, 2017.&nbsp;</span>Come one, come all, bring your friends, and be ready to have your mind blown.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Program</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><span class=\"s1\">Friday, June 30th, 2017</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>6:00 Welcome Reception Drinks &amp; Snacks&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>6:30 Theater Opens</li>\r\n<li>7:00 Show Begins - Lasts 2 hours with 15-minute intermission&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>9:00 Post-Show Reception - Drinks &amp; Networking with other industry influencers, leaders, and artists</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Tickets</strong></p>\r\n<p id=\"d60d\">Thank you for the support and â¤ for ART+TECH. All of you&nbsp;800 people attending, cheering and playing with us. Making this event even more special.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Sponsorships</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Make an in-kind donation (any amount or equipment appreciated) or become a sponsor. Download the brochure&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B3n40RrM7XaNb3g0Vi1LWkQwc2s/view\">here</a>&nbsp;or <a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\" target=\"_blank\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/pages/support-art-tech\">contact us</a>&nbsp;directly.</p>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Learn about other Partnerships options on our <a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">s</a><a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">upport art+tech</a>&nbsp;page.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As a nonprofit, CODAME accepts tax deductible donations as members of&ldquo;Intersection for the Arts&rdquo; a 501(c)(3) organization.</p>\r\n<p>Special thanks to Salesforce, Mozilla and in particular to the&nbsp;Autodesk team, giving all attendee ticket fee&rsquo;s go direct to CODAME in support for our ART+TECH program.</p>\r\n<h3><img style=\"font-size: 11px;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/3d-web-fest-20173.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Volunteers</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/bghi8MPNL7ru8IDQ2\">Apply</a>&nbsp;to be part of the magic! We&rsquo;re looking for outstanding volunteers&nbsp;to support this event and our ART+TECH initiatives.</p>\r\n<p>What are the benefits to you? It&rsquo;s a fun and extremely rewarding experience as you learn new skills and pass your knowledge on to others. You&rsquo;ll meet like-minded people, make friends&nbsp;and build a network of people from all backgrounds who share a common passion for ART+TECH.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ModBod Gallery from&nbsp;3d Web Fest [2017]</h3>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://sketchfab.com/playlists/embed?collection=704ffe3afabb412b8fb477ea2d1e9805\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal; margin: 5px; color: #4a4a4a; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/collections/3dwebfest-2017?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">3dWebFest 2017</a> by <a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME</a> on <a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">Sketchfab</a></p>\r\n<p><!-- pagebreak --></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>3D Web Fest [2017]&nbsp;Highlights</h3>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/227759957\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Codame Code of Conduct</a> for all event attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Palace of Fine Arts photograph by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.keithbodziak.com/\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.keithbodziak.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1498630247970000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFnE-yCKcoMvn6LQRsAxwLtyx7dDg\">http://www.keithbodziak.com/</a></p>', 'mr-doob,jonobr1,marpi,yanling-he,yagiz-mungan,matt-deslauriers,will-eastcott,eve-weinberg,diego-marcos,pol-clarissou,izaak-meckler,juan-miguel-de-joya,ivan-moreno,delia-otetea,can-buyukberber,jeffrey-bryant,george-hurd,sheltron,natalie-sun,lil-pdf,travis-bennett,anastasiia-vedernikova,joe-pea,kinetech-arts,shiya-luo,vanessa-chang,jordan-gray', 'modbod,levels,audiograph,anxiety-brain,what-is-it-like-to-be-a-bat,after-the-flood,a-saturday-night,wish-fishing,under-neon-lights,echolocation-san-francisco,on-love,from-sea-from-land,odra,quatre-mains,duality,mojimixer,polydance', 'autodesk,mozilla,salesforce,silverdraft', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(77, 'CODAME âœ˜ SF Beta', 'codame-sf-beta', '2017-03-29', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-sf-beta.jpg', '<h2>Welcome to Age of Automation: Robotics, AI, and Intelligent Systems</h2>\r\n<p>CODAME is proud to participate in SF Beta\'s special evening focused on innovations at the forefront of automation.<br /><br />Whether it takes the form of a physical robot, an AI algorithm, or a series of \"bots\" deployed in the cloud, Automation is more than just a buzzword &ndash; it\'s a harbinger of progress, transformation, and growth.<br /><br />On Wednesday, March 29, join us for an evening showcase presenting ten startups that are pushing the edge of Automation into new and never-before-seen frontiers.</p>\r\n<h2>WHEN &amp; WHERE</h2>\r\n<p>March 29, 2017<br />From 5:00 PM until 9:00 PM<br />SF BuzzWorks<br />365 11th St., San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/sf-beta-age-of-automation-presented-by-pathbreaker-ventures-tickets-27598663345\" target=\"_blank\">Buy tickets now!</a></p>\r\n<div><img src=\"/uploaded_images/shybot-panel-and-exhibition1.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>', 'donald-hanson,jordan-gray', 'shybot', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(78, 'Bot Like Me', 'bot-like-me', '2017-05-20', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/bot-like-me.png', '<p>As more humans turn to apps and websites to find relationships, a growing non-human presence is rising to meet them. The &ldquo;Bot Like Me&rdquo; symposium explores the transformations emerging from this new frontier of&nbsp;human-machine relationships.&nbsp;Today, we have more smart machines around us, more bots than humans on the web, virtual assistants in our homes, bedrooms and pockets.</p>\r\n<p>The Bot Like Me symposium&nbsp;invites designers, technologists, artists, and writers to share perspectives on the growing intimacy and emotional relationships we have with&nbsp;algorithms, data, and machines &ndash; and the impact they all have on us.</p>\r\n<p>Location: swissnex San Francisco, Pier 17, Suite 800,&nbsp;San Francisco</p>\r\n<p>Date: May 20, 2017 from 1:30 pm to 10:00 pm&nbsp;PST</p>\r\n<p>RSVP: Get $10 <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bot-like-me-symposium-tickets-33743914958?discount=codame\">discount</a> using promo code: \'<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bot-like-me-symposium-tickets-33743914958?discount=codame\">codame</a>\'&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Program</h2>\r\n<p>See full prorgam&nbsp;on the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/event/bot-like-me/\">Swissnex SanFrancisco</a>&nbsp;event page.</p>\r\n<p>1:30pm&nbsp;&ndash; doors open<br />2-2:10 &ndash;&nbsp;opening remarks by Sophie Lamparter and Luc Meier<br />2:10-3:30 &ndash;&nbsp;sessions with !Mediengruppe Bitnik, Annalee Newitz, Liesl Yearsley, Jacqueline Feldman<br />3:30-3:50 &ndash;&nbsp;break<br />3:50-5:10&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;sessions with Christopher Noessel, Jo&euml;l Vacheron, Steve Omohundro, Liz Klinger<br />5:10-5:30&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;break<br />5:30-6:30&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;closing panel: the bot makers<br />6:30&nbsp;&ndash; dinner and&nbsp;DJ: Forlove (Jasper Speicher)</p>\r\n<p>Please note:&nbsp;the Bot Like Me @Night event with Alex Murray-Leslie has been cancelled.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Hosts</h1>\r\n<h2>Sophie Lamparter</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/sophie_web-e1493413843669.jpg\" alt=\"Sophie Lamparter\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/sophielamparter\">Sophie Lamparter</a>&nbsp;is an&nbsp;Associate Director at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/\">swissnex San Francisco</a>. By building networks in science, technology, art, and innovation, she has spearheaded interdisciplinary programs at the edges of art/technology and art/science. She believes in the power of dialogue and is passionate about finding new talent with a creative approach to technology. Sophie&rsquo;s most recent initiative is&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/media/latest-news/dart-17-a-test-laboratory-for-interactive-experiences-objects-and-tools-in-san-francisco/\">DART 17</a>, a testing lab for interactive projects. She is a 2017 jury member at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://starts-prize.aec.at/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Priz Ars Electronica STARTS</a>&nbsp;(Science +Technology + Arts), a new initiative by the European Commission to award artistic projects that drive&nbsp;innovation for industry and research.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><!-- pagebreak --></p>\r\n<h2>Luc Meier</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/LK_luc_meier_12.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/LK_luc_meier_12.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/LK_luc_meier_12-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/LK_luc_meier_12-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"Luc Meier\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p>Luc Meier&nbsp;is a former Associate Director of swissnex San Francisco, Luc was instrumental in setting up the organization&rsquo;s art-technology interface program with partners such as the Swiss Arts Council, Pro Helvetia and a broad range of U.S partners. Luc is currently the Head of Content and curator in chief for the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.artlab.epfl.ch/\" target=\"_blank\">ArtLab Initiative</a>&nbsp;at the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology in Lausanne (EPFL). EPFL ArtLab is a programmatic initiative aiming to position the school&rsquo;s research-education-tech transfer pipeline in the cultural domain through public programs combining art, science and technology.</p>\r\n<h2><!-- pagebreak --></h2>\r\n<h1>Speakers</h1>\r\n<h2>!Mediengruppe Bitnik (via Skype)</h2>\r\n<h3>Desperate Times Call for Desperate Measures, lol</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/03/bitnik.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/03/bitnik.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/03/bitnik-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/03/bitnik-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"!Mediengruppe Bitnik\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p>!Mediengruppe Bitnik&nbsp;live and work in Zurich/Berlin. They are contemporary artists working on, and with, the Internet. Their practice expands from the digital to physical spaces, often intentionally applying loss of control to challenge established structures and mechanisms.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwww.bitnik.org/\">!Mediengruppe Bitnik&rsquo;s</a>&nbsp;works formulate fundamental questions concerning contemporary issues.&nbsp;!Mediengruppe Bitnik are Carmen Weisskopf and Domagoj Smoljo. Their accomplices are the London filmmaker and researcher Adnan Hadzi, and the reporter Daniel Ryser.</p>\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h2><!-- pagebreak --></h2>\r\n<h2>Annalee Newitz</h2>\r\n<h3>Investigating the Ashley Madison Data Dump: Sex and/or Fantasies in the Age of Bots</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Annalee.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Annalee.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Annalee-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Annalee-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"Annalee Newitza\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://twitter.com/annaleen\" target=\"_blank\">Annalee Newitz</a>&nbsp;is an author and journalist who broke the story in 2015 about bots in the Ashley Madison database. She is the Tech Culture Editor at Ars Technica, and the founding editor of io9. Previously, she was the editor-in-chief of popular tech site Gizmodo. She&rsquo;s the author of Scatter, Adapt and Remember: How Humans Will Survive a Mass Extinction (Doubleday and Anchor), which was a finalist for the LA Times book prize. Her first science fiction novel, Autonomous, will be released from Tor in 2017. It is about robots. Learn more at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.techsploitation.com/\">www.techsploitation.com</a>.</p>\r\n<h4><!-- pagebreak --></h4>\r\n<h2>Ben Parr</h2>\r\n<h3>The Bot Makers</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/webBen_Headshot.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/webBen_Headshot.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/webBen_Headshot-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/webBen_Headshot-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"Ben Parr\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/benparr/\" target=\"_blank\">Ben Parr</a>&nbsp;is the author of the best-selling book&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.captivology.com/\">Captivology: The Science of Capturing People&rsquo;s Attention</a>,&nbsp;named the top marketing book of 2015 by&nbsp;Strategy+Business Magazine&nbsp;and&nbsp;Small Business Trends. He is Co-Founder and CMO of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://octaneai.com/\">Octane AI</a>, the easiest way to create a bot and engage your audience via messaging. He sits on the advisory boards of Lufthansa Airlines, Rebelmouse, AngelHack, UploadVR, LeadIQ, DropIn, and Ustream (acquired by IBM). Previously, Parr was a general partner at DominateFund, a columnist and commentator at&nbsp;CNET, and Co-Editor and Editor-at-Large of&nbsp;Mashable. He is a member of the&nbsp;Forbes 30 Under 30.</p>\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h4><!-- pagebreak --></h4>\r\n<h2>Christopher Noessel</h2>\r\n<h3>2,752 Years of Bots&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/chrisnoessel.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/chrisnoessel.png 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/chrisnoessel-160x160.png 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/chrisnoessel-150x150.png 150w\" alt=\"Christopher Noessel\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p>Christopher Noessel&nbsp;is the Global Design Practice Manager with IBM, bringing IBM design to clients. He teaches, speaks about, and evangelizes design internationally. He&nbsp;investigates and speaks on topics ranging from interactive narrative to ethnographic user research, interaction design to generative randomness, and designing for the future. He is keeper of the blog&nbsp;<a href=\"http://scifiinterfaces.com/\" target=\"_blank\">scifiinterfaces.com</a>&nbsp;and author of Designing Agentive Technology: AI That Works for People (Rosenfeld Media, 2017)</p>\r\n<h2><!-- pagebreak --></h2>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>Jacqueline Feldman</h2>\r\n<h3>Other than Human</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Jacqueline.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Jacqueline.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Jacqueline-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Jacqueline-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"Jacquelyn Feldman\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p>Jacqueline Feldman&nbsp;is a Brooklyn-based writer and designer of bot personalities. She has contributed to publications such as The Atlantic, Guernica, The New Inquiry, The New Republic, The New Yorker, The White Review, and Real Life. Her AI design work has been featured in the Guardian, Technical.ly Brooklyn, Refinery29, and in a video profile at Engadget. As a 2012-2013 Fulbright Fellow to France in Journalism, she reported about squatter communities; she has also worked as a translator of fiction and screen and stage plays from French and taught at Panth&eacute;on-Assas University.<br /><!-- pagebreak -->&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Jo&euml;l Vacheron</h2>\r\n<h3>dadaBOT</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.joelvacheron.net/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Joel-copy.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Joel-copy.png 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Joel-copy-148x150.png 148w\" alt=\"Joel Vacheron\" width=\"200\" height=\"203\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.joelvacheron.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Jo&euml;l Vacheron</a>&nbsp;writes about visual culture and the impact of technology on our ways of seeing. He is currently senior lecturer and researcher in visual communication at the University of Art and Design in Lausanne (ECAL) and freelance on diverse editorial projects. He recently published with Nicolas Nova &ldquo;DADABOT: An Introduction to Machinic Creolization,&rdquo; a book about the role of software and bots in cultural production, and the hybridization of cultural forms (music, visual arts, literature) produced by digital technologies. It deals with Twitter bots, generative music, software-based literature, and &ldquo;all those weird art/design experiments&rdquo; with digital hybridization and mash-ups.</p>\r\n<p><!-- pagebreak --></p>\r\n<h2>Jordan Gray</h2>\r\n<h3>Shybot</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/starpause\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/just-jordan-200-copy.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/just-jordan-200-copy.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/just-jordan-200-copy-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/just-jordan-200-copy-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/starpause\" target=\"_blank\">Jordan Gray</a>&nbsp;is representing CODAME, who built&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/shybot\">Shybot</a>&nbsp;with six&nbsp;artist-engineers working under the name of Norma Jeane. Shybot has no function in the traditional sense. Rather, it&rsquo;s been programmed to run away from any human it senses. Premiered at Desert X Biennial in Coachella Valley, Shybot captured the hearts of millions as it was covered by New York Times, Vice, Engadget and many more.&nbsp;<a href=\"/\">CODAME</a>&nbsp;was founded in 2009 by Jordan Gray and Bruno Fonzi to celebrate ART+TECH. Since then CODAME has featured over 200 artists at 60 plus events filled with interactive installations and inspiring experiences. Shybot is one of over 20 projects CODAME has built from scratch.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><!-- pagebreak --></p>\r\n<h2>Liesl Yearsley</h2>\r\n<h3>Truth vs Fiction: Learnings from Hundreds of Millions of Chats</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/liesl/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/lieslyeardly.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/lieslyeardly.jpg 187w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/lieslyeardly-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/lieslyeardly-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"liesl yearsley\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/liesl/\">Liesl&nbsp;Yearsley</a>&nbsp;was CEO of the&nbsp;Artificial Intelligence company Cognea, which was acquired by IBM and is now an integral part of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ibm.com/watson/\" target=\"_blank\">Watson</a>. Prior to that, she was founder&nbsp;and CEO of an AI search engine company, which expanded across Asia and went public overseas. Her research background is in cognitive sciences, and Yearsley has four&nbsp;patents in the field.</p>\r\n<h2><!-- pagebreak --></h2>\r\n<h2>Liz Klinger</h2>\r\n<h3>Great Vibes: How can a vibrator create language, confidence, and intimacy?</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Liz-Lioness.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Liz-Lioness.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Liz-Lioness-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/Liz-Lioness-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"Liz Klinger - Lioness\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p>Liz Klinger&nbsp;is the co-founder and CEO of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://lioness.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Lioness Health</a>, a company dedicated to improving the lives of women by opening up the conversation around women&rsquo;s sexual health using technology. Their first product is a smart vibrator with&nbsp;integrated sensors and an intuitive design to help measure woman&rsquo;s sexual response.&nbsp;Liz has been featured in the The New York Times&rsquo;s Women of the World and was named a Ladies We Love by Ravishly. She has also appeared the Huffington Post Live&rsquo;s morning show and spoken at top universities about women&rsquo;s health and technology. She&rsquo;s also an award-winning artist&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><!-- pagebreak --></h4>\r\n<h2>Steve Omohundro</h2>\r\n<h3>Bots for a Better World</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://steveomohundro.com/\"><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_steve_omohundro1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_steve_omohundro1.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_steve_omohundro1-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_steve_omohundro1-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"Steve Omohundro\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://steveomohundro.com/\">Steve Omohundro</a>&nbsp;founded Possibility Research and Self-Aware Systems to develop beneficial intelligent technologies. He has degrees in Physics and Mathematics from Stanford, and a Ph.D. in Physics from Berkeley. He was a computer science professor at the University of Illinois and cofounded the Center for Complex Systems Research. He designed the programming languages StarLisp and Sather, wrote the 3D graphics system for Mathematica, and invented many machine learning algorithms including manifold learning, model merging, bumptrees, and family discovery. He has built systems that learn to read lips, control robots, and induce grammars.<br /><!-- pagebreak --></p>\r\n<h1>Performances</h1>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Forlove</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://forlove.forloveforlove.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_Forlove.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_Forlove.jpg 200w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_Forlove-160x160.jpg 160w, http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2017/04/web_Forlove-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"Forlove (Jason Speicher)\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://forlove.forloveforlove.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Forlove</a>&nbsp;is San Francisco&rsquo;s&nbsp;Jasper Speicher&nbsp;in an underground electronic sandbox of&nbsp;synthesizers and microphones. His sound is a moving target, with introspection, texture, and body movement always at its center.&nbsp;Specializing in deeply authentic and retro-touched music for physical dancing and&nbsp;mental drifts, Jasper conceived Forlove as a solo project after time spent playing in a number of Bay Area bands.&nbsp;Jasper studied engineering, sculpture, and computer music at Brown University, started playing in bands, and now takes a personal and deeply felt approach to electronic music. He invites you to come dance with him.</p>\r\n<h2>Exhibition</h2>\r\n<p>swissnex Gallery\'s exhibition&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/event/bitnik-san-francisco/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Desperate times call for desperate measures, lol</a>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwwww.bitnik.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">!Mediengruppe Bitnik</a>&nbsp;personifies gigabytes of chatbot script data from the hack of adult website Ashley Madison. The hack of the dating website revealed that virtually no human women were present, and that 75,000 female chatbots were created to fuel the&nbsp;illusion of casual sex opportunities to millions of high paying men subscribers.&nbsp;The artists rebuilt 51 San Francisco fembots for the swissnex gallery to explore these human-bot relationships. Does it matter that users are chatting with bots and not humans? Why? How did the system work? How was trust built into it? Were these relationships &lsquo;fake&rsquo; or &lsquo;real&rsquo;?</p>', 'norma-jeane,bruno-fonzi,jordan-gray', 'shybot', 'swissnex-san-francisco', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(79, 'ART+TECH Festival [2018]', 'art-tech-festival-2018', '2018-06-04', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-festival-2018.jpg', '<div style=\"text-align: left;\">Presenting our Annual <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a>, a four-day conference with workshops, talks and nightlife event&nbsp;with&nbsp;Immersive, engaging, out of the ordinary experiences.&nbsp;Featuring gallery installations, screenings, and performances&nbsp;@&nbsp;The Midway, San Francisco,&nbsp;June 4-7, 2018.</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This year&rsquo;s ART+TECH&nbsp;Festival, codenamed <strong>#ARTOBOTS</strong>, examines the sphere of robotics, automation, and artificial intelligence.&nbsp;Through art, discussion, play and performance, CODAME probes these potentials.</p>\r\n<h2>#ARTOBOTS</h2>\r\n<p>Automatons&nbsp;orchestrate much of our lives, from the artificial intelligences that translate our global conversations to the industrial robots that give us our digital toys. For many of us, this activity hums as background noise to our existence. Yet these processes in robotics, automation and artificial intelligence are already intimately entwined with our bodies and minds.</p>\r\n<p>In the daily movements we make, the messages we send, and the sensations we experience, we already collaborate with these entities in increasingly varied, tactile and tangible ways. Bots mediate our relationships with ourselves, each other and our environments. While many of these interactions are familiar to us, there are a myriad of ways to move, think, sense and feel with our lively machines.</p>\r\n<div data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4ci08\" data-offset-key=\"rc88-0-0\">\r\n<div data-offset-key=\"rc88-0-0\">\r\n<h2>#Program&nbsp;</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4ci08\" data-offset-key=\"8109e-0-0\">\r\n<div data-offset-key=\"8109e-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"8109e-0-0\">Day 1: Mon, June 4th - Workshops</span></div>\r\n<div data-offset-key=\"8109e-0-0\">Day 2: Tue, June 5th - Workshops&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4ci08\" data-offset-key=\"28pua-0-0\">\r\n<div data-offset-key=\"28pua-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"28pua-0-0\">Day 3: Weds, June 6th - Talks +&nbsp; Nightlife (opening night)</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4ci08\" data-offset-key=\"esvib-0-0\">\r\n<div data-offset-key=\"esvib-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"esvib-0-0\">Day 4: Thur, June 7th - Talks + Nightlife&nbsp;</span>(closing night)</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Bringing artists, inventors, dancers, creative technologists, and other thought leaders together in conversation and exploration. By day, an interdisciplinary&nbsp;gathering of innovators will give workshops and lectures on the field\'s urgent questions and latest developments. By night, we will wander the imaginative terrain of interactive installations and performance. We will showcase ambitious explorations in the field of&nbsp;ART+TECH, from&nbsp;work imagining future machines to intelligent automations crafting masterpieces before your eyes.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647\">Get your ticket</a>&nbsp;today!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647?ref=ebtnebregn\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"Eventbrite - ART+TECH Festival [2018]\" /></a></p>\r\n<h2>#Workshops<strong>&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<h2><strong><img src=\"/uploaded_images/visual-strategies-for-neural-artistic-style-transfer1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></strong></h2>\r\n<p>Building and exploring new media boundaries with artists, coders, designers, performers, musicians and other curious people like you.</p>\r\n<p>Day 1: Monday, June 4th @ 6:30</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Workshop</strong>:&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/workshop-visual-strategies-for-neural-artistic-style-transfer\">Visual Strategies for Neural Artistic Style Transfer</a>&nbsp;- Neural Network and Deep Learning Workshop for Artists with&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/gary-boodhoo\">Gary Boodhoo</a></li>\r\n<li><strong>Workshop</strong>:&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/workshop-spatial-audio\">Spatial Audio</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Three-dimensional experiences of sound and music bring people together, catalyzing shared moments of inspiration, empathy, and wonder with <a href=\"/artists/christopher-willits\">Christopher Willits</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Day 2: Tuesday, June 5th @ 6:30</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Workshop</strong>:&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/workshop-fashion-technology\">Fashion Technology</a>&nbsp;- Are you inspired to create high tech wearables but don&rsquo;t know where to start? The Fashion Technology workshop with <a href=\"/artists/anina-net\">Anina Net</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"/artists/cindy-clark\">Cindy Clark</a> is a great jumping off point.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Workshop</strong>:&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/workshop-twitbot-chopshop\">Twitbot Chopshop</a>&nbsp;- Build a Twitter bot with <a href=\"/artists/yiying-lu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists/yiying-lu\">Yiying Lu</a> and <a href=\"/artists/lil-pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists/lil-pdf\">Lil PDF</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"color: #0000ee; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400; text-align: center;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"Eventbrite - ART+TECH Festival [2018]\" /></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>#Talks</strong>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/43f6d79000e02a74159faa0b76fa15726.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"717\" height=\"474\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\">Salon style conversations, 20 mins talk&nbsp;+ 10 mins Q&amp;A,&nbsp;and panels, with top speakers in the art, robotics and human robotics interaction industry.</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><em>Day 3: Wednesday,&nbsp;</em>June 6th from 9:30am to 5pm</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Start the day with some&nbsp;Yoga, taught by the dynamic&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.vazayoga.com/\">VaZa</a>. Bring your own mat.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/ken-goldberg\">Ken Goldberg</a>,&nbsp;artist and professor UC Berkeley, and a pioneer in internet-based robotic telepresence and Cloud-Based Robotics</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/starpause\">Jordan Gray</a> &amp; <a href=\"/artists/cindy-clark\">Cindy Clark</a> presenting <a href=\"/projects/matchy\">Matchy</a>, a chatbot&nbsp;bringing the connect &amp; collaborate ethos of CODAME to a global scale.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/amy-laviers\">Amy LaViers,</a>&nbsp;assistant professor in the Mechanical Science and Engineering Department at the University of Illinois at Champaign-Urbana and director of the Robotics, Automatic, and Dance (RAD) Lab&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/catie-cuan\">Catie Cuan</a>, performer, choreographer, technologist, TED Resident and Research Technician (RAD Lab)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/liat-berdugo\">Liat Berdugo</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/elia-vargas\">Elia Vargas</a>&nbsp;, co-founders and curators of \'Living Room Light Exchange\'</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/brian-christian\">Brian Christian</a>, award-winning poet, author (<em>The Most Human Human;</em>&nbsp;<em>Algorithms to Live By</em><em>)</em> and journalist</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/tanya-gayer\">Tanya Gayer</a>, curator and writer.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/praba-pilar\">Praba Pilar</a>, diasporic Colombian artist and scholar</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/danielle-siembieda\">Danielle Siembieda</a>, ecoartist and Managing Director of Leonardo: The International Society for Arts, Sciences, and Technology</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/raphael-arar\">Raphael Arar</a>, award-winning artist, designer and researcher at IBM Research</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/evo-heyning\">Evo Heyning</a>, founder and executive producer of new game, interactive, live, VR &amp; 360&nbsp;experiences at&nbsp;Light Lodges</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/scot-gresham-lancaster\">Scot Gresham-Lancaster</a>, musician, designer and research scientist</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/james-morgan\">James Morgan</a>, artist, educator, and researcher, director at Ars Virtua</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Day 4: Thusday, June 7th from 9:30am to 5pm</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bring your own mat (BYOM)&nbsp;to&nbsp;start the day with some&nbsp;Qigong techniques to bring balance and equilibrium to our bodies with&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/starpause\">Jordan Gray</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/laura-sydell\">Laura Sydell</a>, award-winning journalist and Digital Culture correspondent for NPR</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/yiying-lu\">Yiying Lu</a>, award-winning artist, designer, and entrepreneur</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/blinkpopshift\">M Eifler</a>, aka BlinkPopShift, artist and leader in XR design</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/anina-net\">Anina.Net</a>, international model, innovator and fashion technologist</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/laetitia-sonami\">Laetitia Sonami</a>, groundbreaking composer, sound artist and technologist</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/eryk-salvaggio\">Eryk Salvaggio</a>, artist and researcher at swissnex San Francisco, discussing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.swissnexsanfrancisco.org/event/mental-work/\">\"Mental Work\"</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/deanna-hood\">Deanna Hood</a>, electrical engineer whose work focuses on humanitarian applications of engineering and robotics</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/piero-scaruffi\">Piero Scaruffi</a>, cultural historian&nbsp;with several published&nbsp;books on Artificial Intelligence and Cognitive Science.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/alex-reben\">Alex Reben</a>,&nbsp;artist and roboticist, exploring humanity through the lens of art and technology</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/john-campbell\">John Campbell</a>, prize-winning professor of Philosophy at UC Berkeley with interests in psychology, psychiatry and social robots&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/meredith-tromble\">Meredith Tromble</a>, artist and writer mixing drawing, performance, and installation.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/joe-andolina\">Joe Andolina</a>, software engineer and mad scientist&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/bruno-fonzi\">Bruno Fonzi</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/starpause\">Jordan Gray</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"/artists/vanessa-chang\">Vanessa Chang</a>, a fireside chat with the people @ CODAME&nbsp;making this happen!&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>...More to be announced...</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"color: #0000ee; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400; text-align: center;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"Eventbrite - ART+TECH Festival [2018]\" /></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>#Nightlife</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/uploaded_images/0_W_nZG9GQY-DjMaPX.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"715\" height=\"674\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><em>Immersive, engaging, out of the ordinary experiences.&nbsp;Featuring gallery installations, screenings, and performances.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\"><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\">Day 3-4: Wednesday, June 6th and Thurday, June 7th, from&nbsp;</em>6pm to 11pm</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/robot-love-robot-hate\">Robot Love Robot Hate</a>, by&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/mark-klink\">Mark Klink</a>,&nbsp;is a meditation on our hopes and fears about robots and other artificial beings, as reflected in popular media.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/deep-dream-vision-quest\">Deep Dream Vision Quest</a>, a psychedelic journey experience inside a neural network by <a href=\"/artists/gary-boodhoo\">Gary Boodhoo</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/the-soft-machine\">The Soft Machine</a>&nbsp;by the pseudonymous artist <a href=\"/artists/norma-jeane\">Norma Jeane</a>, is an installation built on the absent presence of <a href=\"/projects/shybot\">ShyBot</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/illy\">Illy:&nbsp;Primitive Intelligence</a> is a semi-intelligent system powered by Web Audio API and WebGL created by <a href=\"/artists/yagiz-mungan\">Yagiz Mungan</a></li>\r\n<li>Musical performance by <a href=\"/artists/laetitia-sonami\">Laetitia Sonami</a>, groundbreaking composer, sound artist and technologist, known for developing new and experimental instruments such as the Lady\'s Glove and <a href=\"/projects/spring-spyre\">Spring Spyre</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/time-to-compile\">Time to Compile</a>, a dance performance by<a href=\"/artists/amy-laviers\"> Amy LaViers</a> and <a href=\"/artists/catie-cuan\">Catie Cuan</a> that explores the intimacies of humans and robotics</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/aquarium\">Aquarium</a>, a large-scale, immersive, interactive, physics-enabled generative creature universe that makes music and becomes its own audio-visual show, by <a href=\"/artists/marpi\">Marpi</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/y-ti-the-algorithmic-portrait-artist\">Yoti: The Algorithmic Portrait Artist</a>, an installation by&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/jean-philippe-c-t\">Jean-Philippe C&ocirc;t&eacute;</a>, uses salvaged 1980s pen plotters to draw, on actual paper, the likeness of participants using algorithmically generated squiggly lines</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/artists/happy-valley-band\">The Happy Valley Band</a>, pop music as heard by a computer algorithm. Once Bay Area composer and performer David Kant translates machine learning analyses of pop songs into music notation, Happy Valley Band performs these transcriptions live</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/janus\">Janus</a>, a volumetric film and VR experience by <a href=\"/artists/marta-di-francesco\">Marta di Francesco</a> that explores the duality of time, the meaning of one\'s identity in times of transformation, and the interaction of viewer and virtuality</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/looking-glass\">Looking Glass</a>, an installation by <a href=\"/artists/yagmur-uyanik\">Yagmur Uyanik</a> and <a href=\"/artists/joey-verbeke\">Joey Verbeke</a>, explores the idea of self through the interaction between a robotic parabolic mirror and a viewer</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/the-butterfly-room\">The Butterfly Room</a>, by <a href=\"/artists/cynthia-x-hua\">Cynthia X. Hua</a>, is an interactive projection installation where hand-drawn butterflies are brought to life using computer vision and AI</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/luminai\">LuminAI</a>, by <a href=\"/artists/brian-magerko\">Dr. Brian Magerko</a> and <a href=\"/artists/duri-long\">Duri Long</a>, is a shadow-theater style installation in which participants can engage in collaborative movement improvisation with artifically intelligent virtual dance partners</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/activations\">Activations</a>, by <a href=\"/artists/nolan-lem\">Nolan Lem</a>, activates hundreds of light switches en masse in a cryptic communicative interplay</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/the-masking-machine\">The Masking Machine</a>, a performance by <a href=\"/artists/blinkpopshift\">M Eifler, aka BlinkPopShift</a>, uses recursive landmark detection to apply layer upon layer of digital make-up, building eerie distorted masks of their own face</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/glitch-resistance-on-metal\">Glitch Resistance on Metal</a>, a series of prints and Touch Data Body X, an interactive installation, by <a href=\"/artists/vj-um-amel\">VJ Um Amel, Laila Shereen Sakr</a>, use glitch aesthetics to examine the materiality of power relations and infrastructure in much of the Arab-speaking world</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/degenerative-cultures\">Degenerative Cultures</a>, by <a href=\"/artists/cesar-lois\">Cesar &amp; Lois</a>, creates a&nbsp;bio-digital environment that documents the human impulse to dominate nature</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/automatic-for-the-road\">Automatic for the Road</a>, a film by <a href=\"/artists/lewis-rapkin\">Lewis Rapkin</a>&nbsp;that chronicles the journey of technologist Ross Goodwin and his literary artificial intelligence as they set out to write the longest novel in the English language</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/connec-to-me-2-0\">Connec.to.me 2.0</a>, an installation by <a href=\"/artists/daevron\">daevron</a>, immerses audiences in an environment where music, as a universal auditory stimuli, has spatial coordinates we can sail to by way of a synaptic map and the winds of our senses</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/bloom\">Bloom</a>, an interactive work by <a href=\"/artists/xiaohan-zhang\">Xiaohan Zhang</a>, simulates the birth, growth, bloom, and finally, death, of a generative 3D plant that only blooms once an hour</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/non-viral-series\">Non Viral Series</a>, a robotic performer by <a href=\"/artists/pierluigi-dalla-rosa\">Pierluigi Dalla Rosa</a>, light paints patterns inspired by nature&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/side\">Side</a>, a short film by <a href=\"/artists/snow-yunxue-fu\">Snow Yunxue Fu</a>, explores the interstices of physical and digital&nbsp;space</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/projects/dolores\">Dolores</a>, a short film by <a href=\"/artists/noa-kaplan\">Noa Kaplan</a>, ranges cyborg consciousness, constructions of femininity, agency, and empowerment</li>\r\n<li>Live screenprinting by&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/remixed-ink\">Remixed Ink</a>, with whom you can assemble work from their palette of screens and print your own clothing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>...more to be announced...</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"graf graf--p\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"color: #0000ee; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400; text-align: center;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"Eventbrite - ART+TECH Festival [2018]\" /></h2>\r\n<h2 class=\"graf graf--p\"><strong>#RSVP</strong></h2>\r\n<p>As our ART+TECH Festival historically sells out, we encourage you to <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647\">save your spot</a> today!</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=34741461647&amp;ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"1900\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>#Support</strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><em>CODAME runs not for profit events as members of Intersection for the Arts a 501(c)(3) and all proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\">There are many ways to support us:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\">\r\n<li class=\"graf graf--li\">Get your <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647\">tickets</a> for the workshops, conference talks or nightlife event, see you @ The Midway in June!</li>\r\n<li class=\"graf graf--li\">Invite your friends or your teammates</li>\r\n<li class=\"graf graf--li\"><a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" href=\"/pages/join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/pages/join-us\">Join us</a> a volunteer, we always need one more hand</li>\r\n<li class=\"graf graf--li\">Support ART+TECH and become a <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" href=\"/sponsors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/sponsors\">sponsor</a>. <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/pages/support-art-tech\">Contact us</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">Thank you for your support for ART&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\">&hearts;ï¸&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">TECH !!!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf graf--p\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">* Thank you&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/myles-thompson\">Myles&nbsp;Thompson</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;striking poster design!</span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Codame Code of Conduct</a> for all event attendees.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"color: #0000ee; text-align: center;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"Eventbrite - ART+TECH Festival [2018]\" /></p>', 'ken-goldberg,norma-jeane,laura-sydell,yagiz-mungan,mark-klink,jordan-gray,bruno-fonzi,donald-hanson,piero-scaruffi,gary-boodhoo,cindy-clark,alex-reben,myles-thompson,meredith-tromble,laetitia-sonami,amy-laviers,vanessa-chang,dc-spensley,john-campbell,liat-berdugo,elia-vargas,catie-cuan,marpi,marta-di-francesco,deanna-hood,yagmur-uyanik,yiying-lu,joey-verbeke,cynthia-x-hua,cesar-lois,blinkpopshift,vj-um-amel,brian-christian,tanya-gayer,daevron,jean-philippe-c-t,lewis-rapkin,xiaohan-zhang,nolan-lem,happy-valley-band,evo-heyning,duri-long,brian-magerko,james-morgan,joe-andolina,snow-yunxue-fu,praba-pilar,noa-kaplan,anina-net,pierluigi-dalla-rosa,eryk-salvaggio,remixed-ink,waza,kitty-yeung,vaza,william-s-braintree,lil-pdf,misterinterrupt,mailee-hung,przemys-aw-jasielski,yiyue-chen,benjamin-newman,elisa-sassi', 'illy,shybot,matchy,looking-glass,on-simultaneous-art-and-experiment,automatic-for-the-road,deep-dream-vision-quest,spring-spyre,time-to-compile,aquarium,luminai,degenerative-cultures,robot-love-robot-hate,the-soft-machine,janus,dolores,the-butterfly-room,activations,connec-to-me-2-0,the-masking-machine,y-ti-the-algorithmic-portrait-artist,side,glitch-resistance-on-metal,bloom,non-viral-series,filf,beyond-the-uncanny-valley-of-the-dolls-talk,pattern-matching-dress,locust,laser-cut-led-bracelets,touch-data-body-x,re-memory,populace-guise,selections-from-the-superfluous-automation-series,wild-goose-moving-meditation', 'salesforce,grants-for-the-arts,the-midway,the-shop,daylighted', 'intersection-for-the-arts,leonardo,laser,living-room-light-exchange,360fashion,circuit-launch', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(80, 'FILF - Live Fashion and Music', 'filf---live-fashion-and-music', '2017-07-08', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/filf---live-fashion-and-music.jpg', '<p>ModBod 3d Scans by staRpauSe feeding into live catwalk and stage projections by LiL PDF at the annual FILF (Friends In Loaned Fabrics, Forward Into Lost Futures) music and fashion show held at Classic Cars West, Oakland.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://sketchfab.com/playlists/embed?collection=80633e2f4b5d45ecbb76a0890b164b78\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal; margin: 5px; color: #4a4a4a;\"><a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/collections/filf?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">FILF</a> by <a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME</a> on <a style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #1caad9;\" href=\"https://sketchfab.com?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=embed&amp;utm_campaign=share-popup\" target=\"_blank\">Sketchfab</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><!-- pagebreak --></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>W H A T . T H E . F I L F</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the consideration of everyone Frozen In a Loser Faze, and for all the Fiends In Lucifer\'s Favor, we present F I L F : A Live Fashion + Music Event. This summer, ur friends in loaned fabrics are bringing u forward into lost futures.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MUSIC (FALL for INSOLENT LISTENER FAVS)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/dingbatsuperminx/\" target=\"_blank\">Dingbat Superminx</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/the0classical/\" target=\"_blank\">The Classical</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/DIESEL-DUDES-150835648291518/\" target=\"_blank\">Diesel Dudes</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/felixastroblade/\" target=\"_blank\">Felix Astroblade</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/SPELLLING/\" target=\"_blank\">Spellling</a></li>\r\n<li>Tiny Head</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/FRIENDSOFYEARS/\" target=\"_blank\">Y.E.A.R.S.</a></li>\r\n<li>DJ Sets by Alleyes Manifest</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>FASHION (FANCY the ILLEST LOOKS FATHOMABLE)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Anjelica Colliard</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/memoriamemoria1/\" target=\"_blank\">Armando Resendez</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/cosmicpilgrim/\" target=\"_blank\">Ashley Shotwell&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/bbybangz/\" target=\"_blank\">BB Bangz</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/greyonyx/\" target=\"_blank\">Greyonyx</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/hahcouture/\" target=\"_blank\">HAH Couture</a></li>\r\n<li>Io Rose</li>\r\n<li>J. Sayuri</li>\r\n<li>LAF Vintage</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/luciagoodbag/\" target=\"_blank\">Lucia Goodbag</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/maryweatherusa/\" target=\"_blank\">Mary Weather</a></li>\r\n<li>Maya Songbird</li>\r\n<li>Name</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/spaceparty/\" target=\"_blank\">NI&Ntilde;A PI&Ntilde;A</a></li>\r\n<li>Proper Attire US</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/fruiting.body/\" target=\"_blank\">Rebecca Heikkila</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/lorrainegoldenhar/\" target=\"_blank\">Teryn Brown</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tobangus/\" target=\"_blank\">Tobangus</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/toneoutdesign/\" target=\"_blank\">Tone Out Design</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/unhexing/\" target=\"_blank\">Unhexing</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/doggiechow/\" target=\"_blank\">Pauline poderoso</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/soulybaysed/\" target=\"_blank\">Imani Wilson</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/carolynvalentine/\" target=\"_blank\">Carolyn Valentine</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Fly In Looking Fabulous +&nbsp;let the Forces In Left Field move u til the Fear Is Lost Forever!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>F I L F . L O V E S . Y O U</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><!-- pagebreak --></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Classic Cars West Is Fully Wheelchair-Accessible . Please Be Considerate of Chemical Sensitivities . No Non-Consensual Sleaze . No TERFs . No Racists . No Fascists . No Problems ðŸ‘Œ <a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Codame Code of Conduct</a> for all atendees.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'lil-pdf,jordan-gray', 'modbod,filf', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(81, '3D Web Fest Salon [2017]', '3d-web-fest-salon-2017', '2017-08-02', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/3d-web-fest-salon-2017.gif', '<p>3D Web Fest Salon is a perfect chance to catch CODAME Featured Artists in an intimate environment! A much needed offering considering the 800 people we packed into the Palace of Fine Arts for our amazing&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/3d-web-fest-2017\">3D Web Fest 2017</a> event.</p>\r\n<h3>Program</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>6pm Doors open, food and drinks served.</li>\r\n<li>Socialize with 3d Web Fest artists and your peers, the most forward thinking engineers and designers in the bay area!</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.mozvr.com/a-painter/\" target=\"_blank\">A-Painter</a>, a Web VR drawing app, demonstrated by CODAME Featured artists.</li>\r\n<li>Try your own hand at A-Painter to experience the joy of getting creative in VR with WebGL at your fingertips.</li>\r\n<li>Premiere&nbsp;showing of the 3d Web Fest 2017 highlight reel.</li>\r\n<li>10pm lights out, where\'s the after party? ðŸ˜‰</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; text-align: left;\"><iframe src=\"//eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=36452544542&amp;ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"350\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Ticket sales support creativity in San Francisco through the CODAME ART+TECH program. Profits are split with Featured Artists!</p>\r\n<h3>Sponsorships</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Make an in-kind donation (any amount or equipment appreciated) or become a sponsor. Download the brochure&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B3n40RrM7XaNb3g0Vi1LWkQwc2s/view\">here</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\" target=\"_blank\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/pages/support-art-tech\">contact us</a>&nbsp;directly.</p>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Learn about other Partnerships options on our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">s</a><a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">upport art+tech</a>&nbsp;page.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As a nonprofit, CODAME accepts tax deductible donations as members of&ldquo;Intersection for the Arts&rdquo; a 501(c)(3) organization.</p>\r\n<p>Special thanks to Mozilla for providing the event venue, food, and drink!</p>\r\n<h3>Volunteers</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/bghi8MPNL7ru8IDQ2\">Apply</a>&nbsp;to be part of the magic! We&rsquo;re looking for outstanding volunteers&nbsp;to support this event and our ART+TECH initiatives.</p>\r\n<p>What are the benefits to you? It&rsquo;s a fun and extremely rewarding experience as you learn new skills and pass your knowledge on to others. You&rsquo;ll meet like-minded people, make friends&nbsp;and build a network of people from all backgrounds who share a common passion for ART+TECH.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Codame Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all event attendees.&nbsp;</p>', 'yanling-he,yagiz-mungan,travis-bennett,kawandeep-virdee,elisa-sassi,jonathan-wallraven,allen-larson,zizhou-chen,george-hurd,myles-thompson,marpi,lil-pdf,yosun,natalie-sun,vanessa-chang,jordan-gray', 'holoshatter,mojimixer', 'mozilla,autodesk', '', '', '', '0', 'event', NULL, NULL),
(63, 'CODAME âœ˜ Summer Pulse SF', 'codame-summer-pulse-sf', '2016-06-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/summer-pulse.jpg', '<h2>CODAME brings #ModBod3D and #gifSlap at Summer Pulse SF</h2>\r\n<h2><iframe src=\"https://sketchfab.com/playlists/embed?collection=f8ac7b8dc2904183a7edb4853a73e469\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>~~~LOCATION~~~</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Village:&nbsp;</span><span class=\"s1\">470 Stevenson Street, San Francisco</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Date:</strong>&nbsp;Saturday June 11, 2016</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Time:&nbsp;</strong>8PM - 2AM</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>~~~SCHEDULE~~~</strong></p>\r\n<p>Create&nbsp;a 3D body scan of yourself with <a href=\"x-note://blank/projects/modbod3d\"><span class=\"s2\">Modbod3d</span></a> and play with the interactive visuals toy, <a href=\"x-note://blank/projects/gifslap\"><span class=\"s2\">gifSlap</span></a>.</p>\r\n<p><br />CONNECT [8PM-10PM]:&nbsp;<br />---&gt; Get loose, jam out to Deep House Yoga SF Jam session to prepare for the night ahead&nbsp;<br />---&gt;&nbsp;<em>Philosophical Fire Side Chat m</em>oderated by: Anitha Vadavatha (Founder of Misu Labs) with:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jordan Gray (CODAME co-founder&nbsp;<span class=\"s2\"><a href=\"x-note://blank/artists/starpause\">Starpause</a></span>)</li>\r\n<li>The M-Machine</li>\r\n<li>Dan Lynch (Founder of Brandcast)</li>\r\n<li>Chris Tosswill (Founder of Entrigue Me)&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Charles Zhuang (Founder of Sparxo Inc)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br />DANCE [10PM-2AM]:&nbsp;<br />---&gt; Dance to the beats of our headliner, the @M Machine, with support from @Midaz, @Ian Kleinfeld&nbsp;<br />---&gt; Immerse yourself with state-of-the-art panoramic projections, art installations, and lasers at our beautiful venue<br />---&gt; Enjoy our fully-stocked bar with drink specials&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>~~~MUSIC~~~</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The night is headlined by The M Machine with support from other musical acts:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s3\">The M Machine -&nbsp;<a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/themmachine\"><span class=\"s4\">https://soundcloud.com/themmachine</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s3\">Midaz -&nbsp;<a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/m1daz\"><span class=\"s4\">https://soundcloud.com/m1daz</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s3\">Brian Capobianchi -&nbsp;<a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/bcap\"><span class=\"s4\">https://soundcloud.com/bcap</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s3\">Ian Kleinfeld -&nbsp;<a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/ian-kleinfield\"><span class=\"s4\">https://soundcloud.com/ian-kleinfield</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px; margin: 5px; color: #4a4a4a;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><button class=\"sparxo-button sparxo-type-1 sparxo-id-99370341\" style=\"padding: 5px 15px; border-radius: 50px; background: magenta; color: #fff; min-width: 200px;\">Buy Tickets</button></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><strong><a href=\"https://events.sparxo.com/SummerPulse\">More information is available&nbsp;here.</a></strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"photo-block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; margin: 20px auto; width: 287.766px; height: 0px; padding-bottom: 287.766px; overflow: hidden;\">\r\n<div class=\"image-wrap\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; overflow: hidden; border: none; cursor: pointer; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 287.766px; height: 287.766px; display: table-cell; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; background: none;\"><img class=\"