(124, 'Laser Talk @ Stanford', 'laser-talk-stanford', '2020-08-27', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/laser-talk.jpg', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">New Paradigms and Spaces for Artistic Expression</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>aka \"Imagining the Post-pandemic Art World\"</strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rrbOvs9WM58\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><sub><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rrbOvs9WM58\">Video recording of the event&nbsp;at a Stanford LASER</a></sub></p>\r\n<p>Computational forms of art have become widespread, especially among the younger generation of artists/inventors, and at the same time the pandemic is forcing us to rethink art forms for an online world. This evening will focus on three examples of how the process and format of making and exhibiting art is changing.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME&nbsp;founders Bruno Fonzi and Jordan Gray, CODAME Featured Artists&nbsp;Don Hanson and Char Stiles on \"New Paradigms and Spaces for Artistic Expression\"&nbsp;Hosted&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">August 27 @ 6pm (PT)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://event.stanford.edu/events/885/88504/\" target=\"_blank\">Register here</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">hosted online from&nbsp;Stanford University&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">by&nbsp;Piero Scaruffi</p>\r\n<p>CODAME&nbsp;is an art and tech platform and organization founded in 2010 in San Francisco by Bruno Fonzi and Jordan Gray. Codame has staged public events such as festivals and exhibitions that have cemented a community of more than 300 artists and inventors. It has recently opened its own online workshops and exhibition gallerys newart.city.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bruno Fonzi</strong> has been in the software industry since he was a teenager, selling his first software product when he was 15. Born in Italy, he studied in London and Sydney before landing in Silicon Valley where he founded his first start-up, Lanica, a mobile gaming solution. He is currently a Director of Engineering at Salesforce.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Jordan Gray</strong> has pioneered digital distribution of music and manga. Under the staRpauSe alias Jordan performs audiovisual sets. He licenses his output under the Creative Commons to encourage remix culture. staRpauSe sause has been reused in movies, games, VR, and multimedia installations. Jordan\'s work has featured in New York Times, Vice, Engadget, and more. Jordan has also led technology, prototyping, and innovation projects for Fortune 500 companies including Walmart, AT&amp;T, Wells Fargo, Intel, Tesla, and Google.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Don Hanson</strong> is an Internet artist, electronic musician, hardware hacker, graphic designer, visual jockey, gif maker, and new media art researcher based in Oakland. In 2020 Hanson created the online exhibition space newart.city that has been used for major exhibitions of online art by Gray Area and SJSU CADRE.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Char Stiles</strong> is a digital artist, educator and programmer. Using computational systems and algorithms she is producing pieces that span disciplines such as video, dance, interactive installation, performance and online works. She has given talks and lead workshops at Carnegie Mellon University, Duke University, MIT and NYU. She was recently granted an NEA-funded artist residency at the Frank-Ratchye STUDIO for Creative Inquiry at Carnegie Mellon University to develop an open-source toolkit for artists. She is currently giving a series donation based creative coding workshops at CODAME.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About LASER</strong></p>\r\n<p>LASER (Leonardo Art Science Evening Rendezvous) Talks is Leonardo\'s international program of evening gatherings that bring artists and scientists together for informal presentations and conversations. LASER Talks were founded in 2008 by Bay Area LASER Chair&nbsp;Piero Scaruffi&nbsp;and are in more than 30 cities around the world.</p>\r\n<p>Special announcement during COVID-19:&nbsp;Our global speaker series, LASER Talks, will continue to convene moving to an online format. We are offering a Zoom Webinar and Meeting capabilities for all our LASER cities and leaders. Please check with your local LASER Host to see how to participate online.</p>\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n<p>This week LASER Talks at Stanford include:</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// Revolution (in politics, art and science)</strong></p>\r\n<p>August 24 @ 6pm with</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.scaruffi.com/leonardo/harris.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" />&nbsp;<img src=\"https://www.scaruffi.com/leonardo/schuld.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" />&nbsp;<img src=\"https://www.scaruffi.com/leonardo/perlmutt.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" />&nbsp;<img src=\"https://www.scaruffi.com/leonardo/scaruffi.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" /><br /><strong>Dawna Schuld</strong>&nbsp;is Assistant Professor of Modern and Contemporary Art History in the Department of Visualization, Texas A&amp;M University.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Steve Harris</strong>&nbsp;lectures at the Department of History of San Francisco State Univ and has researched revolutions in history.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Saul Perlmutter</strong>&nbsp;is a 2011 Nobel Laureate, sharing the prize in Physics for the discovery of the accelerating expansion of the Universe.</p>\r\n<p>+&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// Covid-19: Where we stand</strong></p>\r\n<p>August 26 @ 6pm&nbsp;with</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.scaruffi.com/leonardo/parsonne.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" /><br /><strong>Julie Parsonnet</strong> is the George DeForest Barnett Professor in Medicine and Professor of Health Research and Policy at Stanford University</p>\r\n<p>More&nbsp;information on: <a href=\"https://www.scaruffi.com/leonardo/aug2020.html\">https://www.scaruffi.com/leonardo/aug2020.html</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vTwHttiY2TI8VZLGi4rTcL-HBsT3TYqyuZUnvwRbp024gDPpwdAVmbJn6SWe4DcjuevdzsoQgaxG2Z6/embed?start=false&amp;loop=false&amp;delayms=3000\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>', 'bruno-fonzi,jordan-gray,char-stiles,d0n-xyz,piero-scaruffi', 'new-art-city,code-art-together,codame-artist-collective', '', 'laser', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://event.stanford.edu/events/885/88504/', NULL),
(121, 'Live Streaming Performances', 'live-streaming-performances', '2020-08-24', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/live-streaming-performances.jpg', '<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdAarvqJ8h5HE9KAkQ7MouaqyHStvDGxNWMaGQyJZE7GLdisQ/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"640\" height=\"2777\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loadingâ€¦</iframe></p>', 'natasha-murray,jordan-gray,char-stiles,jeffrey-yip,dj-celeste,kevin-bednar,danielle-rager,crystal-glass', 'dxgpvwz', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', ''),
(125, 'Exposure', 'exposure', '2020-09-10', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/the-grid-exposure-expo.jpg', '<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span data-offset-key=\"939:0\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\"><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-grid-exposure-tickets-115297331422?aff=codame#tickets\">Get Tickets</a></strong></span></h1>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"939:0\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">Exposure </strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"939:1\">is The Grid&rsquo;s new annual festival format, an</span><span data-offset-key=\"939:2\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\"> art + tech expo in San Francisco</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"939:3\">. Through</span><span data-offset-key=\"939:4\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\"> art, panels, talks, and workshops</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"939:5\">, Exposure works towards shaping technological development in a </span><span data-offset-key=\"939:6\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">sustainable and responsible</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"939:7\" data-slate-fragment=\"\"> manner for the benefit of all.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p data-key=\"1067\"><span data-key=\"830\"><span data-offset-key=\"830:0\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">&ldquo;Blurring Borders&rdquo;</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"830:1\"> encompasses our current state while also calling for action. Both art and technology constantly blur the borders of the possible and the imaginable, the limits of human beings, and the separation of man and machine - thus </span><span data-offset-key=\"830:2\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">opening up new unexpected realities</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"830:3\">. We will blur the artificial boundaries between the silos of </span><span data-offset-key=\"830:4\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">art, technology, and policy</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"830:5\">. We will create a shared experience by blurring the polarization within and between different communities.</span></span></p>\r\n<p data-key=\"1067\"><span data-key=\"1068\"><span data-offset-key=\"1068:0\">The first edition of </span><span data-offset-key=\"1068:1\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">The Grid: Exposure - Art + Tech + Policy Days</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"1068:2\"> takes place </span><span data-offset-key=\"1068:3\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">entirely virtually</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"1068:4\"> between September 10-13, 2020.&nbsp;</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"1074:0\">Exposure will be part of this year\'s </span><span data-offset-key=\"1074:1\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">Ars Electronica Festival 2020 \"In Kepler\'s Garden\" </strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"1074:2\">by curating the </span><span data-offset-key=\"1074:3\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">AIxMUSIC Garden Silicon Valley.&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p data-key=\"836\" data-slate-fragment=\"\"><span data-key=\"837\"><span data-offset-key=\"837:0\"><strong data-slate-leaf=\"true\">The Grid</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"837:1\"> is a global platform connecting artists and tech/nologists. It was launched in Silicon Valley by European representatives and has since transformed into a multi-stakeholder platform of international art organizations, for-profit technology companies, representatives of civil society, academic and research institutions, local and international government offices, start-ups and beyond. The Grid incorporates art-thinking practices into the development of new technologies and jump-starts a conversation between artists, technologists, and policy makers from around the world.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p data-key=\"1073\" data-slate-fragment=\"\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'jordan-gray,shaghayegh-cyrous,michael-scherotter,janessa-robinson,mobina-nouri,kat-mustatea', 'voidopolis', '', 'gray-area,open-austria,zero1,mutek-sf,the-grid', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-grid-exposure-tickets-115297331422?aff=codame#tickets', NULL),
(126, 'Generative Drawing', 'generative-drawing', '2020-08-16', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/generative-drawing.jpg', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">#CodeArtTogether&nbsp;<br />with Samarth Gulati</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/generative-drawing-workshop-codearttogether-tickets-115521392595?aff=dotcom#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=115521392595\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Explore using code for creative expression! Learn foundational blocks and combine them in novel ways for more intricate structues. Generate organic shapes with noise and randomness. In the end, you\'ll&nbsp;render your masterpiece as a GIF for future CODAME gallery shows!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center>\r\n<p><video style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" autoplay=\"autoplay\" loop=\"loop\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\">\r\n  <source src=\"http://codame.com/mp4ftp/generative-drawing/teal-defcon-spiral-xsyochpkwo-116042423_750469015788314_3425617130936877408_n.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" />\r\n  Your browser does not support the video tag.</video></p>\r\n</center>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Time Schedule</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sunday, August&nbsp;16th at 11:00am (PT)&nbsp;<a href=\"https://time.is/1100AM_16_August_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/London/Berlin/Hyderabad?CODAME\">Time.Is</a></li>\r\n<li>2 hour duration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Outline</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This workshop is interactive throughout, including partnered exercises in breakout sessions.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Introduction, concepts, and context.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.p5js.org/\">p5Editor </a>interface and accounts.</li>\r\n<li>Fundamental blocks: Point, Translate, Animation, Blur,&nbsp;Noise, and Stroke Weight</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breakout: Experiment with&nbsp;fundamental blocks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Layering blocks:&nbsp;Rotation, Mix with noise, Successive translation, and rotation</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breakout: Experiment with layering blocks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Power blocks: Polar coorinates, Equations, and HSLA Color</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breakout: Experiment with all your powers!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Share creations as a group and next steps.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Skill Level</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all levels.</li>\r\n<li>No specific background required for this workshop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">What to Bring</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer and internet connection.</li>\r\n<li>Create an account on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://editor.p5js.org/\">editor.p5js.org</a>.</li>\r\n<li>For best experience, it\'s recommend to have a second screen (or tablet) for the video streaming and keep your main for computer display for live coding and test your creations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Tickets</h3>\r\n<p>$25 suggested donation with a sliding scale. Get your&nbsp;ticket&nbsp;now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/generative-drawing-workshop-codearttogether-tickets-115521392595?aff=dotcom#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=115521392595\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center>\r\n<p><video style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" autoplay=\"autoplay\" loop=\"loop\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\">\r\n  <source src=\"http://codame.com/mp4ftp/generative-drawing/teal-shape-changer-f84lon1zqz-100576617_253747935857616_2212571649404256766_n.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" />\r\n  Your browser does not support the video tag.</video></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</center><center>\r\n<p><video style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" autoplay=\"autoplay\" loop=\"loop\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\">\r\n  <source src=\"http://codame.com/mp4ftp/generative-drawing/purple-hypnosis-spiral-vs4jfsdyxt-107237564_2647324132184310_8980460998576452385_n.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" />\r\n  Your browser does not support the video tag.</video></p>\r\n</center>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Join us</h2>\r\n<center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/join-us\">Join us</a>. Sponsor, Volunteer or lead a workshop. <br />What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach? <br />Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.&nbsp;<br /><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n</center><center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts <br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'samarth-gulati', 'code-art-together', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.eventbrite.com/e/generative-drawing-workshop-codearttogether-tickets-115521392595?aff=do', NULL),
(127, 'Series: Building Interactive Installations', 'series-building-interactive-installations', '2020-09-27', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/series-building-interactive-installations.jpg', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">#CodeArtTogether&nbsp;<br />with Mirabelle Jones</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/building-interactive-installations-tickets-115806641783?aff=dotcom#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=115806641783\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Learn Arduino and Touch Designer skills to build the interactive installation of your dreams! Playgrounds like Meow Wolf and Museum of Ice Cream have taken the art world by storm but micro controllers for immersive art has a rich history that includes Disney Park Imagineers. Explore how sensors and inputs can be used to trigger meaningful shifts in LED lighting, projection, and sound.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Each of the 5 workshops can be taken alone, but you\'ll get the most out of joining for the entire ride. The sessions are suitable for&nbsp;beginners to both Arduino and TouchDesigner. They will also be helpful to seasoned developers and designers looking to expand on their existing knowledge of interactive systems.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Please note an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/3333\">Arduino Circuit Playground Express</a>, some&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/3333\">Banana Clips</a>, and a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/2185\">USB Cable</a>&nbsp;are required to follow along. Because of unpredictable shipping times we suggest ordering these ASAP!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Time Schedule</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>10am PST for all workshop dates&nbsp;<a href=\"https://time.is/1000AM_30_August_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/London/Berlin/Hyderabad?CODAME\">Time.Is</a></li>\r\n<li>2 hour duration for each workshop.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>It\'s ok to take any of the workshops stand alone, they are all designed to be beginner friendly.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Upcoming Dates:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>9/27</strong> - <strong>Design a room</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Design a room-scale interactive exhibit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Past Dates:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>9/6</strong> -&nbsp;<strong>LED sculpture or wearable</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Build an interactive LED sculpture or wearable with reactive lighting and sound that responds to sensor input using Circuit Playground.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>9/13</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<strong>Video effects</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Uses sensor data from an accelerometer to manipulate video effects.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>9/20</strong> -&nbsp;<strong>Camera input</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Create an interactive installation that responds to movements using camera input with TouchDesigner and Arduino.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>8/30/2020</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<strong>Sound Sculpture / Instrument&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Build your own interactive capacitive touch instrument with Circuit Playground.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"eventbrite-widget-container-115806641783\">\r\n<script src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/static/widgets/eb_widgets.js\"></script>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">// <![CDATA[\r\nvar exampleCallback = function() {\r\n        console.log(\'Order complete!\');\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    window.EBWidgets.createWidget({\r\n        // Required\r\n        widgetType: \'checkout\',\r\n        eventId: \'115806641783\',\r\n        iframeContainerId: \'eventbrite-widget-container-115806641783\',\r\n\r\n        // Optional\r\n        iframeContainerHeight: 425,  // Widget height in pixels. Defaults to a minimum of 425px if not provided\r\n        onOrderComplete: exampleCallback  // Method called when an order has successfully completed\r\n    });\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Skill Level</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all levels.</li>\r\n<li>No specific background required for this workshop.Hardware to purchase</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will need to Bring Your Own Arduino hardware! The entire kit will cost less than $40 with shipping and tax. Don\'t wait until the last minute, especially with unpredictable shipping times.</p>\r\n<p>Adafruit Circuit Playground Arduino hardware:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/3333\">Arduino Circuit Playground Express</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/1008\">Banana Clips</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/2185\">Mirco USB Cable</a> (maybe you already have one around!)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Software to install</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Install free&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.arduino.cc/en/Main/Software\">Arduino</a>&nbsp;softare. Students on windows will also need the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://learn.adafruit.com/introducing-circuit-playground/windows-driver-installation\">Adafruit Driver</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Install free <a href=\"https://derivative.ca/\">TouchDesigner </a>software.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What to bring</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time</li>\r\n<li>For best experience, it\'s recommend to have a second screen (or tablet) for the video streaming and keep your main for computer display for live coding and test your creations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Tickets</h3>\r\n<p>$25 suggested donation with a sliding scale. Get your&nbsp;ticket&nbsp;now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/building-interactive-installations-tickets-115806641783?aff=dotcom#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=115806641783\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/electricjellyfish2_40percent.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/electricjellyfish4.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span data-key=\"2698\">Electric Jellyfish&nbsp;courtesy Mirabelle Jones</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Join us</h2>\r\n<center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/join-us\">Join us</a>. Sponsor, Volunteer or lead a workshop. <br />What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach? <br />Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.&nbsp;<br /><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n</center><center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts <br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'mirabelle-jones,cathy-laughlin', 'code-art-together', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.eventbrite.com/e/building-interactive-installations-tickets-115806641783?aff=dotcom#tick', NULL),
(128, 'Game Design and Coding for Kids with LeapyBird', 'game-design-and-coding-for-kids-with-leapybird', '2017-11-16', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/game-design-and-coding-for-kids-with-leapybird.jpg', '<p>Learn how to build a game with&nbsp;#LeapyBird&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Customize your #LeapyBird with your own designs, sound effects.</p>\r\n<p>With just a few lines of code, make your bird fly and win levels by literally flopping your hands and smile.</p>\r\n<p>An opportunity for kids (and not only) to learn about game design, coding and have fun!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leadybird-at-mini-maker-faire-with-kids-15jpg_16376206283_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"500\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leadybird-at-mini-maker-faire-with-kids-11jpg_16724298126_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"763\" height=\"429\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leadybird-at-mini-maker-faire-with-kids-7jpg_16724292826_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"760\" height=\"570\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leapybird-adoped-by-github_21942678472_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"760\" height=\"570\" /></p>', 'ani', 'leapybird', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', NULL, NULL),
(136, 'Visualize Music Using Hydra Blockly', 'visualize-music-using-hydra-blockly', '2020-12-05', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/visualize-music-using-hydra-blocks.gif', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">#CodeArtTogether<br />with Samarth Gulati</p>\r\n<h3>What if audio reactive visuals were as easy to create as playing with legos? Use a drag and drop, block based coding environment and they are! Provide instructions to create textures from scratch. Personalize them with symmetry and gradients. Load your own music to bring the visuals to life. Capture your dancing geometric creation to share with workshop peers and the world. Learn each step with <a href=\"https://samarthgulati.com/hydra-blockly\">Hydra Blockly</a> which simplifies coding concepts into interlocking blocks.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this in to your website where you want the widget to appear. Do no change the code or the widget may not work properly. -->\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/450379/chk/2be1/ref/website_widget\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/450379/chk/2be1/ref/website_widget\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- End of Ticket Tailor Widget -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Time Schedule</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sat Dec&nbsp;5, 2020</li>\r\n<li>11am - 1pm PT (2 hours)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://time.is/1100AM_18_October_2020_in_San_Francisco/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\">Time.is Localizer</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Skill Level</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all levels.</li>\r\n<li>No specific background required for this workshop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Workshop Outline</strong></h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li>Intro to Hydra &amp; Blockly interface walkthrough</li>\r\n<li>Oscillator, Noise, Voronoi, Gradient, Custom inputs</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to explore &amp; sharing discoveries</em></li>\r\n<li>Geometry and Color options - Kaleidoscope, Scroll, Scale, Rotate</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to explore &amp; sharing discoveries</em></li>\r\n<li>Audio responsive - FFT, Bins, Isolating frequencies</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to explore &amp; sharing discoveries</em></li>\r\n<li>Next steps: custom Hydra blocks, Live coding</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>What to Bring</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger.</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: 2nd monitor or screen so you can see the Zoom while working.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>We Will Provide</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CODAME Slides</li>\r\n<li>Instructor Slides</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://samarthgulati.com/hydra-blockly\">Hydra Blockly</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Buy tickets for Visualize Music Using Hydra Blocks\" href=\"https://buytickets.at/codame/433765\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://app.tickettailor.com/images/btns/bt_pu.gif\" alt=\"Buy tickets for Visualize Music Using Hydra Blocks\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /> Get tickets now to reserve your spot for <br />an extraordinary learning experience. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/unnamed_(3).gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/unnamed_(2).gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/unnamed_(4).gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">This workshop is part of<br />#CodeArtTogether</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ§ âœ¨</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸŽ¨ðŸš§ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create</span><br /></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ¤©ðŸ’¬ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Celebrate</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The pillars of #CodeArtTogether workshops by CODAME:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Connect</strong> with peers and new neurons in your brain.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Create</strong> art work and generate innovative ideas.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Celebrate</strong> by showing and selling what you build.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We also offer private team building events, <a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">contact us to learn more and support ART+TECH</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Buy tickets for Visualize Music Using Hydra Blocks\" href=\"https://buytickets.at/codame/433765\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://app.tickettailor.com/images/btns/bt_pu.gif\" alt=\"Buy tickets for Visualize Music Using Hydra Blocks\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Join us</h2>\r\n<center>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/join-us\">Join us</a>. Sponsor, Volunteer or lead a workshop.&nbsp;<br />What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;<br />Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>.</p>\r\n<p>All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.&nbsp;<br /><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n</center><center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'samarth-gulati', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://buytickets.at/codame/433765', NULL),
(129, 'Behind the Screens', 'behind-the-screens', '2020-08-25', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/behind-the-screens.gif', '<h3>Introducing CODAME Artists&nbsp;Behind The Screens&nbsp;on KnownOrigin&nbsp;with:</h3>\r\n<p>- Char Stiles</p>\r\n<p>- Snow Yunxue Fu</p>\r\n<p>- Jordan Gray&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Live conversation on</strong></h3>\r\n<p>TUE 25, 8pm (bst)&nbsp;live streaming on&nbsp;YouTube&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zm-3QGgfpVQ\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<h3><strong>In collaboration with&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Serena Tabacchi, Lisa Kolb and the&nbsp;MoCDA: Museum of Contemporary Digital Art</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>', 'snow-yunxue-fu,jordan-gray,char-stiles', '', '', 'knownorigin', '', '', '0', 'event', '', NULL),
(131, 'CODAME ART+TECH Gallery', 'codame-art-tech-gallery', '2020-08-27', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-art-tech-gallery.gif', '<p><strong>JOIN US&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>To celebrate the initial artists, part of the <a href=\"https://shop.codame.com\">shop.codame.com</a> inauguration&nbsp;in a virtual gallery show hosted by newart.city</p>\r\n<p><strong>OPENING NIGHT</strong></p>\r\n<p>Thursday, Aug. 27th at 5:30pm (PST)</p>\r\n<p><strong>WHERE</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://gallery.codame.com\">gallery.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/admin/gallery.codame.com\"><img src=\"https://files.slack.com/files-pri/T024H95R4-F019NETL859/codamegallerypreview.png\" alt=\"\" /><img src=\"/uploaded_images/codamegallerypreview.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>', 'ilithya,char-stiles,pskl,jordan-gray,snow-yunxue-fu,joey-verbeke,mark-klink,yagmur-uyanik', 'new-art-city', '', 'newart-city', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://shop.codame.com', NULL);
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(130, 'Six Hats for Collective Creativity', 'six-hats-for-collective-creativity', '2020-09-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/six-hats-for-collective-creativity.jpg', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">#CodeArtTogether&nbsp;<br />with&nbsp;Shaghayegh Cyrous<br />and Mobina Nouri</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Learn how to separate thinking into six clear functions and roles represented by symbolic \"Thinking Hats.\" By mentally wearing and switching hats, participants can easily focus or redirect thoughts, the conversations and the solutions. Understand the strengths, weaknesses, and your affinity for the different hats to level up your problem solving skills!</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-grid-exposure-tickets-115297331422?aff=codame#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=115297331422\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Time Schedule</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>10am PST on Friday, September 11th (<a href=\"https://time.is/1000AM_11_September_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/London/Berlin/Hyderabad?CODAME\">Time.Is</a>)</li>\r\n<li>2 hour duration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Skill Level</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all levels.</li>\r\n<li>No specific background required for this workshop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>What to bring</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Introduction to creative problem solving.</li>\r\n<li>Breakout groups to pick hats and explore senses.</li>\r\n<li>Instruction on different styles of thinking.</li>\r\n<li>Breakout groups to align one mutual concern/problem.</li>\r\n<li>Homework: participants will have 2 days to explore their solution in real life before sharing it with their peers or on social media.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>De Bono\'s Six Thinking Hats is a powerful technique for creative problem solving and decision making from different points of view. It allows emotion and skepticism to be brought into what might normally be a purely rational process, and it opens up the opportunity for creativity within decision making.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/UZ8vF8HRWE4\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Tickets</h3>\r\n<p>$25 suggested donation with a sliding scale. Get your&nbsp;ticket&nbsp;now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-grid-exposure-tickets-115297331422?aff=codame#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=115297331422\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">#CodeArtTogether</h1>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸŒ±ðŸ§ </span> <span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Grow + Learn</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ’¬ðŸ’ª </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect + Create</span></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸŽ¨ðŸ¤© </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Share + Show</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Connecting, Building, and Sharing are the pillars of <a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">CODAME #CodeArtTogether workshops</a>! Connecting artist and tech community together, learning from each other. Building tangible outcomes in the timeframe of the workshops. Sharing your work is our inspiration to be showcase during and after the workshops.</p>\r\n<p>Workshops are great for team building. They cultivate space to play, which guides sense-making and sparks innovation. In our workshops attendees become featured artists with the option to show their workshop creations in CODAME galleries. <a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">Learn more about this exciting offering</a>!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-grid-exposure-tickets-115297331422?aff=codame#tickets\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=115297331422\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://codame.com/uploaded_images/the-grid-exposure-expo.jpg\" alt=\"Exposure\" /></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400; text-align: -webkit-center;\"><strong>Six Hats for Collective Creativity</strong> is Presented as part of <a href=\"/events/exposure\">EXPOSURE 2020</a>.</span></h2>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"text-align: -webkit-center;\">&ldquo;Blurring Borders&rdquo; encompasses our current state while also calling for action. Both art and technology constantly blur the borders of the possible and the imaginable, the limits of human beings, and the separation of man and machine - thus opening up new unexpected realities. We will blur the artificial boundaries between the silos of art, technology, and policy. We will create a shared experience by blurring the polarization within and between different communities.</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Join us</h2>\r\n<center>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/join-us\">Join us</a>. Sponsor, Volunteer or lead a workshop.&nbsp;<br />What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;<br />Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>.</p>\r\n<p>All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.&nbsp;<br /><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n</center><center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'mobina-nouri,shaghayegh-cyrous', 'code-art-together', '', 'the-grid', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-grid-exposure-tickets-115297331422?aff=codame#tickets', NULL),
(132, 'Discovering Virtual Stages and Performance Platforms', 'discovering-virtual-stages-and-performance-platforms', '2020-09-13', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/discoveries-from-virtual-stages-and-performance-platforms.gif', '<p>This video documents the strategic working session, \"Virtual Stages and Performance Platforms,\" co-presented by EUNIC DC and CODAME. The session gathered leaders and innovators in the performing arts and virtual platforms to explore new formats for digital programming. Partnerships and experimentation continue to create and expand knowledge of the directions in which we could continue taking virtual programming. Documenting session outcomes and charting a path forward for an uncertain, but increasingly virtual, creative future, this video envisions what we might need to make digital cultural programming curatorially coherent, innovative and exploratory, high quality, and interesting for an audience in front of a screen.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Throughout the pandemic, the development of attractive digital cultural programming has accelerated and intensified. It has led to new experiences by forging cultural relationships online and addressing a global audience through virtual means. At the same time, it has been widely acknowledged that &ndash; especially in performing arts fields &ndash; digital formats that are successful with other media cannot always foster the same intimacy, atmosphere, and experience that live performances can foster.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Co-presented with EUNIC DC, this invitation-only strategic working session gathers leaders and innovators in the performing arts and virtual platforms to explore new formats for digital programming, through moderation by Jordan Gray.</p>', 'jordan-gray,claudia-alick,ian-garrett,annastina-haapasaari,drew-lichtenberg,marcus-lobbes,tim-nelson,christine-standfest,rulan-tangen', '', '', 'the-grid', '', '', '0', 'event', '', NULL),
(133, 'Incredible Insights From Art Visualized with Tableau', 'incredible-insights-from-art-visualized-with-tableau', '2020-09-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/incredible-insights-from-art-visualized-with-tableau.jpeg', '<p>Explore how the world&rsquo;s leading visual analytics platform is a forum for expression and inspiration by bringing together the worlds of data and art. Join Tableau experts as they walk through the opportunities for expression, understanding, and community-building of visualized data. The conversation will include discussion of pieces that emerged from working alongside traditional creatives, and those that emerged from the search for voices and insights. Take away a valuable understanding of how shifting the lens on data can wield incredible insights and deliver shareable experiences. Learn more about Tableau&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://public.tableau.com?ref=codame\">free data visualization software</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://thegrid2020exposure.sched.com/event/eF89?iframe=no\">Join us at 1:30pm PT!</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'neil-richards,judit-bekker,andy-cotgreave', '', '', 'the-grid,tableau', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://thegrid2020exposure.sched.com/event/eF89?iframe=no', NULL),
(135, 'Auction: The Creation', 'auction-the-creation', '2020-09-18', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/auction-the-creation.jpg', '<h2 dir=\"ltr\">The <a href=\"https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-560\">Async-hosted auction</a> will be taking place over&nbsp;the week of September 14. Bidding ends on September 18th between 8-10am PST.</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><br /><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Yq6zsKq6_DmDReuJ8wvP_im3c5KtazNFlZRcn7TpmPFInIVXbWcUdlWIK2Omh5f6T0jKjpMNWR0dYL_wtMeb04sgq61rRmMsad6QTywV9a4ihBQ2qPFyJMwGG5ceBbf-Fk20Q1zX\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">CODAME has decided to make a T-shirt of a specified state of the artwork. After the piece is auctioned off on September 18th, we will wait a week for the Layer owners to make their desired changes to the artwork and will gift the Master owner the final T-shirt, as well as offer it as featured merchandise on our Gallery&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/\">Online Store</a>. You can also place&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/products/codame-x-async-art-collaboration-the-creation-t-shirt\">pre-orders</a> for the t-shirt now!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Be sure to follow Async Art on <a href=\"https://discord.gg/Zu2X73q\">Discord</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/AsyncArt\">Twitter</a> so you can get real-time updates on &ldquo;The Creation&rdquo; and all its auctions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/pages/auction-the-creation-a-codame-asyncart-artist-collaboration\">Read more</a> about this cross-contiental collaboration on our blog!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">For those new to Crypto Art here are some resources for you to check out:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">More information about cryptoart and Async Art:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://youtu.be/P_6cjl3bxxw?t=47\">https://youtu.be/P_6cjl3bxxw?t=47</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://youtu.be/P_6cjl3bxxw?t=155\">https://youtu.be/P_6cjl3bxxw?t=155</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here are instructions on how to get started w/ Crypto Wallet:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://www.notion.so/How-Do-I-Start-508cb36dad3e48bd895d942191cb2875\">https://www.notion.so/How-Do-I-Start-508cb36dad3e48bd895d942191cb2875</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'jordan-gray,emi,ooakosimo,janessa-robinson,vans-design', 'the-creation', '', 'async-art', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-560', NULL),
(138, 'E-lit Games (Playing With Words)', 'e-lit-games-playing-with-words', '2020-12-14', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/e-lit-games-playing-with-words.png', '<center style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">Monday, December 14th @ 11:30AM PST (<a href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_14_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\" target=\"_blank\">timezone converter</a>)</center><center style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">\r\n<p id=\"&rdquo;fest-10&rdquo;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong>&nbsp;annual&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n</center>\r\n<h3>Interested in generative poetry and electronic literature? Through collaborative coding projects, we will learn how to build games based on the written word, in the browser. These interactive games will have something in common: they all try to help with the writer\'s block! Bring your imaginary worlds and your creativity to this workshop as we will code interactive games where writing is the main action.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (start) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460516#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a> to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT </strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (end) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SCHEDULE ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mon,&nbsp;Dec 14th, 2020</li>\r\n<li class=\"graf graf--li\">11:30amâ€Š&mdash;â€Š1:30pm PT (2 hours) <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_14_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://time.is/1100AM_18_October_2020_in_San_Francisco/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\">Check your timezone</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž&nbsp;SKILL LEVEL ã€</h3>\r\n<p>We use JavaScript in the workshop. If you are new to JS, please complete this tutorial ahead of time: <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Getting_started_with_the_web/JavaScript_basics\">MDN Getting Started With The Web: JavaScript Basics</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Familiarity with HTML/CSS will be also helpful. Check out <a href=\"https://www.zinesbyjackie.com/activities/build-an-under-construction-page\">Build an Under Construction Mini Site</a> from Zines by Jackie, if you\'re familiar with everything presented they\'re you will be in good shape (and probably smiling from retro cuteness overload). <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Getting_started_with_the_web\">Getting Started With The Web</a> is a more complete guide from MDN. If you\'re short on time just the <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Getting_started_with_the_web/HTML_basics\">HTML Basics</a>&nbsp;are a handy reference.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž WORKSHOP OUTLINE ã€</h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li>Introduction to electronic literature and glitch.com</li>\r\n<li>Walkthough of 3 example e-lit games</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to create, explore, and code</em></li>\r\n<li>Sharing creations and insights</li>\r\n<li>How to remix e-lit games</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout to continue with your original game or remix another game</em></li>\r\n<li>Celebrate your creations &amp; next steps</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž ATTENDES BRING ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger.</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time.</li>\r\n<li>Sign up for a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://glitch.com/\">glitch.com</a> account ahead of time</li>\r\n<li>Optional: 2nd monitor or screen so you can see the Zoom while working.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME PROVIDES ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Instructor Slides</li>\r\n<li>Example projects to clone on glitch.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460516#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a>&nbsp;to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT&nbsp;</strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/e-lit-games-playing-with-words1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME&nbsp;#CodeArtTogether Workshops ã€</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ§ âœ¨</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸš§ðŸŽ¨</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create</span></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ¤©ðŸ’¬ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Celebrate</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Connecting, Creating, and Celebrating&nbsp;are pillars of the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">CODAME #CodeArtTogether workshops</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Workshops are great for team building, remote or IRL. They cultivate space to play, which guides sense-making and sparks innovation. Attendees become featured artists with the option to show their workshop creations in CODAME galleries.&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">Learn more about this exciting offering</a><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486392/chk/4cfa/?modal_widget=true&amp;widget=true&amp;d\">!</a></p>\r\n<p>What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/join-us\">#JOYNT US</a>&nbsp;as a sponsor, volunteer, or workshop leader!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/typewriter-hell-flier.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Support&nbsp;us</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome..</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Join us&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<center>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/join-us\">Join us</a>. Sponsor, Volunteer or lead a workshop.&nbsp;<br />What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;<br />Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>.</p>\r\n<p>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</p>\r\n</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'edith-viau', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460516#ticket_selection', ''),
(139, 'Live Auction: Light Barcode', 'live-auction-light-barcode', '2020-10-16', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/live-auction-light-barcode.png', '<p>Join us on Fri, Oct 16 at 11am in&nbsp;<a href=\"http://t.me/ArtGalleryAuctionHouse\">t.me/ArtGalleryAuctionHouse</a>&nbsp;for a live Auction of Light Barcode by&nbsp;Jordan Gray.</p>\r\n<p>Bidding will be in ETH so top up via&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.coinbase.com/join/gray_pkx\">coinbase</a>&nbsp;(affiliate link) or your favorite crypto on ramp. All are welcome, if you&rsquo;re new to crypto you can still come for the memes and energetic environment!</p>', 'jordan-gray', 'light-barcode', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', '', NULL),
(140, 'ART+TECH Festival 2020 /// JOYNT', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', '2020-12-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt.gif', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; text-align: left;\">Collaborative art is a transformational force that strengthens connections and enhances well-being. Let\'s <strong>JOYNT</strong>&nbsp;together to spark&nbsp;innovative ideas and extraordinary visions! At the 10th annual ART+TECH Festival you will&nbsp;<strong>Connect</strong>&nbsp;with the community,&nbsp;<strong>Create</strong>&nbsp;tangible outcomes, and&nbsp;<strong>Celebrate</strong>&nbsp;creativity.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Watch recordings of 13 Live Events and 16 Workshops from ART+TECH Festival 2020<br />and access 21 Anytime Experiences</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">A post-festival offer for folks who couldn\'t JOYNT us in real time ;)&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\" author-d-iz88z86z86za0dz67zz78zz78zz74zz68zjz80zz71z9iz90z95bcz84zz88z8vz88zz85z26z73zez83zz90zpewjz89zz84zaz90z77c9z76z6z72z\">&atilde;&euro;Ž&nbsp;Live Events Pass&nbsp;&atilde;&euro;</span></h2>\r\n<p>10 days of online content including all live and anytime experiences:</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/events\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://codame.com/events\">Live Events</a></strong>: Time specific happenings such as performances, meet-the-artist sessions, gallery tours, and community meetings.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"/projects\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://codame.com/projects\">Anytime Experiences</a></strong>: Interactive art and digital destinations you can browse at your own leisure.&nbsp;<br /><br />Online Gallery&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://newart.city/show/codame-festival\">&nbsp;2020 [JOYNT] Virtual Gallery</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2><span class=\" author-d-iz88z86z86za0dz67zz78zz78zz74zz68zjz80zz71z9iz90z95bcz84zz88z8vz88zz85z26z73zez83zz90zpewjz89zz84zaz90z77c9z76z6z72z\">&atilde;&euro;Ž&nbsp;Workshops&nbsp;&atilde;&euro;</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>2-3 hour sessions where you\'ll create tangible outcomes.&nbsp;Then stay connected for future inspiration, collaborations, and critiques on the CODAME Discord! You can get tickets to <strong><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame\">individual workshops</a></strong> or get an <strong><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">All Access Pass</a></strong> to attend them all!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2><span class=\" author-d-iz88z86z86za0dz67zz78zz78zz74zz68zjz80zz71z9iz90z95bcz84zz88z8vz88zz85z26z73zez83zz90zpewjz89zz84zaz90z77c9z76z6z72z\">&atilde;&euro;Ž All Access&nbsp;Pass&nbsp;&atilde;&euro;</span></h2>\r\n<p>Access to <strong>all Live Events, Anytime Experiences,&nbsp;</strong>and over <strong>16 Workshops</strong>. Recommend deal for God mode access!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'samarth-gulati,michael-scherotter,max-zsol,abhinay-khoparzi,char-stiles,pikio,jordan-gray,ilithya,ooakosimo,ouchhh,geoffrey-golden,quinn-keck,red-wolf,eliza-struthers-jobin,luluxxx,jj,skipper-gemx,scott-kildall,lia-coleman,michelle-brown,fabin-rasheed,lynette-lee,ash-herr,sam-wray,tim-pietrusky,erica-anderson,donghao-ren,edith-viau,ben-ha,bruno-ruviaro,qiuwen-li,aastha-chawla,josh-mitchell,michael-noonan,ivan-moreno,sven-eberwein,vicente-montelongo,marc-o-matic,mark-savage,manu-luksch,snow-yunxue-fu,janessa-robinson,vans-design,mark-klink,pskl,joey-verbeke,yagmur-uyanik,sukanya-aneja,torin-blankensmith,peter-whidden,hufo,bruno-fonzi,elena-kauffmann,naoto-hieda,illest-preacha,kevin-smuggles,flor-de-fuego,gosh-studio,alex-shortt,william-bear-idressi,claire-abdulla,yiyue-chen-iota,d0n-xyz,lisa-kolb,jilt,nataliia-frank,soliman-lopez', 'minecraft-art-tech-gallery,modbod,holographic-rainbows,the-creation,m-carbon-dioxide,cosmos,vr-music-videos,cangjie-s-poetry,secrets-exchange-crypto-art-generator,i-don-t-know-look-at-it,nexus,arduino-advent,10th-anniversary-art-cards,harddiskmuseum,transcending-taste-in-c0d3-kitchen,glitch-me,spaces-gallery,video-screening', '', 'async-art,newart-city,knownorigin,mocda,tribexr,d2d-art,sketchfab,itseez3d,opensea,cargo,paras', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection', 'festival-grounds-opening,happy-hour-on-discord,mint-crypto-art-tokens,mashup-3d-models-in-blender,modular-audio-visualisation-with-modv,make-art-with-machine-learning,compose-music-with-code,sketching-worlds-in-360,e-lit-games-playing-with-words,sclork-20x20,build-a-virtual-art-gallery-in-minecraft,modv-audio-visual-live-performance,poetic-programming-with-in-verse,botanic-quartet,snipsynth-talk,build-your-being-in-spark-ar,stylize-selfies-with-hydra-blockly,build-an-art-gallery-in-minecraft,ar-vr-art-and-storytelling,regalia-chromology-and-pilgrimage,curiously-minded-live-coding-shaders,creating-vr-music-videos,3d-graphics-and-animation-with-shader-park,transcending-taste-in-c0d3-kitchen-recipes-embedded-developed-and-created-with-algorithms,glitch-me-introduction,build-a-vr-space-with-spaces,poetic-programming-with-in-verse,build-vr-with-js,make-ar-holiday-cards'),
(153, 'Creating VR Music Videos', 'creating-vr-music-videos', '2020-12-18', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/creating-vr-music-videos.png', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Friday, Dec 18, 2020, 5:00pm PST (check your&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7 !important;\" href=\"https://time.is/1000AM_12_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/London/Berlin/Hyderabad?CODAME\">timezone</a>)<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-a7336780-7fff-43db-e918-f1975363585d\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Join Michelle and guests in VR or online as they discuss making virtual reality music videos.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From conception to development, the session will cover the important things you need to think about when creating immersive 360 video clips, along with talking through some of the different art tools and software available for creating virtual experiences.</p>\r\n<p>Taking place in AltspaceVR, attendees can join as avatar guests with a headset or via the online platform, or watch the video stream.</p>\r\n<p>Michelle has created several virtual reality music videos for international and Australian artists and collaborates with other filmmakers, artists and musicians as a VR music video consultant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A selection of Michelle\'s VR Music videos will be available for viewing throughout the Festival as an \"Anytime Experience\" and featured in New Art City.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival Tickets\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'michelle-brown,claire-abdulla', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt'),
(144, 'Make Art with Machine Learning', 'make-art-with-machine-learning', '2020-12-20', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/make-art-with-machine-learning.png', '<center>Sunday, December 20th @ 11:30AM PST (<a href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_20_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\" target=\"_blank\">timezone converter</a>)</center><center>\r\n<p id=\"&rdquo;fest-10&rdquo;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong>&nbsp;annual&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n</center>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-family: Roboto, RobotoDraft, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span>Machine Learning isn\'t just for industry and research! Artists are using machine learning for creative purposes already-- from paintings to poetry!<br /><br />In this hands-on workshop, I\'ll highlight some of my favorite pieces of machine learning art, and show you how to make your own in Google Colab and/or Runway. <br /><br />No prior experience necessary. All you\'ll need is a computer with a stable internet connection, Chrome, and a Google login account. Extra credit: Bring a 1024px x 1024px image that you want to play with!<br /><br /></h3>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (start) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486860/chk/5844/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a> to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT </strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (end) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž&nbsp;SCHEDULE ã€</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sun,&nbsp;Dec 20th, 2020</li>\r\n<li class=\"graf graf--li\">11:30amâ€Š&mdash;â€Š1:30pm PT (2 hours)&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_20_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://time.is/1100AM_18_October_2020_in_San_Francisco/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\">Check your timezone</a>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SKILL LEVEL ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all levels.</li>\r\n<li>No specific background required for this workshop, just bring your curiosity!&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž WORKSHOP OUTLINE ã€</h3>\r\n<ol start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li>Introduction of Lia and her ML Art work + ML Art Inspiration</li>\r\n<li>What is ML?&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Tools Overview: What is Google Colab, Colab vs. Runway, Where to find pretrained models, and what is StyleGAN?</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout: Create your first&nbsp;piece of ML Art</em>&nbsp;(FleshDigressions Colab Notebook)</li>\r\n<li><em>Share your&nbsp;ML Art pieces</em></li>\r\n<li>What is Latent Space? (StyleGAN)</li>\r\n<li>Demo: How to generate new images, How to generate a Latent Walk video</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout: In Colab - Generate new images, Generate a Latent Walk video</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Share your latent walk videos</em></li>\r\n<li>Demo: What is Projection?&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Demo: How to Use Audio to Generate videos&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><em>Breakout:&nbsp;</em>Generate a video with Projection and/or Audio-Reaction</li>\r\n<li><em>Share your videos</em></li>\r\n<li>Further Reading: How to Train Your Own Model in Colab &amp; in Runway, How to Make your Own Training Dataset</li>\r\n<li>Further Reading: ML Ethics, How to Make AI Art Responsibly</li>\r\n<li>Celebrate your creations &amp; Additional ML Resources for next steps</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž ATTENDES BRING ã€</h3>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;Google login account</p>\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;Optional:&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Roboto, RobotoDraft, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">1024px x 1024px image to experiment with</span></p>\r\n<p>And the usual:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger.</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: 2nd monitor or screen so you can see the Zoom while working.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME PROVIDES ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Instructor Slides</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (start) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486860/chk/5844/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a> to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT </strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (end) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/pN9Cf7wd3u8\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/uo2JhdBs728\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/hSK8GbwTtvM\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME&nbsp;#CodeArtTogether Workshops ã€</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ§ âœ¨</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸš§ðŸŽ¨</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create</span></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ¤©ðŸ’¬ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Celebrate</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Connecting, Creating, and Celebrating&nbsp;are pillars of the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">CODAME #CodeArtTogether workshops</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Workshops are great for team building, remote or IRL. They cultivate space to play, which guides sense-making and sparks innovation. Attendees become featured artists with the option to show their workshop creations in CODAME galleries.&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">Learn more about this exciting offering</a><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486392/chk/4cfa/?modal_widget=true&amp;widget=true&amp;d\">!</a></p>\r\n<p>What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/join-us\">#JOYNT US</a>&nbsp;as a sponsor, volunteer, or workshop leader!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486860/chk/5844/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a>&nbsp;to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT&nbsp;</strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>', 'lia-coleman', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486860/chk/5844/#ticket_selection', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt');
INSERT INTO `events` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `date`, `pic`, `description`, `artists_array`, `projects_array`, `sponsors_array`, `partners_array`, `old_url`, `rsvp_url`, `hidden`, `event_type`, `shop_url`, `events_array`) VALUES
(145, 'Regalia, Chromology and Pilgrimage', 'regalia-chromology-and-pilgrimage', '2020-12-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/regalia-chromology-and-pilgrimage.png', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Artist Fabin Rasheed partnered with Async Art on the following three projects that are being shown at the CODAME Art+Tech Festival 2020. They are accessible through the links below and will also be viewable in New Art City throughout the Festival.</p>\r\n<div><br /><a href=\"http://codame.com/projects/regalia\">Regalia</a> and <a href=\"http://codame.com/projects/chromology\">Chromology</a> have open source interactive art creation elements available&nbsp;at the Festival.<br /><br /><a href=\"http://codame.com/projects/pilgrimage\">Pilgrimage</a> is a location based AR project that can be viewed in the areas specified in the map below. If you live near one of those areas or have friends that do.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets\" /></a></p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong><br /><br />REGALIA</strong><br /><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Screen_Shot_2020-11-18_at_7.14_.55_PM_.png\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>CHROMOLOGY</strong><a href=\"https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-363\"><br /></a></div>\r\n<div><strong><img src=\"/uploaded_images/FRChromology.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>PILGRIMAGE</strong><img src=\"/uploaded_images/pilgrimage2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>', 'fabin-rasheed', 'regalia,chromology,pilgrimage', '', 'async-art,newart-city', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt'),
(150, 'Collective Reflections', 'collective-reflections', '2020-12-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/collective-reflections.png', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (free to participate!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Nexus is a hanging collection of creative artifacts participants leave behind to celebrate and connect. It is free to particpate virtually by filling out this&nbsp;<a href=\"https://forms.gle/HrWE1S98PbopgQQa9\">form</a>!</p>\r\n<p>Each participant is given a booklet-shaped ornament and invited to choose from prompts encouraging reflection on their experiences this year and the season, as well as what changes they want to see in the next evolution around the sun. 2020 has been an unprecedented year of great change and isolation, so this piece provides an avenue for collective contemplation in the physical realm. While screens and social media have provided critical avenues for connection in the time of social distancing, Nexus provides a unique and broader social sharing experience that transcends likes, feeds, and followers and is no longer focused on individual profiles.</p>\r\n<p>The artifacts participants leave behind are equalized in their anonymity. Everyone takes up the same amount of space, with no algorithms or sponsors determining whose story is shown to the viewers. Individual experiences are mapped into a collective experience; people can connect through creative reflections on the year without knowing other participants. This group project demonstrates no one is alone in the isolation of this year, and there are many creative avenues to connect this season.</p>\r\n<p>Limited edition Nexus&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/quinn-keck/products/quinn-keck-personalized-nexus-mug\">mugs</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/quinn-keck/products/quinn-keck-nexus-iteration-i-scarf\">scraves</a>&nbsp;are also for sale!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Due to shelter in place orders and the safety of the community, we can no longer have in-person outdoor participation at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://localmakermart.com/\">Local Maker Mart</a> in San Francisco. All particpants in the 2020 ART + TECH Festival Joynt will be sent instructions to participate and the finished group piece will be uploaded here!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/gBQqpkgjRvU\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><br /></p>', 'quinn-keck', 'nexus', '', 'local-maker-mart', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection', ''),
(178, 'Happy Hour on Discord', 'happy-hour-on-discord', '2020-12-11', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/happy-hour-on-discord.png', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">(included in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Friday 12/11 (2020) 5 PM PST (<a href=\"https://time.is/500PM_11_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/London/Berlin/Hyderabad?CODAME\" target=\"_blank\">check your timezone</a>)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Join #happy-hour under General Voice on the CODAME Discord.</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Voice only so save our video-call-scorched retinas and let our hairs down.</li>\r\n<li>Bring WIP, inspirations, soap box, projects, remix chops, or nothing but your love of ART+TECH ðŸ‘¾</li>\r\n<li>Meet the team who put together CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020ã€Ž JOYNT ã€</li>\r\n<li>No format or agenda, just check out and chillax âœŒ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Flyer images features CC-BY-SA art <a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/vaporwave-tokyo-sketchfab-3d-editor-challenge-4eba49b0f6f54ade836a565d98247723\" target=\"_blank\">Vaporwave Tokyo</a>&nbsp;by William Domeyer</em></p>', '', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection', ''),
(143, 'Stylize Selfies With Hydra Blockly', 'stylize-selfies-with-hydra-blockly', '2020-12-19', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/stylize-selfies-with-hydra-blockly.png', '<center style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">Saturday, December 19th @ 11:30AM PST (<a href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_19_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\" target=\"_blank\">timezone converter</a>)</center><center style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">\r\n<p id=\"&rdquo;fest-10&rdquo;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong>&nbsp;annual&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</center>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Explore ways to build your own custom photo filters using a drag and drop, block based coding environment. Adjust&nbsp;colors, apply gradients using different blend modes, and distort the webcam by building our own photo-booth effects. Add interactivity to the filters by tracking mouse movements and make the effects respond to audio.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460622#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a>&nbsp;to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT&nbsp;</strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SKILL LEVEL ã€</h3>\r\n<p>While there is no programming background needed, there will be opportunity for advanced participants to peak under the hood and build their own image manipulation blocks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž WORKSHOP OUTLINE ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TBA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž ATTENDES BRING ã€</h3>\r\n<p>Just the usual:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger.</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: 2nd monitor or screen so you can see the Zoom while working.</li>\r\n<li>Hop on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://discord.gg/pk3C8DB\">CODAME Discord</a>&nbsp;if you have questions!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME PROVIDES ã€</h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">Slides TBA</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SCHEDULE ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-align: center;\">Sat, Dec 18th</span>, 2020</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-align: center;\">11:30am to 1:30 pm</span>&nbsp;PST&nbsp;<a href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_19_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\">Check your timezone</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME&nbsp;#CodeArtTogether Workshops ã€</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ§ âœ¨</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸš§ðŸŽ¨</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create</span></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ¤©ðŸ’¬ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Celebrate</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Connecting, Creating, and Celebrating&nbsp;are pillars of the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">CODAME #CodeArtTogether workshops</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Workshops are great for team building, remote or IRL. They cultivate space to play, which guides sense-making and sparks innovation. Attendees become featured artists with the option to show their workshop creations in CODAME galleries.&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">Learn more about this exciting offering</a><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486392/chk/4cfa/?modal_widget=true&amp;widget=true&amp;d\">!</a></p>\r\n<p>What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/join-us\">#JOYNT US</a>&nbsp;as a sponsor, volunteer, or workshop leader!</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460622#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a>&nbsp;to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT&nbsp;</strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n-->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|-- End TT Button -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'samarth-gulati', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460622#ticket_selection', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt'),
(151, 'Modular Audio Visualisation with modV', 'modular-audio-visualisation-with-modv', '2020-12-16', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/modular-audio-visualisation-with-modv.png', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Wed, Dec 16 @ 11:30AM PT (<a href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_16_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\">time.is localizer</a>) for 2.5 hours.</p>\r\n<p id=\"&rdquo;fest-10&rdquo;\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong> annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">By using the open source software modV you will be able to create audio reactive visualisations by combining different kinds of visual modules (2D, Interactive Shader Format and WebGL Shader) with any kind of audio input like a microphone or your favorite music. In the end you will know all the basics in order to do your first live performance as a VJ.</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (start) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460616#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a> to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT </strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (end) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>In collaboration with <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ilithya_net\">ilithya </a>and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/iamelizasj\">Eliza</a> we are able to use their awesome &ldquo;<a href=\"https://codepen.io/ilithya/pen/poyMNvG\">Movement</a>&rdquo; shader in the workshop as a demo to show you how audio reactivity works. We also used it to generate the workshop cover image. Thank you super much!</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SKILL LEVEL ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Beginner. No Coding required.</li>\r\n<li>If you do like to code, there\'s opportunity to write your own modV modules!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž WORKSHOP OUTLINE ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>History of and introduction to modV</li>\r\n<li>Learning to add images &amp; audio</li>\r\n<li>Audio routing</li>\r\n<li>Audio reactive visuals and techniques&nbsp;for certain effects</li>\r\n<li>How to use modV for a live performance</li>\r\n<li>Break-out rooms for exploration, collaboration, and additional questions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž ATTENDES BRING ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Download the <a href=\"https://github.com/vcync/modV/releases/latest\">latest version of modV</a>&nbsp;for Mac, Win, or Nix.</li>\r\n<li>Test <a href=\"https://modv.vcync.gl/v3/guide/#audio-routing\">audio routing</a> before the workshop. Hop on the <a href=\"https://discord.gg/pk3C8DB\">CODAME Discord</a>&nbsp;for trouble shooting.</li>\r\n<li>Bring a song you want to visualize!&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>And the usual:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger.</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: 2nd monitor or screen so you can see the Zoom while working.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME PROVIDES ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vcync/modV-Workshop\">A link to the repository</a> for the workshop for anything else you might need!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SCHEDULE ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wed, Dec 16&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>11:30 AM PT - 2 PM PT (<a href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_16_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\">time.is localizer</a>)</li>\r\n<li>2.5 hours</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460616#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a>&nbsp;to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT&nbsp;</strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME&nbsp;#CodeArtTogether Workshops ã€</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ§ âœ¨</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸš§ðŸŽ¨</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create</span></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ¤©ðŸ’¬ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Celebrate</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Connecting, Creating, and Celebrating&nbsp;are pillars of the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">CODAME #CodeArtTogether workshops</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Workshops are great for team building, remote or IRL. They cultivate space to play, which guides sense-making and sparks innovation. Attendees become featured artists with the option to show their workshop creations in CODAME galleries.&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">Learn more about this exciting offering</a><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486392/chk/4cfa/?modal_widget=true&amp;widget=true&amp;d\">!</a></p>\r\n<p>What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/join-us\">#JOYNT US</a>&nbsp;as a sponsor, volunteer, or workshop leader!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'tim-pietrusky,sam-wray', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', '', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460616#ticket_selection', ''),
(152, 'SCLOrk 20x20', 'sclork-20x20', '2020-12-19', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/sclork-20x20.png', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Saturday, Dec 19, 2020, 8:00 PM (1 hour) (check your&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7 !important;\" href=\"https://time.is/1000AM_12_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/London/Berlin/Hyderabad?CODAME\">timezone</a>)<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-a7336780-7fff-43db-e918-f1975363585d\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>SCLOrk (the Santa Clara Laptop Orchestra) is an innovative ensemble of up to sixteen players dedicated to the creation and performance of live electronic music. Created in 2012 by SCU faculty Bruno Ruviaro and students, this interdisciplinary group explores the intersection of music composition, live performance, human/computer interaction, programming, and sound design, with emphasis on musical creativity based on cutting-edge technologies.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'bruno-ruviaro,qiuwen-li,aastha-chawla,michael-noonan,josh-mitchell', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt'),
(155, 'Curiously Minded: Live Coding Shaders', 'curiously-minded-live-coding-shaders', '2020-12-12', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/curiously-minded-live-coding-shaders.png', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Saturday, Dec 12, 2020, 10:00am PST (2 hours) (check your&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7 !important;\" href=\"https://time.is/1000AM_12_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/London/Berlin/Hyderabad?CODAME\">timezone</a>)<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-a7336780-7fff-43db-e918-f1975363585d\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">ilithya and Eliza combine creative forces to create colorful shaders. They will be live-coding in the same editor, visuals refreshing in real time and chatting with the audience throughout. This livestream performance will be the premier launch of their new Twitch Channel.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The shader they code will be 2D, colorful, and inspired by optical illusion. They hope to showcase how much fun and approachable shaders can be - how infusing a few simple concepts into a couple of lines of code can yield some pretty intriguing and complex looking results that might even feel 3D!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Shaders are an amazing tool for creativity, but can seem intimidating and might feel like a very advanced topic, especially when you\'re just starting out, or like them, are self-taught programmers with no academic background in Math or CS. In sharing their coding sessions, they hope to encourage and inspire others curious about shaders, to take a dive down the rabbit hole. Or just watch them having fun while they do!<br /><br />All donations made during this performance will go to: <a href=\"https://www.code2040.org/\">CODE2040</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;a nonprofit activating, connecting, and mobilizing the largest racial equity community in tech to dismantle the structural barriers that prevent the full participation and leadership of Black and Latinx technologists in the innovation economy.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">ilithya\'s work is also featured in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/ilithya\">CODAME Shop</a>&nbsp;and can be viewed in the CODAME&nbsp;<a href=\"https://newart.city/show/codame\">New Art City Gallery</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'ilithya,eliza-struthers-jobin', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'event', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt'),
(158, 'Mashup 3d Models in Blender ', 'mashup-3d-models-in-blender', '2020-12-17', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/mashup-3d-models-in-blender.png', '<center>Thursday, December 17th @ 11:30AM PST (<a href=\"https://time.is/11:30AM_17_December_2020_in_San_Francisco/New_York/Berlin/Hyderabad/Shanghai?CODAME\" target=\"_blank\">timezone converter</a>)</center>\r\n<p><!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this in to your website where you want the widget to appear. Do no change the code or the widget may not work properly. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></p>\r\n<center>\r\n<p id=\"&rdquo;fest-10&rdquo;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong> annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</center>\r\n<h3>Create whimsical sculptures by remixing the <a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/collections\">ModBod collection</a> of over 700 full body scans!&nbsp;3d mashups can be used in VR, motion graphics,&nbsp;drawing reference, 3d printing, games, gif art, and more! No previous 3d modeling experience necessary, but you\'ll need blender installed and to be familiar with navigation fundamentals.</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (start) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460619/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a> to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT </strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (end) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SKILL LEVEL ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Beginner. No Coding required.</li>\r\n<li>Be familiar with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ILqOWe3zAbk\">fundamental navigation in Blender</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž WORKSHOP OUTLINE ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TBA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž ATTENDES BRING ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Download the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.blender.org/download/\">latest version of Blender</a>&nbsp;for Mac, Win, or Nix.</li>\r\n<li>Download some 3d models you want to mashup in your remixes:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/codame/collections\">ModBod collection</a>&nbsp;of over 700 full body scans.</li>\r\n<li>Creative Commons&nbsp;<a href=\"https://search.creativecommons.org/search?license=&amp;license_type=&amp;categories=&amp;extension=&amp;aspect_ratio=&amp;size=&amp;source=sketchfab,thingiverse&amp;q=pokemon&amp;searchBy=&amp;mature=\">3d model search</a>.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://poly.google.com/\">poly.google.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>And the usual:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer &amp; power/charger.</li>\r\n<li>Zoom installed ahead of time.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: 2nd monitor or screen so you can see the Zoom while working.</li>\r\n<li>Hop on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://discord.gg/pk3C8DB\">CODAME Discord</a>&nbsp;if you have questions!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž CODAME PROVIDES ã€</h3>\r\n<p>Slides TBA</p>\r\n<h3>ã€Ž SCHEDULE ã€</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Thu, Dec 17</li>\r\n<li>11:30 AM PT - 2 PM PT</li>\r\n<li>2.5 hours</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (start) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #351e58; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460619/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Or get the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\">ALL ACCESS pass</a> to CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT </strong></em><em>for 10 days of Workshops, Live Events, and Anytime Experiences!</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<!-- TicketTailor BUTTON (end) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">ã€Ž CODAME&nbsp;#CodeArtTogether Workshops ã€</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 101px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ§ âœ¨</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Connect</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-81f37ba5-7fff-97be-c713-6edc787897a0\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸš§ðŸŽ¨</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create</span></span></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ðŸ¤©ðŸ’¬ </span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Source Serif Pro\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Celebrate</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: start;\">Connecting, Creating, and Celebrating&nbsp;are pillars of the&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">CODAME #CodeArtTogether workshops</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: start;\">Workshops are great for team building, remote or IRL. They cultivate space to play, which guides sense-making and sparks innovation. Attendees become featured artists with the option to show their workshop creations in CODAME galleries.&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/code-art-together\">Learn more about this exciting offering</a><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/view-event/id/486392/chk/4cfa/?modal_widget=true&amp;widget=true&amp;d\">!</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: start;\">What topics grab your curiosity to learn or teach?&nbsp;Let us know through our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-workshops\">call for workshops</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/join-us\">#JOYNT US</a>&nbsp;as a sponsor, volunteer, or workshop leader!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: start;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: start;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'mark-savage,jilt,yiyue-chen,jj,skipper-gemx', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', 'sketchfab,itseez3d', '', '', '', '0', 'workshop', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/460619/#ticket_selection', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt');
