(71, 'CODAME Artists Agreement', 'codame-artists-agreement', '', '<p><strong>I. Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please read these Artist Terms and Conditions (\"Conditions\") carefully &ndash; by establishing an account with, or providing an artwork for sale by, CODAME, Inc. (\"CODAME\") you are agreeing to the Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>You also agree to the Privacy Policy, which sets out how we deal with CODAME\'s users\' personal information and privacy.</p>\r\n<p>This is a legal document which sets out your rights and obligations, and those of CODAME (\"we\" or \"us\"), in relation to artworks (each a \"Work\") which you provide to us for sale through websites operated by any of us (each a \"Site\") and any other services offered by us through our Sites.</p>\r\n<p>You must take the time to read and understand these Conditions before providing us with a Work for Sale. You accept that you are entering into a contract with us under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>II. Mission Statement</strong></p>\r\n<p>CODAME sparks visionaries by celebrating the value of playful creativity. Our inspiring experiences encourage the use of technology for artistic expression. Since 2010 we have run inclusive workshops, art sales, and a signature ART+TECH Festival.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>III. Scope of our services</strong></p>\r\n<p>CODAME is a platform for artists and their representatives and agents (individually and collectively, the \"Artists\"), which enables them to promote and sell their artwork(s) (the \"Artwork\") in public spaces. Here is a description of the process of our services:</p>\r\n<p>The Artists upload the Artwork to CODAME Shop (The Platform); in addition, they complete a profile and provide information about The Artwork.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME is not responsible for any violation by you or any User or other third party of any CODAME terms of service, privacy policy or any applicable law by any individual or company who has, does or will work for, on behalf of, or with CODAME for the purpose of displaying the Artwork as provided for in this Agreement, or for the purpose of fulfilling any Artwork order, including in relation to the Artwork. CODAME is not responsible for any unauthorized and/or unlawful, copying, distribution, transmission, or sale of Artwork.</p>\r\n<p>You hereby unconditionally and irrevocably release CODAME, its agents, directors, officers, shareholders, and employees from all liability arising out of or in connection with any CODAME Partners\' actions or omissions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>IV. Our Pledge</strong></p>\r\n<p>It is absolutely free to use our service for CODAME Artists.</p>\r\n<p>We display your name and all necessary information for people to buy your Artwork.</p>\r\n<p>We sell your Artwork(s), but, except for any CODAME Fulfilled Orders (as defined in these Conditions below), we do not print or install it for the Users who ordered it. With respect to any orders to be printed and fulfilled by Artists, Artists have full control over the final version of their Artwork.</p>\r\n<p>The Artwork is available to all The Partners. It is the sole decision of the Partners to display your Artwork in their space. We cannot guarantee that The Partners will choose to display your Artwork, nor can we guarantee that the User will buy them.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>V. Your CODAME Artist Profile</strong></p>\r\n<p>In order to become one of CODAME\'s Artists, first, you need to fill out this form providing all requested details. You also must agree to make all representations and warranties stated in these Conditions in favor of us.</p>\r\n<p>You agree that you shall not include in your artist profile appearing on CODAME (\"Profile\") anything that could potentially infringe upon another\'s rights, confuse, or which is offensive, hurtful, or otherwise inappropriate. CODAME reserves the right to change any online Profile in the event we determine, at our sole discretion, that violates these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>You represent that all the information provided, such as your name or surname is yours and legally available for use.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>VII. Representations, Warranties &amp; Covenants of Artists</strong></p>\r\n<p>As a condition of becoming a CODAME Artist, you hereby represent, warrant, and covenant to CODAME:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>You are the sole owner of and have full power to enter into these Conditions and to grant all rights granted or purported to be granted under them, including the grant of any license to use of the Artwork granted herein;</li>\r\n<li>You are the sole author of any Artwork submitted to CODAME and all Artwork(s) are your own original artwork and are not made from copyrighted material or patterns.;</li>\r\n<li>You unconditionally and irrevocably hold 100% exclusive right to all right, title, and interest in and to the Artwork, including copyright;</li>\r\n<li>Your Artwork does not contain any illegal material and/or in itself constitutes illegal material.</li>\r\n<li>You will not post or transmit any content that infringes any copyright or other right of any person;</li>\r\n<li>Your Artwork does not contain anything that may constitute a violation of the personal integrity and privacy of an individual;</li>\r\n<li>Your Artwork does not contain anything that may offend, slander, defame or discriminate any individual, entity or group of people, and that you will not abuse, harass, threaten, impersonate or intimidate any person;</li>\r\n<li>You shall indemnify and hold the CODAME harmless from and against any loss, expense, or damage occasioned by any claim, demand, suit or recovery against Your Artwork, arising out of any alleged use of the image which violates or breaches a third party\'s property rights, or resulting from breach of your obligations under these Conditions including breach of any representation, warranty or covenant contained herein.</li>\r\n<li>You guarantee to be able to process and sell The Artwork displayed by CODAME medium and ordered by CODAME\'s Users in accordance with CODAME\'s standard practices and quality control standards.</li>\r\n<li>You agree to maintain inventory of the merchandise uploaded according to the availability disclaimed by you on CODAME\'s Platform.</li>\r\n<li>Except for any CODAME FulFilled Orders, you are responsible for the creation and shipping of the Artwork.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>VIII. Grant of License</strong></p>\r\n<p>In consideration of our agreement to pay you the Royalty payments stated in these Conditions, by submitting the Artwork to CODAME, you grant to us a worldwide, non-exclusive, unlimited license in and to each Artwork to display, transmit, publish, post online, and to use, sell, and to the extent elected by the Artist in Paragraph XI below of these Terms, print, and ship to a User, on your behalf, the Artwork for purposes as we see fit related to CODAME&rsquo;s business, by any electronic or digital means, method, device, process or medium (now known or hereafter developed) (collectively, the &ldquo;Rights&rdquo;). For the avoidance of doubt, the Rights include the rights (a) to conduct sales of any Artwork including CODAME Fulfilled Orders, (and to grant sub-licensees of the right to conduct sales and fulfillment of any orders), (b) to grant sub-licenses to Users to view, display, purchase and use the Artwork for personal, non-commercial use, and (c) to do and authorize third parties to do anything expressly or impliedly referred to in these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>This license will exist for the period of time during which the Artwork remains on the Platform, and will terminate 30 days after the removal of the Artwork from The Platform. You represent that the Artwork uploaded is yours, duly licensed by you hereby grant to CODAME the right to store your Artwork on its own servers and backups for the duration of the license, including the 30 days, as applicable after removal from the Platform.</p>\r\n<p>At any time you may notify us that you wish to terminate this license with respect to a particular Artwork by emailing us as team_at_CODAME_dot_com (a \"termination notice\"); any termination notice must clearly identify the Artwork in question. We will withdraw that Artwork from the Website within 30 days of our receipt of the termination notice.</p>\r\n<p>You agree that you shall not grant any license or make any agreements in respect of any Artwork (or any part of it or any character therefrom), or allow any such license or agreement to exist, that would in any way conflict with or derogate from the grant of the Rights hereunder.</p>\r\n<p>Upon your breach of these Conditions, CODAME shall be entitled to immediately and without notice to you to cease any payments to you relating to the relevant Artwork in any format, and (b) to recover from you all payments paid to date in relation to that Artwork, in addition to any other legal or equitable rights available to CODAME.</p>\r\n<p>You will remain the owner of your Artwork\'s copyright or of any intellectual property rights or other proprietary rights associated with your Artwork.</p>\r\n<p>You assert to us, our assignees, licensees, and successors in the title your moral right to be identified as the author of each Artwork, including under the Visual Artists Rights Act. We agree to include your name on the pages of CODAME where your Artwork is displayed.</p>\r\n<p>You acknowledge and agree that we may (a) use copies of the Artwork, (b) aggregate copies of one or more of your Artworks with one another or with the works of other artists, and (c) overlay text on copies of your Works online and for offline printed materials, in each case for promotional purposes and without being required to name you as the Artist.</p>\r\n<p>The grant of this license includes a grant to display your Artwork on CODAME\'s website, Platform, or other digital or physical mediums, included in the scope of our services, with the intention, but no obligation, to display and sell your Artwork as announced in the conditions of the agreement.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME is free to use the Artwork provided, as described in the scope of services, without permission or license from any third party. CODAME is granted a non-exclusive, non-transferable, fully paid, worldwide license to use, distribute, modify, adapt, and publicly display such content in connection with the Services as defined in the scope.</p>\r\n<p>By uploading your Artwork to the CODAME website, you retain full rights to those works that you had prior to uploading.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME decides exclusively and in its sole discretion what to publish and display on The Platform.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME can not restrict the ability of users and visitors on The Platform to make a low resolution (maximum of 800x800) or \"thumbnail\" (maximum of 200x200) copies of the Artwork posted on The Platform and you hereby expressly authorize CODAME to permit users and visitors of The Platform to make such low-resolution copies of your Content.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME can not restrict the ability of The Users to take pictures of The Artwork displayed on other digital or physical mediums and you hereby expressly authorize The Users, or other digital or physical medium spectators to take photos of your content.</p>\r\n<p>The license granted to CODAME includes the rights to use, modify, adapt, distribute and publicly display The Artwork fully or partially for promotional reasons. The license also includes the use to redistribute The Artwork to a third party for CODAME\'s promotional reasons.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>X. Sales of Your Artwork &ndash; General Process and Procedures</strong></p>\r\n<p>Any User watching at your Artwork on a Display (other digital or physical mediums) in our Partners\' location can see your name, your Artwork, and a link that invites them to CODAME\'s website.</p>\r\n<p>From CODAME\'s website, Users can order and buy a printed or physical version of your Artwork, in a limited or unlimited edition, in any of the available Formats (such order, an \"Order\").</p>\r\n<p>You shall have previously defined the Formats of the Artwork available for purchase at the time of the upload of the Artwork.</p>\r\n<p>Formats of an Artwork available for sale may include (\"Formats\"):</p>\r\n<p>Original Artwork sales:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hard copy printed versions of the Artwork in giclee fine art prints with archival ink, neither mounted nor framed, except for any custom order where the User agrees in writing to pay for the shipping of the framed Artwork and in such case, you must notify CODAME in writing before shipping, so that CODAME can charge the appropriate party for shipping.</p>\r\n<p>Unless you elect to have an order fulfilled as a CODAME Fulfilled Orders (as defined below), you are responsible for (i) maintaining inventory of the formats listed (for originals and limited editions), (ii) creating and shipping the Artwork that is subject of the Order, (iii) if necessary, to install, the Artwork ordered, and (iv) forward proof of shipment as well as the tracking number of the shipment, the day of the shipment at the email address provided to you during the order.</p>\r\n<p>For each order, you will be paid Royalty payments for the sale of the Artwork in accordance with the schedule that appears in Paragraph XII below, which are subject to change by CODAME, from time to time to the extent provided in these Conditions. We will notify you of changes to the Royalty schedules by sending you an email; however, Royalty payment rates shall be locked in on a per-order basis upon submission of any particular sale.</p>\r\n<p>Completion of a sale transaction of your Artwork will be deemed to be completed forty-five (45) days after payment is received by CODAME from the Customer. Royalty payments shall not be paid in respect of any Artwork that is returned by the Customer for exchange or refund. In this case, the Artwork will be returned to you, at your cost.</p>\r\n<p>Payment will be processed via Intersections for the Arts by check mailed to your address.</p>\r\n<p>Shipping Costs. For custom Artwork (mounted, framed, laminated, etc.), Artists should advise CODAME prior to the shipment, so CODAME can bill the shipping charge directly to the purchasing User.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>XI. Sales Process - CODAME Fulfilled Orders</strong></p>\r\n<p>At your option, by checking the applicable box upon upload of any Artwork, you can elect to have CODAME fulfill any sales orders on your behalf, and you shall be deemed to unconditionally and irrevocably grant to CODAME full rights and authority to print, ship to any User, process payment for, and communicate with such User on your behalf with respect to any order of any Artwork (each such order, a \"CODAME Fulfilled Order\"). Fulfillment of all Digital Edition orders shall be fulfilled by CODAME and shall be deemed a \"CODAME Fulfilled Order\". Your option to elect a CODAME Fulfilled Order is subject to, at all times and in all respects, CODAME\'s current capabilities, and in all cases, CODAME reserves the right to use any third-party vendors, suppliers, delivery agent(s) and other fulfillment partners it chooses in its sole discretion to fulfill any CODAME FulFilled Orders.</p>\r\n<p>Royalty Payments payable to you with respect to any CODAME Fulfilled Orders shall be in accordance with the standard costs and fees stated in Paragraph XII below, subject to CODAME\'s reserved rights to change such rates to the extent stated in these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>XII. Your Royalty Payments; Costs and Fees</strong></p>\r\n<p>For each sale of an Artwork, CODAME will split 70%&nbsp;of the Net Revenues sale of any Artwork (the \"Royalty\") payment with the Artist.</p>\r\n<p>The relevant Royalty will be specified at or before the time when the sale of your Artwork commences.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Note that we may change the Royalty that applies to the various types of sales from time to time. However, any such change will not affect the Royalty you earn on sale which has already occurred, or to the sales of any edition which is already on sale at the time when the change is made: to avoid doubt, the changed Royalty will apply only to the Edition of the next Artwork to go on sale, not to the edition currently on sale at the time when we notify you of the changed sale Royalty rate.</p>\r\n<p>For the purposes of calculating the Royalty, \"Net Revenues\" are amounts actually received by CODAME for sums paid to us for sale of the Artwork, net of all relevant deductions including (without limitation):</p>\r\n<p>Any and all tax, tariffs, and fees (including any VAT taxes); transaction costs; chargebacks and returns; any sums paid or repaid to Users in connection with the relevant sale, any revenue share or commission paid or payable to distributors, licensees or others involved in the sale of an Artwork, and any sums paid, payable, deductible or creditable to third parties in connection with the relevant sale of an Artwork.</p>\r\n<p>Royalties shall be calculated in the national currency in which we are paid, and shall be paid to you in US Dollars using the spot rate of exchange of Wells Fargo Bank, N.A., for the purchase of which the relevant currency prevailing on the date on which we are paid by the User. For the avoidance of doubt, no Royalty is payable in respect of copies of the Artwork included in CODAME\'s publicity and marketing efforts.</p>\r\n<p>For CODAME Fulfillment Orders, we will credit Royalty to you quarterly within the time periods set forth in these Artist Terms and Conditions, or as otherwise mutually agreed to in writing between you and CODAME.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>XIII. Right to Terminate at Any Time</strong></p>\r\n<p>At any time you can remove your Artwork from the Platform. This action will terminate the license you granted to CODAME within 30 days (\"Thirty\")</p>\r\n<p>In all cases, copies of your Artwork posted on any third-party sites and used for promotional purposes will be removed within 30 days (\"thirty\") following your removal request, however, submitted.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>XIV. Reserved Rights of CODAME</strong></p>\r\n<p>CODAME reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to modify or replace these Conditions at any time. If the alterations constitute a material change to these Conditions, CODAME will notify you by posting an announcement on The Platform and by sending you an email.</p>\r\n<p>Using any service or viewing any content following notification of a material change to the Conditions shall constitute your acceptance thereof, as modified.</p>\r\n<p>CODAME is not responsible for all the content uploaded. All the content uploaded is the sole responsibility of the account holder from which such content originates and you acknowledge and agree that you are entirely responsible for all content that you post, or download to The Platform.</p>\r\n<p>Your access, and use of, the Platform may be interrupted from time to time as a result of equipment malfunction, updating, maintenance, or repair of The Platform or any other reason within or outside the control of CODAME. The Platform should not be used or relied upon for the storage of your photographs and images and you are directed to retain your own copies of all content posted on The Platform.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, CODAME may remove any Artwork that it believes to be in breach of the Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>XV. General Conditions</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>CODAME shall not be liable for any failure to perform its obligations where such failure results from any cause beyond CODAME\'s reasonable control.</li>\r\n<li>If any part of these Conditions is held to be invalid or unenforceable, the remainder shall remain valid and enforceable.</li>\r\n<li>Our failure to act with respect to a breach of these Conditions by you or others does not waive our right to act with respect to subsequent or similar breaches.</li>\r\n<li>The headings to the Clauses are for ease of reference only and do not affect the interpretation or construction of these Conditions.</li>\r\n<li>Each party shall execute or cause to be executed all such other documents and do or cause to be done all such further acts and things consistent with the terms of these Conditions as the other party may from time to time reasonably require for the purpose of giving the latter party the full benefit of the provisions of these Conditions.</li>\r\n<li>The validity, construction, and performance of these Conditions shall be governed by the laws of the State of California.</li>\r\n</ol>', '', '0'),
(73, 'Harry Styles - Watermelon Sugar (AI)', 'harry-styles---watermelon-sugar-ai', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/harry-styles---watermelon-sugar-ai-version.jpg', '<div>\r\n<div><span dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/cnielsennyc/\">Christian Nielsen</a> w</span><span dir=\"ltr\">orked on getting the&nbsp;AI to transform everyone into Harry Styles and add more watermelon,&nbsp;and&nbsp;we like it!<br /></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/4tpJ3u_-fbE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>When the world was starved for human contact in the early days of the pandemic, Harry Styles dropped the \"Watermelon Sugar\" music video with a cheeky message: \"This video is dedicated to touching.\"</p>\r\n<p>Released on 18 May 2020, directed by Bradley &amp; Pablo and filmed in&nbsp;Malibu, California, it features Styles alongside&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The video oozes the song\'s warm, seductive, and playful vibe. Styles is surrounded by a plethora of people on the beach, surrounded by enough watermelon to feed a small army.</p>\r\n<p>Despite the video\'s saucy undertones, the intimacy between Styles and the actors held a special place in our hearts in 2020. The hand-holding, hair-stroking, and strawberry-feeding depicted in the video became the stuff of dreams for those starved for physical affection during the quarantine era. Styles\' original video served up a delicious, juicy taste of these longed-for sensations, reminding us all of the sheer joy of human touch during a time when it was most scarce.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/E07s5ZYygMg\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>It\'s not the first time an Artist used AI to recreate Harry Styles\' &lsquo;Watermelon Sugar&rsquo; music video.</p>\r\n<p>Andr&eacute; R&ouml;hrig&nbsp;used&nbsp;AI&nbsp;to recreate Styles&rsquo; song using footage from&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.reaganfoundation.org/library-museum/\" target=\"_blank\">Reagan Presidential Library</a>.</p>\r\n<p>R&ouml;hrig said he got the idea for the project when he noticed that AI and machine learning often fail in interesting ways. Artist&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/quasimondo?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor\" target=\"_blank\">Mario Klingemann</a>&nbsp;is also an inspiration, he said</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/YESTcUCl6pc\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>The original music videos for both&nbsp;Watermelon Sugar&nbsp;and&nbsp;Video Games&nbsp;are nostalgia trips that copy the aesthetic style of the 1960s. According to R&ouml;hrig, this was important to help his AI&mdash;he designed and trained himself&mdash;understand how to make its music video.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div data-component=\"BodyComponentRenderer\">\r\n<p>&ldquo;There are certain parameters like hard cuts and short scenes that are important for the process not to fail,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;And the video footage the AI tries to replicate must be represented to a certain extent within the distribution of the archival footage. Otherwise, the results are not very satisfying. This is the case for these retro style videos I\'ve used here; the \'real\' Lana Del Rey video even uses lots of archival footage.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>According to R&ouml;hrig, creating the AI took about two weeks. Why the Reagan Library, though? After all, there are plenty of other sources of workable video, including the libraries of other American presidents. R&ouml;hrig said that it produced the best results.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Initially, I was looking for footage in the public domain for practical reasons, so the videos don\'t get blocked because of copyright claims,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;This is the case for these public domain presidential video collections. I\'ve tried other collections (Trump, Obama) and also other sources like old educational films produced by the U.S. Government. Still, I\'ve had the best results with the Reagan Library footage. The more recent presidential videos have much better production videos and more editing. In contrast, the Reagan videos are often just someone filming random people at campaign rallies for hours, which is great for a diverse data set vs. just lots of shots of the president.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Other videos on R&ouml;hrig&rsquo;s channel show an AI trained to make abstract art using a&nbsp;Generative Adversarial Network&nbsp;(GAN), a common technique for&nbsp;creating artificial images.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;This animation of abstract images was created by an AI that was trained without any training data,&rdquo;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xXpSXJeZvCk\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;</a>R&ouml;hrig&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xXpSXJeZvCk\" target=\"_blank\">said</a>&nbsp;in the video&rsquo;s description. &ldquo;Instead, an adversarial training process of different deep convolutional neural networks against each other was used to create \'pure\' abstract visuals.</p>\r\n<p><span data-component=\"TextBlock\">You read more about it on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vice.com/en/article/4ad8ew/artist-uses-ai-to-recreate-watermelon-sugar-music-video-using-footage-of-ronald-reagan\">Vice Motherboard</a>,&nbsp;written by&nbsp;</span>Matthew Gault on February 17, 2021</p>\r\n<p>Are there going to be more AI-generated videos of Watermelon Sugar? We can\'t wait!</p>\r\n<div class=\"contributors\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Lora, Georgia, serif; font-size: 16px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '0'),
(13, 'Intersection for the Arts', 'intersection-for-the-arts', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/intersection-for-the-arts.png', '<p>We are members of <a href=\"http://theintersection.org\" target=\"_blank\">Intersection for the Arts</a>,&nbsp;a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, which allows us to offer you tax deductions for your contributions.</p>\r\n<p>Select CODAME ART+TECH as the&nbsp;designated <a href=\"https://donatenow.networkforgood.org/1442843\" target=\"_blank\">donation</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About <a href=\"http://theintersection.org\" target=\"_blank\">Intersection for the Arts</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>Established in 1965, Intersection is a pioneering arts and community development organization that brings people together across boundaries to instigate break-through change. Intersection&rsquo;s programs emphasize relationships, collaboration, and process. Intersection works with hundreds of artists through residencies, commissions, fellowships, fiscal sponsorship and incubation, performances, exhibitions, workshops and public art projects. Annually, Intersection works with more than 50 community partners across sector and field.</p>\r\n<p>Intersection is a lead collaborator on the 5M Project, a 4-acre multi-phase, mixed-use development project located in downtown San Francisco. With The 5M Project, Intersection is helping to prototype the next generation of urban development that embraces diversity of thought, life experience, and culture as essential to positive economic and social change in our neighborhoods. 5MPlaceWorks, a collaboration led by Intersection for the Arts, brings the 5M Project and Central Market neighbors together with artists, makers, entrepreneurs, social change agents, and technology innovators to collaboratively develop a new kind of place that unlocks resources, connection, and creativity across silos and disciplines.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://theintersection.org\" target=\"_blank\">http://theintersection.org</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://donatenow.networkforgood.org/1442843\" target=\"_blank\">Donate Now!</a></p>', '', '1'),
(14, 'Q&A with ANI, Artist in Residence @GeekdomSF', 'q-a-with-ani-artist-in-residence-geekdomsf', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/q-a-with-ani-artist-in-residence-geekdomsf.jpg', '<header>\r\n<div>As part of the CODAME \"Adopt an Artist\" series of interviews.</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<article id=\"post-4254\"><hr />\r\n<p>Meet&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.ani-web.com/\" target=\"_blank\">ANI</a>, the first official artist in residence at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.geekdom.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Geekdom</a>&nbsp;(which is notably the first official sponsor of CODAME&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-musician-ani-amy-lee-aka-ani/www.codame.com/adopt/%E2%80%8E\" target=\"_blank\">Adopt An Artist</a>&nbsp;program)! &nbsp;Her current work developing an iOS app for iBeacon looks to completely transform the CODAME experience for audiences by giving them unfettered access to digital content about the featured artists and their work.</p>\r\n<p>We spoke with ANI earlier this month about her recently launched iPad instrument, why she joined CODAME, and what she&rsquo;s developing during her GeekdomSF Residency supported by Rackspace.</p>\r\n<p>So ANI, tell us about yourself</p>\r\n<p>I am a live looping musician and I got pretty serious about it a couple of years ago. Before then I was just a typical web developer working at startups in the Bay Area and also doing bits of visual design. I&rsquo;ve been looking for ways to combine my love for music and high technology for a long time and now I&rsquo;m on the path to some very interesting things.</p>\r\n<p>What kinds of interesting things?</p>\r\n<p>I build songs in real-time out of nothing but a couple of iPads and maybe a keyboard controller. I have a rough idea of what I want to do but I try to let the crowd tell me where to go: it is a kind of interactive performance art. What&rsquo;s different about what I&rsquo;m doing is I weave songs together over an entire music set without breaks, not unlike a DJ.&nbsp;I had been recording videos and putting them up on YouTube, then I started playing live every few weeks. Last year I got the chance to travel to and be part of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://y2kloopfest.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Y2K Loopfest</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nwloopfest.com/\" target=\"_blank\">NW Loop Fest</a>,&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"/\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME</a>&nbsp;live looping festivals which draw performers and admirers from around the world. These days I&rsquo;m working on building my own music instruments that are entirely iPad based to take my looping music further. &nbsp;I also serve&nbsp;as a coordinator for&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.sf-emm.org/\" target=\"_blank\">San Francisco Electronic Music Meetup</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Why did you join CODAME?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;I&rsquo;m part of CODAME because I feel it is one of the best underground art organizations that has a super strong focus on the use of cutting edge technologies like 3D printing, motion-reactive visualizations, iBeacons, and mobile computing. We get to truly unite artists with the best in technology, and expose new tech-based artists to the world. It excites me to see our organization grow to hosting these amazing festivals where we transform spaces into interactive, immersive playgrounds.</p>\r\n<p>What was your first CODAME event?</p>\r\n<p>Amy:&nbsp;My first CODAME event I think was the October 2012 CODAME festival where I did a set. Since then I&rsquo;ve been doing photography and videography, trying to capture the energy and amazement our events evoke. More recently I&rsquo;ve been working with our CODAME artists and developers to create an iPhone app that lets our guests become even more immersed at our events.</p>\r\n<p>Tell us about your Geekdom residency projects</p>\r\n<p>Amy: My current project is my iPad-based instrument called sBASSdrum (said &ldquo;space drum&rdquo;) which launched on the Apple App Store in February. I&rsquo;m working on making this universal for iPhones too. More news soon!&nbsp;I&rsquo;m also deep into working with iBeacon technology to develop the iOS app for CODAME. &nbsp;CODAME the organization has been artists in residence at Geekdom since last year, and we&rsquo;ve held many events in the Geekdom space. This year I was honored to become their first person artist in residence and they&rsquo;ve provided space for me to develop my art, my apps, and CODAME&rsquo;s technology.</p>\r\n<p>What do you hope your residency work will achieve?</p>\r\n<p>Amy: I hope the residency work will help CODAME extend its experience directly to our attendees. We hope to create a lasting impression of our events, to give people truly something they can take home with them.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><img class=\"\" style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px;\" src=\"https://31.media.tumblr.com/e16e01449db03196860f12a730990998/tumblr_inline_n5dfunL5No1sfxgsr.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"887\" height=\"591\" /></p>\r\n</article>\r\n</div>', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/geekdom-artist-in-residence-ani/', '1'),
(15, 'Q&A with Micah Elizabeth Scott, CODAME Featured Artist', 'q-a-with-micah-elizabeth-scott-codame-featured-artist', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/q-a-with-micah-elizabeth-scott-codame-featured-artist.gif', '<header>\r\n<div>As part of the CODAME \"Adopt an Artist\" series of interviews.</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<article id=\"post-4280\">\r\n<p>We spoke with CODAME Featured Artist&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/micah/\">Micah Elizabeth Scott&nbsp;</a>to learn more about her installation, &ldquo;Ecstatic Epiphany,&rdquo; and in the process discussed her thoughts on the direction of San Francisco&rsquo;s art/tech movement, her encyclopedic knowledge of hardware/software, and her infamous tutorial, &ldquo;How to Hack Your Vagina&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://assets.tumblr.com/assets/scripts/vendor/tiny_mce_3_5_10/themes/advanced/img/trans.gif\" alt=\"\" />By&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/LaurynPorte\">Lauryn Porte</a>&nbsp;on April 30, 2014</p>\r\n<p>A sheet of warm-white, concave tiles radiate ambient patterns as they hang innocuously between an aerial hoop and long curtains (or to the knowledgeable: lyra and silks, which are used for acrobatic performances) in a spacious loft above a SoMa Mexican restaurant. Welcome to the studio of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://scanlime.org/\">Micah Elizabeth Scott</a>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;an open, light-saturated place full of project leftovers, eclectic interests and micro controllers of all shapes and sizes.</p>\r\n<p>Micah Elizabeth Scott is a San Francisco-based, Colorado-raised, artist and engineer to be reckoned with. &nbsp;The ambitious Scott has developed the LED interface board&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.sparkfun.com/products/12821\">Fadecandy</a>, award-winning raytracer&nbsp;<a href=\"http://zenphoton.com/\">Zen Photon Garden</a>, and given talks at Autodesk and GAFFTA. &nbsp;She is currently one of CODAME&rsquo;s Featured Artists up for&nbsp;<a href=\"/adopt/\">Adoption</a>&nbsp;along with many others with a similarly electric palette. Scott&rsquo;s engineering background is visible in her varied projects, mixing technology&rsquo;s practicality and artwork&rsquo;s ingenuity. &nbsp;Her upcoming installation for CODAME&rsquo;s ART+TECH Playground incorporates the contemplative hues of the best cyber-sunset you&rsquo;ve never seen, with all of the mental stimulation of a mathematical concept come to life.</p>\r\n<p>Tell me about your upcoming light installation &ldquo;Ecstatic Epiphany&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>To me it&rsquo;s a visual metaphor for this&nbsp;&lsquo;Ah ha&rsquo;&nbsp;moment of creation &ndash; a process for the inspiration for making art, which seems appropriate.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/scanlime/ecstatic-epiphany/blob/master/notes/2014-05-02.md\">Read more</a>&nbsp;about Micah&rsquo;s personal process and reflections while considering her installation, &lsquo;Ecstatic Epiphany&rsquo;.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Absolutely. &nbsp;What is it made out of and how does it work?</p>\r\n<p>The structure is all made of out mat board&ndash;&nbsp;it&rsquo;s the same stuff you would use for framing photos. &nbsp;I ended up using something that is just very slightly warm-white so it evens out the color temperature of the LEDs. It diffuses the light really nicely. &nbsp;I laser-cut the mat board into small boxes that have a concave interior that traps the light&ndash;&nbsp;those boxes all have strips of addressable LEDs and they&rsquo;re all wired together by hand, in complex way so that the wiring is hidden in the creases of the boxes, and it seems like this uniform hanging sheet. &nbsp;The LED controller is the Fadecandy board that I designed. The algorithmic software I&rsquo;m writing and the computer vision software runs on a small embedded Linux board.</p>\r\n<p>Fadecandy is for sale, right?</p>\r\n<p>Yeah! &nbsp;Now it&rsquo;s an open hardware project that you can buy from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/products/1689\">Adafruit</a>&nbsp;and from distributors like SparkFun electronics. &nbsp;They&rsquo;re pretty easy to use. &nbsp;What I wanted to do is take some of the algorithms that I happened upon, the temporal dithering for increasing the color-depth of the LEDs, the interpolation for smoothing out frames&ndash;&nbsp;I had originally made these so that I could make art that had smoother LED effects but I wanted to bring those techniques to a wider audience. &nbsp;So Fadecandy was my attempt at, concurrently with making the art myself, making tools that other people could use to make art. &nbsp;So with Fadecandy, that was my first attempt at making a product that you could buy on the Internet.</p>\r\n<p>What tools do you normally use for your projects?</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve used a lot of different tools over the years. &nbsp;I guess I feel like I&rsquo;m really picky about tools. &nbsp;So I end up getting attached to some tools. There are microcontrollers that I have an unreasonable fondness for, like the Parallax Propeller&ndash;&nbsp;it&rsquo;s cute and adorable in this strange way. It has a really weird architecture that makes it really annoying to program in some ways, because the toolchain is very nonstandard, but makes it capable of some really beautiful things, because you can write programs that are actually eight different programs that run completely concurrently in hardware, real-time on eight separate processors. There are some tools where I just think they&rsquo;re delightfully quirky like a cult-classic movie or something.</p>\r\n<p>With the LED-stuff I&rsquo;ve been working on now, I don&rsquo;t really have a software tool chain that I&rsquo;ve been using that is anyone else&rsquo;s&ndash;&nbsp;I&rsquo;ve ended up just building my own thing from the ground up in C++. &nbsp;I&rsquo;ve tried other things, other languages, trying to make a higher-level thing like with Javascript, I&rsquo;ve tried Processing. Those are good for different things, but the stuff I&rsquo;m doing right now uses just a lot of CPU power and it&rsquo;s convenient to have it running on something that&rsquo;s small and embedded, and easy to run off of a small embedded Linux image on a micro-SD card. &nbsp;So yeah, I guess my software toolchain has been pretty minimal lately. For hardware I&rsquo;ve been using whatever small embedded Linux board that I can, and the latest one that I&rsquo;ve been using is almost like if you took a Raspberry Pi but built it around a really modern cell phone processor, quad-core and 1.7 GHz&ndash;&nbsp;so I&rsquo;ve been using that board plus the Fadecandy LED controllers that I&rsquo;ve designed.</p>\r\n<p>Can you talk about where you see this art/tech movement in SF going, and how you perceive its impact the city?</p>\r\n<p>That question has been on my mind a lot lately. &nbsp;And I can&rsquo;t say I have any idea about where exactly it&rsquo;s going at this point. &nbsp;You know, there&rsquo;s a pretty good chance that the prices are just going to get so high that no one is going to be able to afford to live here, and there&rsquo;s also a chance that maybe the tech people are putting more money into art. &nbsp;And I know right now a lot of the funding that art projects that I do, and that friends do, comes indirectly from tech, either from people that have been in tech and have money to spend on art, or people who end up working with tech companies for art projects. &nbsp;A lot of it is going to depend on how much that actually happens relative to how much the cost of living keeps going up. &nbsp;I don&rsquo;t know where it&rsquo;s going to go, but I feel like artists&ndash;&nbsp;even if we&rsquo;re not in a position to influence the direction that much, we can certainly call attention to what&rsquo;s happening and try to spark discussions&ndash;&nbsp;and this is one reason why I&rsquo;m excited to do a public piece in an area the city is actively trying to change. I think it&rsquo;ll be really interesting to try to do something that creates a positive change and use it as a discussion point.</p>\r\n<p>Do you have any other projects happening right now?</p>\r\n<p>I have a really hard time multi-tasking projects. I tend to really want to put all of my creative energy in one place and then do that one thing, and switch gears completely. I&rsquo;ve been experimenting with this way of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://thecrystalandthedemon.tumblr.com/\">collaborative drawing</a>&nbsp;with my friend&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.cheimonette.com/\">Eden</a>. She&rsquo;s a really talented illustrator&ndash;&nbsp;she&rsquo;s designed her own Tarot deck, and very realistic/abstract illustrations. And we wanted to try this technique where we both start a new drawing and occasionally just swap and just try to complete each other&rsquo;s sentences effectively.</p>\r\n<p>Ah &ndash; it&rsquo;s like&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exquisite_corpse\">exquisite corpse</a>!</p>\r\n<p>Yeah! &nbsp;It&rsquo;s taught us both a lot about the nature of collaboration. We&rsquo;ve been trying to figure out how to integrate that project in with more of our work. I think it has some really interesting things to say about explicitly making room for collaboration in your work, and I think this is a message that is especially lost in tech communities. I know a lot of people in tech come from this background where things are more competitive, and it&rsquo;s more about making the best widget than collaborating in the smoothest way. There are movements I&rsquo;ve seen that are working against that, back towards healthy collaboration, things like pair programming. I&rsquo;ve often found it challenging to integrate real collaboration into heavily tech-oriented art, because tech skill and implementation is for so many people not a process that really works especially well with collaboration. &nbsp;People tend to want to get a task to do, and then do the task and check in their code and both be working at the same time&ndash;&nbsp;so I think this drawing collaboration with Eden has really helped explore, by switching medium, taking those same problems and framing them in a way that&rsquo;s not tech-specific. She&rsquo;s not from a tech background and I am, and that&rsquo;s let us meet in the middle and explore how collaboration works.</p>\r\n<p>That sounds like a pretty big departure from your current projects &ndash; what drives your inspiration from project to project?</p>\r\n<p>I tend to like doing one thing at a time. &nbsp;Lately I&rsquo;ve been spending a lot of time working. &nbsp;When I&rsquo;m not working, I like traveling, I like drawing in parks, I like going on walks. Mostly, I like being in motion. I feel like keeping moving is what keeps me inspired, and when I&rsquo;m not really deep in my work I want to be gathering inspiration.</p>\r\n<p>Speaking of inspiration, I feel like issues of gender identity have been a lot more visible in the mainstream media lately. There&rsquo;s Janet Mock, we&rsquo;ve got Laverne Cox, there are many people speaking out about their lives and experiences.&nbsp;What do you think about the role gender identity plays in your work? &nbsp;Has it manifested itself at all, or is it a non-factor?</p>\r\n<p>Gender identity does not play a role in my current work, but it is something that I want my future work to explore. I&rsquo;m not 100% sure how I want to do that yet, but I have some ideas. It&rsquo;s not just specifically the process that people have to go through during transition, like figuring out self discovery and how to sort of reconnect with society and all the physical and emotional hardship that involved in transition&ndash;&nbsp;it&rsquo;s also really about trying to come to terms with things about the past that can&rsquo;t be changed. Things that are lost. Like the idea that if my childhood had been different maybe I wouldn&rsquo;t feel that in some ways it was lost time or in some ways it was scarring. It&rsquo;s something where I can reframe it as being a necessary catalyst for ways of inspiring other people that I can repurpose for generative use, and not just something that&rsquo;s going to stick around and just be this depressing vortex.</p>\r\n<p>(Admittedly, at this point, I am not doing a good job of communicating how I think being extremely candid with me, a stranger, about using one&rsquo;s self-acceptance as a platform to inspire others is admirable, and pretty brave. &nbsp;So I will mention it here.) I don&rsquo;t think it&rsquo;s depressing [to harness your own experience]! &nbsp;But I had some definite reservations about bridging the subject, because I also realize that people don&rsquo;t want to be labeled a certain way regarding their work and have that be a looming suffix to what&rsquo;s seen in their practice.</p>\r\n<p>Yeah, it&rsquo;s not something that I really want to hide, but I also don&rsquo;t think that should be the first thing people find out about me. It just feels like: would you introduce somebody with their hometown, or their race, or whatever? It just seems like one of those things that just feels like an unnecessary spotlight. It is something that I don&rsquo;t feel like my art has addressed yet&ndash;&nbsp;I intend for that to be something I want to highlight. &nbsp;A lot of what I do is taking things that I found difficult and turning those around into these inspirational objects or experiences I can make for other people.</p>\r\n<p>Changing gears, so while browsing your blog, I came upon a very interesting tutorial I really wanted to ask you about. &nbsp;Tell me about how you&nbsp;<a href=\"http://scanlime.org/2012/11/hacking-my-vagina/\">hacked your vagina</a>&nbsp;&ndash; what was the impetus for that?</p>\r\n<p>It was one of those things where it seemed like a worthwhile project: it was something I wanted, it was something I could document, and it was something I could use to get people interested in having more control over their own personal objects. Especially if I can put plans out there for anyone to make it easy for people to get control over their own sex toys, I think that&rsquo;s a good thing. I dunno, it was a good combination of something that I wanted to do anyway that was relatively easy to do and was fun to document, and use as an education tool.</p>\r\n<p>What are you up to right now? &nbsp;Are you working full time anywhere?</p>\r\n<p>Right now I&rsquo;m dedicating my time to developing my practice. I was working full-time at a start up, Sifteo making a new game console, and then early last year did some consulting work, but lately I&rsquo;ve just been living off of savings from previous jobs and my goal with that is if I can actually focus on producing some work that is really representative of what I want to do, then I&rsquo;ll be able to attract more jobs and commissions. Sort of taking a chance on myself.</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n</article>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/qa-with-codame-featured-artist-micah-elizabeth-scott/', '1');
INSERT INTO `pages` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `pic`, `description`, `old_url`, `hidden`) VALUES
(16, 'Q&A with Reza Ali, CODAME Featured Artist', 'q-a-with-reza-ali-codame-featured-artist', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/q-a-with-reza-ali-codame-featured-artist.gif', '<p>We caught up with CODAME Featured Artist, Reza Ali during his solo exhibition &ldquo;FluidScapes&rdquo; at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://organiclabs.tumblr.com/\">Organic</a>, where we talked about the manipulation of form, the underlying Lego narrative in his life, and his advice for aspiring new media artists.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>By Lauryn Porte on May 1, 2014</p>\r\n<p>New media artist&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.syedrezaali.com/\">Reza Ali&nbsp;</a>materializes complex data visualizations, multi-dimensional trans-architecture, and generative mathematical abstraction through his spatial sculptures and interactive installations. Ali explores the realms of art, science, and mathematics to make complex phenomena digestible, epitomizing the tension between material and immaterial space in his works. &nbsp;Some of his projects include: ofxUI, an&nbsp;<a href=\"http://ofxaddons.com/\">addon</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.openframeworks.cc/\">openframeworks</a>&nbsp;, POSSIBLE, an audio-visual VJ app for&nbsp;<a href=\"/wp-admin/www.deadmau5.com/%E2%80%8E\">Deadmau5</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/42583130\">iCubist</a>, an ipad app that augmented the Cubists Exhibit at the Santa Barbara Museum of Art.</p>\r\n<p>So, who are you and what do you do?</p>\r\n<p>My name is Reza, and I am an artist, designer and maker. &nbsp;I have a technical background in engineering, but my primary obsession is with visual aesthetics, product design, generative form making and the future.</p>\r\n<p>Can you talk about what mediums do you use to realize those ideas?</p>\r\n<p>It really depends on the idea, I think the mediums I&rsquo;ve been playing with have been software &ndash; I&rsquo;ve been building a software studio space where the code is the thing that helps you research and learn, but also it helps you produce the work, and helps you generate 3D models per say, or it helps you just get your artwork out there into the world. &nbsp;It is a way of thinking that leads to other mediums whether they&rsquo;re interactive on the web, or they&rsquo;re installations that people experience, or physical devices or hardware/software combos that do things that allow people to experience something.</p>\r\n<p>Describe the work you have on display, what are &lsquo;FluidScapes&rsquo;?</p>\r\n<p>Sweet, yeah. &nbsp;I got really interested in the book&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Poetics_of_Space\">The Poetics of Space</a>, architecture and fluid dynamics &ndash; this happened while I was in grad school when I was studying trans-architecture with Marcos Novak, which is basically the concept of reactive architecture. &nbsp;So ok the walls we have here are flat, they don&rsquo;t change color, but in software, things are so malleable, things are so flexible, you can change anything in real-time, so the whole idea of trans-architecture is about taking that whole concept of malleability and transformability and applying it the buildings and spaces we live in.</p>\r\n<p>Marcos proposed this question a while ago, which was: How do you get people to be aware of the space that they exist in? &nbsp;And I was really fascinated by that question. As humans we&rsquo;re conscious of our personal space &ndash; because we know when someone&rsquo;s in it &ndash; but I think great pieces of architecture have this presence that you feel when you enter the space. &nbsp;I got really obsessed with this whole concept of space, so I started studying fluid dynamics because the space that we inhabit is completely filled with fluids, like oxygen, and you can kind of see it when there&rsquo;s like a hot area in a room that&rsquo;s dissipating, and if you were to take a temperature measurement in that space, you could actually see the heat coming towards you &ndash; which is a really interesting concept, right? &nbsp;So the pieces in the gallery are really about making the invisible visible, and the underlying concept are fluid dynamics, fluidscapes, so it&rsquo;s kind of like giving that invisible beast of fluids a physical representation.</p>\r\n<p>What did you use to make FluidScapes?</p>\r\n<p>I wrote Fluid Solver in C++ and used openframeworks to help me visualize it in 3D. &nbsp;It was software that was written to get those pieces to exist in the real world. FluidScapes exist as 3D models in the software, but I manifested them as prints, because I wanted to see them off the screen &ndash; I wanted to see them bigger, and more impactful. &nbsp;It&rsquo;s totally different when it&rsquo;s on your screen, versus when it&rsquo;s aligned vertically and put in a gallery space.</p>\r\n<p>So you&rsquo;re exploring this kind of dense idea of the materiality of absence, and spaces &ndash; it sounds like it would be interesting if you could make a room with these visuals for a more immersive experience.</p>\r\n<p>Yeah, there are certain people that are doing that right now! &nbsp;It&rsquo;s really exciting, like some visual artists working with lasers, and creating these breathtaking spaces.</p>\r\n<p>What else influences your work?</p>\r\n<p>Generally, some concepts in math and science are super inspirational, for example &ndash; n-body particle systems are pretty interesting to me, basically n-body particles are aware of other particles around it. You can design algorithms to influence the physical properties of these particles (position, velocity, acceleration, etc) and how they interact with other particles around them. These generative algorithms allow you to design simple relationships that create insanely interesting emergent behavior. Most of the time I find happy accidents and behaviors that make me think of the book Vehicles Experiments in Synthetic Psychology, by Braitenberg.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m getting more and more physical every month, so I&rsquo;ve been thinking about smart materials &ndash; imagine you had shades that become darker when you become more self-conscious or intimidated by your environment. &nbsp;I find myself putting on my shades all the time because I want to escape and go away &ndash; so it&rsquo;d be kind of interesting to play with how human emotion can influence the products around us and how they look. &nbsp;Anouk had a kind of similar project &ndash;</p>\r\n<p>&ndash; Right, she had that dress that becomes transparent based on body heat or something (I didn&rsquo;t remember the name at the time, but the dress I&rsquo;m referring to is called Intimacy 2.0, which is made of conductive e-foils that become transparent when exposed to electricity from an accelerated heartbeat or an increase in body heat.)</p>\r\n<p>Yeah she&rsquo;s fantastic! &nbsp;Also,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roberthodgin.com/%E2%80%8E\">Robert Hodgin</a>&nbsp;for this work with graphics,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://thesystemis.com/\">Zach Lieberman</a>&nbsp;with his work with play and interactivity, Golan Levin, for his work in computational design, Casey Reas and Ben Fry, for their work with Processing.org, the concept of the software studio, and their signficiant contributions to the open source movement and making code visual and fun. &nbsp;And my peers are constantly inspiring, everyone who&rsquo;s an artist for CODAME is really inspirational, and artists who give talks at GAFFTA are amazing as well &ndash; I get inspiration anywhere and everywhere.</p>\r\n<p>Can you describe the first tech project you ever built?</p>\r\n<p>Hmm. &nbsp;I would take apart my remote control cars, and I would Frankenstein them together. &nbsp;I was always interested in how these things work, so I would take them apart and break them, and I&rsquo;d try to put them back together. &nbsp;And most of the time I was unsuccessful, but &ndash; what I would do is borrow parts from one and glue it to the other, and it was sort of like this monstrosity. &nbsp;It was beautiful in its own way. &nbsp;I remember as a kid building things with Legos all the time too; I was building things and tearing them down and figuring out new ways of building, and it&rsquo;s the whole concept of playing with Legos has carried through my whole life, like when I pay with software &ndash; it&rsquo;s like Legos. &nbsp;When I play with 3D printing, it&rsquo;s like Legos. &nbsp;When I was tearing apart those cars &ndash; I thank my parents for not getting too frustrated.</p>\r\n<p>At least you didn&rsquo;t get to the toaster</p>\r\n<p>No, I got everywhere. &nbsp;Flashlights, remote control cars, airplanes &ndash; anything that was a toy. &nbsp;And pens, and objects that I found really beautiful &ndash; I would destroy them.</p>\r\n<p>Then I hope you didn&rsquo;t have any pets!</p>\r\n<p>Oh no. I grew up with 2 dogs &ndash; but I wouldn&rsquo;t do that</p>\r\n<p>Where did you grow up?</p>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s see, for the first six years I was in Pakistan, and then the next 12 were in Miami, FL, then NY, and then Santa Barbara, LA , and now the Bay Area; I&rsquo;ve been living here for the last year and a half.</p>\r\n<p>Ok, I have a hypothetical question, if someone came up to you and said I want to do what you&rsquo;re doing -, i.e. awesome art and tech &ndash; what advice would you give them?</p>\r\n<p>I would say make as much as possible. &nbsp;Give yourself a goal. &nbsp;If you see something that&rsquo;s inspirational to you, think about how it was made, and try to learn the things you need to learn that will allow you to make those things. &nbsp;I think the first thing that I ever did formally in the field was learn processing, and learn how to write code &ndash; not seriously like a computer science student, but enough where I could use it as a tool.</p>\r\n<p>Were you self taught?</p>\r\n<p>I have a technical background in engineering, but I hated coding in undergrad. &nbsp;It was the worst &ndash; there&rsquo;s so much pressure to write whatever bank software that they were trying to get you to implement. &nbsp;So I rebelled against it for the longest time. &nbsp;In grad school I realized that to do the things I wanted to do I &nbsp;couldn&rsquo;t do them by hand &ndash; it would take me days or weeks to get projects done, and at that point I was like, alright, I gotta go to the dark side, and figure it out &ndash; it was painful. &nbsp;Learning in general is painful, so you gotta just remember to keep at it, your goal of what you want to make should drive you forward no matter what. &nbsp;I feel like a lot of people just give up because it&rsquo;s hard, and it&rsquo;s painful, but if you&rsquo;re really passionate about making, you&rsquo;ll get over the learning curve. &nbsp;That&rsquo;s something that I would advise. &nbsp;Take something that inspires you, deconstruct it, re-make it &ndash; just to learn the craft. Once you learn the craft you can start thinking about ideas and new things that exist within the field, right? The Legos that we play with now are so diverse.</p>\r\n<p>I think that&rsquo;s excellent advice, I buy the idea that you don&rsquo;t really deserve satisfaction unless you&rsquo;ve worked hard for it. &nbsp;Changing topics a bit, I noticed a lot of your past projects have incorporated music with hardware/software &ndash; what do you listen to while you&rsquo;re working?</p>\r\n<p>Again, it really depends. &nbsp;If I&rsquo;m working on an audio-visualization, I&rsquo;m really thinking about what kind of music that&rsquo;s going to go it. &nbsp;Personally I listen to electronic music, chillstep, dubstep, electronica, electro, etc &ndash; that kind of music does something to my brain. Especially when I listen to Autechre, Boards of Canada, or Richard Divine or most of the artists from Ghostly. I listen to music to help my brain focus and drown out distractions and help myself get into another space.</p>\r\n<p>That makes sense, it seems like a lot of your work kind of parallels the structure of electronic music, which is, uh (unable to articulate anything verbally, I explain by drawing an imaginary square with my index fingers)</p>\r\n<p>Yeah, and you feel it &ndash; the more eclectic the music, the more it stimulates your brain. &nbsp;When you see something that&rsquo;s normal, you don&rsquo;t even consider it, you don&rsquo;t listen to it&hellip; it&rsquo;s kind of like when someone shows up to work all disheveled, and you&rsquo;re like-</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Hey you, what&rsquo;s going on there?&rdquo; Is listening to this kind of &lsquo;disruptive&rsquo; music normally apart of your process?</p>\r\n<p>When I&rsquo;m working I like to listen to music with no lyrics and completely engulf myself in whatever I&rsquo;m doing and just, flow &ndash; I was up til 5 a.m. today working. &nbsp;My process is really about letting whatever you&rsquo;re doing come out of you, and I&rsquo;ve heard this works for writers as well, and artists as well. &nbsp;I&rsquo;ve given up trying to get up early and work, I&rsquo;ve realized inspiration is probably going to come at 11 a.m. or 11 p.m. and who knows when it&rsquo;s going to leave. &nbsp;So I keep working until I pass out &ndash; that&rsquo;s my process.</p>\r\n<p>How did you get involved in CODAME?</p>\r\n<p>I met Bruno (CODAME Commodore) randomly one night when I was hanging out with Robert Hodgin and a couple other friends. &nbsp;Bruno told me about CODAME, and I was like that sounds fantastic and I&rsquo;d love to be a part of that in any way possible. &nbsp;We followed up over email, and I think the first thing we ever did was this Halloween thing &ndash; it was really weird and that&rsquo;s why I loved it.</p>\r\n<p>Why was it weird?</p>\r\n<p>It was weird because I was projecting visuals in this room, where there were these people dressed all in white &ndash;</p>\r\n<p>Oh &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/5enses/%E2%80%8E\">5enses</a>!</p>\r\n<p>I think so! &nbsp;And they were all sort of moving in space. &nbsp;And I was like, this is awesome. &nbsp;This is weird, and I like what it&rsquo;s doing to my brain. &nbsp;Yeah, I think CODAME has been super helpful in terms of fostering the growth, Bruno and Jordan are fantastic, and always invite me to show work or talk, and I just want to say that those guys have been really critical to my growth as an artist in SF.</p>\r\n<p>On that note, can you talk about CODAME&rsquo;s Adopt and Artist program, and what you&rsquo;re looking for in patronage &ndash; why do you want to be &ldquo;adopted&rdquo;?</p>\r\n<p>I think it&rsquo;s an interesting concept &ndash; if you go back to the early days of the Renaissance, there were patrons that would encourage/fund artists to make their work, and these artists would become influential in history, not only for what they painted and how beautiful it was at the time, but what they were saying with their work. &nbsp;I think as with artists today, especially living in the Bay Area and working in the tech/art field, there&rsquo;s a lot of people who are like, &ldquo;Come work for my start up. Write JavaScript for me.&rdquo; And I think that&rsquo;s interesting and fun, but, there aren&rsquo;t a lot of places that are truly encouraging artists to make with technology. &nbsp;And I think technology has only been around for what, 40 years &ndash; so in my opinion, we know so little about this field, and there&rsquo;s tons of new things, like social media, new applications that connect people, and a lot of unknowns: ethically, socially, emotionally, and I think artists need to be exploring right now.</p>\r\n<p>What did you do before you started pursuing your art practice full time?</p>\r\n<p>I worked at this company called Famo.us, and they are reinventing the web and the interfaces on the web. &nbsp;Those interfaces are really about movement, aesthetics, design and performance, because the web all seems slow &ndash; and apps are faster. &nbsp;So the whole concept there is &ldquo;make it better&rdquo; &ndash; create frameworks that allow people to do what I do, with real-time graphics but on the web. &nbsp;So that whole feedback cycle of hey let&rsquo;s make art with JavaScript, was an interesting concept because I had a constraint, but I had to be really creative with that constraint, which forces me to think differently and feedback. &nbsp;In that way it was a challenge for both of us, but both parties equally benefitted from having each other around.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;d love for companies to have Artist in Residencies that actually pay decent salaries, so I could do what I do and be more sustainable. &nbsp;Now I&rsquo;m like, extremely cheap, and I dunno &ndash; it&rsquo;s sort of uncomfortable sometimes, coming from making six figures to making less than 30. is a huge, drastic change. &nbsp;So it&rsquo;d be great if companies were more willing to be experimental. &nbsp;I think all the good ones like Google, Apple, Salesfoce</p>\r\n<p>&ndash; even Facebook</p>\r\n<p>Yeah, I think those companies &ndash; Autodesk of course&ndash; &nbsp;are really leading the effort forward. &nbsp;I would like more companies to embrace it. &nbsp;Adopt an Artist is a great movement because patronage is dead, but it needs to come back.</p>\r\n<p>Are you currently working on any other projects?</p>\r\n<p>I just finished a project that&rsquo;s all about 3D scanning and sculpture that&rsquo;s for children and students &ndash; that&rsquo;s going to be released, formally written up on my website, probably in a month. &nbsp;The project is collaboration with this guy Jeff, who runs&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.botndolly.com/\">Bot and Dolly</a>&nbsp;(with Randy), a company that does some insane things with robots; they&rsquo;re the guys who helped shoot Gravity &ndash; these robotic arms that do amazing movements around the actors.</p>\r\n<p>Oh, and one small side project I&rsquo;m going to be working on at Autodesk is all about generative&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Voronoi_diagram\">voronoi</a>&nbsp;puzzles.<img src=\"https://31.media.tumblr.com/1c27de1325992087d2f676c08894d76d/tumblr_inline_n5mqcj71pF1sfxgsr.gif\" alt=\"image\" /></p>\r\n<p>What is a &lsquo;voronoi&rsquo;?</p>\r\n<p>So let&rsquo;s say you have two points here (gestures with index fingers), there&rsquo;s a line that basically is in between them that&rsquo;s equidistant to the points. &nbsp;So if you have another set of points here (more pointing), there&rsquo;s another line, and then these lines are connected together to basically create closing spaces- it&rsquo;s like another type of algorithm in computational geometry. &nbsp;So the whole concept of the puzzle is to have these certain points moving to certain algorithms over time, and generating from their movements a three-dimensional cell or puzzle that anyone can put together. &nbsp;It&rsquo;s really a project all about form in a generative way. &nbsp;I think these shapes are really beautiful when you see them in the software, these sort of like these curved surfaces that evolve just because these particles are moving in space to certain algorithms, and when you look at them they&rsquo;re totally far out, and when you touch them, you feel something, and then when your brain uses its power to put them together in a puzzle it&rsquo;s really satisfying.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m seeing the Lego pieces come together here.</p>\r\n<p>Yeah, right. &nbsp;There&rsquo;s generative systems driving form, which is driving 3D prints, which is then being made into things, which is then illuminated from the bottom &ndash; all these pieces come together and I find it fascinating. &nbsp;I don&rsquo;t know what else to do with my life&nbsp;(laughter).</p>\r\n<p>Actually what I want to do in the future is have my work be way more interactive, and way more engaging where you&rsquo;re not just looking at a pretty picture and appreciating it for the underlying mathematics and aesthetics, but you are engaging in it to the degree where you&rsquo;re touching it, you&rsquo;re feeling it, to accomplish something like a mental puzzle.</p>\r\n<p>Edited for length.&nbsp;&nbsp;Reza Ali is currently an&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.instructables.com/id/Overview-Access-to-Autodesk-Pier-9-Workshop/\">Artist in Residence at Autodesk</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/reza/\">Featured Artist at CODAME</a>&nbsp;who&rsquo;s currently up for Adoption,&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:sponsor@codame.com\">Contact us</a>&nbsp;if you have questions or ideas.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/artists\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100px\" /></a></p>', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/qa-with-reza-ali-codame-featured-artist/', '1'),
(17, 'ART+TECH Playground [Photos]', 'art-tech-playground-photos', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-playground-photos.jpg', '\r\n						<p style=\"color: #444444;\">Photos from <a href=\"https://flic.kr/s/aHsjY2XKh3\">https://flic.kr/s/aHsjY2XKh3</a></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4705\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296661980_f64f4b0153_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296661980_f64f4b0153_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"></p>\r\n<p>On Saturday, May 31st, 2014 CODAME transformed the Doll House, future home of CounterPULSE in the Tenderloin, into a vibrant <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/playground/\">Playground</a> for ART + TECH enthusiasts and practitioners. A playful day full of ART+TECH activities, live performances, workshops, electronic music, and interactive projections supporting artists and the community!</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4706\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296662480_1faf481e20_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296662480_1faf481e20_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4707\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296665740_4fb1c164b8_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296665740_4fb1c164b8_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4708\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296667019_6c758ef1ca_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296667019_6c758ef1ca_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4709\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296667219_e9e28711d0_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296667219_e9e28711d0_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1095\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4710\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296668399_ba4e9005f0_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296668399_ba4e9005f0_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4712\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296668579_36edc78c02_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296668579_36edc78c02_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4713\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296704328_172715f9f2_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296704328_172715f9f2_o\" width=\"1067\" height=\"1600\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4714\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296704868_f69c6244d3_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296704868_f69c6244d3_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4715\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296705098_b0737c2346_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296705098_b0737c2346_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4716\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296705938_419767e511_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296705938_419767e511_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1050\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4717\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296706418_f3ac7be888_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296706418_f3ac7be888_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4718\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296859037_8817515c51_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296859037_8817515c51_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4719\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296859747_d3cb5c2b1a_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296859747_d3cb5c2b1a_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4720\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296860057_35870d0524_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296860057_35870d0524_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4721\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14296860447_a85a44990a_o.jpg\" alt=\"14296860447_a85a44990a_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4722\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14460188676_3e1b4b6f1c_o.jpg\" alt=\"14460188676_3e1b4b6f1c_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4723\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14460189036_77a46bc0f4_o.jpg\" alt=\"14460189036_77a46bc0f4_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4724\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14460189646_8aaa8c33ff_o.jpg\" alt=\"14460189646_8aaa8c33ff_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"997\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4725\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14482028752_30a0327736_o.jpg\" alt=\"14482028752_30a0327736_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4726\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14482029762_06aa5df5ac_o.jpg\" alt=\"14482029762_06aa5df5ac_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4727\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14482032242_7bed70746d_o.jpg\" alt=\"14482032242_7bed70746d_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4728\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14482032552_640520705e_o.jpg\" alt=\"14482032552_640520705e_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4729\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14482066244_68c456f26d_o.jpg\" alt=\"14482066244_68c456f26d_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4730\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14482066594_2bf77ffdb5_o.jpg\" alt=\"14482066594_2bf77ffdb5_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"> <img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4731\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/14483286225_6f5b80b311_o.jpg\" alt=\"14483286225_6f5b80b311_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\"></p>\r\n<p>Find more photos and tag your friends on our <a href=\"http://on.fb.me/1pwqNiw\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook page</a> too!</p>\r\n											', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/arttech-playground-photos/', '1'),
(18, 'Re/code: ART+TECH Rendezvous', 're-code-art-tech-rendezvous', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/re-code-art-tech-rendezvous.jpg', '<h1>Friday Night in San Francisco and the GIF Art Is Pumping</h1>\r\n<p>Photos and Article by <a href=\"http://twitter.com/NellieBowles\" target=\"_blank\">Nellie Bowles</a>,&nbsp;August 16, 2014,&nbsp;<a href=\"/post/portfolio/arttech-rendezvous-recode/2014/08/16/friday-night-in-san-francisco-and-the-gif-art-is-pumping/\" target=\"_blank\">recode.net</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>It was a Friday night co-working happy hour in San Francisco. The 3-D body scanner was out. An interactive version of Flappy Bird was cued up. And the GIF art was pumping. The monthly happy hour, called <a href=\"/post/portfolio/arttech-rendezvous-geekdomsf-aug-2014/\">Rendezvous</a> and meant to showcase local digital artists over cocktails, started at a co-working space called <a href=\"http://twitter.com/GeekdomSF\" target=\"_blank\">@GeekdomSF</a> at 7 pm. At 7:01, it was already packed with about 150 tech workers looking to nerd out over some source code and dancing GIFs. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s an eager crowd,&rdquo; said organizer Jordan <a href=\"http://twitter.com/Starpause\" target=\"_blank\">Starpause</a> Gray, who wore a patterned t-shirt and a mohawk.</p>\r\n<p>&hellip; more&nbsp;on <a href=\"/new/admin/2014/08/16/friday-night-in-san-francisco-and-the-gif-art-is-pumping/\" target=\"_blank\">recode.net</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://recode.net/2014/08/16/friday-night-in-san-francisco-and-the-gif-art-is-pumping/\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dsc02861-1120x746.jpg\" alt=\"Photo by Nellie Bowles (recode.net)\" width=\"1120\" height=\"746\" /></a> <a href=\"http://recode.net/2014/08/16/friday-night-in-san-francisco-and-the-gif-art-is-pumping/\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dsc02902-1120x746.jpg\" alt=\"Photo by Nellie Bowles (recode.net)\" width=\"1120\" height=\"746\" /></a> <a href=\"http://recode.net/2014/08/16/friday-night-in-san-francisco-and-the-gif-art-is-pumping/\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dsc02917-1120x746.jpg\" alt=\"Photo by Nellie Bowles (recode.net)\" width=\"1120\" height=\"746\" /></a> <a href=\"http://recode.net/2014/08/16/friday-night-in-san-francisco-and-the-gif-art-is-pumping/\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dsc02950-1120x1146.jpg\" alt=\"Photo by Nellie Bowles (recode.net)\" width=\"1120\" height=\"1146\" /></a> <iframe src=\"http://player.theplatform.com/p/PhfuRC/vNP4WUiQeJFa/embed/select/ZToJ_qrdx2c2?width=640&amp;height=360\" width=\"915\" height=\"515\" frameborder=\"0\" seamless=\"seamless\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\">Your browser does not support iframes.</iframe></p>', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/arttech-rendezvous-recode/', '1'),
(19, 'LeapyBird Adopted by Shopify', 'leapybird-adopted-by-shopify', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/leapybird-adopted-by-shopify.jpg', '\r\n						<p> </p>\r\n<p>We are happy to announce <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/leapybird/\">LeapyBird</a> has found a home and patron: <a href=\"http://shopify.com/wix\" target=\"_blank\">Shopify</a></p>\r\n<p>Thanks to <a href=\"http://shopify.com/wix\" target=\"_blank\">Shopify</a> appreciation of art+tech+games LeapyBird will be flying high at the <a href=\"http://bit.ly/codamecodelocal\" target=\"_blank\">CodeLocal Event</a> at the Wix Lounge.</p>\r\n<p>Interview with Shopify and ANI on the ART+TECH Collection post on <a href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/codame-art-tech-3c7ec572c131\" target=\"_blank\">Medium by Jessica Hunt</a>. Enjoy!</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://bit.ly/codamecodelocal\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5430\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/2172ee_e2908a4436bc40afb6b7f399ae637735.png_srz_p_135_135_75_22_0.50_1.20_0.png\" alt=\"2172ee_e2908a4436bc40afb6b7f399ae637735.png_srz_p_135_135_75_22_0.50_1.20_0\" width=\"135\" height=\"135\"></a></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"font_3\">Develop 24 Web Apps in 24 Hours</h3>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">Celebrate the launch of Wix new San Francisco <a href=\"http://www.wix.com/lounge/san-francisco\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"color_13\">Developers Lounge</span></a> with a 24-hour Code Lab. Collaborate with fellow developers, designers and techies to create web apps that solve the needs of local businesses.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"font_3\">Give Back & Get Rewarded</h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Complete the Code Lab and get:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"p1\">A 6-month membership to our awesome developers-only workspace</li>\r\n<li class=\"p1\">Free marketing of your app to over 52 million Wix users</li>\r\n<li class=\"p1\">Prizes like a parrot drone, Playstation 4, Fitbit & more</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Featured Speakers:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Harley Finkelstein: Shopify Chief Platform Officer</li>\r\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Yoav Abrahami: Wix Chief Architect</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Other Awesomeness:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul1\">\r\n<li class=\"li1\">Interactive video game installation by CODAME</li>\r\n<li class=\"li1\">3D badges from Shapeways</li>\r\n<li class=\"li1\">delicious food like ramen burgers, waffles, avocado fries and beyond!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Adopt #LeapyBird for your events too!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://bit.ly/codamecodelocal\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5431 size-large hoverZoomLink\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/leapybird_custom3b-1024x642.jpg\" alt=\"leapybird_custom3b\" width=\"1024\" height=\"642\"></a></p>\r\n											', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/leapybird-adopted-by-shopify/', '1'),
(23, 'Labs', 'labs', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/labs.png', '<p>A creative space where interdisciplinary collaborations take place between artists, designers, architects, engineers, scientists and technologists.</p>\r\n<p>Artists at CODAME LABS&nbsp;will lead in-house developments focused on intersecting art with technology.</p>\r\n<p>The CODAME LABS&nbsp;includes projects in&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Design Software</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">3D Modeling</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">3D Printing</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Fashion Design</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Wearables</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Prototyping</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Interactive Visualizations</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Sensor-based Installations</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Sound Design</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Creative Coding</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Engineering</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Robotics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>All projects, concepts and installations created in the LABS will be shown at special events, partners events and annual ART+TECH Festival.</p>\r\n<p>Get involved!</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// ARTISTS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Let us know about you and your project,&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-proposals\">send us</a> a project proposal&nbsp;to join&nbsp;the CODAME&nbsp;or to be part of our ART+TECH Events.</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// SUPPORTERS</strong></p>\r\n<p>A great opportunity for exposure and brand recognition as creative lead innovators.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Join our list of amazing&nbsp;<a href=\"/sponsors\">Sponsors</a>.</p>\r\n<p>An&nbsp;opportunity for you to join one of the most innovative initiatives in&nbsp;San Francisco.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sponsor a project</li>\r\n<li>Build a project together</li>\r\n<li>Run Workshops/Lectures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Drop us a note,&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:team@codame.com\">contact us</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '1'),
(28, 'CODAME Artist Collective', 'codame-artist-collective', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-artist-collective.gif', '<p>Be part of the CODAME Artist Collective. If accepted, you will receive access&nbsp;to all future CODAME ART+TECH events. Submit your online or&nbsp;<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-73f5222a-7fff-3879-c672-7558cee95985\">physical&nbsp;</span>projects: workshops, installation&nbsp;experiences, performances, or artwork for the opportunity to be showcased at CODAME&nbsp;<a href=\"/events\">Events</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://gallery.codame.com\">Galleries</a>,&nbsp;and/or have your artwork prints for sale&nbsp;in our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com\">Shop</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nft.codame.com\">NFTs</a></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-1b82c33a-e394-61c3-97e1-44f6b3a1e7ce\">To&nbsp;apply:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Read&nbsp;the CODAME Artists&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/codame-artists-agreement\">Agreement</a></li>\r\n<li>Send us your project&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-proposals\">Proposal</a></li>\r\n<li>Upload your artwork&nbsp;<a href=\"https://forms.gle/kj6cDdywq3dYHehe9\">Here</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Our curators will follow up with you&nbsp;with an acceptance letter or for further information.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"mailto:art@codame.com\">Contact us</a>&nbsp;or join&nbsp;the CODAME&nbsp;<a href=\"https://discord.com/invite/pk3C8DB\">Discord</a>&nbsp;ART+TECH community&nbsp;for&nbsp;any questions you might have.</p>\r\n<h2>/// Why should I join?</h2>\r\n<p>CODAME Offers</p>\r\n<p>- Curation assistance (selecting the right work for the right platform, release schedule).</p>\r\n<p>- Minting assistance and guidance.</p>\r\n<p>- Promotion can include social media, artist profile page on codame.com, interviews, critiques, etc.</p>\r\n<p>- Selling art opportunities at our auctions, galleries,&nbsp;and&nbsp;festival events.</p>\r\n<p>You</p>\r\n<p>- Will retain all copyrights.</p>\r\n<p>- Get 70% of the profit (from the original sale and \"Forever Royalties\")</p>\r\n<p>- Support CODAME mission and ART+TECH community with&nbsp;the remaining&nbsp;30% from the sales</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>/// What are the requirements for the upload?</h2>\r\n<div>The file size should be below 50GB. As a general guideline, artwork resolution is at least 4k (3840x2160px). The highest you have is the best. While we love programmatic and interactive artwork, image and video files are the best fit for upload to the&nbsp;CODAME Artist Collective HD Collection.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>/// Where can I upload my files?</h2>\r\n<div>Please submit your Artwork to this&nbsp;<a href=\"https://forms.gle/kj6cDdywq3dYHehe9\">HD Asset Uploader</a>. Form uploads are limited to 10GB so email <a href=\"mailto:art@codame.com\">art@codame,com</a>&nbsp;if you need to transfer bigger files (or if you have any other issues).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>///&nbsp;For NFTs</h2>\r\n<p>2020 brought CODAME artists great success in the NFT market. At the beginning of 2021 we took a pause to&nbsp;do things right &amp; address concerns we heard from our artists. Partnering with MINTBASE on NEAR ticks all of our boxes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Carbon neutral gen3 blockchain built for global adoption.</li>\r\n<li>Support the CODAME ART+TECH mission by splitting sales profits and royalties.</li>\r\n<li>Fast &amp; inexpensive transfers.</li>\r\n<li>Web-native UX (no browser extensions required).&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The remaining&nbsp;profit from the NFT shop will go to a&nbsp;CODAME Community&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nearguilds.com/2021/03/03/sputnik-dao-is-here-lets-break-down-what-that-means/\" target=\"_blank\">Decentralized Autonomous Organization</a>. Anyone in the community will be able to make proposals for the&nbsp;council to greenlight. Self-governance and royalty distribution are just a few things blockchain technology can automate, let\'s build the future together!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you don\'t have a yourname. near wallet you can&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wallet.near.org/\" target=\"_blank\">get one for free</a>. The $NEAR crypto currency can be bought and traded at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.gate.io/ref/63013\" target=\"_blank\">gate.io</a>&nbsp;(USA option) or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://messari.io/asset/near-protocol/exchanges\" target=\"_blank\">other exchanges</a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>/// What about exclusivity?</h2>\r\n<div>Your artwork remains your own. The terms and conditions in our&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/codame-artists-agreement\">Agreement</a>&nbsp;contain a non-exclusive license with CODAME.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>/// What kind of work should I upload?</h2>\r\n<div>You are able to upload any selection of work you choose,&nbsp;our curators will work with you on the selection.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>/// Can I opt-out at any time?</h2>\r\n<div>Yes, you can delete your work from the collection at any time. We request that you allow us 30 days to cycle the art out of all distribution channels. We can also delete your profile&nbsp;at your request.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>/// Can I create limited editions?</h2>\r\n<div>Yes, you can specify the number of limited editions when uploaded. A certificate may be requested by the customer.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>/// What do I get?</h2>\r\n<div>For each sale of an Artwork, CODAME&nbsp;will pay you 70% of the royalties.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Note that we may change the Royalty that applies to the various types of sales from time to time. However, any such change will not affect the Royalty you earn on sale which has already occurred, or to the sales of any edition which is already on sale at the time when the change is made: to avoid doubt, the changed Royalty will apply only to the Edition of the next Artwork to go on sale, not to the edition currently on sale at the time when we notify you of the changed sale Royalty rate.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>For the purposes of calculating the Royalty,&nbsp;\"Net Revenues\"&nbsp;are amounts actually received by CODAME&nbsp;for sums paid to us for sale of the Artwork, net of all relevant deductions including (without limitation):</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Any and all tax, tariffs, and fees (including any VAT taxes);</li>\r\n<li>transaction costs;</li>\r\n<li>chargebacks and returns;</li>\r\n<li>any sums paid or repaid to Users in connection with the relevant sale,</li>\r\n<li>any revenue share or commission paid or payable to distributors, licensees, or others involved in the sale of an Artwork, and</li>\r\n<li>any sums paid, payable, deductible or creditable to third parties in connection with the relevant sale of an Artwork.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>/// Who pays for US sales taxes?</h2>\r\n<div>We charge the buyers US sales taxes, separately on top of the set price.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>---</div>\r\n<div>Credit: Artwork from <a href=\"/projects/the-creation\">The Creation</a> project&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '1'),
(47, 'Call for Stream Performances', 'call-for-stream-performances', '', '<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdAarvqJ8h5HE9KAkQ7MouaqyHStvDGxNWMaGQyJZE7GLdisQ/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"640\" height=\"2885\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loadingâ€¦</iframe></p>', '', '0'),
(22, 'Join Us', 'join-us', '', '<p><iframe style=\"border: 1px solid #EEE; background: white;\" src=\"https://codame.substack.com/embed\" width=\"480\" height=\"320\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong>/// STAY IN TOUCH</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://codame.substack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sign-up</a>&nbsp;to our newsletter&nbsp;to be notified about&nbsp;our new events or initiatives, call for artists, project proposals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"mailto:team@codame.com\">Contact us</a>&nbsp;for any enquiry&nbsp;or just to say hi!</p>\r\n<p>Stay connected&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/admin/twittter.com/codame\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://codame.substack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Substack</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/codame/\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a>, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-xKBSgGX4xfLS7-O3w9xBQ\">Youtube</a>, <a href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech\">Medium</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/codame\">LinkedIn</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/codame\">GitHub</a>, <a href=\"https://discord.com/invite/pk3C8DB\">Discord</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tiktok.com/@codame\">TikTok</a>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.tumblr.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Tumblr</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// VOLUNTEERS</strong></p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a fun and extremely rewarding experience as you learn new skills and pass your knowledge on to others. You&rsquo;ll meet like-minded people, make friends&nbsp;and build a network of people from all backgrounds who share a common passion for ART+TECH.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/call-for-volunteers\">Apply</a> to be part of the magic! We&rsquo;re looking for outstanding volunteers&nbsp;to support our ART+TECH initiatives.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>/// ARTISTS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Be part of the <a href=\"/pages/codame-artist-collective\">CODAME Artist Collective</a>. If accepted, you will receive access&nbsp;to all future CODAME ART+TECH events. Submit your online or&nbsp;<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-73f5222a-7fff-3879-c672-7558cee95985\">physical&nbsp;</span>projects: workshops, installation&nbsp;experiences, performances, or artwork for the opportunity to be showcased at CODAME&nbsp;<a href=\"/events\">Events</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://gallery.codame.com\">Galleries</a>,&nbsp;and/or have your artwork prints for sale&nbsp;in our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com\">Shop</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nft.codame.com\">NFTs</a></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-1b82c33a-e394-61c3-97e1-44f6b3a1e7ce\">To&nbsp;apply:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Read&nbsp;the CODAME Artists&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/codame-artists-agreement\">Agreement</a></li>\r\n<li>Send us your project&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-proposals\">Proposal</a></li>\r\n<li>Upload your artwork&nbsp;<a href=\"https://forms.gle/kj6cDdywq3dYHehe9\">Here</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Our curators will follow up with you&nbsp;with an acceptance letter or for further information.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"mailto:art@codame.com\">Contact us</a> or join&nbsp;the CODAME&nbsp;<a href=\"https://discord.com/invite/pk3C8DB\">Discord</a>&nbsp;ART+TECH community&nbsp;for any questions you might have.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>///&nbsp;SPONSORS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Join our list of amazing <a href=\"/sponsors\">Sponsors</a>. Be recognized as the innovative and visionary organization, partner with us on:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bring a CODAME Artist installation or performance to your event or team offsite</li>\r\n<li>Sponsor a CODAME&nbsp;<a href=\"/events\">event</a>&nbsp;or workshop</li>\r\n<li>Build a visionary&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects\">project</a>&nbsp;with us</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">Contact Us</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>///&nbsp;DONATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH</p>\r\n<p>CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p>All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.flipcause.com/secure/cause_pdetails/NjU0OA==\">Donations</a>&nbsp;are always welcome.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">contact Us</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;us&nbsp;if interested to make an in kind donation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/join-us2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"767\" height=\"269\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '0'),
(20, 'Team', 'team', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/team.jpg', '<p>A bunch of peeps with a thing for Art and Technology!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Commodore&nbsp;(in-Chief): Bruno Fonzi @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/BrunoFonzi\" target=\"_blank\">BrunoFonzi</a><br />Amiga&nbsp;(Guru Meditation Handler): Jordan Gray @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/Starpause\" target=\"_blank\">staRpauSe<br /></a>(Curator): Vanessa Chang @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/vxchang\">vxchang<br /></a>Compaq (Investigative Wordsmith): Irene Malatesta @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/irenekaoru\">IreneKaoru</a><br />Atari&nbsp;(Artist Canvas): Vicente Montelongo @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/mexist\" target=\"_blank\">Mexist</a><br />Cray1&nbsp;(TechArt Ninja):&nbsp;Kevin Koechley @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/kkoechley\" target=\"_blank\">KKoechley<br /></a>Strela&nbsp;(Social Cyberfly): Olia Pospelova&nbsp;@<a href=\"https://twitter.com/oliapospelova\">OliaPospelova</a><br />Gravis Ultrasound&nbsp;(Media Munger): Amy Lee @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/animusicsf\" target=\"_blank\">AniMusicSF</a><br />JUNO-60&nbsp;(Markup Master): Donald Hanson @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/Gridwalk\" target=\"_blank\">Gridwalk</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/LaurynPorte\" target=\"_blank\"><br /></a></p>\r\n<p>/// FRIENDS + SUPPORTERS<br />Dat Phan, Justing Kinder, Tiare Ribeaux, Irene Grossrubatscher, Jaquie Bacich-Paratt, Valerie Alloix, Stefano Corazza, Kiri Rong, Vicky Chen, Karen Hsu,&nbsp;Nancy Garcia,&nbsp;Julie Goldsmith,&nbsp;Allen Ellison,&nbsp;Drew Clark,&nbsp;Tarwin Stroh-Spijer,&nbsp;Bernie Samson,&nbsp;DC Spensley,&nbsp;Lauren Anderson,&nbsp;Michael Conover,&nbsp;Andrea Starr,&nbsp;Felipe Brahm, Hanna Regev, Jesse Fulton, Misaki C. Kido, Jonathan Wallraven, Julia&nbsp;Sun, Lauryn Porte&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists\">&hellip; and more than 100 amazing&nbsp;artists&nbsp;and volunteers!</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a>&nbsp;if you&rsquo;re interested in&nbsp;joining our&nbsp;team, if you have any enquiry&nbsp;or just to say hi!</p>', '', '1');
INSERT INTO `pages` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `pic`, `description`, `old_url`, `hidden`) VALUES
(35, 'Code of Conduct', 'code-of-conduct', '', '<h1>Codame Code of Conduct&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p>All attendees, speakers, sponsors and volunteers at our events&nbsp;are required to agree with the following code of conduct. Organisers will enforce this code throughout the event. We expect cooperation from all participants to help ensure a safe environment for everybody.</p>\r\n<h2>Need Help?</h2>\r\n<p>You have our contact details in the emails we\'ve sent.</p>\r\n<h2>The Quick Version</h2>\r\n<p>Our event is&nbsp;dedicated to providing a harassment-free event&nbsp;experience for everyone, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, age, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, religion (or lack thereof), or technology choices. We do not tolerate harassment of event&nbsp;participants in any form. Sexual language and imagery is not appropriate for any event&nbsp;venue, including talks, workshops, parties, Twitter and other online media. Event&nbsp;participants violating these rules may be sanctioned or expelled from the event&nbsp;without a refund&nbsp;at the discretion of the event&nbsp;organisers.</p>\r\n<h2>The Less Quick Version</h2>\r\n<p>Harassment includes offensive verbal comments related to gender, gender identity and expression, age, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, religion, technology choices, sexual images in public spaces, deliberate intimidation, stalking, following, harassing photography or recording, sustained disruption of talks or other events, inappropriate physical contact, and unwelcome sexual attention.</p>\r\n<p>Participants asked to stop any harassing behavior are expected to comply immediately.</p>\r\n<p>Sponsors are also subject to the anti-harassment policy. In particular, sponsors should not use sexualised images, activities, or other material. Booth staff (including volunteers) should not use sexualised clothing/uniforms/costumes, or otherwise create a sexualised environment.</p>\r\n<p>If a participant engages in harassing behavior, the event&nbsp;organisers may take any action they deem appropriate, including warning the offender or expulsion from the event&nbsp;with no refund.</p>\r\n<p>If you are being harassed, notice that someone else is being harassed, or have any other concerns, please contact a member of event&nbsp;staff immediately. Event&nbsp;staff can be identified as they\'ll be wearing branded clothing and/or badges.</p>\r\n<p>Event&nbsp;staff will be happy to help participants contact hotel/venue security or local law enforcement, provide escorts, or otherwise assist those experiencing harassment to feel safe for the duration of the event. We value your attendance.</p>\r\n<p>We expect participants to follow these rules at event&nbsp;and workshop venues and event-related social events.</p>', '', '1'),
(25, 'Call For Volunteers', 'call-for-volunteers', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/call-for-volunteers.jpeg', '<p dir=\"auto\">We offer a fun and rewarding experience, where you can learn new skills and pass your knowledge on to others. An opportunity to meet like-minded people, make friends and build a network of people from all backgrounds who share a passion for ART+TECH. We are also offering free tickets to various <a href=\"/events\">activities</a> planned&nbsp;at&nbsp;our&nbsp;events&nbsp;or workshops.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"auto\">All skill sets, strengths, and levels of commitment are welcome, but there are a few skills that we would find particularly valuable.</p>\r\n<h1>In high demand:</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Video Star: </strong>Create&nbsp;short&nbsp;movies&nbsp;to showcase artists work and inspire others.</li>\r\n<li id=\"f82d\"><span data-creator-ids=\"4ae3f675837c\"><strong>Media Press Liaison</strong>: Spread the good word and make sure the world doesn&rsquo;t miss out.</span></li>\r\n<li id=\"aaee\"><strong>Hack Designer</strong>: Push the boundaries of ART+TECH to express what CODAME is all about.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Workshop Booster</strong>:&nbsp;Lead and coordinate our workshops, learn and build stuff together with our&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists\">Artists</a>.</li>\r\n<li><strong>VR Architect</strong>: take the work of our artists to the next level&nbsp;to be experienced also in virtual galleries.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Web Dev Ninja</strong>: Build&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/orgs/CODAME\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"https://github.com/orgs/CODAME\">websites</a>, design as fluidly as drinking a glass of wine.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cyber Conservator:</strong> Connect with artists around the world to include in the CODAME HD Collection.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Volunteer Champion</strong>: Lead,&nbsp;coordinate and recruit&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/call-for-volunteers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/pages/call-for-volunteers\">more champions</a></li>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Poet</strong>: </strong>Keep our&nbsp;ART+TECH posts on <a href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech\" target=\"_blank\" data-href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech\">Medium</a> or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://codame.substack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Substack</a><strong>&nbsp;</strong>fresh with your wit and insights.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Street Team Member</strong>: Take our message to the people via&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/codame\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"https://twitter.com/codame\">Twitter</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\">Facebook</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/codame/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"https://www.instagram.com/codame/\">Instagram</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://codame.tumblr.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.tumblr.com/\">tumble</a>, <a href=\"https://www.tiktok.com/@codame\">TikTok</a>,&nbsp;or even myspace if you want!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1 dir=\"auto\">Evergreen Opportunities:&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Event Curator</strong>: Have an idea for a great event? Let\'s make it happen!</li>\r\n<li id=\"caee\"><strong>Event preparation</strong>: Meet beforehand to set everything up, prepare workshop materials, refreshments, put up signs, etc.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li id=\"d55d\"><strong><strong>Event Liaison</strong>: </strong>Greet attendees, provide badges and give out information.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li id=\"d55d\"><strong><strong>Stage Manager</strong>:&nbsp;</strong>Bring your own&nbsp;shepherd\'s crook, be close to the action!&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li id=\"d55d\"><strong><strong>Emcee</strong>:&nbsp;</strong>Be the charismatic glue weaving through an amazing line of acts.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li id=\"3663\"><strong>Hollywood Buster</strong>: Shoot like a paparazzi and go viral as a cat!&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li id=\"3663\"><strong>ModBod Scanner</strong>: Run the <a href=\"/projects/modbod\">full body capture interactive installation</a>, always a hit!&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Event tear-down</strong>: What goes up must come down</li>\r\n<li id=\"f82d\"><strong>Event Master</strong>: overseeing event operations, guiding volunteers, artists, and coordinating technical and production aspects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1YW5H5kAhJbclkOU2bYBqUu8b0y34ziXNHFgBxOmayEE/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"100%\" height=\"1600\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loading...</iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vRlKjbmbKkcBZwfVYkm400ukwm0AqfL1xeh3Ow1NYxD5Y1SqA5l3Xs-jjJGJOm6DXSPgJwyoGTEszN-/embed?start=false&amp;loop=false&amp;delayms=3000\" width=\"620\" height=\"377\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>', '', '1'),
(26, 'Partners + Sponsorship Enquiry', 'partners-sponsorship-enquiry', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/partners-sponsorship-enquiry.png', '<p><iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-image: url(\'/admin/img/object.gif\');\" src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1smT0-ikGFdd-vZGfI40FnMZ25srVuMaGnT6kqN9mu7Y/embed?start=true&amp;loop=true&amp;delayms=5000\" width=\"760\" height=\"474\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1dHvD3v2gPvG--x9wlpR4EIMEcdjucVjmWCxcIGcFD7E/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"100%\" height=\"1200\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loading...</iframe></p>', '', '1'),
(27, 'NEWS: ANNOUNCING CODAME LABS', 'news-announcing-codame-labs', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/news-announcing-codame-labs.png', '<p class=\"graf--p\"><strong class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\">LEADING ART+TECH ORGANIZATION ANNOUNCES the LAUNCH of CODAME LABS</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\"><a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"http://labs.codame.com\" data-href=\"http://labs.codame.com\">labs.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\"><strong class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\">SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIAâ€Š&mdash;â€ŠFebruary 22, 2016â€Š</strong>&mdash;â€ŠCODAME, a leading organization producing cutting edge experiences at the intersection of art and technology, announces today the launch of CODAME Labs. Located in downtown San Francisco, the new dedicated research and development studio will focus on collaborative innovation through CODAME&rsquo;s curated network of local and international artists, engineers, architects, fashion designers, scientists, and major tech companies to accelerate the field of art and technology.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">CODAME Labs will be lead by Creative Director, renowned Dutch designer, Anouk Wipprecht, whose key focus is to make fashion ahead of her time, combining the latest in science and technology to create an experience that transcends appearances. Partnering with companies such as Intel, Autodesk, Google, Microsoft, Cirque Du Soleil, Audi, and 3D printing company Materialise she researches how our future would look as we continue to embed technology into what we wear.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p graf--startsWithDoubleQuote\">&ldquo;CODAME Labs is a place where hardware gets tested, robotics get styled, and electronic textiles get crafted in order to make a push for a new generation of devices that is not handheldâ€Š&mdash;â€Šbut wearable or even omnipresent living around us. Having access to the newest gadgets and tools including 3D scanners, 3D printers, VR, microcontrollers, and tiny sensor modules, CODAME Labs is determined to playfully produce amazing projects around the clock&rdquo; says Wipprecht.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">Founder, Bruno Fonzi says, &ldquo;We are excited to expand CODAME with the launch of CODAME Labs. With Anouk bringing her expertise in the fashion and wearable technology, this will be an incredible year and we are looking forward to seeing what prototypes the lab inspires our artists to create. With our partnerships with some of Silicon Valley&rsquo;s leading tech companies, this is an incubator that will drive innovation in the art and tech space.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">CODAME Labs is now seeking proposals from San Francisco bay-area based and international designers, artists, engineers and technologists with a taste for fashion and an urge to create innovative projects around the theme of &ldquo;INTERFACE&rdquo; by taking a look into new interactions we can have with the world around us on the topic of Fashion-Tech. Current participants include renowned and forward thinking artists such as Tiffany Trenda, Behnaz Farahi, Ricardo O&rsquo;Nascimento, Valerie Lamontagne, Alex Murray-Leslie of Chicks on Speed; futuristic fashion labels like Elecktro Couture and Sensoree, and many more.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">Propose a project at <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"/pages/call-for-proposals\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/pages/call-for-proposals\">codame.com/pages/call-for-proposals</a> and join this incredible collective.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">This powerful lineup of researchers, emerging talent, designers and tech pioneers will be in partnership with some of the most forward-thinking companies in the Bay Area and beyond. CODAME has a history of partnering with technology companies to bring funding to artists and community recognition to brands. CODAME Labs will offer additional sponsorship opportunities that include lectures, workshops, space at our ART+TECH Festival and Labs project collaboration.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">For more information on how to get involved as a sponsor, visit: <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"/pages/partners-sponsorship-enquiry\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/pages/partners-sponsorship-enquiry\">codame.com/pages/partners-sponsorship-enquiry</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\"><strong class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\">About CODAME:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">CODAME produces ART+TECH projects and events that inspire through experience while embracing innovation through design, creativity, and collaboration between artists and technologists.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">Since 2009, Codame has been going strong in building 50+ projects in collaboration with their 200+ tech artists collective around the globe, producing over 60 events. Honing in on the surrounding diverse communities, CODAME ART+TECH continues to embrace and showcase creative collaborations in the arts, technology, design, music, dance, data visualization, creative coding and innovation, using these avenues to broaden our horizon.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">CODAME has a highly engaged community of 20k and growing top-industry engineers, designers and artists. CODAME has received support from tech companies such as Google, Salesforce, GitHub, Box, Adobe, Rackspace, Unity, BlackBerry, Shopify, Mozilla, Autodesk, and Organic, as well as upcoming startups like CoreOS, Retronyms, and Chartio.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">They are fiscally sponsored by &ldquo;Intersection for the Arts&rdquo; a 501(c)(3) non profit organization.</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\"><a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"http://labs.codame.com\" data-href=\"http://labs.codame.com\">labs.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\">â€Š&mdash;â€Š-</p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p\"><a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"/\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/\">CODAME.COM</a> ~ twitter: <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"https://twitter.com/codame\" data-href=\"https://twitter.com/codame\">@CODAME</a> ~ tag: <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"https://instagram.com/codame/\" data-href=\"https://instagram.com/codame/\">#CODAME</a> ~ facebook: <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\" data-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH\">CODAME.ART.TECH</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"graf--p graf--empty\">&nbsp;</p>', '', '1'),
(29, '#ARTEX Volunteers', 'artex-volunteers', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/artex-volunteer-sign-up.jpg', '<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeLR4ujGiCe6dx243Le81OSiUmrkxxJQMfy1QZ1rWBooAnppw/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"760\" height=\"2700\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loading...</iframe></p>', '', '1'),
(32, '2018 Program', '2018-program', '', '<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1jEE4F1p1SRw6esYJ1P6Wq2t7DjKOQvsY9eCHcMvDyS8/embed?start=true&amp;loop=true&amp;delayms=5000\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">CODAME 2018 Core initiatives...</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2018\">ART+TECH Festival</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;#ARTOBOT -&nbsp;June 6-7th @&nbsp;2018</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3D Web Fest&nbsp;(TBA) - San Francisco</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Workshops, such as <a href=\"/events/workshop-visual-strategies-for-neural-artistic-style-transfer\">Visual Strategies for Neural Artistic Style Transfer</a>&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a href=\"/artists/gary-boodhoo\">Gary Boodhoo</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/projects\">CODAME Labs</a> Projects:&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/matchy\">Matchy</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/projects/modbod\">ModBod</a>, <a href=\"/projects/shybot\">Shybot</a>, <a href=\"/projects/outerbody\">Outerbody</a>, <a href=\"/projects/holoshatter\">Holoshatter</a>&nbsp;...&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b27a3f6c-9499-d4d6-3355-a29509b9169f\">Sustainability Model:&nbsp;</span>Sharing profits, Commissioning and Selling Art</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Past</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Previous years ART+TECH Festivals:&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2016---artex\">2016</a>, <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2015\">2015</a>, <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2014\">2014</a>, <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2013\">2013</a>, <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2012\">2012</a>, <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2011---video\">2011</a>, <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2010\">2010</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/projects/shybot\">Desert X</a> - Coachella Valley</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/events/scene-with-shybot\">Scene with Shybot</a>&nbsp;- @TheLabs San Francisco</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/events/matchbox-salons\">Matchbox</a> - CounterPulser</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">CODAME ART+TECH @ <a href=\"/events/maker-faire\">Makerfaire</a></li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/events/3d-web-fest-2017\">3D Web Fest</a> &ldquo;Connections&rdquo; - San Francisco</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/events/3d-web-fest-germany-2017\">3D Web Fest&nbsp;Germany</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Contact us if interested to support or help, more on&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">Support ART+TECH</a></p>', '', '0'),
(33, 'TERMS AND CONDITIONS', 'terms-and-conditions', '', '<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdt_O4qbna2y5ss93ZJhuJThPBRW9YLJdbGgPGuS3CamjF7fA/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"760\" height=\"17550\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loading...</iframe></p>', '', '1'),
(42, 'Making Magic Happen: CODAME Sponsorship Q&A', 'making-magic-happen-codame-sponsorship-q-a', '', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Curating and hosting large scale creative art and technology events requires a lot of effort, planning, and technical gear. On the CODAME blog, we spend a lot of our time promoting and highlighting the artists and installations themselves, but we couldn&rsquo;t create these events without our sponsors and supporters.</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this Q&amp;A, volunteer Irene Malatesta chats with founders <a href=\"/artists/bruno-fonzi\">Bruno Fonzi</a> and <a href=\"/artists/jordan-gray\">Jordan Gray</a> (AKA staRpauSe) about the sponsors who make events like the CODAME ART+TECH Festival possible, and how new supporters can get involved.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/bruno-fonzi2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"/artists/jordan-gray\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists/jordan-gray\">Jordan Gray</a> and <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"/artists/bruno-fonzi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://fonzi.com/\">Bruno Fonzi</a> co-founders at <a class=\"markup--user markup--p-user\" href=\"https://medium.com/u/4ae3f675837c\" target=\"_blank\" data-href=\"https://medium.com/u/4ae3f675837c\" data-anchor-type=\"2\" data-user-id=\"4ae3f675837c\" data-action-value=\"4ae3f675837c\" data-action=\"show-user-card\" data-action-type=\"hover\">CODAME</a></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Q: Who is sponsoring CODAME ART+TECH Festival 2019?</strong></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Bruno</strong>: We have not yet nailed down all our sponsors yet, but we are in talks with some leading technology companies with a presence in the Bay Area. We do have some partners lined up already, including Open Austria, Intersection for the Arts, the San Francisco Arts Commission, Palacio, Zero1, CounterPulse, and LASER. As we add more partners and sponsors, you&rsquo;ll be able to find them <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2019-space\">on the festival website here</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Jordan</strong>: One thing we can say is that we&rsquo;re very excited to be working with Open Austria. It\'s rare to see a government organization with so much passion for the arts. Can\'t wait to announce everything we have cooking!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Q: Who are some of your favorite long-time CODAME sponsors?</strong></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Bruno</strong>: We&rsquo;ve been fortunate to have support from Adobe. They were heavily involved in the early days of CODAME, which really helped us get started. Autodesk, Github, and Salesforce have also been important sustaining sponsors for several years.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Jordan</strong>: I don&rsquo;t think I can choose a favorite&mdash;this is as dangerous as picking a favorite parent! Aside from those Bruno mentioned, we&rsquo;ve partnered with Mozilla on some exciting launches, like their VR-enabled web browser. They\'ve also been gracious hosts to our salons. Those salons are fantastic events to meet artists outside of our exciting ART+TECH Festival environment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Swissnex is an inspiring group we partnered with last year to look at automation and play in the workplace. Their programming, office space, and people are already one foot into the future.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/photo_2019-03-28_18.52_.07_.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Featured artist <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--figure-anchor\" href=\"/artists/deanna-hood\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists/deanna-hood\">Deanna Hood</a> speaking at <a class=\"markup--anchor markup--figure-anchor\" href=\"https://festival.codame.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://festival.codame.com/\">ART+TECH Festival 2018</a> #ARTOBOTS</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Q: Who are some of CODAME&rsquo;s most recent new supporters?</strong></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Jordan</strong>: At the end of 2018, we partnered with Leonardo to celebrate their 50th anniversary at an event we called <a href=\"/events/intersections\">Intersections</a>. It was an honor to bring the unique flavor of CODAME celebration to an institution with such a rich history.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Q: There are a few ways that sponsors get involved, from making donations, to hosting workshops, to bringing their entire teams to events. Why do companies choose to support events like the CODAME ART+TECH Festival?</strong></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Bruno</strong>: Companies, especially leading tech companies, want to be recognized as supporting innovation, leading the way and being visionaries. Our sponsors are companies leading the way, both in technological innovation and in creating globally-recognized employee cultures of excellence and engagement.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Jordan</strong>: Engagement is really key, both for employees of our sponsor companies, and engagement within the broader Bay Area art and tech community. Engaged employees are happier, they innovate more, and they build more trust in their organizations. 51% of the U.S. workforce is &ldquo;not engaged&rdquo; which ends up costing organizations between $450 and $550 billion annually. Taking your team to a CODAME event is an inexpensive way to open eyes and light fires. Being part of the event demonstrates that you value diversity and fresh thinking.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/sponsors.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"/sponsors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/sponsors\">CODAME Sponsors</a></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Q: What kind of organizations get the most out of partnering with CODAME?</strong></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Bruno</strong>: Organizations that value creativity and art, want to reach out for more, and are interested supporting the art and tech community are a great fit for working with CODAME.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Our sponsor Salesforce doesn&rsquo;t target necessarily only creatives, but also highly values non-profits organizations. . They find brand value simply in giving and being associated with the independent creative tech community. Autodesk, on the other hand, have been great partners who do target creatives and speak the same language. It&rsquo;s a pleasure working together on events like the <a href=\"/events/3d-web-fest-2017\">3DWebFest</a> which we co-produced. Autodesk went above and beyond as a very engaged sponsor and partner.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Jordan</strong>: All of our sponsorships are the result of a champion blowing the ART+TECH horn inside their organization. These people have been all over the ladder but all of them understand the inherent value of creativity. If that sounds like you, we definitely want to hear from you!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Q: How does CODAME work with sponsors creatively to both make sponsors happy and maintain artistic, creative integrity of our events?</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Bruno</strong>: The ART+TECH Festival is not a conventional event with expos and company brands all over the place. That&rsquo;s part of what makes it unique. CODAME events are about building inspiring experiences, playful ART+TECH projects, and supporting artists. Sponsors can expect a tasteful brand presence on site, social media promotion, and promotion during the festival where it aligns with event content.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Jordan</strong>: Plopping down a booth or throwing up a banner would look out of place at carefully curated CODAME events. We find tasteful ways to bring brands into the <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2019-space\">[ SPACE ]</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">For examples. if a company sponsors the sound system, their name will be there on the program handed to all attendees. Similar little pieces that bring an ART+TECH Festival to life are a great way to get involved. It feels huge when your team rolls through the event and realize that an international artist is there because their company authentically contributed.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/1_loRmPxBwLs1-kZKA1ihzww.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" href=\"/events/workshop-fashion-technology\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/events/workshop-fashion-technology\">Workshop: Fashion Technology</a> series as part of the <a href=\"/admin/festival.codame.com\">ART+TECH Festival</a> 2018 #ARTOBOTS</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Q: How does the CODAME mission inform the way we work with our sponsors?</strong>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Bruno</strong>: Our values inform everything about how we work with supporters. We meet them, talk to them, and organize a pre-festival event with a more intimate presence with artists, supporters, and potential sponsors. We show them what we are building, what we plan to build. We share our learnings and explore opportunities with them where they can join us in the future. In that way, we connect with them very closely.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Jordan</strong>: CODAME &ldquo;shapes the future through inspiring experiences and playful ART+TECH projects.&rdquo; It\'s not just cute wording in a tagline&mdash;it&rsquo;s a mission we are very focused on and passionate about. We are building things the world has never seen before with our partners and sponsors.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Play is core to our engagements. If we aren\'t having fun then we\'re doing it wrong! But we don\'t take play lightly, it\'s our number one tool for learning and sense-making. That includes understanding our sponsors goals and helping them get there.</p>\r\n<p>Inclusion is another core value we bring to our partnerships. When we work with technologists we help them see the value of creativity. When we work with artists we help them understand the value and expressiveness of new media. When we work with companies we help them discover hidden treasures inside themselves and their teams.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;Interested in getting involved? Want to donate, support, or volunteer?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/join-us1.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We accept tax deductible donations as members of Intersection for the Arts 501(c)(3) non profit organization. We&rsquo;d love to hear from you. <a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">Contact</a> the CODAME team <a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">here.</a></p>', '', '0'),
(36, 'Call for Proposals', 'call-for-proposals', '', '<p>Submit your projects proposal:&nbsp;workshops, installation&nbsp;experiences, performances, or artwork for the opportunity to be to join the <a href=\"/pages/codame-artist-collective\">CODAME Artist Collective</a>&nbsp;and be showcased at CODAME ART+TECH Festival,&nbsp;<a href=\"/events\">Events</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://gallery.codame.com/\">Galleries</a>,&nbsp;and/or have your artwork prints for sale&nbsp;in our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/\">Shop</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nft.codame.com/\">NFTs</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Projects should relate to ART+TECH or&nbsp;the current ART+TECH Festival theme for this year.</p>\r\n<p>Our curators will follow up with you&nbsp;with an acceptance letter or for further information.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeInrIbTeVjyVJFx94Qo2rDbjz5NCB6r7M-y2_oNFLL48LtAg/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"800\" height=\"3700\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loading...</iframe></p>', '', '1'),
(37, 'fobi test', 'fobi-test', '', '<p><iframe src=\"https://fobi.io/#/f/mmxZ6bD\" width=\"300\" height=\"700\">Your browser does not support iFrames. Please proceed to <a href=\"https://fobi.io/#/f/mmxZ6bD\">https://fobi.io/#/f/mmxZ6bD</a>.</iframe></p>', '', '1'),
(39, '3D Web Fest Germany [2017] - Call', '3d-web-fest-germany-2017---call', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/3d-web-fest-germany-2017---call.gif', '<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdWBavcxN085mpTUk6CpmJuvJkstkkroqWe5oKh8KtMi3s4Fg/viewform?embedded=true\" width=\"760\" height=\"2300\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\">Loading...</iframe></p>', '', '1');
INSERT INTO `pages` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `pic`, `description`, `old_url`, `hidden`) VALUES
(40, 'Newsletter Apr. 13, 2018', 'newsletter-apr-13-2018', '', '<p><a href=\"/pages/subscribe\" target=\"_blank\">Subscribe to our newsletter</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>for new events, project updates, call for artists, discounts and&nbsp;more inspiring ART+TECH news.</p>\r\n<table id=\"bodyTable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; background-color: #1d021d; text-size-adjust: 100%; height: 5186px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 672px; font-family: Times; font-size: medium;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td id=\"bodyCell\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; height: 5206px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 1384px;\" align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; height: 5193px;\" border=\"0\" width=\"720\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td id=\"templateBody\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; background-image: none; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-position: center center; background-size: cover; border-top: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 36px; padding-bottom: 54px;\" align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" data-template-container=\"\">\r\n<table class=\"templateContainer\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; max-width: 600px !important; width: 600px !important;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"bodyContainer\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-size-adjust: 100%; background-image: none; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-position: center center; background-size: cover; border-top: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextBlock\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody class=\"mcnTextBlockOuter\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; padding-top: 9px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><img style=\"border: 0px; height: 60px; outline: none; width: 54px;\" src=\"/sendy/uploads/1523515369.png\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextContentContainer\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; background-color: #d6e6fa; text-size-adjust: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextContent\" style=\"background-color: #1d021d; text-size-adjust: 100%; word-break: break-word; color: #808080; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; padding: 0px 18px 9px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\">Featured Artists and Speakers</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\">Interview Series</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\">by Irene Malatesta</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=\"mcnImageBlock\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody class=\"mcnImageBlockOuter\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnImageBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; padding: 9px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Leading up to the ART+TECH Festival #ARTOBOTS&nbsp;we are publishing a series of interviews with the artists and speakers on&nbsp;<a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"http://medium.com/codame-art-tech/\">Medium</a></span><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Enjoy some highlights below and don\'t forget to RSVP!</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647?discount=CODAME-20\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\">Register with this link for a limited time&nbsp;20% off</span></span></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnImageBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; padding: 9px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/interview-with-mark-klink-de407a014a2c\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\"><img style=\"border: 0px; height: 584px; outline: none; text-decoration-line: none; width: 619px;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/0*W_nZG9GQY-DjMaPX.\" alt=\"\" /></span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"color: #d3d3d3;\"><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/interview-with-mark-klink-de407a014a2c\">Interview with Mark Klink</a></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p id=\"98b1\" style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Visual artist&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"https://medium.com/@markaklink\" target=\"_blank\" data-action=\"show-user-card\" data-action-type=\"hover\" data-action-value=\"3c1c7c9759bb\" data-anchor-type=\"2\" data-href=\"https://medium.com/@markaklink\" data-user-id=\"3c1c7c9759bb\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Mark A Klink</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">&nbsp;is interested in robots, artificial intelligence, and how we humans handle encounters with the unreal. From his early digital experiments to his current 3D work, he&rsquo;s focused on manipulating and stretching modern technologies, often subverting them to produce unexpected aesthetic results....&nbsp;[read more&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\"><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/interview-with-mark-klink-de407a014a2c\">here</a>]</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextBlock\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody class=\"mcnTextBlockOuter\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; padding-top: 9px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextContentContainer\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextContent\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; word-break: break-word; color: #808080; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; padding: 0px 18px 9px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><img style=\"border: 0px; height: 833px; outline: none; width: 605px; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/0*4Mn7D2zgaypNUi41.\" alt=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"color: #d3d3d3;\">\"Exploring the Unseen\"</span><br /><span style=\"color: #d3d3d3;\"><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #00add8;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/exploring-the-unseen-42e1775e3b13\">Interview with&nbsp;Norma Jeane</a></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p id=\"b089\" style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 24px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">When considering multimedia artist&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #00add8;\" href=\"/artists/norma-jeane\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists/norma-jeane\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Norma Jeane</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">, the first impression that strikes is one of mystery and denial. Norma Jeane is the pseudonym of an Italian artist who does not wish to be identified. Where many discussions of an artist&rsquo;s body of work might begin with personal biography in an attempt to understand the human experience that led to creating the work, that won&rsquo;t do in the case of the elusive, cerebral, and multi-talented Norma Jeane....&nbsp;[read more&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #00add8;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/exploring-the-unseen-42e1775e3b13\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">here</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">]</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p id=\"98b1\" style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><img style=\"border: 0px; height: 420px; outline: none; float: left; width: 640px;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*gQ1mqNJJ7lhtq-keupfM8w.gif\" alt=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table class=\"mcnTextBlock\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody class=\"mcnTextBlockOuter\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnTextBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; padding-top: 9px;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p id=\"c2a2\" style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"color: #d3d3d3;\">\"Science Fiction Cave Paintings\"</span><br /><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/gary-boodhoos-science-fiction-cave-paintings-f347cfe7e5f\">Interview with Gary Boodhoo</a></span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">CODAME Featured Artist&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"/artists/gary-boodhoo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists/norma-jeane\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Gary Boodhoo</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">&nbsp;is an interaction designer who draws on his digital training as well as a longtime fascination with psychedelic experiences to create his artworks. Under the label,&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"/projects/deep-dream-vision-quest\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/projects/deep-dream-vision-quest\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">DeepDreamVisionQuest</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">, he explores the nature of games and perception, producing what he refers to as &ldquo;science fiction cave paintings.&rdquo; Recalling the ancient images at Lascaux, this term is one way to describe the primal human expression he seeks to make possible using cutting edge visualization technology.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p id=\"147b\" style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">In my recent conversation with Boodhoo, we discussed his technical background and the multiple threads of inquiry that led him to DeepDreamVisionQuest. We also examined the aesthetic and intellectual challenges that inevitably occur when enlisting artificial intelligence and machine learning in creating original artwork....&nbsp;[read more&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/gary-boodhoos-science-fiction-cave-paintings-f347cfe7e5f\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">here</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">]</span></span></span></p>\r\n<table class=\"mcnDividerBlock\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%; table-layout: fixed !important;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody class=\"mcnDividerBlockOuter\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnDividerBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%; padding: 18px 18px 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><img style=\"border: 0px; height: 327px; outline: none; width: 621px;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/0*5HSHT_e1137iVBPF.\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"color: #e6e6fa;\"><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"http://medium.com/codame-art-tech/a-conversation-with-yagiz-mungan-codame-artist-9213cf8d73d9\">Interview with Yagiz Mungan</a></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Interdisciplinary artist&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"/artists/yagiz-mungan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/artists/yagiz-mungan\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">Yagiz Mungan</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">&nbsp;creates work that blends VR/AR, sound/music, interaction, performance, virtual worlds and gaming. He is especially interested in generative strategies of creating visuals and sound, and ways to use technology to push the boundaries of human perception and emotional response. His work often aims to recontextualize familiar experiences, or addresses uncanny technological encounters in modern life....&nbsp;[read more&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"https://medium.com/codame-art-tech/a-conversation-with-yagiz-mungan-codame-artist-9213cf8d73d9\"><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">here</span></a><span style=\"color: #a9a9a9;\">]</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnDividerBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%; padding: 18px 18px 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #d6e6fa;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\">CODAME&nbsp;<a style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #4ac3ed !important;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/arttech-festival-2018-tickets-34741461647?discount=CODAME-20\">ART+TECH Festival</a>&nbsp;[2018] code named #ARTOBOTS</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #d6e6fa;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\">June 4&ndash;7, @The Midway, San Francisco&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #d6e6fa;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'helvetica neue\';\">Four days of workshops, talks, and nightlife celebration!</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"mcnDividerBlockInner\" style=\"text-size-adjust: 100%; min-width: 100%; padding: 18px 18px 0px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; text-align: center;\"><span sty