(14, 'Retrobooster', 'retrobooster', '            <p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><iframe style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/Zmt8B1okxPU?wmode=transparent&autohide=1&egm=0&hd=1&iv_load_policy=3&modestbranding=1&rel=0&showinfo=0&showsearch=0\" width=\"400\" height=\"225\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">CODAME Featured Game:  <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.reallyslick.com/retrobooster/\" target=\"_blank\">Retrobooster</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">With the <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Today, we show you <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.reallyslick.com/retrobooster/downloads.html\" target=\"_blank\">Retrobooster</a> on Windows and Linux. </em></p>\r\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: solid none none; border-top-color: #dcdcdc; clear: both; color: #eeeeee; height: 1px; width: 675px; margin: 0px auto 2em; padding-top: 0px; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">I’m a former <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Fox_(video_game)\" target=\"_blank\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Star Fox</em></a> addict, so I will need minimal convincing to pick up <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Retrobooster.  </em></span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">But how would you convince a regular ol’ gamer to drop everything they’re doing and give it a try?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://twitter.com/TerryMWelsh\" target=\"_blank\">Terry Welsh</a> (Lead Developer):  </span><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Retrobooster</em> is an old-school survival shooter and cave-flyer. Most cave-flyers go to a lot of trouble to slow you down and help you stay in control. However, <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Retrobooster</em> gives you an extremely fast and nimble ship, which makes it as much about flying skill as it is about enemy blasting.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">The level design takes advantage of the flying mechanics by confronting you with speed-flying challenges and puzzles. Of course, there is also an impressive set of weapons, plenty of juicy monsters, and some ludicrous bullet-hell action.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">All in all, this game requires pure skill and plenty of brains if you want to survive to the end.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">What’s the single most memorable part of your game that you want people to never forget?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Retrobooster</em> is all about the feel of controlling its quick-thrust ship. A great deal of effort went into achieving the right interplay of flight dynamics, detailed physics, and responsive controls to give the player a challenging, skill-based experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">Players are often surprised that I had the nerve to make the ship so difficult to control. They tell me they keep playing for the overall feel of the game and, before they know it, become competent pilots.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">What was the biggest challenge you had in creating your game?</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" /><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">How did you overcome it?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">That’s easy — finding enough time to work on it!</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">This game started as a hobby project years ago, but with a full-time job it was inching along with no end in sight. Eventually, I got tired of that situation and had enough positive feedback from testers to take it to the next level. So, I quit my job programming simulations at NASA’s Ames Research Center and dove into<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Retrobooster</em> full-time, and now the finish line is fast approaching…</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">We’ll be there when you fly across it.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" /></span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Thanks for talking to us, Terry!</span></p>\r\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: solid none none; border-top-color: #dcdcdc; clear: both; color: #eeeeee; height: 1px; width: 675px; margin: 0px auto 2em; padding-top: 0px; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Join <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\"> <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite <span class=\"vevent\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span class=\"description\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Indie Game!</span></span></span></em></p>          ', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/retrobooster.png', '', 'http://www.reallyslick.com/retrobooster/', 'terry-welsh', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-retrobooster-join-codame/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(15, 'Enhanced Wars', 'enhanced-wars', '\r\n						<div class=\"figure\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1531\" alt=\"tumblr_mrlqn129V11qixx7ho2_500\" src=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\"></div>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME Featured Game:  <a href=\"http://www.enhancedwars.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Enhanced Wars</a><br> </strong></p>\r\n<p><em>With the <a title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Below is a run-down of <strong>Enhanced Wars</strong> for Windows, Mac, and Linux.</em></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p><strong>This game looks like a cross between Chess and good ol’ fashioned <a href=\"http://www.tintoyarcade.com/products/Green-Army-Men-Playset-Strike-Force.html?gclid=CLbuycHpgLkCFeZxQgodLnoAqg\" target=\"_blank\">Army Men</a>.<br> Is my presumption accurate at all?</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/FamousAspect\" target=\"_blank\">Ethan Levy</a> (lead designer):</strong> Sort of — <em>Enhanced Wars</em> is a turn-based war game that is designed for fulfilling asynchronous multiplayer gaming.</p>\r\n<p>Basically, the game takes classic, turn-based strategy gameplay found in games we love and updates it for modern sensibilities. It’s designed from the ground up to deliver a fast, accessible, and fulfilling experience that focuses on strategic use of your army, not resource-hoarding and base defense.</p>\r\n<p>Most turn-based strategy games are great as single-player experiences when you are crushing the computer, but lose sight of fun when you play another human and get locked in frequent stalemates or long, boring mop-up phases. Our goal in designing <em>Enhanced Wars</em> is to fix all that.</p>\r\n<p><strong>So, how exactly will <em>Enhanced Wars </em>fix those ‘fun leakage’ problems?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Being a multiplayer game, <em>Enhanced Wars</em> is all about interactions with other people. When you’re playing with a real person, the emotional stakes are much higher. We want a player to never forget that one tense match where they came from behind and executed an intricate strategy perfectly to trap their friend and win the game.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What was the biggest challenge in creating the game?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Honestly, our biggest challenge is funding.</p>\r\n<p>We are launching a Kickstarter campaign in late-August and, unless we are successful, will not be able to take our multiplayer demo and turn it into a finished game.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Crowdfunding can do <a href=\"http://readwrite.com/2013/05/13/ouyas-crowd-funded-android-powered-cloud-gaming-console-first-look\" target=\"_blank\">big things</a> — just don’t neglect that pitch video.<br> Thanks for talking to us, Ethan, and good luck in Kickstarting <em>Enhanced Wars!</em></strong></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p><em><strong>Join <a title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</strong><strong> <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</strong><strong>o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite <span class=\"vevent\"><span class=\"description\">Indie Game!</span></span></strong></em></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/enhanced-wars.png', 'https://twitter.com/FamousAspect', 'http://www.enhancedwars.com/', 'ethan-levy', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-enhanced-wars-with/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(16, 'Full Bore', 'full-bore', '                        <p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><iframe style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/EXhOyTD6Tik?wmode=transparent&autohide=1&egm=0&hd=1&iv_load_policy=3&modestbranding=1&rel=0&showinfo=0&showsearch=0\" width=\"400\" height=\"225\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">CODAME Featured Game:  <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.wholehog-games.com/fullbore/\" target=\"_blank\">Full Bore</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">With the <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">This morning, we bring you <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/whole-hog-games/full-bore-an-underground-puzzle-adventure\" target=\"_blank\">Full Bore</a> on Windows and Linux. </em></p>\r\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: solid none none; border-top-color: #dcdcdc; clear: both; color: #eeeeee; height: 1px; width: 675px; margin: 0px auto 2em; padding-top: 0px; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">I’m a fan of most things pork-related. So, what’s <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Full Bore </em>all about?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://twitter.com/WholeHogGames\" target=\"_blank\">Casey Carlin</a> (Lead Programmer):  </span>Full<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"> Bore</em> is a game about curiosity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">It’s a ‘<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metroid\" target=\"_blank\">Metroid</a><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Castlevania\" target=\"_blank\">Vania</a>‘ of sorts where you start out with all your abilities, but don’t lose them in the first cutscene.  Instead, it’s up to the player to take hints from their surroundings and the puzzles they are confronted with to figure out how to push, dig, and stomp their way through a world filled with block puzzles. Taking the initiative and exploring the world as your knowledge of the game mechanics expands will reveal shortcuts, secrets, and even harder puzzles to test your mettle.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">With great graphics, fast-action gameplay, and an overall awesome design, what’s the utmost memorable part of <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Full Bore</em>?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">We’d like our players to never forget the experience of solving a puzzle that they found really fiendishly hard. It will likely be a different puzzle for everyone, but we’re hoping that <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Full Bore</em> offers a good enough gradient of challenge that every player has at least one of these moments before they beat the game.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">What was the biggest obstacle you encountered during the making of <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Full Bore?</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">The hardest part of creating <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Full Bore</em> was figuring out what the game was really about.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">We had the pieces lying around for a long time: a unique setting, an interesting visual style and tricky block puzzles, but those pieces had nothing holding them together.  It took us a long period of soul-searching, watching play testers, and playing the game ourselves, to tease out that curiosity was core concept behind everything we had done so far.  <span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Realizing that overarching “message” really helped pull the game and narrative together — but it took us a year and a half to find it!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Well, hey, at least you eventually <em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">did</em> figure out a point to your game!  It looks great, and we look forward to seeing your full-fledged CODAME demo.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Thanks for taking time to talk to us, Casey! </span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"> </p>\r\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: solid none none; border-top-color: #dcdcdc; clear: both; color: #eeeeee; height: 1px; width: 675px; margin: 0px auto 2em; padding-top: 0px; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" />\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Join <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\"> <a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite <span class=\"vevent\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span class=\"description\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Indie Game!</span></span></span></em></p>                    ', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/full-bore.png', '', 'http://www.wholehog-games.com/fullbore/', 'casey-carlin', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-full-bore-join-codame/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(17, 'Super Marshmallow Ninja', 'super-marshmallow-ninja', '\r\n						<div class=\"figure\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1528\" alt=\"tumblr_mrtaq0LJKh1qixx7ho1_500\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tumblr_mrtaq0LJKh1qixx7ho1_500.png\" width=\"419\" height=\"635\"></div>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME Featured Game:  <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id652168386\" target=\"_blank\">Super Marshmallow Ninja</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><em>With the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Next up, <a href=\"http://www.ardentkid.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Super Marshmallow Ninja</a> on iOS and Android. (well, soon!) </em></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p><strong>Pretend like I’m a stranger with an iPhone whom you just approached — give me a quick pitch for <em>Marshmallow Ninja</em> before I run away!</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Omid Ahourai (Founder, <a href=\"http://www.ardentkid.com/\" target=\"_blank\">ArdentKid</a>):</strong>  You are a marshmallow ninja, fighting to defeat the evil king crumble and his chocolate chip cookie army from taking over Marshmallow Kingdom in this action-packed top-scroller.</p>\r\n<p><strong>In six words and one hyphen, describe the coolest part of your game.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The intense timing-based battle interactions.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What was the biggest challenge in making the game?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The biggest challenge for me is always making it simple. I always want to add more features than I have the time to create, so that’s exactly why I made <em>Super Marshmallow Ninja</em> first, knowing I would add to it for the sequel.</p>\r\n<p><strong>And thus begins the <em>Super Marshmallow Ninja</em> dynasty…<br> Thanks for talking to us, Omid!</strong></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p><em><strong>Join <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</strong><strong> <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</strong><strong>o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite <span class=\"vevent\"><span class=\"description\">Indie Game!</span></span></strong></em></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/super-marshmallow-ninja.png', '', 'https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id652168386', 'omid-ahourai', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-super-marshmallow-ninja/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(18, 'Lost Toys', 'lost-toys', '\r\n						<div class=\"figure\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1526\" alt=\"tumblr_mrp0l4hkZX1qixx7ho1_500\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tumblr_mrp0l4hkZX1qixx7ho1_500.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"325\"></div>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME Featured Game:  <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/66695448\" target=\"_blank\">Lost Toys</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><em>With the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Today, we give you a glimpse of <a href=\"http://www.joystiq.com/2013/08/06/lost-toys-picks-up-most-promising-game-award-at-casual-connect-u\" target=\"_blank\">Lost Toys</a> on mobile (iOS, Android, and BlackBerry). </em></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p><strong>The visuals on <em>Lost Toys</em> are incredible.<br> </strong><strong>What’s the rest of the game about? </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/danielleswank\" target=\"_blank\">Danielle Swank</a> (Founder, <a href=\"http://barkingmousestudio.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Barking Mouse Studio</a>):</strong><em>Lost Toys</em> is a 3D puzzle game for introverts. It has a diverse set of influences ranging from Rene Magritte’s <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Treachery_of_Images\" target=\"_blank\">The Treachery of Images</a>, modern games such as <a href=\"http://www.cogsgame.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Cogs</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zen_Bound\" target=\"_blank\">Zen Bound</a> along with my own experiences as a volunteer firefighter and background as both, an artist and programmer.</p>\r\n<p>The game is set in a surreal game world with a restricted viewpoint, where players can examine and effect the objects around themselves. It’s a game we wished was already out in the world — but since it wasn’t, we decided to make it!</p>\r\n<p><strong>What’s the single most memorable part of your game that you want people to never forget?</strong></p>\r\n<p>It’s hard to pick a favorite part — but if we have to, it’s the opening sequence.</p>\r\n<p><em>Lost Toys</em> opens with a descending spiral, where mixed-up toys emerge out of the murk of a burned and ruined room. To move upwards and progress through the game, players restore jumbled toys. There are no timers, points, scores, or percentages in Lost Toys, but there are subtly discordant music transitions and trombone camera zooms. Turns can be infinitely undone without penalty, however the amount of time undoing takes encourages deliberate moves and forward thinking.</p>\r\n<p>All the levels take place in the same environment (past and future levels can be seen in the background) and the player is transitioned seamlessly from level to level.</p>\r\n<p><strong>You’ve thoroughly documented the making of <em>Lost Toys</em> on your <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/BarkingMouseStudio\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook Page</a> over the last few months. What was the biggest challenge you encountered in making the game?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Being an indie developer, <em>everything</em> is challenging. There’s never enough time or money to do all the things that you want to get done.</p>\r\n<p>We wanted to take full advantage of a touch interface, so the hardest part for us was getting the right “feel.” Our main <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/66695448\" target=\"_blank\">rotational mechanics</a> took three months, several revisions and many individual attempts before we pair-programmed a solution.</p>\r\n<p><strong>And it didn’t turn out too shabby at all!  I’m looking forward to seeing it in action at CODAME.<br> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Thanks for taking time to talk to us, Danielle! </strong></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p><em><strong>Join <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</strong><strong> <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</strong><strong>o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite <span class=\"vevent\"><span class=\"description\">Indie Game!</span></span></strong></em></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/lost-toys.png', '', 'http://vimeo.com/66695448', 'danielle-swank', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-lost-toys-join-codame/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(19, 'byteRider', 'byterider', '\r\n						<div class=\"figure\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1524\" alt=\"tumblr_mrvdfooIwc1qixx7ho1_500\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tumblr_mrvdfooIwc1qixx7ho1_500.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\"></div>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>CODAME Featured Game:  </strong><strong>byteRider</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em>With the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span><strong>byteRider</strong> is a social, arcade racer (currently in alpha). Race in against friends in an asynchronous, time-trial game with a retro vibe. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">A mobile game from <a class=\"account-group js-account-group js-action-profile js-user-profile-link js-nav\" href=\"https://twitter.com/alecmce\" target=\"_blank\" data-user-id=\"44088910\">Alec McEachran</a><span> built for iOS + Android</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em><strong>Join <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</strong><strong> <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</strong><strong>o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite Indie Game!</strong></em></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/byterider.png', '', '', 'alec-mceachran', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-byterider-with-the-codame/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(20, 'Undead Overlord', 'undead-overlord', '\r\n						<div class=\"figure\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1517\" alt=\"tumblr_mrvdusJL6U1qixx7ho1_1280\" src=\"http://codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tumblr_mrvdusJL6U1qixx7ho1_1280.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"375\"></div>\r\n<p><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong>CODAME Featured Game: </strong><a href=\"http://undeadoverlord.com/game.html\" target=\"_blank\">Undead Overlord</a></span></span><span> </span><span>by JumpCore Productions</span></p>\r\n<p><em>With the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span>Undead Overlord is an all-out mayhem Zombie Dominion RTS game where the goal is to create as much chaos as possible while wiping out the humans!</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Undead Overlord is born of a passion to see something different exhumed from the zombie games space. So in the tradition of games like Dungeon Keeper, we’ve turned the genre on its head, and put the player in charge of the zombie horde.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As an Undead Overlord, the world is yours to conquer and remake in your own grotesque image.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Make your horde deadly enough to overwhelm modern armaments.</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Grow deadly Boss Zombie mutations with behavior and abilities modified to provide strategic advantages to your horde.</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Time powerful special attacks properly to maximize effects.</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Create the most chaos possible in your quest to undermine the very basis of reality!</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Bringing many of the classic RTS controls and strategies into the mix, Undead Overlord’s design includes a custom touch screen interface for tablet players. Inspiration from the huge body of work in the fertile zombie genre led to one of the distinguishing aspects of the game’s design:</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><strong><span>Your enemy is your resource.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">That means that each time a human unit is killed and makes the transition to being undead, the player assumes control of that unit. It means that the tide of battle can shift quickly when a soldier’s wingman not only goes out of action, but is suddenly working for the other side. That’s a crushing blow to morale, and one that could send that soldier fleeing in panic, or even leave him cowering in abject fear – making him easy, tender, juicy pickings.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em><strong>Join <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</strong><strong> <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</strong><strong>o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite Indie Game!</strong></em></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/undead-overlord-by-jumpcore-productions.jpg', '', 'http://undeadoverlord.com/game.html', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-undead-overlord-by-jumpcore/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(21, 'Canon Brawl', 'canon-brawl', '\r\n						<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/GIr122R6mH8?wmode=transparent&autohide=1&egm=0&hd=1&iv_load_policy=3&modestbranding=1&rel=0&showinfo=0&showsearch=0\" height=\"225\" width=\"400\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong>CODAME Featured Game:  </strong><strong><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"s2\"><a href=\"http://turtle-sandbox.com/website/index_stage.html\" target=\"_blank\">Canon Brawl</a> </span></span></strong><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"s2\">by</span></span><strong><span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"s2\"> </span></span></strong><span>Turtle Sandbox</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>With the <a title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> showdown only days away, we thought we’d give you preview of the indie games that will be duking it out on August 21 for top bragging rights and a trip to the <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482642732\" target=\"_blank\">ARTS+TECH Festival</a>.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><span>Cannon Brawl is a 2D action strategy game with big explosions and destructible terrain. Command the action from your airship to build cannons, capture mines, expand your territory and more. Choose from a multitude of buildings, cannons and towers to assemble a force that will rain destruction from the sky and defeat your enemy! Advance your military campaign across the map in single player mode, or duke it out in multiplayer mode. </span></p>\r\n<p><span>Cannon Brawl is being developed for PC. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><em><strong>Join <a title=\"CODAME Games\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME GAMES</a> on</strong><strong> <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/event/5482598600\" target=\"_blank\">August 21st</a> t</strong><strong>o be inspired, learn, play and vote for your favorite Indie Game!</strong></em></strong></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/canon-brawl-by-turtle-sandbox.png', '', 'http://turtle-sandbox.com/website/index_stage.html', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/codame-featured-game-canon-brawl-by-turtle/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(22, 'Phracktography', 'phracktography', '<div class=\"figure\">A collaboration between Jordan Gray and Felipe Brahm inspired phracktography 3.0. A video booth experience of a stylized modular analog video synthesizer before being captured and projected&nbsp;for a unique photo booth experience.</div>\r\n<p>See for yourself at the CODAME 2013 ART+TECH Festival - 5ENSES experience&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/da85177e3b03b275c6722921853e6392.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"figure\">\r\n<figure><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/77cc6405ec550c79f4c3fa42652dbabc2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n<p>You can&nbsp;learn more about&nbsp;Phracktography in this article from <a href=\"https://www.vice.com/en/article/3d583j/phracktography-hacker-portraits-for-the-surveillance-age\">Vice</a>&nbsp;and find more&nbsp;outputs in this <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/codame/albums/72157635147099236\\\">photo gallery</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/phracktography.jpg', '', 'http://thecreatorsproject.vice.com/blog/phracktography-hacker-portraits-for-the-surveillance-age', 'angat-gaada,vicente-montelongo,jordan-gray', '', '0', '1697362140', '', '', '', 'project'),
(23, 'Billion Jelly Bloom', 'billion-jelly-bloom', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">CODAME Featured Artist:&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.billionjellybloom.org/#about-home\">Billion Jelly Bloom</a>&nbsp;is, ostensibly,&nbsp;a large-scale participatory little mermaid musical on acid.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000;\">Their website explains, &ldquo;The group is a&nbsp;performance art dance theater mega-puppet tripper trap founded by Patricia &amp; Robert Lord in San Francisco, California, USA circa 2010. Inspired by our own prodigiously vertiginous Burning Man experiences, Billion Jelly Bloom is our extension of Burning Man&rsquo;s transformative tentacles. &nbsp;Billion Jelly Bloom&rsquo;s Burning Man-ifested, benthic bumpin&rsquo; performance art transforms the night air into an ocean depth inhabited by an undulating, luminous jellyfish bloom. Our 15 foot tall, 640 lumen bright, performer-articulated OMFG Jellyfish dip and swarm and sting and dance and participatorily, interactively, immersively engage creatures, sounds and environs like it ain&rsquo;t no thing. BOOM *drops the mic*&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4773\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 5px 0px;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/14460189036_77a46bc0f4_o.jpg\" alt=\"14460189036_77a46bc0f4_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-projectimage wp-image-4774\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 5px 0px;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/14482066244_68c456f26d_o.jpg\" alt=\"14482066244_68c456f26d_o\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4777\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 5px 0px;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/static.squarespace.jpg\" alt=\"static.squarespace\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1499\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4779\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 5px 0px;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/1379646_649602661756516_183996556_n.jpg\" alt=\"1379646_649602661756516_183996556_n\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\" /></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/billion-jelly-bloom.jpg', '', 'http://www.billionjellybloom.org/#about-home', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/billion-jelly-bloom/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(24, 'Ecstatic Epiphany', 'ecstatic-epiphany', '<header>\r\n<div>\"The idea to use the Turk street building itself as an artist canvas was initiated by CODAME\'s own Vicente Montelongo. They set out to find an artist capable of taking this on, and Micah was the perfect fit.\"</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<article id=\"post-4433\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center><center><center><center><center>An&nbsp;interactive site-specific light installation at CounterPULSE, 80 Turk, SF, produced in collaboration with&nbsp;CODAME.</center></center><center></center><center></center></center><center>FREE&nbsp;PUBLIC&nbsp;INSTALLATION</center><center>LED light on laser-cut mat board, 4&times;8&prime;</center><center></center><center><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></center></center></center>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center></center><iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/94695180?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ecstatic Epiphany&nbsp;is a human-scale window into an imaginary space, installed in public behind an existing glass block wall. This piece is for anyone on the sidewalk to watch and control. Walking past it, your movement is amplified into a shift in perspective. Sometimes this is a passive action, other times it can lead to a dramatic change as chaos unfolds in the generative algorithms. The choreography of this mathematical world forms a continuous cyclic narrative of creation, depression, agency, and rebirth. Each moment is unique, echoed but never repeated.</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.flickr.com/slideShow/index.gne?group_id=&amp;user_id=96696316@N08&amp;set_id=72157644751124773&amp;tags=art\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" align=\"center\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>Some takes form the making of the&nbsp;&ldquo;Ecstatic Epiphany&rdquo; LED installation.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</article>\r\n</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/ecstatic-epiphany.jpg', '', '', 'micah-scott', '', '0', '1472004943', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(76, 'Luminous Waveforms', 'luminous-waveforms', '<p><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Illuminated&nbsp;Parametric Seating</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The organic curves are inspired by nature and soundwaves, sliced into a repeating rhythm. The fluid elegance of the forms, and gradual color shifts from the interior illumination, transforms the physical experience of the seating. This artwork is both form and function.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s1\">Constructed from CNC cut plywood and illuminated with APA102 LEDs</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s1\">Custom illuminated seating, prices&nbsp;available&nbsp;upon <a href=\"mailto:us@codame.com\">request</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/MG_8543.jpg\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/MG_8586.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/MG_8644.jpg\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">&nbsp;<img src=\"/uploaded_images/MG_8554.jpg\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/luminous-waveforms.jpeg', '', '', 'phil-spitler,victoria-mara-heilweil', '', '0', '1478629471', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(61, 'Recurrent', 'recurrent', '<p>Recurrent investigates the way that light&nbsp;interfaces with itself and metal.</p>\r\n<p>According to Nikola Tesla, the sun is the past, the earth is the present, and the moon is the future.</p>\r\n<p>Recurrent consists of looped cycles of light reflections with different frequencies creating a recurring orbital mechanic.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-2\"><img src=\"http://codame.com/uploaded_images/recurrent-ii-1.jpg\" alt=\"Recurrent II-1\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Buy&nbsp;<a style=\"text-align: center;\" href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-2\">Recurrent II-1</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-2\">shop.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-1?pr_prod_strat=collection_fallbac\"><img src=\"http://codame.com/uploaded_images/recurrent-ii-2.jpg\" alt=\"Recurrent II-2\" /></a><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-1?pr_prod_strat=collection_fallbac\">Recurrent II-2</a> Buy on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-1?pr_prod_strat=collection_fallbac\">shop.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print\"><img src=\"http://codame.com/uploaded_images/recurrent-ii-3.jpg\" alt=\"Recurrent II-3\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Buy&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print\">Recurrent II-3</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print\">shop.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http://codame.com/uploaded_images/recurrent-ii-4.jpg\" alt=\"Recurrent II-4\" />Buy&nbsp;<span style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-3\">Recurrent II-4</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;</span><a style=\"text-align: center;\" href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke-print-3\">shop.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/57P1LAJtXyM\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>A gaze becomes an infinite circuit and process becomes the content.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://static1.squarespace.com/static/55307e7be4b0082925555ae4/57df5dfa37c581c512a9c679/57df5ea5cd0f68d629327761/1474256554216/IMG_3891.jpg?format=1500w\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"844\" /></p>\r\n<p>Nine acts of lights have been programmed into three microcontrollers and&nbsp;infinitely recur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://static1.squarespace.com/static/55307e7be4b0082925555ae4/57df5dfa37c581c512a9c679/57df5ec4cd0f68d629327808/1474256598593/IMG_3954_2.jpg?format=1500w\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"852\" /></p>\r\n<p>A&nbsp;collaborative piece by Joey Verbeke and Yagmur Uyanik. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/recurrent1.jpg\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/recurrent.gif', '', 'http://www.joeyverbeke.com/recurrent', 'joey-verbeke,yagmur-uyanik', '', '0', '1598156225', 'https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke', NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `projects` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `description`, `pic`, `twitter`, `website`, `artists_array`, `old_url`, `hidden`, `edited`, `shop_url`, `partners_array`, `sponsors_array`, `is_nft`) VALUES
(25, 'CODAME VJ-Cart!', 'codame-vj-cart', '\r\n						<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Support us creating the CODAME VJ-Cart, a new kind of medium for digital, audio, and visual artists to showcase their work.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">What if we had a fleet of these bikes we can summon to perform with bands or different events around the city? Or projecting onto any building or screen?</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><strong>Adopt this project for your events!</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\">We’re looking for a team of extraordinary designers and builders to create an amazing mobile art piece: the <strong>VJ-Cart</strong>. Inspired by <em><a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=%E3%83%87%E3%82%B3%E3%83%81%E3%83%A3%E3%83%AA&espv=210&es_sm=119&tbm=isch&tbo=u&source=univ&sa=X&ei=5aPhUobKIJKFogTiroDYBQ&ved=0CCYQsAQ&biw=1110&bih=742\">dekochari</a></em> bikes, it’s a traveling show that will have lights, lasers, projects, or whatever we can dream up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\">Are you one of the extraordinaires? <a href=\"http://codame.com/call-for-artists/\">Contact us</a> to join our team!</p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/codame-vj-cart.png', '', '', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/vj-cart/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(26, 'OuterBody', 'outerbody', '<hr />\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><a href=\"http://outerbody.org/\">OuterBody</a> hacks your sense of self, transforming a technologically induced out-of-body-experience into a gaming platform.</p>\r\n<p>You might have seen OUTERBODY at CODAME ART+TECH Oct. 31st, at Geekdom, San Francisco</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\">You can also have this project at your events!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-4758 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/jpeg-2.jpg\" alt=\"jpeg-2\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" /><br /> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-4755 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/awesomeposter.jpg\" alt=\"awesomeposter\" width=\"1200\" height=\"777\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-4757 aligncenter\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/jpeg-1.jpg\" alt=\"jpeg-1\" width=\"454\" height=\"682\" /></p>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Would you or your&nbsp;organization&nbsp;like to support ?</strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\" style=\"text-align: left;\">CODAME events are made possible thanks to&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"/contribute\">volunteers</a>, event&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\">donation</a>&nbsp;tickets and&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"/sponsors\">sponsors</a>.&nbsp;We welcome the opportunity for you to join us in a collaborative relationship with support, either financial or in-kind, to continue raising the bar of what&rsquo;s possible at the nexus of ART+TECH. Any bits or pixel counts!</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Can I make a nonprofit - Tax Deductible Donation&nbsp;?</strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\">Yes! We are members of&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://theintersection.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Intersection for the Arts</a>,&nbsp;a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, which allows us to offer you tax deductions for your contributions.</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"https://donatenow.networkforgood.org/1442843\">Donate Now!</a>&nbsp;Make sure to select CODAME ART+TECH as the&nbsp;designated donation.</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-9 last\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/outerbody.gif', '', 'http://outerbody.org/', 'jason-wilson', '', '0', '1579399937', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27, 'Techn(O)pticon', 'techn-o-pticon', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>A camera booth&nbsp;generating&nbsp;special effect animated GIF images.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Two monitors display the Techn(O)pticon&rsquo;s digitally distorted view of the world. At the press of a button, your animated GIF image is captured and preserved forever by being automatically uploaded to the internet. Users can collect their images by the short URLs displayed along with the previous captures.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Built using WebGL Shaders to melt your face before uploading it to <a href=\"http://dollhousephotobooth.imgur.com\">IMGUR</a> for permanent archival.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"wp-image-5420 size-project-image hoverZoomLink\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/IMG_0178-1120x840.jpg\" alt=\"TechnOpticoN\" width=\"711\" height=\"533\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"text-align: center;\">TechnOpticoN in Action!</p>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"wp-image-4959 size-full\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/TechnopticonReduxX06.png\" alt=\"Early concept\" width=\"710\" height=\"516\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"text-align: center;\">TechNopTICon Booth, an early concept by Jonathan Wallraven</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">---</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adopt this project&nbsp;for&nbsp;your events!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/techn-o-pticon.gif', '', '', 'jonathan-wallraven,jordan-gray,vicente-montelongo', '', '0', '1697372452', '', '', '', 'project'),
(45, 'Ludovico', 'ludovico', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;\">A music visualizer leveraging social media content. Audio input is analyzed to automate visual effects and playback parameters videos and animated gifs.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;\">Without any customization, the app produces engaging visuals synced to the music. Casual users can start customizing by specifying tags to focus the loaded video content and by selecting stylized effects. Power users can program new automated behavior and effects which can be saved and shared.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;\">Ludovico brings video art to the masses and form a collaborative network for creating and consuming music visualization styles.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;\">Check Ludovico out with this <a style=\"background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eDI82fS5Kd8\" target=\"_blank\">Video Demonstration</a></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/ludivico.gif', '', 'http://ludovico.io/', '', '', '0', '1605826473', '', '', '', NULL),
(28, 'FIRE.ME', 'fire-me', '            \r\n						<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><strong>PLAY WITH ME, PLAY WITH FIRE!</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\">Adopt this project for your events!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><object width=\"802\" height=\"451\" classid=\"clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" data=\"https://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf\"><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"intl_lang=en-US&photo_secret=02f7174cf0&photo_id=10716513783&hd_default=false\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"https://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#000000\"><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"><embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" src=\"https://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf\" bgcolor=\"#000000\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" flashvars=\"intl_lang=en-US&photo_secret=02f7174cf0&photo_id=10716513783&hd_default=false\" width=\"802\" height=\"451\"></object></p>\r\n<p>A project built with <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech Arts</a></p>\r\n											          ', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/fire-me.jpg', '', '', 'kinetech-arts', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/fire-me/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29, '#LeapyBird', 'leapybird', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Literally flap your way to victory!<span id=\"more-5014\"></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Your bird wants to go on an adventure of epic proportions but needs you to make him fly! Place your hands over the sensor and flap your way through video game land, San Francisco, and CODAME memories on your way to the amazing end stage. 11 wholly frustrating and tiring scenes will have you dodge all manner of obstacles. Only the bravest and strongest can survive!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><br /><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/leapybird/www.freesound.org/people/ani_music/packs/15109/\">Download</a>&nbsp;the sound effects for free!</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/rQCaHp50hrI?rel=0\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>LeapyBrid is not just a fun game, book it&nbsp;for a<strong>&nbsp;Creative&nbsp;Workshops</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Learn how to build a game with&nbsp;#LeapyBird&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Customize your #LeapyBird with your own designs, sound effects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>With just a few lines of code, make your bird fly and win levels by literally flopping your hands and smile.</p>\r\n<p>An opportunity for kids (and not only) to learn about game design, coding and have fun! For all ages!</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leadybird-at-mini-maker-faire-with-kids-7jpg_16724292826_o1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leadybird-at-mini-maker-faire-with-kids-11jpg_16724298126_o1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leadybird-at-mini-maker-faire-with-kids-15jpg_16376206283_o1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/leapybird-workshop1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"/uploaded_images/leapybird3.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<div id=\"fb-root\">&nbsp;</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/leapybird.jpg', '', '', 'ani', '', '0', '1490333964', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(47, 'Windows', 'windows', '<p>Windows&nbsp;is an installation that is meant to highlight the convergence of the digital and physical realities we are moving towards. Although the phenomenon of digital reality is currently disparate from physical reality, what will happen as the lines become indistinguishable? The computer is a new kind of window, one that does not limit our attentional proximity to our immediate physical location.&nbsp;Windows&nbsp;speaks on the relationship we have with our computers and the rest of the world&mdash;not merely on the access it provides us on a daily basis, but as a symbol for our relation to its information as well as its context.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Don\'t miss <em>Windows</em></strong><strong> by CAPSVLE at the 2015 <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2015\">CODAME Art+Tech Festival</a> on October 23+24th.</strong></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/windows-by-capsvle.jpg', '', '', 'capsvle,cruise,ooggee', '', '0', '1606785160', '', '', '', NULL),
(30, 'Mobile Cloud Platform', 'mobile-cloud-platform', '<p>Mobile Cloud adds whimsy to any event but shines in an outdoor space where it can provide a full scale specticle, up to the height of a 4 story building.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you\'re seeking interaction, the audience is invited to play conductor and take control of the Cloud&rsquo;s cutting-edge LED and sound effects, creating an orchestra of sunsets, lightning storms, and thunder with the touch of a button.</p>\r\n<p>At California Academy of Sciences&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=4926\">NightLife LIVE</a>, CODAME demonstrated the thrill of adding an aerialist (Lyra Levin) to the Mobile Cloud appearance!</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/SAM_5566-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/ardent-mobile-cloud-platform.jpg', '', '', 'ian-baker', '', '0', '1518717903', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(106, 'Spring Spyre', 'spring-spyre', '<p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">The Spring Spyre, the latest instrument created by Laetitia Sonami, is made of found and hacked parts and uses Machine Learning software to control audio synthesis in realtime.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Three audio pick ups &nbsp;connected with thin metal springs generate audio signals which are parsed and fed to the Neural Synths.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Sonami started developing this new instrument after using her iconic&nbsp;<em>lady\'s glove &nbsp;</em>for over twenty years.</span></div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/spring-spyre.jpg', '', '', 'laetitia-sonami', '', '0', '1520902047', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(98, 'Cake23', 'cake23', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The interactive installation piece Cake 23 combines markerless full body and gesture tracking with trippy visualizations and simulations. Perhaps you\'ve seen one of his various fluid simulations or particle cloud animations. The GPU accelerated feedback loop engages the unexpecting user to playfully explore reaction-diffusion systems, fractals and cellular automatons. At times it makes you feel like you\'re inside a drippy wet painting, and the next moment you hallucinate tiger or zebra stripe patterns or find yourself harnessing swarms of energetic particles.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cake23 is written in C#.NET, using a tiny WPF GUI, Owin Self-Host, Razor templates, SignalR Websocket abstractions, wraps the MS Kinect SDK 2.0 and a MIDI library, and it servicec multiple Vanilla JS WebGL clients.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px;\">&nbsp;</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/cake23.png', '', '', 'felix-woitzel', '', '0', '1505581739', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(31, 'FluidScapes', 'fluidscapes', '<p>FluidScapes are about making the invisible visible and the interplay of two generative systems. These images are snapshots in time of a simulated fluid field affecting the height of a generative terrain made from particles and springs.</p>\r\n<p>Custom software is used to simulate and visualize the generative systems interplay with each other in real-time. In this exhibition the FluidScapes are rendered as prints, but they exist as digital files which can be 3D printed or CNC machined into FluidScape Sculptures by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/reza/\">Reza Ali</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a>&nbsp;and bring FluidScapes into your life, brighten your environment and add sparkles to your event!</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/fluidscapes.gif', '', '', 'reza-ali', '', '0', '1472005753', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(60, 'Deep Dream Vision Quest', 'deep-dream-vision-quest', '<div><a href=\"https://www.deepdreamvisionquest.com\">DeepDreamVisionQuest</a> is a neural image synthesizer that creates and explores multiplayer hallucinations. Behind the screen is a neural network that reinterprets the world it sees through a live camera. Its memories intensify the longer the field of vision remains motionless. Standing in front of it, you will see creatures emerge from suddenly alien landscapes, only to fade the second you move. The surprising truth behind artificial intelligence is that Mind emerges from the environment. You complete the circuit.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><img src=\"/uploaded_images/deepdreamvisionquest_022.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div><img src=\"/uploaded_images/deepdreamvisionquest_032.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div><img src=\"/uploaded_images/deepdreamvisionquest_042.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><img src=\"/uploaded_images/deepdreamvisionquest_051.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><img src=\"/uploaded_images/deepdreamvisionquest_061.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/189656794?title=0&amp;byline=0\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"></iframe></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Software:</div>\r\n<div>Linux, Python 2.7, OpenCV, Caffe Deep Learning Framework</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Neural Networks:</div>\r\n<div>GoogLeNet, VGG-19, VGG-16</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Hardware:</div>\r\n<div>Intel Core i7 6700 3.4GHz Quad Core CPU</div>\r\n<div>Nvidia GeForce GTX Titan X (Pascal) GPU</div>\r\n<div>2x Logitech C920 webcams</div>\r\n<div>60\" HDTV display</div>\r\n<div>Medical cart (for CPU workstation)</div>\r\n<div>Chief MFCUS Medium Flat Panel Mobile AV Cart</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/deep-dream-vision-quest.jpg', '', 'http://www.deepdreamvisionquest.com/', 'gary-boodhoo', '', '0', '1526918765', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(32, 'ART+TECH Mascot', 'art-tech-mascot', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">An iBeacon powered 3D Printed mascot to connect artists and their work with people.</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This little guy features a face that rotates to reveal three different emotions &amp; the opposable tentacles can be made in different colors for fun mix-and-match monsters.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME ART+TECH\'s mascot, an evolution of designs by Vicente Montelongo and Gavin Strange, freshly modeled for 3d printing of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.jam-factory.com/droplet/\">Droplet</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Support CODAME to re-design a 3d printed object as a give away for our <a href=\"/artists\">artists</a>&nbsp;to integrate the iBeacon &nbsp;low energy Bluetooth 4.x Powered Mascot with their projects.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Adopt this project!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.jam-factory.com/droplet/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2903\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Droplet-Series-2.jpg\" alt=\"Droplet-Series-2\" width=\"550\" height=\"187\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050;\"><a href=\"/support\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2867\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Support-ART+TECH-small.png\" alt=\"Support ART+TECH small\" width=\"596\" height=\"209\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5394  hoverZoomLink\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/9275229_orig-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"CODAME Mascot\" width=\"596\" height=\"447\" /></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-mascot.jpg', '', 'http://www.jam-factory.com/droplet/', 'justin-kinder', '', '0', '1472524777', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(33, 'Collab Zone', 'collab-zone', '<p><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Imagine a social graph. Not for your network of friends. But for the people you work with. Your co-workers, vendors, suppliers, and customers.</em></p>\r\n<p>What do you imagine it will look like?</p>\r\n<p><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Collab Zone</em>, an installation that visualizes the modern workplace, uses real data to illustrate the radical changes taking place in the way we work. It shows how workers are growing more collaborative and the depth of those interactions. It unravels the shift in work habits in seven industries including tightly regulated ones like healthcare and finance.</p>\r\n<p>The result is an interactive piece that combines physics, data visualization, and performance art created by CODAME and Kinetech Arts.</p>\r\n<p>This immersive experience, a truly remarkable undertaking, was made possible thanks to the generous support of Box as part of CODAME&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/adopt\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\">Adopt an Artist</a>&nbsp;program.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.lightisdance.com/graph3d/public/\" width=\"779\" height=\"519\"></iframe>As seen at&nbsp;the&nbsp;<em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Collab Zone</em>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://boxworks2014.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-href=\"http://boxworks2014.com\">BoxWorks</a>&nbsp;2014 from Sept 3&ndash;4, 2014 at The Moscone Center North.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Check out the reportage on&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/06/how-big-companies-and-their-tech-suppliers-are-changing-together\">The New York Times</a>:&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://nyti.ms/1u9hOrO\">How Big Companies and Their Tech Suppliers Are Changing Together</a>&ldquo;</em></p>\r\n<div class=\"image\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\">\r\n<div class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 602px;\"><img id=\"100000003093374\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2014/09/06/technology/06bits-corporate/06bits-corporate-tmagArticle.jpg\" alt=\"Box has a gesture-based screen to examine things such as who from different companies in a film production is working on what parts of a project.\" width=\"592\" height=\"395\" />\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; font-size: 15.75px; font-style: italic;\">Box has a gesture-based screen to examine things such as who from different companies in a film production is working on what parts of a project. Credit Quentin Hardy/<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/06/how-big-companies-and-their-tech-suppliers-are-changing-together\">The New York Times</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_5284\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px; width: 886px;\"><img class=\"wp-image-5284 size-full\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/IMG_0864.png\" alt=\"IMG_0864\" width=\"876\" height=\"533\" />Collab Zone&nbsp;will be on view at BoxWorks 2014 from Sept 3&ndash;4, 2014 at&nbsp;The Moscone Center North,&nbsp;San Francisco, CA.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><iframe class=\"vine-embed pinged   \" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://vine.co/v/Ml9UXODQDAT/embed/simple\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><iframe class=\"vine-embed pinged    \" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://vine.co/v/OurOpY2erTv/embed/simple\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><iframe style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/USwt4nqG2zg?rel=0\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Creative minds behind&nbsp;<em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Collab Zone:</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adoptees&nbsp;(<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://box.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-href=\"http://box.com\">Box Inc</a>): Vinit Patil, Spencer Sass and Sunjin Kim.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adopted (<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-href=\"http://codame.com\">CODAME</a>): Weidong Yang and Travis Bennett.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 2em; color: #505050; font-family: Open-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 29.25px;\"><img class=\"graf-image aligncenter\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; display: block; margin: 5px auto; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"https://d262ilb51hltx0.cloudfront.net/max/1600/1*2LGb-wQx68M4y0O0CQ-iJQ.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-image-id=\"1*2LGb-wQx68M4y0O0CQ-iJQ.jpeg\" data-width=\"600\" data-height=\"600\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">For more information about the Adopt ART+TECH program,&nbsp;</em><a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #00a4a7; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"mailto:adopt@codame.com\" data-href=\"mailto:adopt@codame.com\"><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">get in touch</em></a><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">!</em></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/collab-zone.png', '', '', 'weidong-yang,travis-bennet', '', '0', '1443073377', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(46, 'Ãœbungsraum', 'bungsraum', '<p dir=\"ltr\">&Uuml;bungsraum, or Personal Movement Space, is a Kinesthetic interactive sound and vision experience. Sensors track the bodies that enter the a space, while harmonious sound and light react. The work is centered on extending the natural understanding of our physical awareness. Body vibrations and patterns of movement will be reflected, creating a unique playable instrument out of human, light, and sound. Frenetic dancing is encouraged, as well as calm meditative movement.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Collaborators:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Jacob Fenwick is a little bit maybe gearhead and a kind of techno wizard obsessed with making aluminium objects. He owed the other colaborators a debt and so they got him to wrangle the sensor network.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Matt Howell, misterinterrupt, is a hacker and audio synthesist focused on uncovering exoteric truths via hypnogogic sound and mediated proprioception. His interactive artworks aim to inspire the discovery and embodiment of creative human agency.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Donald Hanson is a new media artist and visual designer that uses code as a medium for expression. He also works on <a href=\"http://gifslap.com\">gifSlap</a> and cofounded the&nbsp;electronica label, <a href=\"http://gridwalk.net\">Gridwalk</a>.</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/bungsraum.gif', '', 'http://github.com/jfenwick/rpikinect', 'd0n-xyz,jacob fenwick,misterinterrupt', '', '0', '1590773331', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(48, 'PhenoTyptych', 'phenotyptych', '<p><strong>PhenoTyptych directed by Michael Garrigues, Choreographed by Jenay &ldquo;ShinobiJaxx&rdquo; Anolin, Sound design by Barragoon. Presenting dancers&nbsp;Anastasia Ryzhova and Nina Wu.</strong></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/142472437?byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><br />&ldquo;PhenoTyptych,&rdquo; tracks the arc of evolution from simple life forms to our current competitive complex organisms - &nbsp;followed by de-evolution back into baser life forms after&nbsp;the implosion of our hyper-networked social and over-complex technological networks.&nbsp;<br /><br />Choreography by Jenay &ldquo;ShinobiJaxx\" Anolin will illustrate this journey ranging from precise technical movements, to bursts of street moves celebrating contemporary&nbsp;culture. LED lights outline the dancers bodies as they move through darkened space. Via a slow motion effect applied during projection, their forms become expressions of&nbsp;light energy - sliding, writhing and dancing.<br /><br />Dancers Anastasia Ryzhova and Nina Wu will be accompanied by DJ Barragoon&rsquo;s rich soundscape, which will carry us on a journey from the bubbling soup of early life to&nbsp;when electrons take their final spin around the freezing atoms of the universe.<br /><br /><strong>Director</strong><br />Michael Garrigues first explored &nbsp;the intersection of the human form and technology creatively with his play &ldquo;Waiting for the Inkie&rdquo; a cyber-family satire, where human&nbsp;embryos are augmented by smart drugs, and language tapes, to his feature documentary &ldquo;J, Robot&rdquo; &nbsp;which explores why Japan of all the other nations in the world have a&nbsp;special fondness for the humanoid robot form. &nbsp;&ldquo;J, Robot&rdquo; appeared in numerous film festivals and was a featured film at the Robot Art Festival in Prague, selected for&nbsp;Australian Scienema Science Film Festival and shown in 400 schools, libraries, art galleries and museums throughout &nbsp;Australia in 2012.<br /><br /><strong>Choreographer</strong><br />Jenay &ldquo;ShinobiJaxx&rdquo; Anolin is the Co-Founder and Director of Mix&rsquo;d Ingrdnts Dance Company. She previously was a member of Philadelphia&rsquo;s Hip Hop Dance Theater&nbsp;Company Rennie Harris RHAW. She started the Oakland youth group &ldquo;The GroovLings&rdquo; and has performed with Bay Area Dance Companies such as The Oakland Ballet&nbsp;Company, New Style Motherlode, and La Femme Panache.<br /><br /><strong>Soundscape Designer</strong><br />Julian Barragan, a DJ/Producer known as &ldquo;Barragoon&rdquo; pushes his experimental beats all around his native city of Chicago.&nbsp; HIs beats have been heard at The Mid, Concord&nbsp;Music Hall, Evil Olive, and North Coast Music Festival, just to name a few.</p>\r\n<p><strong>PhenoTyptych will be premiering at the 2015 <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2015\">CODAME Art+Tech festival</a> on Saturday October 24th.</strong></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/phenotyptych.gif', '', '', '', '', '0', '1445216530', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(34, 'LED PIXEL ART', 'led-pixel-art', '\r\n						<p class=\"p1\"><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/al-linke/\">Al Linke</a> is the creator of an LED display for art and advertising called <a href=\"http://ledpixelart.com/\"><span class=\"s1\">PIXEL</span></a>, a successfully crowd funded project. With it’s ultra-bright LEDs, the effect is quite unique. And unlike other LED displays, PIXEL can be programmed from the ease of an Android phone.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Get your PIXEL for your office, home, event or as a present to a special person that appreciate Art, Technology and LEDs. We can create customized animations for your PIXEL.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">We can also run a workshop for you and your team. An introduction on pixel art is and how to create your own pixel art using your Android phone and display it on PIXEL. We have a few extra devices available for those without an Android. In the meantime, feel free to download the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ledpixelart.pixelesque\"><span class=\"s1\">pixel art editor Android app</span></a> now and start creating as well as the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ledpixelart.piledriver\"><span class=\"s1\">app for PIXEL’s</span></a><span class=\"s1\"> built in content</span><span class=\"s1\">.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Check out Al’s newest pieace called “<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BV2cUweLCio\"><span class=\"s1\">Signs of Temptation</span></a>”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Adopt PIXEL</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/GqK45AUPkfM?rel=0\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/led-pixel-art.gif', '', '', 'al-linke', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/pixel/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(35, 'Receipt Bots', 'receipt-bots', '<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/rb-logo-white1.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Inspired by retro robots, <strong>Receipt Bot</strong> is a photo booth like no other. Her&nbsp;eyes are beautiful, candy-like buttons that blink irreverently. Her nose is a pinhole HD camera. Her mouth is a thermal printer, spitting out your photos in state-of-the-art&nbsp;dot-matrix style quality (she also does <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASCII_art\">ASCII art</a>).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Receipt Bots</strong> love parties and gatherings and any other place that friends come together to take photos. Don&rsquo;t you want to meet one?<a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-5362 hoverZoomLink\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Cleaned-Up-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Cleaned Up\" width=\"907\" height=\"604\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5991\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/IMG_2875.jpg\" alt=\"Receipt Bot\" width=\"2448\" height=\"2448\" /></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/receipt-bots.gif', '', '', 'jamie-kosoy', '', '0', '1490891545', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79, 'Levels', 'levels', '<p>This fractal visualization explores the relationship between chaos and rules. Given simple objects and processes, iteration yields an unprecedented network of connections and complexity. All parameters controls can be changed on the fly, with 3D controls.</p>\r\n<p>This is a fundamental property of all organisms around us. Simple cells follow iterative processes, generating the richness in forms of the natural world. This work illustrates these connections with a powerful 3D fractal renderer capable of visualizing complex networks from tree structures to immersive surreal landscapes.</p>\r\n<p>Most fractal art cheats the viewer out of this powerful knowledge that the blueprint is very simple, and the complexity comes from iteration. The complex images are simply presented without context. In this educational piece, Nick Shelton demonstrates the construction of these forms from primitives, showing iterative processes of translation, rotation and scaling. By viewing the process step by step, the viewer gains insight into the connections being presented, and hopefully, structures in the natural world around them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Technology: WebGL, GLSL raymarching, GLW.js by Mikael Emtinger and Olov Lassus, ThreeAudio by Steven Whittens</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/levels.gif', '', 'https://nshelton.github.io/glsl/fractal/audioreactive/webgl/2016/10/30/LEVELS.html', 'sheltron', '', '0', '1497977863', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(36, 'DataGeyser', 'datageyser', '\r\n						<hr>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">An immersive VR experience of data on Social Network.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Give us your data, login to facebook or twitter and check it out yourself.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">As seen at CODAME <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/?p=5644\">ART+TECH Virtual Reality</a> @ Mozilla, San Francisco, Friday Nov. 21st.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Adopt #DataGeyser for your events!</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Developers: James Edward, Kim Marquardt, Travis Bennett and Weidong Yang</p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/datageyser.jpg', '', '', 'weidong-yang,travis-bennet', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/datafountain/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(37, 'DANCE + DRAW', 'dance-draw', '<header>\r\n<div>Painting is generated by almost invisible movement of a dancer.</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<article id=\"post-5554\"><hr />\r\n<p>A fractal based painting visualizing subtle dance of weight shifting.</p>\r\n<p>A floor projection. Stand on a Wii balance board, we collect your body weight&nbsp;and start to paint with the data we collect.</p>\r\n<p>Adopt this project for your events!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/adopt\"><img src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a></p>\r\n<div id=\"fb-root\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div><iframe id=\"fb_xdm_frame_http\" tabindex=\"-1\" title=\"Facebook Cross Domain Communication Frame\" src=\"http://static.ak.facebook.com/connect/xd_arbiter/xRlIuTsSMoE.js?version=41#channel=f2e09c1288&amp;origin=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.codame.com\" name=\"fb_xdm_frame_http\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe><iframe id=\"fb_xdm_frame_https\" tabindex=\"-1\" title=\"Facebook Cross Domain Communication Frame\" src=\"https://s-static.ak.facebook.com/connect/xd_arbiter/xRlIuTsSMoE.js?version=41#channel=f2e09c1288&amp;origin=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.codame.com\" name=\"fb_xdm_frame_https\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div data-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CODAME.ART.TECH/photos/a.737427473000250.1073741898.121190041290666/736853276391003/?type=1\" data-width=\"600\"><iframe class=\"\" title=\"fb:post Facebook Social Plugin\" src=\"http://www.facebook.com/plugins/post.php?app_id=&amp;channel=http%3A%2F%2Fstatic.ak.facebook.com%2Fconnect%2Fxd_arbiter%2FxRlIuTsSMoE.js%3Fversion%3D41%23cb%3Df3734bd4d%26domain%3Dwww.codame.com%26origin%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fwww.codame.com%252Ff2e09c1288%26relation%3Dparent.parent&amp;container_width=675&amp;href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FCODAME.ART.TECH%2Fphotos%2Fa.737427473000250.1073741898.121190041290666%2F736853276391003%2F%3Ftype%3D1&amp;locale=en_US&amp;sdk=joey&amp;width=600\" name=\"f1f0dcbd88\" width=\"600px\" height=\"1000px\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n<div id=\"fb-root\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>First seen&nbsp;at CODAME&nbsp;&nbsp;ART+TECH Event Oct. 31st, at&nbsp;Geekdom &ndash; 620&nbsp;Folsom St., San Francisco</p>\r\n<p>Performer:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/kinetech/\">Kinetech Arts</a>&nbsp;dancers</p>\r\n<p>Developer: Travis Bennett and Weidong Yang</p>\r\n</article>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/dance-draw.jpg', '', '', 'weidong-yang,travis-bennett', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/dance-draw/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(38, 'Surveillance Mode', 'surveillance-mode', '\r\n						<hr>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/qGoTkaw_j-g?rel=0\" width=\"922\" height=\"519\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Tech/Cabaret song by <a href=\"http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/jasper-paterson/\">Jasper Patterson</a>. Using “Emotional Augmentation” in OpenFrameworks by Weidong Yang, imported into realtime audio city in Unity3d, projection mapping through Touch Designer, by Chris Crismond. Sets by Arashi Seirika</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Adopt “Surveillance Mode” for your events!</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Enjoy the show at CODAME <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\"><IN.SECURE></a> ART+TECH Friday Oct. 31st, at Geekdom – 620 Folsom St., San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=12716570605&ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"410\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/surveillance-mode.png', '', '', 'jasper-patterson', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/surveillance-mode/', '1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(39, 'Surveillance Phone', 'surveillance-phone', '\r\n						<hr>\r\n<p>Cave Plexum is an “alternate reality” in which the object <a href=\"http://www.viviancharlesworth.com/installation-2/surveillance-phone\">Surveillance Phone</a> is the rabbit hole*.</p>\r\n<p>Surveillance Phone and Cave Plexum are collaborative pieces by <a href=\"http://www.viviancharlesworth.com/\">Vivian Charlesworth</a> and <a href=\"http://www.alysonogasian.com/\">Alyson Ogasian</a></p>\r\n<p><i>* “A rabbithole, or trailhead, marks the first media artifact, be it a website, contact, or puzzle, that draws in players.”</i></p>\r\n<p>Vivian Charlesworth and Alyson Ogasian’s collaborative work draws from multiple disciplines including geology, politics, history, archeology, and environmental science, as well as their diverse professional experience in the fields of law, theater and environmental political action. Ogasian and Charlesworth work as artists and researchers to generate narratives that explore environmental disintegration, public policy and military industrial development.  Together they use science fiction as a methodology to create work that re-examines historical and current events. </p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>Experience Surveillance Phone at CODAME <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\"><IN.SECURE></a> ART+TECH Friday Oct. 31st, at Geekdom – 620 Folsom St., San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=12716570605&ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"410\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=12716570605&ref=etckt\" width=\"100%\" height=\"410\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"5\" marginheight=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Adopt Surveillance Phone for your events!</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology</a></strong></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/surveillance-phone.gif', '', 'http://www.viviancharlesworth.com/installation-2/surveillance-phone', '', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/surveillance-phone/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `projects` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `description`, `pic`, `twitter`, `website`, `artists_array`, `old_url`, `hidden`, `edited`, `shop_url`, `partners_array`, `sponsors_array`, `is_nft`) VALUES
(40, 'Faraday Cave', 'faraday-cave', '\r\n						<hr>\r\n<p>Kiss your connectedness goodbye in a tinfoil tent chill zone, big enough for you and a friend (or 3). Also protects from EMP attacks and prying eyes. Thank <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faraday_cage\">Faraday</a>!</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/sJyuKCrxgA4?rel=0\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><strong>Adopt this project for your events!</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" title=\"Adopt an Artist, Support ART+TECH\" href=\"http://codame.com/adopt\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3942\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Codame_Badge_02_AdoptAnArtist_200px.png\" alt=\"Adopt an Artist\" width=\"200\" height=\"145\"></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #505050; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #00a4a7;\" href=\"http://www.codame.com/support/\">Support Art and Technology!</a></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>Crawl into the Faraday Cave at CODAME <a href=\"http://codame.eventbrite.com/\"><IN.SECURE></a> ART+TECH Friday Oct. 31st, at Geekdom – 620 Folsom St., San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5679\" src=\"http://www.codame.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/faraday-cave-trans.png\" alt=\"faraday-cave-trans\" width=\"999\" height=\"945\"></p>\r\n											', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/faraday-cave.png', '', '', 'dat-phan', 'http://www.codame.com/post/portfolio/faraday-cave/', '0', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(41, 'I Know Where Your Cat Lives', 'i-know-where-your-cat-lives', '<hr />\r\n<p>I Know Where Your Cat Lives is a data experiment that visualizes a sample of 1 million public pics of cats on a world map, locating them by the latitude and longitude coordinates embedded in their metadata. The cats were accessed via publicly available APIs provided by popular photo sharing websites. The photos were then run through various clustering algorithms using a supercomputer at Florida State University in order to represent the enormity of the data source.</p>\r\n<p>This project explores two uses of the internet: the sociable and humorous appreciation of domesticated felines, and the status quo of personal data usage by startups and international megacorps who are riding the wave of decreased privacy for all. This website doesnï¿½t visualize all of the cats on the net, only the ones that allow you to track where their owners have been.</p>\r\n<p>This project, by Owen Mundy, was launched in July 2014 to critical international acclaim with press including Motherboard/Vice Magazine, The New York Times, Time Magazine, The Atlanticm, Wired (UK) MSNBC, NPR..</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/i-know-where-your-cat-lives.png', '', '', 'owen-mundy', '', '0', '1520842173', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108, 'Janus ', 'janus', '<p><em>Janus</em>&nbsp;is a project with two faces: a volumetric film and a VR experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Janus</em> is an art&nbsp;experience that explores the duality of time and its effects on our identity. Inspired by the ancient god of time - the two-faced Janus, the project questions the meaning of one&rsquo;s identity intimes of transformation, as past and future face each other. In <em>Janus</em>, the viewer finds themselves witnessing adance, a dialogue between two dancers who reveal to be past and future - the two faces of time.</p>\r\n<p>Based on a moving image piece created by Marta in December 2017, <em>Janus VR</em> is the next step in her exploration of digital identity, sculptural time and presence, concepts previously explored using time displacement techniques such as slit scanning and volumetric aesthetics. The combination of VR and volumetric techniques used in the creation of the piece is key for the artist to explore the boundary between real and virtual, for theaudience to experience a deeper sense of presence, and for the dancers to test new approaches in choreography.</p>\r\n<p>Through the VR headset, the viewer will place themselves in the centre of the experience, beingfully immersed in the dancers&rsquo; performance. <em>Janus VR</em> is a poetic journey in which the notions of self and wholeness are raised and questioned against the theme of disintegration and dilution of one&rsquo;s identity. The story that guides the viewer is carefully delivered through script, the voice-over recordings and ambisonic soundscape. The piece explores movement, embodiment, perception, awareness and sense of presence. In these times of distraction and disconnectivity, the piece invites the audience to acknowledge a sense of \"now\", to reflect on past and future, and be aware of \"a sense of self, agency\" intended as \"taking action now\'.</p>\r\n<p>The concept of liminality or a&ldquo;transitional period&rdquo; is also explored in <em>Janus</em>. Liminality is relevant in questioning and defining the meaning of time when everything around us is changing. &ldquo;We are at the threshold of a new era that will be defined by our ability to learn from the past in order to move forward into the future. A deep sense of presence is necessary in moments of transition which are often accompanied by loss of identity. Presence is necessary to understand this moment and to be able to take action in response to it.&rdquo; - Marta Di Francesco.</p>\r\n<p><em>Janus VR</em> is a project by London-based artist Marta Di Francesco, produced by Carmen Salas with funding from Arts Council England, and the support of Ugly Duck.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/janus.jpeg', '', 'http://cargocollective.com/mdf/Janus', 'marta-di-francesco', '', '0', '1520895803', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52, 'Metamorphosis', 'metamorphosis', '<p>The Metamorphosis interactive installation brings insight into the notion of self in an effort to embrace togetherness.</p>\r\n<p>Facing each side of the transformation portal viewers align their physical symmetry with each others to create changing personas in real time and co-create unity.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s also a platform for various art forms to take place including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Performance arts (Dance, Theater)</li>\r\n<li>Photography and videography (from participants)</li>\r\n<li>Interactive &amp; Transformative arts&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Meta_ligth_02.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>The Metamorphosis project brings forth changes and insights through physical, sociological, psychological and spiritual transformation. It can help bridge the differences perceived by:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Age: Young / Elderly</li>\r\n<li>Colors: Black / White</li>\r\n<li>Gender: Male /Female</li>\r\n<li>Social Status: Rich / Poor</li>\r\n<li>Religion &amp; culture: Jewish / Muslim</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/FFeppvV2UUc\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Metamorphosis is a collaborative, playful, Inner-Active and unique transformative experience inspired by the following key concepts:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Equality</li>\r\n<li>Unity &amp; Collaboration</li>\r\n<li>Truth &amp; knowledge</li>\r\n<li>Art &amp; Expressive freedom</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/meta01.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:DocumentProperties>\r\n  <o:Revision>0</o:Revision>\r\n  <o:TotalTime>0</o:TotalTime>\r\n  <o:Pages>1</o:Pages>\r\n  <o:Words>152</o:Words>\r\n  <o:Characters>868</o:Characters>\r\n  <o:Company>Salesforce</o:Company>\r\n  <o:Lines>7</o:Lines>\r\n  <o:Paragraphs>2</o:Paragraphs>\r\n  <o:CharactersWithSpaces>1018</o:CharactersWithSpaces>\r\n  <o:Version>1