(233, 'Generative Sketches 3', 'generative-sketches-3', '', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/generative-sketches-3.png', '', '', 'yagmur-uyanik', '', '0', '1598076120', 'https://shop.codame.com/collections/yagmur-uyanik-joey-verbeke/products/yagmur-uyanik-print', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(234, 'Merchandise', 'merchandise', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support&nbsp;and&nbsp;ðŸ’Ÿ for ART+TECH!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">You can find more CODAME merchindes on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise\">shop.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise/products/codame-unisex-short-sleeve-tee\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/tshirt2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise/products/codame-unisex-short-sleeve-tee\">CODAME t-shirt</a> @&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise/products/codame-unisex-short-sleeve-tee\">shop.codame.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise/products/codame-enamel-mug\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/mug.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise/products/codame-enamel-mug\">CODAME&nbsp;Mug</a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise/products/codame-enamel-mug\">shop.codame.com</a></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/merchandise.jpg', '', '', 'vicente-montelongo', '', '0', '1598126660', 'https://shop.codame.com/collections/codame-merchandise', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(236, 'Gorges', 'gorges', '<p>Gorges contemplates contemporary technological society&rsquo;s relationship with the natural world. While clouds are synonymous with digital culture, rendered rivers and mountains are realistically depicted stationary with highly saturated color directly from the RGB scale. The naturalistic compositions ties visually to landscape paintings (both Chinese and Western), play on perception and desire for a relationship with nature; yet it is synthetic, a liminal realm that we experience but cannot touch. Gorges offers an experience of the digital sublime, which overlaps with our perception of the digital, landscape, our relationship with each, and the fundamental questions that follow, peering into the nature of our existence.</p>\r\n<p>Make an offer on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://knownorigin.io/edition/203325\">Knownorigin</a></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/gorges.jpg', '', '', 'snow-yunxue-fu', '', '0', '1598370297', 'https://knownorigin.io/edition/203325', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(237, 'DXGPVWZ', 'dxgpvwz', '<p>DXGPVWZ is the audio-visual collaborative brainpup of {arsonist} &amp; spednar. The duo crossbreed their experimental electronic production talents to create a new, designer form of IDM (Intelligent Dog Music). Interfacing visual tools such as Unity, OpenFrameworks, GLSL, and Unreal Engine, they create real-time, audio-reactive 3D worlds of frolicking fun and absurdism that serve as windows into the depths of the canine psyche.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"padding: 56.25% 0 0 0; position: relative;\"><iframe style=\"position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/448655239?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/dxgpvwz.jpg', '', '', 'kevin-bednar,danielle-rager', '', '0', '1599606668', '', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(239, 'The Creation', 'the-creation', '<p>When you buy a layer you have the opportunity to influence your favorite artists\' work. Layers are endowed with special abilities decided by the artist. When you change something on a layer the Master image will reflect this regardless of who owns it! The image below runs through a mix of the various layers and states to give an overview of some of the possibilities.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/ezgif-4-aced3dd7d8e1.gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>The Creation&nbsp;</strong>explores \"Blurring Borders\", the theme of The Grid: Exposure, part of&nbsp;<strong>Ars Electronica 2020</strong>. It is a cross-continental collaboration between CODAME Artists&nbsp;Jordan Gray&nbsp;(US),&nbsp;Janessa Robinson&nbsp;(US), and&nbsp;OoakosiMo&nbsp;(PH) and veteran Async Artist&nbsp;Vans Design&nbsp;(IT). As layers are purchased and their states manipulated, lines between creator, collector, and curator will blur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">CODAME is thrilled to partner with the amazingly innovative team at&nbsp;Async Art&nbsp;in the creation of a programmable blockchain art piece. Async Art is a new art movement to create, collect, and trade programmable art. Digital paintings are split into \"Layers\", which you can use to affect the overall image. Art that can evolve over time, react to its owners, or follow a stock price is now all possible with programmable art.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The Creation Async-hosted Auction&nbsp;will be taking place on&nbsp;Sep 14. Bidding will close on Sep 18 between 8-10 am PST. Follow instructions on&nbsp;<a href=\"/events/auction-the-creation\">auction-the-creation</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">25% of the total sales will be donated to The Grid in support of the organization&rsquo;s international solidarity fundraiser in support of the local art scene in the San Francisco Bay Area.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Yq6zsKq6_DmDReuJ8wvP_im3c5KtazNFlZRcn7TpmPFInIVXbWcUdlWIK2Omh5f6T0jKjpMNWR0dYL_wtMeb04sgq61rRmMsad6QTywV9a4ihBQ2qPFyJMwGG5ceBbf-Fk20Q1zX\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">To emphasize the power of the future Layer holders, CODAME has decided to make a T-shirt of a specified state of the artwork. After the piece is auctioned off on September 18th, we will wait a week for the Layer owners to make their desired changes to the artwork and will gift the Master owner the final T-shirt, as well as offer it as featured merchandise on our Gallery&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com\">Online Store</a>. You can place&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/products/codame-x-async-art-collaboration-the-creation-t-shirt\">pre-orders for the t-shirt now</a>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/the-creation.gif', '', 'https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-560', 'jordan-gray,janessa-robinson,ooakosimo,emi,vans-design', '', '0', '1640805374', 'https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-560', '', '', 'nft'),
(238, 'VOIDOPOLIS', 'voidopolis', '<p>Voidopolis is a digital performance about loss and memory presented as an AR book with a limited lifespan. The story is a loose retelling of Dante&rsquo;s Inferno, informed by the grim experience of wandering through NYC during a pandemic. Instead of Virgil, the narrator is guided through this modern hellscape by a caustic hobo named Nikita.</p>\r\n<p>Voidopolis is meant to culminate in loss. Its images are created by digitally &ldquo;wiping&rdquo; humans from stock photography and the text is generated without the letter &lsquo;e&rsquo; using a modified GPT-2 text generator. The book, adapted from a series of Instagram posts that was ultimately deleted, is likewise designed to disappear: the book&rsquo;s pages are garbled and can only be deciphered with an AR app, which, after enough readings, decays the images and words just as memory would. The printed book, with its unintelligible pages, remains as a leftover artifact. By disappearing, the story makes a case for the collective amnesia that follows great cataclysm.</p>\r\n<p>For&nbsp;Exposure, new episodes of VOIDOPOLIS are being exhibited on <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/codame/\">CODAME\'s instagram</a> over the entire week, from 7 September through 13 September.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/VPatArs.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"559\" /></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/voidopolis.jpeg', '', 'https://www.mustatea.com/voidopolis', 'kat-mustatea', '', '0', '1670347727', '', '', '', 'project'),
(241, 'Paris', 'paris', '<p><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/janessa-robinson/products/janessa-robinson-print\">Print Edition</a>: 1/10<br />HahnemuÌˆhle Photo Rag Fine Art Print<br />Image&nbsp;5 x 8n.&nbsp;<br />Unique</p>\r\n<p>This work is also tokenized as a crypto-collectible digital item.</p>\r\n<p>You can own and trade on&nbsp;<img src=\"https://a.slack-edge.com/production-standard-emoji-assets/10.2/apple-medium/1f48e@2x.png\" alt=\":gem:\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" data-stringify-type=\"emoji\" data-stringify-emoji=\":gem:\" />&nbsp;<a href=\"https://superrare.co/artwork-v2/paris-13911\">SuperRare</a>&nbsp;<span data-qa=\"emoji\" data-sk=\"tooltip_parent\"><img src=\"https://a.slack-edge.com/production-standard-emoji-assets/10.2/apple-medium/1f48e@2x.png\" alt=\":gem:\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" data-stringify-type=\"emoji\" data-stringify-emoji=\":gem:\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>Also available as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/products/janessa-robinson-weekender-bag?pr_prod_strat=collection_fallback&amp;pr_rec_pid=5648033382556&amp;pr_ref_pid=5647544254620&amp;pr_seq=uniform\">Weekender Bag</a></p>\r\n<p>Our oversized Weekender Tote is perfect for your weekend at the beach or in town. The wide-mouthed, durable bag holds a generous amount of personal items and is easily held by its thick rope handles.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/products/janessa-robinson-weekender-bag?pr_prod_strat=collection_fallback&amp;pr_rec_pid=5648033382556&amp;pr_ref_pid=5647544254620&amp;pr_seq=uniform\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/57708ea00ad88ebd1914139bc9f170e2_1296x.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\r\n<h1 class=\"product-single__title\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; margin: 0px 0px 15px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.73333em; color: #5d5a5a;\">&nbsp;</h1>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/paris.gif', '', '', 'janessa-robinson', '', '0', '1618947253', 'https://shop.codame.com/collections/janessa-robinson/products/janessa-robinson-print', '', '', 'nft'),
(242, 'Butterfly Blend', 'butterfly-blend', '<p>Edition: 1/10</p>\r\n<p>HahnemuÌˆhle Photo Rag Fine Art Print<br />Image&nbsp;5 x 8 in.&nbsp;<br />Unique</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/butterfly-blend.png', '', '', 'janessa-robinson', '', '0', '1618947234', 'https://shop.codame.com/collections/janessa-robinson/products/copy-of-janessa-robinson-print', '', '', 'nft'),
(243, 'Screen Dye', 'screen-dye', '<p>Screen Dye is a nonrepresentational time-based form, inspired by tie-dye and water caustics. These shapes were created by GLSL code, using math to describe shape, color and flow. This work was generated by a small graphics program written by Char Stiles. She writes GLSL code, specifically GLSL, on-the-fly and creates these graphics using a method of 3D rendering which uses contained mathematical functions to describe shapes and the materials which make up the shapes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/char-stiles/products/char-stiles-print-3\">Print Edition</a>: 1/1<br />GLSL Code<br />HahnemuÌˆhle Photo Rag Fine Art Print<br />Print: 11x17 inches<br />Unique</p>\r\n<p>This work is also tokenized as a crypto-collectible digital item.</p>\r\n<p>You can own and trade on&nbsp;<img src=\"https://a.slack-edge.com/production-standard-emoji-assets/10.2/apple-medium/1f48e@2x.png\" alt=\":gem:\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" data-stringify-type=\"emoji\" data-stringify-emoji=\":gem:\" />&nbsp;<a href=\"https://superrare.co/artwork-v2/screen-dye-13878\">SuperRare</a> <span data-qa=\"emoji\" data-sk=\"tooltip_parent\"><img src=\"https://a.slack-edge.com/production-standard-emoji-assets/10.2/apple-medium/1f48e@2x.png\" alt=\":gem:\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" data-stringify-type=\"emoji\" data-stringify-emoji=\":gem:\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/char-stiles/products/char-stiles-print-3\"><img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0398/6178/0636/products/ScreenShot2020-09-23at12.36.49AM_300x300.png?v=1600846722\" alt=\"CHAR STILES - PRINT\" width=\"761\" height=\"492\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Prints and more available on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/char-stiles/products/char-stiles-print-3\">shop.codame.com</a></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/screen-dye.gif', '', '', 'char-stiles', '', '0', '1600925071', 'https://shop.codame.com/collections/char-stiles/products/char-stiles-print-3', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(245, 'Nexus', 'nexus', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (free for all to particpate!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><br />Nexus is a hanging collection of creative artifacts participants leave behind to celebrate and connect.&nbsp; It is free to particpate virtually by filling out this <a href=\"https://forms.gle/HrWE1S98PbopgQQa9\">form</a>&nbsp;and generate an image!&nbsp; Nexus will also be a pop up at <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><a style=\"color: #0000ff;\" href=\"https://visitvulcan.com/\">Vulcan Park &amp; Museum</a>&nbsp;</span>where participants&nbsp;can fill out a booklet outdoors and leave it on display at the park!&nbsp; where</p>\r\n<p>Each participant is given a booklet-shaped ornament and invited to choose from prompts encouraging reflection on their experiences this year and the season, as well as what changes they want to see in the next evolution around the sun. 2020 has been an unprecedented year of great change and isolation, so this piece provides an avenue for collective contemplation in the physical realm. While screens and social media have provided critical avenues for connection in the time of social distancing, Nexus provides a unique and broader social sharing experience that transcends likes, feeds, and followers and is no longer focused on individual profiles.</p>\r\n<p>The artifacts participants leave behind are equalized in their anonymity. Everyone takes up the same amount of space, with no algorithms or sponsors determining whose story is shown to the viewers. Individual experiences are mapped into a collective experience; people can connect through creative reflections on the year without knowing other participants. This group project demonstrates no one is alone in the isolation of this year, and there are many creative avenues to connect this season.</p>\r\n<p>All particpants in the 2020 ART + TECH Festival Joynt will be sent instructions to participate and the finished group piece will be uploaded here!</p>\r\n<p>Limited edition Nexus&nbsp;<a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/quinn-keck/products/quinn-keck-personalized-nexus-mug\">mugs</a> and <a href=\"https://shop.codame.com/collections/quinn-keck/products/quinn-keck-nexus-iteration-i-scarf\">scraves</a> are also for sale!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/gBQqpkgjRvU\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/nexus-example1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/nexus.png', '', '', 'quinn-keck', '', '0', '1608489119', 'https://codame.com/projects/nexus', 'local-maker-mart', '', NULL),
(246, 'ART+TECH FESTIVAL 2020ã€Ž JOYNT ã€', 'art-tech-festival-2020-joynt', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 26pt; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Codame_Badge_Logo_08_white_web.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"98\" height=\"83\" /></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: center; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 26pt; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ART+TECH Festival 2020</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;JOYNT&nbsp;=&nbsp;Connect&nbsp;+&nbsp;Create&nbsp;+&nbsp;Celebrate</h2>\r\n<!-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|-- Ticket Tailor Widget -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong> annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|-- End Ticket Tailor Widget -----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>When</strong>: December 11th - 20th, 2020</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Where</strong>: Online &amp; Physical (following local safety guidelines).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>What:</strong>&nbsp;Workshops, Performaces, Meet the Artist, Auctions and Physical&nbsp;installations&nbsp;to be announced here</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|-- TT BUTTON -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|-- End TT BUTTON ----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">ã€Ž Volunteers ã€</h2>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;re looking for outstanding volunteers to support our ART+TECH Festival.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It&rsquo;s a fun and extremely rewarding experience as you learn new skills and pass your knowledge on to others. You&rsquo;ll meet like-minded people, make friends and build a network of people from all backgrounds who share a common passion for ART+TECH.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/pages/call-for-volunteers\">Joyn</a>&nbsp;us to be part of the magic!&nbsp;<br /><br /></p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">ã€Ž Partners &amp; Sponsors&nbsp;&nbsp;ã€</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Join our list of amazing&nbsp;<a href=\"/sponsors\">Sponsors</a>.&nbsp;Be recognized as an innovative and visionary organization, partner with us.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"/pages/support-art-tech\">Contact Us</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Asap,sans-serif; color: #ffffff; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; background-color: #000000; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/custombutton?eid=34741461647\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Workshops\" /></a></p>\r\n<center>ðŸ’Ÿ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’œ ðŸ‘¾ ðŸ’Ÿ</center>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">CODAME is a member of Intersection for the Arts&nbsp;<br />a non profit 501(c)(3)&nbsp;organization.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All proceeds will be split with the participating artists.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thank you for your support for ART &hearts;ï¸ TECH !!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"/pages/code-of-conduct\">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;for all attendees.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt.gif', '', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/', '', '', '0', '1605897858', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/', '', '', NULL),
(255, 'COSMOS', 'cosmos', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>COSMOS is an exploratory exercise to visualize space objects and events. From Calabi Yau Shapes* floating with a background of a galaxy (This is impossible to visualize because those shapes are geometries of higher dimensions inside protons and neutrons inside the atom nucleus, but it is my artistic interpretation on the subject), to interplanetary star systems like our solar system, to black holes (Small black holes with relatively small mass) When the user interacts with an artwork by touching the screen, the specific experiment will transform and give to the spectator a new sensation related to the visualization and subject. The project is built using web open source technologies.</p>\r\n<p>* The Calabi Yau Geometries were built from the research of Andrew J. Hanson and Paul Masson math framework. All the experiments are rendered with three.js and animated with gsap.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/cosmos.png', '', '', 'ivan-moreno', '', '0', '1607580721', '', 'd2d-art', '', NULL),
(256, 'VR Music Videos', 'vr-music-videos', '<p>Michelle Brown is an Australian based new media artist and art director focused on immersive and interactive art installations and creating XR storytelling experiences. She has produced documentary series for Australian television, created music videos and visuals for a variety of artists and organisations and exhibited VR experiences internationally.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this in to your website where you want the widget to appear. Do no change the code or the widget may not work properly. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------><center>\r\n<p id=\"&rdquo;fest-10&rdquo;\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong> annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n</center><!-- End of Ticket Tailor Widget ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h3>Conrad Greenleaf&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/462300021?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"274\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Richard In Your Mind</h3>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/324772078?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"274\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Vape Dadz</h3>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/423907927?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"274\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/vr-music-videos.png', '', 'https://creator.oculus.com/community/802877400141713/', 'the-bad-lament---michelle-brown', '', '0', '1606852302', '', '', '', NULL),
(257, 'Secrets Exchange/Crypto Art Generator', 'secrets-exchange-crypto-art-generator', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Launched as an Anytime Experience at</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://secrets.exchange/\" target=\"_blank\">Secrets Exchange</a> creates moments of serendipitous connection and resonance between strangers who will never meet each other. The project reimagines new uses for blockchain technology and encourages active participation through sharing your own and being empathetic to the secrets of others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The metadata for each secret and its unique artwork counterpart will be stored in a secure, off chain database. When a participant submits a secret, they will be able to see someone else&rsquo;s secret and also the artwork attached to that secret. They can then decide whether or not they want to pay gas in order to mint the NFT and get it in their wallet. Otherwise the secret is lost forever.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A simple smart contract is integrated into the backend and will mint on the ETH blockchain using ERC-721 if the user wants the NFT.</p>\r\n<p>MetaMask wallet set-up instructions can be found here: <a href=\"https://metamask.io/\">https://metamask.io/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Examples of minted secrets:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/Screen_Shot_2020-12-10_at_4.58_.13_PM_.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"608\" height=\"338\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Example of a unique&nbsp;gif generated for each secret:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/secrets.gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/secrets-exchange-crypto-art-generator.png', '', 'https://secrets.exchange/', 'lynette-lee', '', '0', '1623111649', 'https://secrets.exchange/', '', '', 'project'),
(258, 'I DON\'T KNOW. LOOK AT IT.', 'i-don-t-know-look-at-it', '<p>Erica Anderon\'s Gallery Show \"I DON\'T KNOW. LOOK AT IT.\" with New Art City is based on 2020\'s current circumstances. We are all stuck in quarantine, and we can\'t leave our homes. But what if there was a place that\'s beyond ourselves? A purely digital realm that we can all go too, be in the presence of inter-dimensional creatures, and briefly see outside our current surroundings.&nbsp;<br /><br />\"I DON\'T KNOW. LOOK AT IT.\" is featured as part of the CODAME Art+Tech Festival with links to the works available for sale on <a href=\"https://knownorigin.io/ericaofanderson\">KnownOrigin</a>.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">I DON\'T KNOW. LOOK AT IT.&nbsp;is included in the Art+Tech Festival Pass and&nbsp;All Access Pass</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center><!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this in to your website where you want the widget to appear. Do no change the code or the widget may not work properly. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------><center>\r\n<p id=\"&rdquo;fest-10&rdquo;\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Part of the&nbsp;<strong>10th</strong> annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></em></p>\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/447187/chk/adef/ref/website_widget\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/checkout/new-session/id/447187/chk/adef/ref/website_widget\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n</center><!-- End of Ticket Tailor Widget ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</center>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/i-don-t-know-look-at-it.png', '', '', 'erica-anderson', '', '0', '1623111731', '', 'knownorigin,newart-city', '', 'project'),
(265, 'Video Screening ', 'video-screening', '<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/video-screening.png', '', '', 'gosh-studio,ouchhh,marc-o-matic,weidi-zhang,donghao-ren', '', '0', '1607654087', NULL, '', '', NULL),
(264, 'VISUAL POETRY', 'visual-poetry', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Visual Poetry is created by GOSH Studios, brought to the CODAME JOYNT Festival by and D2D Art and featured&nbsp;in New Art City</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Gosh is a visual creation studio dedicated to experiential contents and new media art.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Created by Bonjour Lab and les Gentils Gar&ccedil;ons, Gosh aims to design and produce new storytelling approaches and share them to the public, by blending real time technologies and visual poetry.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Passionate about space design and architecture, the studio brings a very special care to imagine meaningful immersive concepts that foster connections with audiences.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/visual-poetry.png', '', 'https://gosh.studio/', 'gosh-studio', '', '0', '1607640631', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection', 'd2d-art,newart-city', '', NULL),
(262, 'Glitch-me', 'glitch-me', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">The project is a work-in-progress online platform for networked performances, which aims to introduce performative coding experiences to non-coders. When opened on a browser, the website shows a fullscreen-canvas of analog-synthesizer-inspired glitches, which may operate on a webcam feed, using Hydra live-coding environment created by a collaborator, Olivia Jack. In addition to showing &ldquo;video effects,&rdquo; multiple buttons and sliders appear on the webpage that trigger different video sources including webcam and effects; moreover, the trigger is also sent to other browsers opened online, in other words, everyone can influence each other&rsquo;s video feed with or without the knowledge of programming language. This opens up opportunities to online art-technology collaboration in different ways, for example, to be used for a networked performance between a dancer and a digital artist or a casual video call in which participants trigger different effects to add intimacy to the communication.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/glitch-me.png', '', '', 'naoto-hieda,flor-de-fuego', '', '0', '1607580818', '', 'd2d-art', '', NULL),
(247, 'Regalia', 'regalia', '<div>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Experience&nbsp;Regalia as part of</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT</a></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this in to your website where you want the widget to appear. Do no change the code or the widget may not work properly. -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- End of Ticket Tailor Widget -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Regalia is a generative, participatory and interactive artwork meant to let the audience be a part of the creation of the art itself. As an extension of the&nbsp;watercolor-imaginarium&nbsp;project, I trained a set of watercolour paintings which I had curated (using StyleGAN). Images generated from this were photo-manipulated to create a set of Insignias - the symbols at the centre of each Regalia. The area around the Insignia is a playground where anyone can draw and complete the artwork. Regardless of skill levels, anyone can make amazing creations because of the use of symmetry. Although it uses a&nbsp;simple algorithm to draw, this artwork tries to push the boundaries of generative art ownership using the Async Art platform and also tries to bring in for the first time, code-rendered artworks in the Blockchain art world.<br /><br /></div>\r\n<div>I believe that a true artist starts by creating/curating his tools of creation. In the same spirit, many of my works hitherto have been on creating tools, digital or otherwise, and then using those tools to create art. Regalia is also created with the same concept in mind. Regalia is an effort to showcase the power of generative art, fractal ownership of parts of such an artwork and finally the introduction of interactive, generative art in the Blockchain art platform.</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/regalia.png', '', '', 'fabin-rasheed', '', '0', '1623111636', 'https://async.art/art/master/0x6c424c25e9f1fff9642cb5b7750b0db7312c29ad-256', 'async-art', '', 'project'),
(248, 'Chromology', 'chromology', '<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Chromology is a play of colours. It is a generative, participatory and interactive artwork intended to create a collaboration between the artist and the audience. The concept of the artwork was to break away from set forms, and engage in creations which are abstract in nature. In this way, the artwork is intended for \"play\" as opposed to \"make\". There are 4 styles of creations controlled by the \"Expression\" layer. There are 5 colour themes controlled by the \"Theme\" layer. I believe that a true artist starts by creating/curating his tools of creation. In the same spirit, many of my works hitherto have been on creating tools, digital or otherwise, and then using those tools to create art. Chromology is also created with the same concept in mind.<a href=\"https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-363\"><br /><br /><br /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module video project-module-video js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 720px; max-height: 720px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 720px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 720px; height: 720px;\" title=\"Video Player\" src=\"https://www-ccv.adobe.io/v1/player/ccv/8uRRyrVf6Xq/embed?bgcolor=%23191919&amp;lazyLoading=true&amp;api_key=BehancePro2View\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module video project-module-video js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 720px; max-height: 720px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 720px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 720px; height: 720px;\" title=\"Video Player\" src=\"https://www-ccv.adobe.io/v1/player/ccv/2GsuGHARaQ_/embed?bgcolor=%23191919&amp;lazyLoading=true&amp;api_key=BehancePro2View\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/4d5142f0-c384-4cbc-a949-41a8c4623770.jpg?h=ea4378f8ee3a016e09b9cb8e10921e54\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/4d5142f0-c384-4cbc-a949-41a8c4623770_rw_1920.jpg?h=cf996ae53c3c31b661bce36766fd9d4d\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/4d5142f0-c384-4cbc-a949-41a8c4623770_rw_600.jpg?h=d53b20b2d5e3c0c9e17ebc3962e84a03 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/4d5142f0-c384-4cbc-a949-41a8c4623770_rw_1200.jpg?h=2b8ab76997b73993682ca78632706d30 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/4d5142f0-c384-4cbc-a949-41a8c4623770_rw_1920.jpg?h=cf996ae53c3c31b661bce36766fd9d4d 1280w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" /></div>\r\n</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/chromology.jpg', 'https://twitter.com/fabinrasheed', '', 'fabin-rasheed', '', '0', '1618947045', 'https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-363', 'async-art', '', 'nft');
INSERT INTO `projects` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `description`, `pic`, `twitter`, `website`, `artists_array`, `old_url`, `hidden`, `edited`, `shop_url`, `partners_array`, `sponsors_array`, `is_nft`) VALUES
(249, 'Pilgrimage', 'pilgrimage', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Join the Pilgrimage&nbsp;<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-8f553345-7fff-c959-e22e-8a23fe130c2b\">journey</span>&nbsp;and collect your models as part of</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT</a></h3>\r\n<p>Pilgrimage is an artwork comprising of a series of 9 artworks (3D models), which were distributed across 9 locations around&nbsp;the globe. These 9 models could be unlocked only by travelling to the place&nbsp;. The first person to reach a location, unlock a model and share the video of the model was rewarded with the NFT token of that artwork.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- Ticket Tailor Widget. Paste this in to your website where you want the widget to appear. Do no change the code or the widget may not work properly. -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget\">\r\n<div class=\"tt-widget-fallback\">\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to buy tickets</a><br /><small><a class=\"tt-widget-powered\" href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com?rf=wdg\">Sell tickets online with Ticket Tailor</a></small></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/js/widgets/min/widget.js\" data-url=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/all-tickets/codame/ref/website_widget/\" data-type=\"inline\" data-inline-minimal=\"true\" data-inline-show-logo=\"false\" data-inline-bg-fill=\"true\"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- End of Ticket Tailor Widget ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Pilgrimage - a&nbsp;story of the intelligence who created humanity<br /><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>Millions of years ago a race existed called the \"M\"&nbsp;(pronounced \'mmm\') on Earth. They evolved over many years&nbsp;and transcended variance of time and space. They reached a stage of evolution where all of time and space was accessible instantly to them. This is when they invested in simulations&nbsp;and creating a new type of intelligence. At first, these were systems to&nbsp;help the M\'s&nbsp;work. But this intelligence evolved into what later became known as humankind. It so happened that the intelligence progressed high enough to replace the M\'s on Earth, while the M\'s transcended completely into another dimension.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Remnants of the M\'s are still seen in humankind. For example, humans were created in a form similar to that of the M\'s. Also, the sound that humans can make with their mouths closed, is the M sound.&nbsp;The interesting thing is that millions of years later, because of the fractal nature of the universe,&nbsp;humanity is in the verge of creating \"artificial intelligence\" which could potentially become sentient and replace them, just like how the M\'s were replaced by humans.</div>\r\n<div>Although in the alternate dimension, some of the M\'s still stay back at the key energy centres of the earth. Across 9 locations around the globe, these energy centres have, over the years, evolved into prime cultural centres on Earth.</div>\r\n<div>And now it is up to us to travel to these centres to meet them and understand and learn from the secrets of the past.<br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>The Map<br /><br /></strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 983.242px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/9a1e9d3a-7cbb-4bc2-8e6b-5fa52ef5beb3.png?h=45626699de726d1e974db3cbd72093c6\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/9a1e9d3a-7cbb-4bc2-8e6b-5fa52ef5beb3_rw_1920.png?h=bd039096c3254723830cd8e9a52bb7c9\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1541px) 100vw, 1541px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/9a1e9d3a-7cbb-4bc2-8e6b-5fa52ef5beb3_rw_600.png?h=00e7bc85d2b44ff172fe0dfa79851acd 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/9a1e9d3a-7cbb-4bc2-8e6b-5fa52ef5beb3_rw_1200.png?h=38f2ca73b61d4872476eb6804d24015b 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/9a1e9d3a-7cbb-4bc2-8e6b-5fa52ef5beb3_rw_1920.png?h=bd039096c3254723830cd8e9a52bb7c9 1541w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1541\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>The Artwork<br /><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>The Pilgrimage was a journey to each of the 9 locations above&nbsp;to find the corresponding M and to collect the artwork (figurines) representing the M. These artworks were&nbsp;3D models&nbsp;which could be accessed only by going to the locations (details below)<br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/549455e1-0f10-456a-a9b7-55b0e9c14f6d.png?h=5a00118714ee78a347edbb4a50964ec0\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/549455e1-0f10-456a-a9b7-55b0e9c14f6d_rw_1200.png?h=344ba01539f664fa3008c54688de5251\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/549455e1-0f10-456a-a9b7-55b0e9c14f6d_rw_600.png?h=d7381d1dd005441cf0762a2679636374 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/549455e1-0f10-456a-a9b7-55b0e9c14f6d_rw_1200.png?h=344ba01539f664fa3008c54688de5251 1024w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><br /><strong>Artist\'s note:<br /><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>I made this artwork since I could not travel due to the pandemic&nbsp;situation. I wanted my art to travel instead of me. I completely understand that not everyone would be able to travel and collect&nbsp;the 9 NFTs, and only the people closest to these locations could immediately get it. But beyond the 9 NFTs, this artwork will live forever in these locations and some day,&nbsp;when circumstances are better, if you get to travel to these locations, the art will always be there for you to view and enjoy.<br /><br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>And what happened - The collection story<br /><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>How people from the world over coordinated and collected<br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Within the first 2 weeks of the release of the artwork, 8 models out of 9 were collected. People not only were enthusiastic to collect but coordinated with others continents apart for collecting.<br /><br /></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/fcdbc375-b430-41ce-89f5-f4d6402a3ec3.png?h=2fc34bcd9cefc4172a568727362e6d50\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/fcdbc375-b430-41ce-89f5-f4d6402a3ec3_rw_1920.png?h=1fcb1d56a126bcd7ee8efa68e1d7afcd\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1577px) 100vw, 1577px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/fcdbc375-b430-41ce-89f5-f4d6402a3ec3_rw_600.png?h=a65d80e9cb731c6aa8565d096dcc0832 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/fcdbc375-b430-41ce-89f5-f4d6402a3ec3_rw_1200.png?h=5d9f8358228a70b048d8be828c351ab3 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/fcdbc375-b430-41ce-89f5-f4d6402a3ec3_rw_1920.png?h=1fcb1d56a126bcd7ee8efa68e1d7afcd 1577w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1577\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Collection Videos</strong></div>\r\n<div>Following are the collection videos in Augmented Reality<br /><br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cwr2Lv-1py8\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/H6151_f1CaM\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/kaPqdbonQ7I\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/IvgJjeXiZuk\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/TM62PE6XaXg\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/5lSIUCDW5cg\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/IxnfOuMpt4M\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module embed project-module-embed js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-dimensions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 560px; max-height: 315px; margin: 0px auto;\">\r\n<div class=\"embed-aspect-ratio\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-bottom: 315px; position: relative; height: 0px;\"><strong><iframe class=\"embed-content\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 560px; height: 315px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/3ekdS_Wfh7c\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>The Art Creation</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong>Sketches, process, prototyping, collaterals</strong><br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>It all started when I thought of leaving some notes for my fianc&eacute; to read along the route&nbsp;of&nbsp;her daily morning walk. I wanted to see if there was any tool that could do the same. I found the geolocation ai which can find the location of a person in web and also the model-viewer which can view a 3D model in AR or on screen. I drafted a quick code and shared it with her to check it out. It worked and she had a great time reading all the notes along her route.</div>\r\n<div>I then decided to create a globally distributed artwork out of it. I had no idea how it will turn out. I started by making sketches of model I had in mind. I wanted to keep the model humanoid,&nbsp;unisex (as far&nbsp;as&nbsp;possible), and out of the world. I quickly converged on the following designs:<br /><br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/c55cd16d-429b-4856-9083-93985b8db473.png?h=f6054b90efb4e660f556c0d3bf6585cc\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/c55cd16d-429b-4856-9083-93985b8db473_rw_1920.png?h=24fccdb3177aae8e856d5b38f57eb6f5\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1542px) 100vw, 1542px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/c55cd16d-429b-4856-9083-93985b8db473_rw_600.png?h=96cbb97b9191ef539805868a05607f5a 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/c55cd16d-429b-4856-9083-93985b8db473_rw_1200.png?h=2526b7c287d8075a424a97a597fadbb0 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/c55cd16d-429b-4856-9083-93985b8db473_rw_1920.png?h=24fccdb3177aae8e856d5b38f57eb6f5 1542w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1542\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/92f73371-abf1-4c06-a403-d2b5c94aa3cb.png?h=46f6d94c9046f67355b0176318b3e5eb\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/92f73371-abf1-4c06-a403-d2b5c94aa3cb_rw_1920.png?h=397da881e21ee31824cb2e42596f4cbd\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1637px) 100vw, 1637px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/92f73371-abf1-4c06-a403-d2b5c94aa3cb_rw_600.png?h=412949190674d060131661513b9b95c8 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/92f73371-abf1-4c06-a403-d2b5c94aa3cb_rw_1200.png?h=ef5887e9bcea3e352127eeefa226951d 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/92f73371-abf1-4c06-a403-d2b5c94aa3cb_rw_1920.png?h=397da881e21ee31824cb2e42596f4cbd 1637w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1637\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>I then brought the sketch into Blender and sculpted the model out of it, made a rig and made 9 poses out of it. I also made the material variations and colours. Each pose and colour set had a personal meaning to me.<br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/f154efc9-a1ae-4ce5-af72-e811f62e6ee6.png?h=e9d4b2b85b0f5aed344c0e9643987168\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/f154efc9-a1ae-4ce5-af72-e811f62e6ee6_rw_1920.png?h=a42d9955c989ba2cb52f42679555e73e\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1453px) 100vw, 1453px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/f154efc9-a1ae-4ce5-af72-e811f62e6ee6_rw_600.png?h=877e23872511f7008fa5f9770fa64619 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/f154efc9-a1ae-4ce5-af72-e811f62e6ee6_rw_1200.png?h=926ee15875a32fdd7d181b0ffa19965c 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf4.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/f154efc9-a1ae-4ce5-af72-e811f62e6ee6_rw_1920.png?h=a42d9955c989ba2cb52f42679555e73e 1453w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1453\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>The fun part was coding. The code was surprisingly one of the smallest codes that I have written, thanks to the libraries. But testing them involved me taking my motorbike and travelling several kilometres and coming back. I did this a few times before finalising the code. The locations around the world were chosen based on cultural history. I knew there were many other beautiful sites around the world, but this was more of a personal choice based on my readings.<br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Finally made some renders of the models in Adobe Dimension for marketing and deployed it in GitHub.<br /><br /><br /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf2.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/3dbfe063-2231-40af-ae52-c0a17f5633c9.png?h=89a3cea77835ffaa0627fd8343a1424f\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf2.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/3dbfe063-2231-40af-ae52-c0a17f5633c9_rw_1200.png?h=45e8ace29416eb4ab61481dbba8b9793\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf2.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/3dbfe063-2231-40af-ae52-c0a17f5633c9_rw_600.png?h=bea5fc6b2211458da3ffe8b3168b2c6e 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf2.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/3dbfe063-2231-40af-ae52-c0a17f5633c9_rw_1200.png?h=45e8ace29416eb4ab61481dbba8b9793 1024w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf6.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/78aac95f-c071-4de9-9262-0099db39cf2b.png?h=86aa7380fb2b9c0bc33018ead450f281\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf6.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/78aac95f-c071-4de9-9262-0099db39cf2b_rw_1200.png?h=54c51ad0d0a8e3813dea2ace3e1fe75e\" sizes=\"(max-width: 946px) 100vw, 946px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf6.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/78aac95f-c071-4de9-9262-0099db39cf2b_rw_600.png?h=08a0aee9b3bdc89c5890e19a5e69108e 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf6.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/78aac95f-c071-4de9-9262-0099db39cf2b_rw_1200.png?h=54c51ad0d0a8e3813dea2ace3e1fe75e 946w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"946\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/40a08bcc-ec0e-4766-9f52-b6e61c0eff09.png?h=8cff426f0bc1bce91ce72c04a9bd8962\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/40a08bcc-ec0e-4766-9f52-b6e61c0eff09_rw_1920.png?h=da98be123696e6a4c21014af2a26ae29\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1837px) 100vw, 1837px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/40a08bcc-ec0e-4766-9f52-b6e61c0eff09_rw_600.png?h=3908e66541d6be7e2fd7331cab2e95ee 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/40a08bcc-ec0e-4766-9f52-b6e61c0eff09_rw_1200.png?h=7e959fc2e9254996737e975ddcb9f0ec 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/40a08bcc-ec0e-4766-9f52-b6e61c0eff09_rw_1920.png?h=da98be123696e6a4c21014af2a26ae29 1837w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1837\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/b21a0ce2-9c88-4aca-8a30-a15f587558c8.png?h=3c5b300b5d06895ff11d754428573ffc\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/b21a0ce2-9c88-4aca-8a30-a15f587558c8_rw_1920.png?h=08b1d93639d68013628797301eb5d254\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/b21a0ce2-9c88-4aca-8a30-a15f587558c8_rw_600.png?h=b66c878bd228e997a33e4adef55659b0 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/b21a0ce2-9c88-4aca-8a30-a15f587558c8_rw_1200.png?h=f72af57d0748653db25d44b4b76fda37 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/b21a0ce2-9c88-4aca-8a30-a15f587558c8_rw_1920.png?h=08b1d93639d68013628797301eb5d254 1280w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/429da660-f7ee-4f81-a8b7-6aac959e7d2b.jpg?h=8995a35f8836d2ad1f8aa2df5ccfd9f4\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/429da660-f7ee-4f81-a8b7-6aac959e7d2b_rw_1920.jpg?h=5b252ddb6b3ebdab1f7373d9dba17e13\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/429da660-f7ee-4f81-a8b7-6aac959e7d2b_rw_600.jpg?h=6f6888703cccbb8fbb61d14de3d03879 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/429da660-f7ee-4f81-a8b7-6aac959e7d2b_rw_1200.jpg?h=d119aab9662fabfbef08a0eb7ce28cab 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf3.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/429da660-f7ee-4f81-a8b7-6aac959e7d2b_rw_1920.jpg?h=5b252ddb6b3ebdab1f7373d9dba17e13 1920w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"project-module module image project-module-image js-js-project-module\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; clear: both; word-break: break-word; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 0px; max-width: 100%; width: 1229.06px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"js-lightbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/20e0dc9f-10e8-4ad5-bbf8-92705a806506.png?h=b99d119c338e71a88ff6e6b9e66ef18b\"><img class=\"js-lazy e2e-site-project-module-image image-loaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: top; display: block; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/20e0dc9f-10e8-4ad5-bbf8-92705a806506_rw_1920.png?h=70182de222261f526292d4bdbb7f9b63\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/20e0dc9f-10e8-4ad5-bbf8-92705a806506_rw_600.png?h=826a065060a635d6bfefa82b8559f931 600w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/20e0dc9f-10e8-4ad5-bbf8-92705a806506_rw_1200.png?h=dabcd1c02d68430428afd0642a579e95 1200w,https://pro2-bar-s3-cdn-cf1.myportfolio.com/02c5201375c3706250b26cf840ace79c/20e0dc9f-10e8-4ad5-bbf8-92705a806506_rw_1920.png?h=70182de222261f526292d4bdbb7f9b63 1920w,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/pilgrimage.jpg', '', '', 'fabin-rasheed', '', '0', '1623111642', '', 'async-art', '', 'project'),
(253, 'M Carbon Dioxide', 'm-carbon-dioxide', '<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p id=\"a600\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">M Carbon Dioxide&nbsp;is one of Sven Eberwein\'s latest works of art and represents 1000 tonnes of CO2 formerly purchased and retired as verified credit units (VCUs) on the Verra registry and minted to the blockchain as an NFT. The amount of CO2 offset by this NFT is equivalent to the emissions that person living in an industrialized country would emit over the course of 40 years. To give context, the typical roundtrip transatlantic flight from NYC to London emits 2 tonnes of CO2 per passenger seated in economy class. Thus, this NFT represents 500 such flights!</p>\r\n<p id=\"b610\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">The offsets identified and selected for this artwork were derived from Offsetra&rsquo;s sustainability project portfolio. The Bull Run project and the Cerro de Hula project were both selected during the creation of this NFT.</p>\r\n<p>More information about the process:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>For every tonne of CO2, there was a corresponding Verified Carbon Reduction Unit (VCU) purchased on behalf of the work.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Every VCU represents one tonne of CO2 offset from forestry protection and renewable energy projects.</li>\r\n<li>This work is listed in the exact dollar amount required to offset the corresponding CO2 reduction and acts only as a transmitter.</li>\r\n<li>The VCUs have been purchased via @offsetra and attributed to this work.</li>\r\n<li>They can be accessed via the link present in the QR code.</li>\r\n<li>The owner of this work would be supporting the reduction of emissions equivalent to the average first world citizens emissions for the next 5 years.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View the work in <a href=\"https://newart.city/preview/codame-festival\" target=\"_blank\">NewArt.City CODAME Festival Ground</a></p>\r\n<p id=\"cb03\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Read Sven\'s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://knownorigin.io/journal/spotlight/sven-eberwein\">Artist Spotlight on KnownOrigin&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n<p data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><a href=\"https://offsetra.medium.com/m-carbon-dioxide-sven-x-offsetra-998ee52f28bf\">https://offsetra.medium.com/m-carbon-dioxide-sven-x-offsetra-998ee52f28bf</a></p>\r\n<p data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Experience M Carbon Dioxide <br />in New Art City as part of</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://codame.com/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\">ART+TECH Festival 2020 #JOYNT</a></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div id=\"tt-widget-inline-0\"><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/m-carbon-dioxide.gif', 'https://twitter.com/sven_eberwein', 'https://superrare.co/artwork-v2/m-carbon-dioxide-15566', 'sven-eberwein', '', '0', '1622645711', 'https://superrare.co/artwork-v2/m-carbon-dioxide-15566', 'newart-city,knownorigin', '', 'nft'),
(252, 'Cangjie\'s Poetry', 'cangjie-s-poetry', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (free for all to particpate!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cangjie&rsquo;s Poetry&nbsp;is a multimodal intelligent system that was designed as a conceptual response to the future semantic human-machine reality. Inspired by Cangjie, an ancient Chinese legendary historian (c.2650 BCE), who invented Chinese characters based on his observation of characteristics of everything on earth, we trained a neural network to learn the constructions and principles of over 9000 Chinese characters and named it&nbsp;Cangjie.&nbsp;Cangjie&nbsp;first&nbsp;<wbr />transforms surroundings perceived by the neural network&nbsp;through a camera into a cluster of ever-changing new symbols&nbsp;that are constructed&nbsp;by Chinese strokes. Those novel symbols compose&nbsp;a dynamically evolving poem.&nbsp;In the meantime,&nbsp;Cangjie&nbsp;also creates meanings for those symbols&nbsp;by using computer vision systems to generate descriptive sentences of the surroundings in natural&nbsp;language that humans can read.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #212121; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; text-align: justify; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: 0.01em;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-style: italic;\"><img src=\"/uploaded_images/cjp__100153.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/cangjie-s-poetry.png', '', '', 'weidi-zhang,donghao-ren', '', '0', '1607667698', 'https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/', '', '', NULL),
(259, '10th Anniversary Art Cards', '10th-anniversary-art-cards', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">6 collectable art cards <br />released over 10 days <br />at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://paras.id/codame.near\">paras.id/codame.near</a>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To celebrate the&nbsp;<a class=\"cs jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\" href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">10th annual ART+TECH Festival</a>, CODAME is&nbsp;launched a set of digital art cards on Paras. The designs reach back into the vaults of&nbsp;<a class=\"cs jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://www.vicentemontelongo.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Vicente Montelongo</a>, the non-profits original Chief Creative Officer and a constant inspiration for CODAME branding. The card backs tell the tale of \"Venusian Orbs\" by flash fiction author Max Zsol.&nbsp; Let us know <tt>yourname.near</tt> wallet address (or what name you\'d like so we can set you up) to recieve a card <em>(while supplies last)</em>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/uploaded_images/download_(1).png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Paras and CODAME share a healthy overlap of ART+TECH interests. Goals of both platforms include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Creating accessible platforms for artists.</li>\r\n<li>Elevating the value of art during technological advancement.</li>\r\n<li>Driving innovation across silos and meaningful engagement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For these reasons, Paras will #JOYNT the ride for their&nbsp;<a class=\"cs jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\" href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">CODAME ART+TECH FESTIVAL 2020</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>JOYNT us on PARAS art card platform</h1>\r\n<p>First you\'ll need to create a <a href=\"https://wallet.near.org/\">NEAR wallet</a>, it\'s an alternative chain to ETH/BTC. Perfect to get into if GAS is killing you ðŸ˜‰ Process will look something like this:</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vQOBJG6Tr-C8hdyH0EN2B_THgvDrs6_gdec1NXfEP_EaB46nd-SnRhUrPCjpuHuQ3jeSCDAJFHPHzJP/embed?start=false&amp;loop=false&amp;delayms=3000\" width=\"960\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<center><!--1--><embed src=\"https://paras.id/token/Qmc6Efc6sE6Pjhht4ggbY1j8qd5YaxG6bv1hVKo3PYAfhA\" width=\"600px\" height=\"2000px\"></embed><br /><br /> <!--2--><embed src=\"https://paras.id/token/QmWUP8PqVviQxXdoy6WkTfUMhkmH8j9MggunEPCY6vkRhD\" width=\"600px\" height=\"2000px\"></embed><br /><br /> <!--3--><embed src=\"https://paras.id/token/QmeEE5KTgkQWEKuow9keBqRsyh1YVs51uzC31kQ77AV5Li\" width=\"600px\" height=\"2000px\"></embed> <br /><br /><!--4--><embed src=\"https://paras.id/token/QmX51QPBYSKFrNbLhL19MeC77P9BW9mdLEKJstmYzYtfai\" width=\"600px\" height=\"2000px\"></embed> <br /><br /><!--5--><embed src=\"https://paras.id/token/QmT8rgHKLxGG6V51YXWwfsn4iFaCVv51YbBqWAQVNizvjH\" width=\"600px\" height=\"2000px\"></embed> <br /><br /><!--6--><embed src=\"https://paras.id/token/QmbUMDD7XwC4CGbmoTztJLkgi3BBnMbvi6n3BAAqkJSHuZ\" width=\"600px\" height=\"2000px\"></embed></center>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/10th-anniversary-art-cards.jpg', '', '', 'vicente-montelongo,max-zsol,danica-sapit,jordan-gray', '', '0', '1629173217', 'https://paras.id/codame.near', 'paras', '', 'nft'),
(260, 'Harddiskmuseum', 'harddiskmuseum', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The Harddiskmuseum is a Museum of digital and new media art content based in a hard drive of 2TB founded by the artist Solim&aacute;n L&oacute;pez in 2015.&nbsp;<br /><br />Now in 2020 the Museum includes the pieces of 110 artists from more than 20 different countries. Artworks of video, static images, video games, text, audio pieces, interactive pieces and a long etc.. are part of this unique repository.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At the end of 2020 the Museum will have its version in genetic code. The first Museum in history to store its content in DNA.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/harddiskmuseum.png', 'https://twitter.com/harddiskmuseum', 'https://harddiskmuseum.com/', 'soliman-lopez', '', '0', '1684173252', '', 'd2d-art', '', 'project'),
(261, 'Transcending Taste in c0d3 Kitchen', 'transcending-taste-in-c0d3-kitchen', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Part of the 10th annual <a href=\"/events/art-tech-festival-2020-joynt\" target=\"_blank\">CODAME ART+TECH Festival</a> (included in the</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\">Festival Pass and All Access Pass</a>&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Transcend Taste is a digital exploration of how dining is an immersive experience. When people think of dining and food, their cultural and personal preferences are shown. From being a picky eater to collaborations for the betterment of the taste buds. One thing we forget at times is how this entity of object has the ability to make us wonder through both positive and negative connotations, depending on what is being discussed. In our performance/immersive installation, we will be breaking down the dining experience through different lenses. Particularly aiming at the 5 senses while reevaluating the meaning of some of our semantics towards this experience.<br /><br />Through different creative coding environments in conjunction with online spaces meant for exploration, c0d3 kitchen will be showcasing the kitchen in a deconstructed format. Where obejcts and sense will be and will not be how they normally are to promote thinking. A timeless performance that depending on your mood and how you interact with the space will bring upon a different sensation every time. Should be noted, it won\'t necessarily be a drastic change but one that emulates the ability to feel different, even if eating the same food twice.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/events/codame/442122/#ticket_selection\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto; font-family: Asap, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #00a4a7; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/uploaded_images/button_(6).png\" alt=\"CODAME ART+TECH Get Tickets Button\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', 'http://codame.dreamhosters.com/uploaded_images/c0d3-kitchen.png', '', '', 'illest-preacha,elena-kauffmann,kevin-smuggles', '', '0', '1607367868', '', 'd2d-art', '', NULL);
